STATE PASS TO YUGOSLAVIA WORKING GROUP AND EUR/EEY 
 
BRUSSELS FOR USEC; VIENNA ALSO FOR USDEL CSBM 
 
E.O. 12356:  N/A 
TAGS: PGOV, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: WGYOOL:  RESOLUTIONS PASSED BY THE CROATIAN 
                   PARLIAMENT ON AUGUST 3 
1.  SUMMARY:  AS REPORTED IN SEPTEL, THE FOLLOWING 
IS AN ENGLISH TRANSLATION OF THE SIXTEEN RESOLUTIONS 
PASSED BY THE CROATIAN PARLIAMENT REGARDING THE 
POLITICAL CONDITIONS IN CROATIA AND THE 
 
IMPLEMENTATION OF THE CONSTITUTIONAL RESOLUTION ON 
THE SOVEREIGNTY AND INDEPENDENCE OF CROATIA.  END 
SUMMARY. 
 
2.  BEGIN TEXT: 
 
ON THE BASIS OF ARTICLE 2 OF THE CONSTITUTION OF THE 
REPUBLIC OF CROATIA AND THE CONSTITUTIONAL 
RESOLUTION ON THE SOVEREIGNTY AND INDEPENDENCE OF 
THE REPUBLC OF CROATIA, 
 --  FULLY SUPPORTING THE POLITICAL VIEWS ON THE 
CAUSES OF THE CRISIS AND THE WAR AND THE ROADS TO 
PEACE AS EXPOSED IN THE ADDRESS OF THE PRESIDENT OF 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01189  01 OF 05  061107Z 
THE REPUBLIC TO THE CROATIAN AND INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITIES ON JULY 8, 1991 AND IN THE REPLY OF THE 
PRESIDENT OF THE PARLIAMENT TO THE ASSEMBLIES OF THE 
REPUBLIC OF SERBIA AND THE REPUBLIC OF MONTENEGRO. 
 --  TAKING INTO ACCOUNT THE OPEN AGGRESSION ON THE 
REPUBLIC OF CROATIA WHICH IS EVIDENT IN THE THREAT 
TO ITS SOVEREIGNTY, INDEPENDENCE AND TERRITORIAL 
INTEGRITY, IN THE KILLINGS OF ITS CITIZENS, THE 
DESTRUCTION OF ITS ECONOMIC AND CULTURAL RESOURCES 
AND IN OTHER CRIMES UNPRECEDENTED IN OTHER CIVILIZED 
COUNTRIES, 
 --  BASED ON THE FACT THAT THE CROATIAN NATION AND 
ALL OTHER CITIZENS OF THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA MUST 
DECISIVELY RESIST THE GREATER SERBIAN CHETNIK 
OUTLAWS AND THE OCCUPATION BY THE YUGOSLAV PEOPLES\' 
ARMY, 
 --  BY RECONFIRMING OUR DEDICATION TO A PEACEFUL, 
GRADUAL AND DEMOCRATIC DISASSOCIATION OF THE FORMER 
SFRJ, BUT NOT SURRENDERING THE FULL SOVEREIGNTY OF 
THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA, 
 --  RESPECTING THE PRINCIPLES OF THE HELSINKI 
AGREEMENT, THE PARIS CHARTER AND THE BRIONI 
DECLARATION, ON THE 3RD OF AUGUST, 1991, THE 
PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA ADOPTED THE 
FOLLOWING RESOLUTIONS 
 
1.  THE COMMUNIST AUTHORITIES OF THE REPUBLIC OF 
SERBIA, WITH THE ASSISTANCE OF THE YUGOSLAV PEOPLES\' 
ARMY, ARE CONDUCTING AN AGGRESSIVE AND 
EXPANSIONISTIC POLICY AGAINST THE SOVEREIGN AND 
INDEPENDENT REPUBLIC OF CROATIA, ENTICING AND OPENLY 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01189  01 OF 05  061107Z 
ASSISTING THE TERRORISTS AND THEIR ACCOMPLICES IN 
CROATIA FOR THE PURPOSE OF CONQUERING TERRITORIES OF 
THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA. 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
NNNN 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
