TAGS: PGOV, MOPS, MOPS, MOPS, MOPS, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  REPORTS OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITY 
MONITORS, CROATIAN ARMY AND JNA ON EVENTS IN WESTERN 
SLAVONIA 
UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
SIPDIS 
 
1.  WE HAVE COMPILED A SERIES OF REPORTS FROM THE EC 
OBSERVERS (WHO WERE IN GRUBISNO POLJE ON NOVEMBER 6 
AND PLAN TO RETURN NOVEMBER 7), THE FIFTH MILITARY 
DISTRICT OF THE JNA, AND CROATIAN ARMY HEADQUARTERS 
ON EVENTS, ALLEGED AND OTHERWISE, THAT HAVE RECENTLY 
TAKEN PLACE IN WESTERN SLAVONIA.  THE TEXTS OF THOSE 
REPORTS FOLLOW. 
 
--  REPORT ON EC MONITORING MISSION TEAM NOVEMBER 6 
VISIT TO GRUBISNO POLJE AREA 
 
2.   BEGIN TEXT.  ON 6 NOVEMBER, AN EC MONITORING 
TEAM VISITED THE GRUBISNO POLJE AREA TO INVESTIGATE 
A REPORT BY THE PRESIDENCY OF THE SFR YUGOSLAVIA 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01569  01 OF 04  071627Z 
(LETTER DATED 4 NOV) THAT FORCES OF THE CROATIAN 
NATIONAL GUARD (CNG) HAD BURNT OR DESTROYED SERBIAN 
VILLAGES IN THE AREA AND KILLED THOSE INHABITANTS 
WHO WERE UNABLE TO ESCAPE. 
 
3.  THE TEAM WERE ESCORTED BY THE PERSONNEL FROM THE 
CNG.  AS SERBIAN IRREGULARS AND UNITS OF THE 
YUGOSLAV PEOPLES ARMY (YPA) REMAINED OPERATIONAL IN 
THE AREA, THERE WERE SOME VILLAGES WHICH THE TEAM 
WERE UNABLE TO VISIT FOR SAFETY REASONS. 
 
4.  THE TEAM INTERVIEWED THE COMMANDER OF THE LOCAL 
CNG FORCES IN GRUBISNO POLJE WHO SAID THAT CROATIAN 
FORCES HAD \"LIBERATED\" THE IMMEDIATE AREA IN TWO 
DAYS OF FIGHTING FROM 31 OCT TO 1 NOV; THIS HAD 
FOLLOWED A PERIOD OF 2-3 MONTHS OCCUPATION IN WHICH, 
IT WAS CLAIMED, A NUMBER OF LOCAL CZECHS AND 
CROATIANS HAD BEEN KILLED (16 IN THE VILLAGES 
SUBSEQUENTLY VISITED), HOUSES BURNT AND OTHER LOCAL 
INHABITANTS TERRORISED. THIS WAS SAID TO HAVE BEEN 
DONE BY SERBIAN IRREGULARS (CHETNIKS) MADE UP FROM 
AMONG THE LOCAL SERBIAN VILLAGERS.  WITH THE ADVANCE 
OF THE CNG FORCES, THE SERBIAN FORCES, SUPPORTED BY 
YPA UNITS, HAD WITHDRAWN TOGETHER WITH MOST OF THE 
LOCAL SERBIAN POPULACE FROM THE VILLAGES CONCERNED. 
THE TEAM, STILL WITH CNG ESCORT FOR SAFETY, 
SUBSEQUENTLY VISITED THE VILLAGES OF VELIKA 
PERATOVICA, D RASENICA AND IVANOVO SELO; THEY ALSO 
PASSED THROUGH PARTS OF THE VILLAGES OF MALA 
PERATOVICA AND POLJANI AND THROUGH SERBIAN AREAS OF 
GRUBISNO POLJE.  THERE WAS CONVINCING EVIDENCE OF 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01569  01 OF 04  071627Z 
CHETNIK KILLINGS OF CZECH INHABITANTS OF VELIKA 
PERATOVICA AND IVANOVO SELO, INCLUDING GRAVES, BLOOD 
STAINED BLANKETS ACCOMPANIED BY BROKEN HUMAN TEETH, 
AND THE PERSONAL WITNESS OF A NUMBER OF LOCAL CZECH 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
