VILLAGERS.  ONLY ONE SERBIAN COUPLE WAS FOUND DURING 
THE VISITS BUT THEY CONFIRMED CNG CLAIMS THAT THERE 
HAD BEEN NO CNG MALTREATMENT OF THOSE SERBIANS WHO 
HAD REMAINED IN THEIR VILLAGES.  THIS WAS ALSO 
CONFIRMED BY THE SIGNIFICANT NUMBER OF CZECHS TO WHOM 
THE TEAM TALKED.  THERE WAS NO EVIDENCE OF SYSTEMATIC 
DESTRUCTION OF SERBIAN HOMES THOUGH A NUMBER OF 
HOUSES, INCLUDING THOSE OF LOCAL SERBS, HAD BEEN 
DAMAGED IN THE CONFLICT.  SOME OF THE DAMAGE TO 
SERBIAN HOMES WAS SEVERE REFLECTING THE CNG USE OF 
ARTILLERY.  THERE WAS ALSO EVIDENCE OF MORE RECENT 
BURNING OF A SMALL NUMBER OF SERBIAN HOUSES, FARM 
BUILDINGS AND HAY STACKS.  THE TEAM WAS UNABLE TO 
ESTABLISH FROM THOSE INTERVIEWED WHETHER THIS WAS DUE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01569  02 OF 04  071628Z 
TO ACTS OF LOCAL REVENGE AGAINST THE PROPERTY OF 
LEADING CHETNIK FIGURES, TO CNG ACTION OR TO A 
RETROSPECTIVE SERBIAN SCORCHED EARTH POLICY. 
 
5.  IN CONCLUSION, WHILE THERE WAS COMPELLING 
EVIDENCE OF CHETNIK EXCESSES DURING THEIR 2-3 MONTHS 
PERIOD OF CONTROL OF THE AREA, THE TEAM COULD FIND NO 
EVIDENCE OF SUBSEQUENT CROATIAN KILLINGS OR OF A 
SYSTEMATIC POLICY OF DESTRUCTION OF SERBIAN PROPERTY 
ON THE PART OF THE CNG OR LOCAL CROAT OR OTHER 
MINORITY GROUPS.  A SECOND VISIT WILL BE MADE BY AN 
EC MONITORING TEAM ON 7 NOV TO INVESTIGATE THE 
POSITION IN OTHER VILLAGES REFERRED TO IN THE LETTER 
FROM THE PRESIDENCY OF SFR YUGOSLAVIA.  END TEXT. 
 
-- JNA REPORT 
 
6.  BEGIN TEXT.  ON 1 NOV 91 THE MEMBERS OF NATIONAL 
GUARD AND MINISTRY OF HOME AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC OF 
CROATIA HAVE UNDERTAKEN A BROAD AND EXTREMELY BRUTAL 
OFFENSIVE AGAINST THE SERBIAN POPULATION IN THE AREA 
OF SOUTHERN SLOPES OF MT. BILOGORA AND AT THE 
DIRECTIONS OF VELIKI GREDJEVAC-GRUBISNO POLJE-IVANOVO 
SELO AND THE VILLAGE OF LEVINOVAC-MIOKOVICEVO. 
UNCLASSIFIED 
 
SIPDIS 
 
7.  EIGHTEEN (18) SERBIAN VILLAGES WERE SET ON FIRE, 
AS PER INCOMPLETE DATA AND INFORMATION, WHILE THE 
NUMBER OF KILLED AND WOUNDED CITIZENS IS HIGH. 
 
8.  REFUGE OF SEVERAL THOUSANDS OF SERBS, MOSTLY 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
