- 
EC REPORTS ON HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS 
------------------------------------- 
6.  THE EC MONITORS\' GROUP PROVIDED US THIS 
AFTERNOON WITH COPIES OF THEIR LENGTHY 
CONFIDENTIAL REPORTS ON ALLEGATIONS OF 
 
SIPDIS 
VIOLATIONS OF HUMANITARIAN LAW IN THE ZADAR 
AREA, IN SLAVONSKA POZEGA (IN RESPONSE TO JNA 
CHARGES THAT SERBIAN VILLAGES WERE BEING 
FORCIBLY EVACUATED BY THE CROATS), AND 
ELSEWHERE, AND ON EC MONITORS\' VISITS TO 
VUKOVAR.  THE REPORTS INCLUDE A CONCLUSION OF 
SERIOUS JNA VIOLATIONS IN SOME AREAS OF THE 
SECOND PROTOCOL OF THE GENEVA CONVENTION.  WE 
ARE POUCHING FULL COPIES TO EMBASSY BELGRADE. 
STEPHENS 
 
 
 
