TAGS: PINR, PGOV, CA, PGOV, CA, PGOV, CA, PHUM, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  TUDJMAN LETTER TO PRESIDENT OF THE WORLD 
JEWISH CONGRESS 
FOLLOWING IS A LETTER FROM CROATIAN PRESIDENT FRANJO 
TUDJMAN TO EDGAR BRONFMAN, PRESIDENT OF WORLD JEWISH 
CONGRESS.  BEGIN TEXT: 
 
DEAR MR. BRONFMAN, 
 
I AM ADDRESSING YOU ON BEHALF OF THE REPUBLIC OF 
CROATIA, CURRENTLY THE YOUNGEST EUROPEAN STATE, BUT 
A STATE WITH A CENTURIES-LONG TRADITION OF 
STATEHOOD.  CROATIA NOW SEEKS THE RECOGNITION OF HER 
INDEPENDENCE AS EXPRESSED BY THE WILL OF HER 
CITIZENS AT THE REFERENDUM OF MAY 15, 1991.  AT THE 
REFERENDUM, THE OVERWHELMING MAJORITY OF CROATIAN 
CITIZENS CHOSE TO LIVE HENCEFORTH IN THE INDEPENDENT 
REPUBLIC OF CROATIA, A DEMOCRATIC STATE ASSURING ALL 
ITS CITIZENS EQUAL RIGHTS, REGARDLESS OF RELIGIOUS, 
NATIONAL OR POLITICAL AND OTHER AFFILIATIONS, AND 
REGARDLESS OF ANCESTRY OR SOCIAL STATUS.  THE 
CROATIAN PEOPLE WISH TO ACHIEVE THE BASIC RIGHT OF 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00066  01 OF 03  161536Z 
EVERY NATION TO SELF-DETERMINATION. 
 
I TAKE THIS OPPORTUNITY TO ASK FOR YOUR ASSISTANCE 
AND SUPPORT IN THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE FREELY 
EXPRESSED WII) 9| 5#3 :858\"3, 9| 5#3 4307?)8: 9| 
:49-58-, HAVING IN MIND YOUR INTERNATIONAL STATURE 
AND YOUR POSITION, AS THE PRESIDENT OF THE WORLD 
JEWISH CONGRESS, THE HIGHEST REPRESENTATIVE BODY OF 
THE JEWISH PEOPLE IN ALL COUNTRIES WHOSE CITIZENS 
INCLUDE JEWS.  I SINCERELY HOPE THAT THE JEWISH 
PEOPLE WILL SHOW UNDERSTANDING AND SUPPORT OUR 
EFFORTS, WHICH ARE ALMOST IDENTICAL WITH THE 
LONG-STANDING STRUGGLE OF THE JEWISH PEOPLE TO 
REALIZE THEIR NATIONAL RIGHT TO STATEHOOD, A RIGHT 
AFFIRMED BY THE WORLD IN 1948 WHEN THE STATE OF 
ISRAEL WAS PROCLAIMED. 
THE MILLENNIAL DREAM OF THE JEWISH PEOPLE, REALIZED 
IN THE ESTABLISHMENT OF THE STATE OF ISRAEL, WAS 
ASSOCIATED WITH HORRIBLE SUFFERING AND PERSECUTION, 
CULMINATING IN THE TRAGIC EVENTS DURING THE SECOND 
WORLD WAR.  AS IN MOST EUROPEAN COUNTRIES, THE 
CROATIAN JEWISH COMMUNITY, WHOSE CONTRIBUTION TO THE 
CULTURAL, PUBLIC, ECONOMIC AND SPIRITUAL LIFE OF 
CROATIA HAS BEEN INVALUABLE, SUFFERED TRAGIC LOSSES 
DURING THE WAR.  ABOUT THREE HUNDRED THOUSAND 
CROATIAN CITIZENS- CROATS, SERBS, JEWS AND OTHERS - 
FELL IN THE ANTIFASCIST STRUGGLE AND AS VICTIMS OF 
FASCISM AND NAZISM.  THE USTASHA REGIME OF THE 
INDEPENDENT STATE OF CROATIA COMMITTED COUNTLESS WAR 
CRIMES AND CRIMES AGAINST HUMANITY.  THAT WAS A 
REGIME WHICH, UNDER THE PROTECTION OF THE NAZI AND 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00066  01 OF 03  161536Z 
FASCIST OCCUPATION FORCES, PERSECUTED JEWS AND 
MEMBERS OF OTHER NATIONALITIES AS WELL AS CROATIAN 
POLITICAL OPPONENTS IN THE MOST BRUTAL MANNER.  WITH 
 
 
