SUBJECT:  ZAGREB UPDATE:  MARCH 17, 1992 
 
 
UNPROFOR ARRIVES IN SLAVONIA 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
5.  ACCORDING TO THE MARCH 17 ZAGREB PRESS, THE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00409  03 OF 03  171525Z 
FIRST CONTINGENT OF UN TROUPS DESTINED FOR THE 
OCCUPIED TERRITORY OF SLAVONIA HAVE BEGUN 
ARRIVING.  THE PRESS ACCOUNTS INDICATE THAT 38 
RUSSIAN OFFICERS ARRIVED MARCH 16 IN DALJ IN 
EASTERN SLAVONIA.  THEY HAVE BEGUN TO EXAMINE 
POSSIBILITIES FOR FUTURE UN FORCES BASES. 
 
CARRINGTON AND VANCE TO SLOVENIA? 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
6.  THE ZAGREB DAILY \"VECERNJI LIST\" OF MARCH 17 
QUOTES THE SLOVENIAN PRESIDENT MILAN KUCAN AS 
HAVING TOLD A SLOVENIAN ASSEMBLY COMMITTEE THAT 
THE EC MEDIATOR, LORD CARRINGTON, AND THE UN ENVOY 
CYRUS VANCE MAY VISIT SLOVENIA THIS WEEK. 
ACCORDING TO THE PRESS REPORTS, KUCAN IMPLIED THAT 
VANCE AND CARRINGTON WOULD HOLD TALKS WITH 
SLOVENIAN OFFICIALS ON SUCCESSOR STATE ISSUES. 
KUCAN HAS COME OUT AGAINST THE \"RUSSIAN MODEL\", 
WHICH ALLOWED FOR THE RUSSIAN REPUBLIC TO BECOME 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00409  03 OF 03  171525Z 
THE INTERNATIONALLY RECOGNIZED LEGAL SUCCESSOR OF 
THE USSR.  ACCORDING TO KUCAN, ALL SIX YUGOSLAV 
REPUBLICS HAVE THE SAME RIGHTS TO SUCCESSION. 
(CONSULAR STAFF MEMBER WILL VISIT LJUBLJANA ON 
THURSDAY, MARCH 19, AND WILL ATTEMPT TO CONFIRM IF 
VANCE AND CARRINGTON WILL VISIT LJUBLJANA). 
 
RECOGNITION UPDATE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
7.  IN ADDITION TO THE 47 STATES WHICH HAVE 
ALREADY RECOGNIZED CROATIA, PERU (ON MARCH 15) AND 
JAPAN (ON MARCH 17) HAVE BECOME THE LATEST TO ALSO 
RECOGNIZE THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA. 
ROSE 
 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
