- 
1.  CONFIDENTIAL - ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
THE SERBIAN CHARGE:  FEAR, EXPULSIONS AND 
DISAPPEARANCES 
--------------------------------------------- --------- 
 
4.  WITH THE \"HOT\" WAR ABATING, DAMPENED BY THE 
ARRIVAL OF UN PEACEKEEPING FORCES, THE FIGHT OVER 
LAND (WITH ORDINARY CITIZENS AS THE COMBATANTS) IS 
HEATING UP.  EMBASSY BELGRADE AND CONGEN ZAGREB HAVE 
REPORTED ON THE EFFORTS OF BOTH SIDES TO FORCE 
CIVILIANS TO FLEE THEIR HOMES AND RESETTLE EITHER 
CROATS OR SERBS IN THE ABANDONED PROPERTIES IN ORDER 
TO REARRANGE THE ETHNIC MAKE-UP OF ENTIRE VILLAGES 
AND TOWNS.  EVEN IN THE LARGER CITIES, THERE HAVE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  02 OF 09  310735Z 
BEEN CHARGES THAT A CLIMATE OF FEAR AND INTIMIDATION 
HAS BEEN CREATED TO PRESSURE MEMBERS OF ONE ETHNIC 
GROUP TO LEAVE, THEREBY REDUCING THE PERCENTAGE OF 
THAT GROUP WITHIN THE OVERALL POPULATION.  THE 
FOLLOWING SCORE CARDS ARE NOT ALL-INCLUSIVE, OTHERS 
SUCH AS HELSINKI WATCH HAVE MORE RESOURCES TO COMPILE 
SUCH DATA.  THE OBJECTIVE HERE IS RATHER TO HIGHLIGHT 
THE MAJOR CASES AND GIVE A SENSE OF THE ATMOSPHERE AS 
THE UN PEACEKEEPERS BEGIN TO ARRIVE. 
- 
5.  ON THE SERB SIDE, CASES OF ABUSE ARE REPORTED 
ALMOST DAILY IN THE BELGRADE PRESS.  LOCAL ZAGREB 
BASED HUMAN RIGHTS ACTIVISTS ARE ALSO KEEPING TRACK, 
THOUGH IT IS DIFFICULT TO VERIFY THE REPORTS OF EVEN 
THE MOST CREDIBLE SOURCE.  FOR AN UPDATE, WE SPOKE 
WITH SERBIAN ACTIVIST MILORAD PUPOVAC ON MARCH 25, 
WHO CONFIRMED THAT PRESSURE CONTINUES TO BE EXERTED 
ON THE SERBIAN COMMUNITY OF CROATIA.  PUPOVAC AGAIN 
EXPRESSED PARTICULAR CONCERN ABOUT THE FORCED FLIGHT 
OF URBAN SERBS.  MOST RECENTLY, IN THE MAJOR COASTAL 
CITY OF ZADAR, THE SERBIAN LEADER CLAIMED THAT THE 
HOMES AND PROPERTY OF SERBS WHO HAVE TEMPORARILY LEFT 
ARE BEING \"MINED AND BLOWN UP.\"  IN THE CASE OF 
ZAGREB, PUPOVAC ESTIMATED THAT PERHAPS HALF OF THE 
SERBS WHO HAD BEEN RESIDING IN THE CROATIAN CAPITAL 
HAD LEFT, AT LEAST TEMPORARILY.  HE POINTED TO THE 
NON-PAYMENT OF PENSIONS TO RETIRED JNA OFFICERS 
(WHICH HE SAID HAD A GREATER IMPACT ON THE SERBIAN 
COMMUNITY) AS A SERIOUS MATTER WHICH COULD LEAD TO 
ABANDONMENT OF HOUSES AND APARTMENTS SINCE THE 
RESIDENT ARE UNABLE TO PAY FOR UTILITY SERVICES AND 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  02 OF 09  310735Z 
OTHER RELATED EXPENSES.  (FYI:  WE HAVE MIXED REPORTS 
ON THIS, WITH SOME SERBS SAYING THEY CONTINUE TO 
ROUTINELY RECEIVE THEIR JNA PENSIONS.) 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
