TAGS:  PGOV, PHUM, PREL, YO 
SUBJECT:  SERBS AND HUMAN RIGHTS:  A QUESTION OF 
DEMOCRACY IN CROATIA 
- 
1.  CONFIDENTIAL - ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
6.  AS HE DID IN OUR PREVIOUS MEETINGS, PUPOVAC CITED 
A NUMBER OF SPECIFIC AND DETAILED ABUSES AGAINST 
SERBS.  HE ADMITTED THAT SOME OF THE INCIDENTS HAD 
BEEN INVESTIGATED BY CROATIAN OFFICIALS.  BUT WHILE 
MANY IN THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT UNDERSTOOD THAT THOSE 
RESPONSIBLE SHOULD BE PUNISHED, IT APPEARED THAT THE 
MORE HARD-LINE ELEMENT HOLDS GREAT SWAY AT THE 
MOMENT.  HERE ARE SOME OF THE SPECIFICS PUPOVAC 
CITED.  (FYI:  ALL OF THESE CASES HAVE BEEN REPORTED 
EARLIER BY EITHER CONGEN, EMBASSY OR HELSINKI WATCH.) 
- 
--  GOSPIC:  PUPOVAC SAID 180 SERBS HAD DISAPPEARED 
THERE.  SIXTY-THREE WERE CONFIRMED DEAD, THE REST ARE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  03 OF 09  310736Z 
PRESUMED JAILED OR DEAD.  IN SEPARATE INSTANCES, 
SERBS FROM ZAGREB HAD BEEN KIDNAPPED FROM ZAGREB AND 
TAKEN TO GOSPIC.  WE HAVE BEEN TOLD BY SEVERAL OF OUR 
CONTACTS THAT THE CROATIAN SIDE WAS KIDNAPPING SERBS 
TO USE AS BARTER TO OBTAIN THE RETURN OF CAPTURED 
CROATIAN CIVILIANS. 
 
--  PUPOVAC SAID SERBS WHO RETURNED TO THEIR HOMES 
AFTER FLEEING THE FIGHTING WERE BEING MISTREATED.  HE 
CITED THE CASE OF DARUVAR, WHERE HE SAID SIGNS WERE 
POSTED LISTING 9,000 NAMES OF AREA SERB RESIDENTS; 
THESE SIGNS ACCUSED ALL OF THEM OF BEING ENEMIES OF 
CROATIA AND CALLED FOR THEIR EXPULSION. 
 
--  HE SAID 100 SERBS FROM VIROVITICA HAD DISAPPEARED. 
 
7.  MORE GENERALLY, PUPOVAC SAID THAT WHILE HE FOUND 
SOME MEMBERS OF THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT INDIVIDUALLY 
UNDERSTANDING OF THE NEED TO COME TO TERMS WITH THE 
PROBLEMS FACING SERB-CROAT RELATIONS IN AN 
INDEPENDENT CROATIA (HE SPECIFICALLY SPOKE OF HAVING 
A LONG AND USEFUL TALK WITH OPPOSITION LEADER DRAZEN 
BUDISA WHILE HE WAS STILL IN THE GOVERNMENT AND OF 
GOOD CONTACTS WITH SAVKA DABCEVIC-KUCAR, AN 
UNANNOUNCED CANDIDATE FOR PRESIDENT), TUDJMAN HIMSELF 
DOES NOT HAVE SUFFICIENT CREDIBILITY WITH SERBS TO 
REACH AN ACCORD WITH THEM, AND THE CROATIAN 
GOVERNMENT AS A WHOLE IS NOT READY TO SOLVE THE 
PROBLEMS OF URBAN SERBS IN CROATIA.  IN HIS MOST 
PESSIMISTIC NOTE, PUPOVAC SPECULATED THAT CROATIAN 
AUTHORITIES ARE ACTUALLY HOPING THAT THE FEAR AND 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  03 OF 09  310736Z 
PRESSURES NOW ON URBAN SERBS WILL HELP REDUCE THE 
POPULATION TO BELOW 8 PERCENT OF THE REPUBLIC\'S 
TOTAL, THEREBY EXCLUDING IT FROM THE GUARANTEES FOR 
REPRESENTATION AS SPELLED OUT IN THE NEW ELECTION 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
