LAW.  HE CLAIMED THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT WAS TRYING 
TO DRIVE OUT MILAN DUKIC, THE LONELY SERB IN THE 
CROATIAN ASSEMBLY.  (NOTE: MANY HERE BELIEVE THAT 
DUKIC READILY PLAYS THE ROLE OF THE \"GOOD SERB\" AND 
EVEN RECEIVES FINANCIAL SUPPORT FOR HIS PARTY FROM 
THE GOVERNMENT.  DUKIC HAS NEVER, TO OUR KNOWLEDGE, 
EXPRESSED ANY CONCERN FOR HIS WELL-BEING, OR ANY 
INTENTION TO ABANDON CROATIA.) 
 
8.  ALTHOUGH PUPOVAC\'S ALLEGATIONS ARE THE MORE 
DETAILED AND SPECIFIC, OTHERS (INCLUDING CROATS) HAVE 
EXPRESSED SIMILAR CONCERNS ABOUT THE STATE OF HUMAN 
RIGHTS IN CROATIA.  DUKIC, DESPITE THE DOUBTS ABOUT 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  04 OF 09  310737Z 
HIS BONIFIDES TO SPEAK AS A REPRESENTATIVE OF THE 
SERBIAN PEOPLE, HAS RECENTLY BEEN MORE ASSERTIVE IN 
DENOUNCING ABUSES AGAINST SERBS IN THE REPUBLIC. 
CROATIAN OPPOSITION POLITICAL FIGURES, SUCH AS SAVKA 
DABCEVIC KUCAR OF THE CROATIAN NATIONAL PARTY AND 
DRAZEN BUDISA OF THE CROATIAN SOCIAL LIBERAL PARTY 
HAVE, WITHIN THE CONTEXT OF DECRYING THE 
CONCENTRATION OF POWER IN THE HANDS OF ONE MAN AND 
THE INCREASING SENSE OF VITUAL LAWLESSNESS IN SOME 
PARTS OF THE REPUBLIC, COMPLAINED OF THE DECREASING 
RESPECT FOR DEMOCRATIC PRINCIPLES. 
 
THE CROATIAN CHARGE:  FEAR, EXPULSIONS AND KILLINGS 
--------------------------------------------- ------ 
 
9.  THE CROATS, TOO, HAVE MADE A CASE FOR THE ABUSE 
AND GRIEVOUS MISTREATMENT OF CROATIAN RESIDENTS BY 
JNA/SERB FORCES IN THE OCCUPIED TERRITORIES OF 
CROATIA-  WE PROVIDE THE FOLLOWING ILLUSTRATIVE 
INFORMATION REPORTED IN THE CROATIAN MEDIA: 
 
--  ON MARCH 15, 139 CROATIAN CITIZENS OF THE VILLAGE 
OF BOKSIC, NEAR VUKOVAR, WERE EXPELLED BY SERBIAN 
TERRITORIAL DEFENSE UNITS FROM THE NEARBY VILLAGE OF 
CAKOVAC. 
- 
--  IN TORDINCI, A VILLAGE IN SLAVONIA WHICH HAS BEEN 
UNDER THE CONTROL OF THE JNA FOR ALMOST FIVE MONTHS, 
30 INNOCENT PEOPLE HAVE BEEN KILLED.  THE CROATS 
ALLEGED THAT THEIR BODIES WERE BURIED IN A MASS GRAVE 
NEAR THE CATHOLIC CHURCH. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  04 OF 09  310737Z 
 
--  FROM THE ILOK REGION, 12,000 PEOPLE HAVE 
REPORTEDLY BEEN EXPELLED.  AFTER THE EXODUS, ONLY 
3,780 CROATS REMAIN.  IN THIS REGION, BEFORE THE 
 
 
