FIGHTING, SERBS WERE IN THE MINORITY.  ACCORDING TO 
CROATIAN FIGURES, THE POPULATION HAD BEEN COMPRISED 
OF 11,500 CROATS (71 PERCENT) AND 2,000 SERBS (12 
PERCENT). 
 
--  ON JANUARY 19, 64 PEOPLE FROM AN AREA AROUND 
BENKOVAC WERE FORCED TO ABANDON THEIR HOMES AFTER THE 
JNA FAILED TO PROVIDE SECURITY FROM POTENTIAL ATTACKS 
FROM CHETNIK BANDS. 
 
--  ON JANUARY 22, 110 PEOPLE OF CROATIAN NATIONALITY 
