THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT: GROWING CONCERNS 
------------------------------------------ 
 
10.  ALTHOUGH THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT CONTINUES TO 
VIEW HUMAN RIGHTS ISSUES AS POLITICAL PROBLEMS, WHICH 
ACCOUNTS FOR ITS ALMOST TIT-FOR-TAT REPORTING OF 
SERBIAN VIOLATIONS OF THE RIGHTS OF CROATS, THERE IS 
A GROWING SENSE THAT THE OVERALL SECURITY SITUATION 
IN THE REPUBLIC IS SPIRALLING OUT OF CONTROL. 
GENERAL CRIME IS ON THE RISE AND THERE IS A GROWING 
BREAKDOWN OF LAW AND ORDER.  AT LEAST SOME OFFICIALS 
IN THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT HAVE MADE THE CONNECTION 
BETWEEN TOLERATION OF VIOLATIONS OF HUMAN RIGHTS 
AGAINST SERBS AND THE DECLINING STATE OF DEMOCRACY IN 
THE REPUBLIC. 
- 
11.  IN AN ARTICLE PUBLISHED IN THE JANUARY 31 
EDITION OF THE POLITICAL INFLUENTIAL DAILY \"VJESNIK\", 
SOME CASES WERE REVEALED ABOUT THE BEHAVIOR OF 
PERSONS IN CROATIAN UNIFORMS AND LOCAL OFFICIALS FOR 
WHOM THE WAR HAS BECOME A COVER-UP FOR THE 
ACHIEVEMENT OF NUMEROUS PRIVATE, COLLECTIVE AND PARTY 
INTERESTS ACCORDING TO \"VJESNIK\": 
 
--  A RULE WAS ESTABLISHED IN KARLOVAC THAT EACH 
DYNAMITING OR SHELLING OF CROATIAN HOUSES IN THE 
KARLOVAC SUBURBS (THE ZONE WHICH IS UNDER SERB/JNA 
CONTROL) WOULD RESULT IN RETALIATORY EXPLOSIONS OF 
HOUSES OF EXILED SERBS; 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  05 OF 09  310738Z 
--  IN ZADAR, UNIFORMED \"DEFENDERS\", INSTEAD OF 
DEFENDING THEIR CITY, \"DEFENDED\" WITH GUNS THE 
APARTMENTS OF JNA OFFICERS WHO HAD MOVED AWAY; 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
