BRUSSELS ALSO FOR USEC; VIENNA ALSO FOR USDEL CSBM 
 
E.O. 12356:  DECL:  OADR 
TAGS:  PGOV, PHUM, PREL, YO 
SUBJECT:  SERBS AND HUMAN RIGHTS:  A QUESTION OF 
DEMOCRACY IN CROATIA 
- 
1.  CONFIDENTIAL - ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
--  ON THE WESTERN SLAVONIA FRONT, ONE CROATIAN UNIT 
\"KEPT SECRET\" FOR TWO DAYS THEIR ENTRY INTO ONE OF 
THE MORE PROSPEROUS SERBIAN VILLAGES IN ORDER TO HAVE 
ENOUGH TIME TO \"CLEAN IT UP\"; 
 
--  UNIFORMED PERSONS ENTER LOCAL BARS WITH THEIR 
FIREARMS, SHOOTING TO QUIET DOWN THE MUSIC, AND 
DRINKING AT THE EXPENSE OF \"CROATIA\".  PASSING 
THROUGH SERBIAN VILLAGES, THESE PERSONS FIRE OFF 
THEIR WEAPONS IN ORDER TO CREATE A \"WAR ATMOSPHERE\" 
AND CALL INTO QUESTION THE SECURITY OF THE LOCAL 
POPULATION; 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  06 OF 09  310740Z 
--  EXECUTIVE ORGANS HOLD \"ALL POWER\" IN LOCAL 
COMMUNITIES AND ACT WITH IMPUNITY IN THEIR DEALINGS 
WITH RESIDENTS, ESPECIALLY SERBS. 
 
12.  IN A MARCH 5 PRESS CONFERENCE, CROATIAN PRIME 
MINISTER, FRANJO GREGURIC, EXPRESSED EXPLICIT CONCERN 
OVER THESE NEGATIVE TRENDS.  AMONG OTHER POINTS, HE 
STATED THAT: 
- 
--  THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT MUST RENEW ITS EMPHASIS 
ON RESPECT FOR CITIZENS\' RIGHTS, PUBLIC ORDER AND 
PEACE.  \"THOSE WHO DO NOT WISH TO FOLLOW SUCH A 
POLICY\", SAID GREGURIC, \"WILL HAVE TO LEAVE.\" 
BURGLARIES, ROBBERIES AND BOMBINGS OF PRIVATE HOMES 
AND BUILDINGS MUST STOP; 
 
--  THE GOVERNMENT HAS PROPOSED AND PRESIDENT 
TUDJMAN HAS ACCEPTED, THE ABOLISHMENT OF THE 
REPUBLICAN AND COMMUNITY CRISIS HEADQUARTERS.  LOCAL 
EXECUTIVE COUNCILS, AS THE LEGAL CIVIL AUTHORITIES, 
MUST REGAIN AUTHORITY ON THEIR TERRITORY; 
 
--  THE EMERGENCY LEGAL POWER WHICH WAS GRANTED BY 
THE ASSEMBLY TO THE GOVERNMENT TO ISSUE BINDING 
DECREES IN TIME OF WAR WILL SOON BE \"RETURNED\" TO THE 
ASSEMBLY; 
 
--IT IS NECESSARY TO SECURE DISCIPLINE IN CROATIAN 
ARMY UNITS.  NO PARALLEL MILITARY FORMATIONS CAN BE 
TOLERATED; 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  06 OF 09  310740Z 
--  THE SIZE AND MISSION OF THE CROATIAN ARMY MUST BE 
CLEARLY DEFINED.  \"CROATIA MUST NOT BE A MILITARISTIC 
COUNTRY.\"  IN THE FUTURE, THE GOVERNMENT WILL MORE 
CLOSELY CONTROL CROATIAN ARMY EXPENSES.  JNA BARRACKS 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
