1.  CONFIDENTIAL - ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
HAVE TO BE RETURNED TO THE CITIES FOR CIVILIAN USE. 
THOSE WHICH HAVE \"FAVORABLE LOCATIONS\" COULD BE 
OFFERED TO THE U.N. PEACEKEEPING FORCES IN CROATIA; 
 
--  THE GOVERNMENT IS MAKING EFFORTS TO SOLVE THE 
REPUBLIC\'S ECONOMIC PROBLEMS.  BECAUSE PRODUCTION HAS 
TO BE STIMULATED, MILITARY FORCES HAVE TO BE 
REDUCED.  THE GOVERNMENT IS ALSO WORKING SERIOUSLY ON 
A PRIVATIZATION PROGRAM. 
- 
13.  CROATS OUSIDE OF THE GOVERNMENT HAVE ALSO BECOME 
CONCERNED WITH WHAT EFFECT THE FIGHT AGAINST THE 
SO-CALLED \"FIFTH COLUMN\" OF DISLOYAL SERBS AND OTHERS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  07 OF 09  310742Z 
HAS DONE TO THE STATE OF DEMOCRACY IN CROATIA.  THE 
WELL RESPECTED, INDEPENDENT POLITICAL WEEKLY \"DANAS\" 
HAS CONSISTENTLY OVER THE PAST SEVERAL MONTHS RAISED 
THE SPECTER OF AN ELABORATE STATE SECURITY APPARATUS 
EXISTING BEYOND THE CONTROL OF THE GOVERNMENT, UNDER 
THE CONTROL OF LONG-TIME TRUSTED TUDJMAN CRONY JOSIP 
MANOLIC (A SECURITY OFFICIAL UNDER FORMER COMMUNIST 
REGIMES) AND ANSWERABLE ONLY TO TUDJMAN.  THE CIRCLE 
THAT SERVES AS THE CROATIAN PRESIDENT\'S REAL ADVISERS 
GROWS TIGHTER, WITH DISPROPORTIONATE POWER RESTING IN 
THE HANDS OF AN EVER SMALLER GROUP.  THE RECENT 
PETITION DRIVE OF YOUTH OPPOSITION LEADERS CALLING 
FOR THE RESIGNATION OF MEDIA CZAR ANTON VRDOLJAK 
(ANOTHER CLOSE TUDJMAN ADVISER) IS ANOTHER REFLECTION 
OF THIS CONCERN. 
 
TUDJMAN: THE NEW CROATIAN HUMAN RIGHTS MAN? 
------------------------------------------- 
 
14.  AT A FEBRUARY 3 PRESS CONFERENCE, THE CROATIAN 
PRESIDENT, FRANJO TUDJMAN, ENDORSED A CALL BY THE 
EXECUTIVE COUNCIL OF HIS OWN PARTY FOR A \"POLITICAL 
ACTION\" AGAINST ABUSE AND CRIME.  \"LEGALITY HAS TO 
RULE IN CROATIA\", SAID TUDJMAN AND \"CROATIA MUST BE A 
LEGAL STATE WHICH IS AGAINST ALL FORM OF ABUSE AND 
ARBITRARINESS.\"  ACCORDING TO JOURNALISTS, TUDJMAN 
NOTED THAT IN ADDITION TO THE LEGAL AND POLITICAL 
PROBLEMS INHERENT IN THE CROAT-SERB RELATIONSHIP, A 
PSYCHOLOGICAL PROBLEM IS ALSO PRESENT.  THE CROATIAN 
PRESIDENT REPORTEDLY CALLED FOR A CONCILIATORY HAND 
TO BE EXTENDED TO THOSE \"WHO PROVOKED THE WAR.\" 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  07 OF 09  310742Z 
 
15.  IN RECENT DAYS, TUDJMAN HAS CONTINUED HIS HUMAN 
RIGHTS OFFENSIVE, HOLDING CORDIAL MEETINGS WITH 
DELEGATIONS FROM HELSINKI WATCH, THE EC, AND A LOCAL 
 
 
