SUBJECT:  SERBS AND HUMAN RIGHTS:  A QUESTION OF 
DEMOCRACY IN CROATIA 
- 
1.  CONFIDENTIAL - ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
AMNESTY COMMITTEE MADE UP OF SERBS AND OPPOSITION 
FIGURES.  IN PARTICULAR, CROATIA\'S RESPONSE TO THE 
HELSINKI WATCH REPORT ON HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS IN 
CROATIA DID NOT HAVE THE DEFENSIVE, PRICKLY SLANT 
WHICH THE GOVERNMENT NORMALLY TAKES IN RESPONDING TO 
SUCH ALLEGATIONS.  TO BE SURE, THE CROATIAN 
GOVERNMENT TOOK THE OPPORTUNITY TO CHIDE HELSINKI 
WATCH FOR NOT BEING MORE INTERESTED IN THE PLIGHT OF 
CROATS IN THE SO-CALLED JNA-OCCUPIED REGIONS.  BUT 
THE CROATIAN REPLY WAS DETAILED AND REVEALED CLEARLY 
THAT THE CROATS HAD TAKEN SERIOUSLY THE ALLEGATIONS. 
 
16.  EVEN MORE IMPORTANTLY, FOR THE FIRST TIME THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00468  08 OF 09  310744Z 
CROATS APPEARED TO REACT IN A CONSTRUCTIVE WAY TO THE 
CHARGES AND ADMITTED SHORTCOMINGS IN ITS 
RESPONSIBILITY TO PROTECT THE RIGHTS OF ALL OF ITS 
CITIZENS.  IN ITS INTRODUCTORY STATEMENT, THE TUDJMAN 
GOVERNMENT DECLARED THAT \"THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT IS 
AWARE THAT SOME CRIMES HAVE BEEN COMMITTED ALSO BY 
PERSONS WEARING THE UNIFORMS OF THE CROATIAN FORCES,\" 
BUT QUICKLY NOTED THAT \"THESE PERSONS HAVE BEEN 
ARRESTED AND PROSECUTED.\"  THE STATEMENT ROUNDLY AND 
UNEQUIVOCALLY CONDEMNED SUCH CRIMES, INDICATED THAT 
THE GOVERNMENT HAD REQUESTED FROM ITS DEPARTMENTS 
REPORTS ON VIOLATIONS OF HUMAN RIGHTS AND CONCLUDED 
THAT \"SPECIAL STRESS IS ON THEIR GREATER COMMITMENT 
TO PREVENT THE RECURRENCE OF SIMILAR CASES.\"  AND, IN 
A MOST ATYPICAL TONE, EXPRESSED \"THANKS TO THE 
HELSINKI WATCH COMMITTEE FOR THE ATTENTION IT HAS 
DEDICATED TO THE EVENTS IN CROATIA AND FOR THE 
ATTEMPT TO PRESENT THE FACTS ABOUT ABUSES IN AN 
OBJECTIVE MANNER.\" 
 
17.  COMMENT:  ARE WE BEGINNING TO SEE A KINDER, 
GENTLER CROATIAN PRESIDENT ON THE ISSUE OF HUMAN 
RIGHTS?  WE WOULD LIKE TO BE ABLE TO CONCLUDE THAT 
OUR MANY PROTESTATIONS TO TUDJMAN AND HIS AIDES ON 
THESE QUESTIONS ARE FINALLY STARTING TO PAY 
DIVIDENDS, BUT WE ARE NOT FULLY CONVINCED OF THIS. 
FOR TUDJMAN, HUMAN RIGHTS IS STILL A NAGGING 
POLITICAL ISSUE.  OTHERS (GREGURIC, TOMAC) MAY BE 
SINCERELY TROUBLED BY THIS INCREASING SPIRAL OF 
VIOLENCE.  FOR THEM, OUR PRESSURE AND THAT OF OTHERS 
MAY HAVE HAD AN IMPACT IN MAKING IT CLEAR TO THEM 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00468  08 OF 09  310744Z 
THAT ALONG WITH GRANTING RECOGNITION, THE WORLD WILL 
INSIST ON CERTAIN STANDARDS IN TERMS OF HUMAN 
RIGHTS.  AS WE MOVE BEYOND THE WAR STAGE, THESE 
PEOPLE ARE AWARE THAT THERE WILL BE NO MORE READY 
 
 
