SIPDIS 
 
 
BRUSSELS ALSO FOR USEC; VIENNA ALSO FOR USDEL CSBM 
 
E.O. 12356: DECL: OADR 
TAGS: PREL, PGOV, ECON, YO 
SUBJECT:  CROATIA, SLOVENIA AND THE U.S.:  THE FUTURE 
IS NOW 
 
20.  IN SPITE OF ALL OF CROATIA\'S INTENTIONS AND 
HOPES FOR CLOSE, FRIENDLY TIES, THAT RELATIONSHIP 
WILL BE AT TIMES STRAINED BY ALMOST INESCAPABLE HUMAN 
RIGHTS PROBLEMS ARISING FROM THE WAR AND OTHER ISSUES 
OF DEMOCRATIC DEVELOPMENT.  THE EC WILL, OF COURSE, 
HAVE A ROLE.  BUT POLITICAL LEADERS AND ORDINARY 
CITIZENS WILL LOOK TO THE U.S. TO TAKE THE LEAD. 
MORE SO THAN THE SLOVENES, THE CROATS SEE THE U.S. 
GOVERNMENTAL STRUCTURE AS THE MODEL THEY WOULD PREFER 
TO EMULATE, WITH CERTAIN CROATIAN-INSPIRED 
MODIFICATIONS.  STRUCTURAL CHANGES ASIDE, THE REAL 
TEST OF GOVERNING ULTIMATELY RESTS ON ACTIONS TAKEN. 
CROATIA HAS A HARDER ROAD TO TRAVEL THAN SLOVENIA IN 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00527  07 OF 07  091307Z 
TERMS OF DEVELOPING A DEMOCRATIC, FREE MARKET 
SYSTEM.  ITS SUCCESS WILL BE OF GREATER INTEREST, NOT 
ONLY TO EUROPE BUT ALSO TO THE U.S.  WE COULD HAVE 
MAJOR INFLUENCE IN HELPING THEM DO IT RIGHT.  EINIK 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
