BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA AND THE CONCLUSION OF THE PEACE 
CONFERENCE IN BRUSSELS.  IT IS THEREFORE NECESSARY TO 
CONSIDER OTHER MEANS, IN ADDITION TO ALREADY EXISTING 
ECONOMIC AND POLITICAL PRESSURE, IN ORDER TO HALT THE 
AGGRESSION AND TO GUARANTEE INTERNATIONAL PEACE, AS 
ENVISIONED IN THE UNITED NATIONS CHARTER. 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00557  02 OF 02  141422Z 
 
YOUR EXCELLENCY, IN THE NAME OF DEMOCRATIC PRINCIPLES 
AND PEACE BETWEEN NATIONS AND PEOPLES, FOR WHICH YOU 
HAVE INTERCEDED, I APPEAL TO YOU TO DO ALL IN YOUR 
POWER AND IN THE POWER OF THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY 
TO HALT THE BARBARIC AGGRESSION AND PREVENT FURTHER 
DESTRUCTION OF ENTIRE COMMUNITIES, AS WELL AS THE 
DEATH AND SUFFERING OF HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF 
CIVILIANS, INNOCENT AND WEAK ELDERLY CITIZENS, WOMEN 
AND CHILDREN. 
 
IN THE HOPE THAT YOU WILL IMMEDIATELY UNDERTAKE 
EFFECTIVE AND DECISIVE MEASURES, PLEASE ACCEPT, YOUR 
EXCELLENCY, THE EXPRESSION OF MY DEEPEST RESPECT. 
 
PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA 
DR. FRANJO TUDJMAN 
 
ZAGREB, APRIL 13, 1992 
 
END TEXT. 
 
