TAGS: PGOV, PREL, PHUM, HR, PREL, PHUM, HR, PREL, PHUM, HR, PREL, PHUM, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  MAY 04 APPEAL FOR ACTION BY CROATIAN 
          GOVERNMENT 
 
 
1.  CROATIAN FOREIGN MINISTER SEPAROVIC CALLED IN THE 
CONSULAR/DIPLOMATIC CORPS LATE YESTERDAY AFTERNOON 
(MAY 05) TO PRESENT THE FOLLOWING STATEMENT WHICH WAS 
AGREED TO DURING THE PREVIOUS DAYS CABINET MEETING 
AND IS SIGNED BY PRIME MINISTER GREGURIC.  IT CALLS 
ON THE WORLD TO TAKE AGGRESSIVE ACTION TO COUNTER 
WHAT ZAGREB CONSIDERS AS A WORSENING SITUATION IN 
BOTH CROATIA AND BOSNIA/HERCEGOVINA. 
 
2.  BEGIN TEXT (ENGLISH TRANSLATION AS PROVIDED BY 
THE FORMIN). 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00692  01 OF 04  061328Z 
STATEMENT BY THE GOVERNMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA 
 
AT ITS SESSION ON MAY 4, 1992, THE GOVERNMENT OF THE 
REPUBLIC OF CROATIA REVIEWED THE STATE OF SECURITY IN 
THE REPUBLIC IN THE WAKE OF INTENSIFIED AGGRESSIVE 
MOVES BY THE FORMER YUGOSLAV PEOPLE\'S ARMY (JNA), 
SERBIA AND MONTENEGRO AGAINST CROATIA.  THE 
GOVERNMENT ALSO CONSIDERED THE AFTERMATH OF THE 
ATTACK ON THE REPUBLIC OF BOSNIA & HERCEGOVINA AND 
ARRIVED AT THE FOLLOWING CONCLUSIONS: 
 
1.  THE FORMER JNA AND THE REPUBLICS OF SERBIA AND 
MONTENEGRO, IN THEIR REFUSAL TO ABIDE BY SOME BASIC 
STANDARDS PREVAILING IN THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY 
TODAY AND RELATED TO THE PROHIBITION OF WAR 
OPERATIONS, THE PROVISIONS OF THE GENEVA AND SARAJEVO 
AGREEMENTS ON THE CEASEFIRE IN CROATIA, THE 
RESPECTIVE UN PEACE PLAN AND OTHER DOCUMENTS ISSUED 
BY THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY, HAVE RENEWED THEIR 
ATTACKS AT CROATIA WITH INCREASED INTENSITY AND 
APPLICATION OF HIGHLY DESTRUCTIVE WEAPONS FORBIDDEN 
BY INTERNATIONAL CONVENTIONS.  WANTON DEVASTATION OF 
OSIJEK, VINKOVICI, ZADAR, METKOVIC AND OTHER TOWNS 
AND PLACES GO ON UNABATED.  THE ATTACK ON SLAVONSKI 
BROD IS AN EXAMPLE OF A BRUTAL CRIME COMMITTED 
AGAINST INNOCENT CIVILIANS, DEFENCELESS WOMEN AND 
CHILDREN.  THE AGGRESSORS CONTINUE TO BURN DOWN 
DWELLING AND COMMERCIAL BUILDINGS, TO EXPEL CROATS 
AND OTHER NON-SERBIANS FROM OCCUPIED AREAS AND TO 
LAUNCH INSIDIOUS ATTACKS AT CIVILIAN TARGETS AND THE 
CROATIAN ARMY DEFENCE POSITIONS.  SUCH ATTACKS, AS 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00692  01 OF 04  061328Z 
WELL AS THOSE AGAINST EEC MONITORS AND THE ACTIONS 
THWARTING THE UNPROFOR PEACE OPERATIONS ARE DESIGNED 
TO ESCALATE THE CURRENT WAR CONFLICT AND TO UNDERMINE 
THE INTERNATIONAL PEACE EFFORTS, WHICH SHOULD ENABLE 
SERBIA, MONTENEGRO AND EX-JNA TO REALIZE BY FORCE 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
