TAGS:  PGOV, PREL, PREF, PHUM, MOPS, HR, YO 
SUBJECT:  SERBS AND CROATS IN GORSKI KOTAR:  A TALE 
OF TWO DISTRICTS 
 
 
6.  THE SECOND REASON IS THAT SERBS AND CROATS DID 
NOT FLEE THE VRBOVSKO DISTRICT AS THEY DID IN 
OTHERS.  BOTH GROUPS STUCK IT OUT THROUGH THE 
DIFFICULTIES AND NOW BOTH SIDES ASSERT THAT A CERTAIN 
NORMALIZATION IS RETURNING TO THE SERB-CROAT 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  03 OF 08  111237Z 
RELATIONSHIP THERE.  IN THE DISTRICT AS A WHOLE, THE 
POPULATION BREAKDOWN IS ABOUT 65 PERCENT CROAT, 35 
PERCENT SERB.  NATURALLY, SOME VILLAGES ARE 100 
PERCENT ONE WAY OR THE OTHER AS IS THE CASE FOR 
GOMIRJE AND SRPSKE MORAVICE (BOTH NEARLY 100 PERCENT 
SERB). 
 
VRBOVSKO:  NOT WITHOUT ITS PROBLEMS 
----------------------------------- 
 
7.  BOTH SIDES ADMITTED TO SERIOUS STRAINS IN THE 
RELATIONSHIP THAT THEY BLAMED ON SMALL GROUPS OF 
CROATIAN AND SERBIAN \"EXTREMISTS\".  \"EVERYONE IS 
ARMED,\" SAID LEADERS OF BOTH COMMUNITIES, LEADING TO 
THE PROMISE OF MUTUALLY ASSURED DESTRUCTION IN CASE 
OF ANY BREAKDOWN IN THE CURRENT PEACE.  SOME OF THE 
CAUSES OF INSTABILITY IN THE DISTRICT OVER THE LAST 
10 MONTHS INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING: 
- 
--  IN VRBOVSKO, PRIOR TO THE WAR, THERE WERE 18 
POLICEMEN, HALF OF WHOM WERE SERBS.  SINCE THE WAR, 
THE TOTAL NUMBER HAS INCREASED TO 62, TEN PERCENT OF 
WHOM ARE SERBS.  WHILE SERBS HAVE NOT BEEN FIRED FROM 
THE POLICE FORCE, THEY HAVE NOT BEEN HIRED EITHER, 
CONTRARY TO A NATIONAL REGULATION WHICH REQUIRES 
DISTRICTS TO HIRE BASED ON THE PROPORTION OF THE 
POPULATION WHICH IDENTIFIES ITSELF WITH DIFFERENT 
ETHNIC GROUPS. 
 
--  SERB LEADERS IN VRBOVSKO CONFIRMED THAT SERBS 
EMPLOYED BY THE CROATIAN RAILROAD FROM THAT AREA HAD 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00954  03 OF 08  111237Z 
LOST JOBS RECENTLY SIMPLY BECAUSE OF THEIR 
NATIONALITY.  THE CROATIAN OFFICIALS FROM VRBOVSKO 
DID NOT ARGUE WITH THIS ASSESSMENT.  LOCAL SERBS 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
