BLAMED RAILROAD AUTHORITIES IN RIJEKA AND ZAGREB FOR 
THE FIRINGS.  WHILE THE SERBS WE SPOKE WITH DID NOT 
BELIEVE THAT THIS WAS OFFICIAL CROATIAN GOVERNMENT 
POLICY, THEY FELT THAT ON SUCH ISSUES, STATED POLICY 
AND ACTUAL PRACTICE WERE QUITE DIFFERENT. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  04 OF 08  111238Z 
--  SERBS IN THE AREA WERE ARMED BEFORE THE WAR. 
CROATS ONLY GOT WEAPONS AFTER THE UNCONTROLLED 
DISBURSAL OF ARMS FROM THE FORMER JNA BASE IN OGULIN. 
 
--  PRE-WAR AND INITIAL ADDITIONAL POLICE HIRES WERE 
NOT WELL-QUALIFIED OR TRAINED FOR POLICE WORK. 
CONSEQUENTLY, TRUST IN THE POLICE, PARTICULARLY AMONG 
SERBS EBBED TO A VERY LOW LEVEL. 
 
--  FOUR HUNDRED MEMBERS OF THE CROATIAN ARMY ARE 
BASED IN VRBOVSKO.  AT THE OUTSET OF THE WAR, THE 
ARMY WAS NOT PARTICULARLY DISCIPLINED AND INCIDENTS 
INVOLVING DRUNKEN, ARMED CROATIAN SOLDIERS PROVOKING 
PEOPLE IN SERB VILLAGES WERE FREQUENT. 
 
--  SERBS AND CROATS IN VRBOVSKO BLAMED THE MEDIA FOR 
INCITING HATRED. 
- 
TURNING THINGS AROUND 
--------------------- 
 
8.  HAVING MADE IT THROUGH THE BULK OF THE WAR 
WITHOUT CONFLICT, BOTH SIDES SAID THAT THEY WERE 
COMMITTED TO IMPROVING THE SITUATION.  SERB LEADERS 
SAID THAT THERE HAVE BEEN NO PROVOCATIVE INCIDENTS 
OVER THE LAST MONTH AND A HALF.  THE ATMOSPHERE IS 
MORE AND MORE POSITIVE.  THE POLICE CHIEF SAID THAT 
HIS ORGANIZATION WAS STRIVING TO INCREASE ITS 
PROFESSIONALISM AND THAT THE POLICE HAD \"SOLVED\" MOST 
CASES OF PROVOCATION.  ALL FIVE LEADERS FROM VRBOVSKO 
DISTRICT COMPLAINED ABOUT \"EXTREMISTS\" (SERBS AND 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00954  04 OF 08  111238Z 
CROATS) WHO ESSENTIALLY STIRRED UP TROUBLE, WERE NOT 
RESPONSIBLE FOR THE CONSEQUENCES OF THEIR ACTIONS, 
AND DID NOT PARTICIPATE IN CONSTRUCTIVE SOLUTIONS. 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
