INDIVIDUALS RESPONSIBLE.  STILL, ONE FORMER SABORSKO 
RESIDENT SAID HE HAD NOTHING AGAINST THE SERBS AS A 
PEOPLE, HE JUST WANTED THOSE RESPONSIBLE TO BE 
PUNISHED 
 
11.  SUCH A POSITIVE ATTITUDE OFTEN DOES NOT MANIFEST 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  06 OF 08  111240Z 
ITSELF IN PRACTICE.  SOME EXAMPLES: 
 
--  BEFORE THE WAR, IN OGULIN, ACCORDING TO THE 
DISTRICT PRESIDENT (A MEMBER OF THE RULING CROATIAN 
DEMOCRATIC UNION, CDU), 75 PERCENT OF THE POLICE 
FORCE WAS MADE UP OF SERBS.  NOW THAT FIGURE HAS BEEN 
REVERSED IN FAVOR OF CROATS.  WERE SERBS FIRED?  NO, 
SAY CROATS.  SERBS IN THE POLICE LEFT OGULIN; THE 
TOTAL NUMBER OF POLICE WAS INCREASED; ALL FIVE POLICE 
INSPECTORS ARE SERBS WHO HAVE BEEN KEPT ON IN ORDER 
TO \"USE\" THEIR KNOWLEDGE. 
(COMMENT:  WE ARE NOT IMPRESSED BY CLAIMS THAT NOONE 
WAS FIRED IN OGULIN BASED ON NATIONALITY.  THE 
REPORTS FROM VRBOVSKO AND ELSEWHERE SAY OTHERWISE. 
END COMMENT.) 
 
--  ACCORDING TO A SERB MEMBER OF THE CROATIAN 
ASSEMBLY, EMPTY HOUSES, KNOWN TO HAVE BEEN OCCUPIED 
BY SERBS HAVE BEEN THE TARGETS OF BOMB ATTACKS. 
NOONE PRESENT DENIED THE CLAIM.  HOWEVER, SYMBOLIC OF 
THE DIPLOMATIC LANGUAGE THAT SERBS IN THE ROOM FELT 
COMPELLED TO USE, THE SERB ASSEMBLYMAN SAID THAT 
THESE WERE \"CONSEQUENCES OF A PROCESS I UNDERSTAND.\" 
HE WAS REFERRING, AS DID OTHER SERBS, TO THE 
EGREGIOUS ACTS OF FELLOW SERBS AROUND OGULIN, THE 
KRAJINA AND IN THE REST OF CROATIA. 
 
--  THE SAME ASSEMBLY MEMBER NOTED THE KILLING OF 10 
PEOPLE (PRESUMABLY SERBS) IN THE OGULIN PRISON. 
(COMMENT:  IT IS OUR UNDERSTANDING THAT THIS ACT IS 
CURRENTLY BEING PROSECUTED BY CROATIAN AUTHORITIES. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00954  06 OF 08  111240Z 
END COMMENT.) 
 
JASENAK 
 
 
