SUBJECT:  SERBS AND CROATS IN GORSKI KOTAR:  A TALE 
OF TWO DISTRICTS 
 
------- 
 
12.  JASENAK IS A PREDOMINANTLY SERB VILLAGE IN THE 
OGULIN DISTRICT WHICH HAS BEEN THE SUBJECT OF SOME 
CONTROVERSY WITH ALLEGATIONS BY SERBS REGARDING THE 
TEMPORARY SETTLEMENT OF NON-SERB DISPLACED THERE. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  07 OF 08  111240Z 
ACCORDING TO THE OGULIN DISTRICT CHIEF, THERE ARE 
CURRENTLY 200 DISPLACED PEOPLE HOUSED NEAR JASENAK (A 
VILLAGE OF SEVERAL HUNDRED PEOPLE) IN AN UNUSED 
RESORT THAT HAS 1600 AVAILABLE BEDS.  THE SERB MEMBER 
OF THE CROATIAN ASSEMBLY TOLD US THAT THERE HAD BEEN 
LENGTHY PREPARATIONS BEFORE THE DISPLACED PERSONS HAD 
BEEN BROUGHT TO JASENAK.  DISCUSSIONS HAD BEEN HELD 
WITH THE DISPLACED AND THE VILLAGERS SEPARATELY IN 
ORDER TO PREPARE THE GROUNDWORK FOR THE ARRIVAL OF THE 
DISPLACED.  IN ADDITION, BOTH THE EC MONITORING 
MISSION, WITH REPS HOUSED IN THE AREA, AND THE UNHCR 
ARE ACTIVELY ENGAGED IN MAKING THE JASENAK SITUATION 
WORK.  FRESH FROM A JUNE 5 VISIT TO JASENAK, UNHCR 
CROATIA HEAD JEAN-CLAUDE CONCOLATO TOLD US JUNE 9 
THAT THERE WERE ONLY 38 DISPLACED STAYING NEAR 
JASENAK.  ALL OF THEM WERE OF RUTHENIAN NATIONALITY. 
FOR NOW, THE SITUATION IS UNDER NEW CONTROL AND NO 
NEW, IMMEDIATE INFLOWS OF DISPLACED ARE PLANNED. 
 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
13.  THE EXPERIENCE OF VRBOVSKO SUGGESTS THAT IN 
THESE AREAS OF CROATIA WHERE FIGHTING OR EXPULSIONS 
DID NOT TAKE PLACE, THERE IS SOME HOPE OF 
RECONCILIATION.  UNFORTUNATELY, A FAVORABLE LOCAL 
CLIMATE CAN BE SPOILED BY OUTSIDE ACTIONS (E.G. 
DISMISSALS MADE BY ORGANIZATIONS BASED OUTSIDE THE 
AREA OR MEDIA HYPE FROM ZAGREB THAT INACCURATELY 
DESCRIBES A PARTICULAR SITUATION).  ELSEWHERE, WHERE 
LARGE NUMBERS OF SERBS OR CROATS FLED, AND FIGHTING 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00954  07 OF 08  111240Z 
ENSUED, IT\'S GOING TO TAKE MORE.  ALL SERBS RETURNING 
TO THEIR VILLAGES WILL BE VIEWED SUSPICIOUSLY 
(WITNESS THE LENGTHY WAR CRIMES LISTS ALREADY BEING 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
