PRINTED IN CROATIAN NEWSPAPERS).  EVERYONE FEELS 
VIOLATED OR BETRAYED, AND IN MANY CASES BY FORMER 
FRIENDS, RELATIVES OR NEIGHBORS.  FOR SERBS WHO 
STAYED THROUGHOUT, IT WILL BE REQUIRED, RIGHTLY OR 
WRONGLY, THAT THEY ESTABLISH THEIR LOYALTY AND ATONE 
IN SOME WAY FOR THE TRANSGRESSIONS OF THEIR BRETHREN. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  08 OF 08  111303Z 
- 
14.  IT IS OUR VIEW THAT EVEN IN AREAS WHERE SOME 
EFFORTS TOWARD RECONCILIATION ARE UNDER WAY, ANY REAL 
SUCCESS DEPENDS ON THE OVERALL CLIMATE AS DEFINED BY 
ZAGREB.  PROGRESS IN INTER-ETHNIC RELATIONS HAS BEEN 
TENUOUS AT BEST IN A FEW AREAS, WHILE IN MOST AREAS 
NO SUCH EFFORTS HAVE GOTTEN UNDER WAY, NOR WILL THEY 
UNTIL THE WAR IS OVER AND THE UNPROFOR HAS DONE ITS 
JOB.  SUCCESS IN REINTEGRATING SERBS INTO CROATIA 
WILL COME ONLY IN CONJUNCTION WITH A POSITIVE 
ATTITUDE ON THE PART OF THE REPUBLIC LEADERSHIP.  WE 
BELIEVE LITTLE IMPROVEMENT IS POSSIBLE WITHOUT CLEAR 
SIGNALS FROM ZAGREB.  END COMMENT.  EINIK 
 
 
 
