SUBJECT:  LETTER TO SECRETARY BAKER FROM FOREIGN 
MINISTER SKRABALO 
 
 
- 
1.  PROVIDED HEREIN IS TEXT OF A LETTER FAXED TO 
THE CONSULATE FROM CROATIAN FOREIGN MINISTER 
ZDENKO SKRABALO, REGARDING THE SITUATION IN BOSNIA 
-HERCEGOVINA (ENGLISH VERSION AS PROVIDEDB 
CROATIANS). 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01169  01 OF 03  141311Z 
 
2.  BEGIN TEXT: 
 
                             ZAGREB, JULY 11, 1992 
 
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA 
DEPARTMENT OF STATE 
H.E. 
JAMES BAKER 
SECRETARY OF STATE 
 
SIPDIS 
 
YOUR EXCELLENCY, 
 
ONLY A DAY AFTER THE END OF THE HELSINKI SUMMIT 
FROM WHICH (JUST LIKE THE BOSNIAN-HERCEGOVIAN 
DELEGATION WHOM WE SAW OFF FROM ZAGREB THIS 
MORNING) WE RETURNED FULL OF HOPES THAT THE 
SITUATION IN CROATIA AND BOSNIA-HERCEGOVINA WOULD 
IMPROVE, I AM COMPELLED TO SEND OUT THIS DRAMATIC 
APPEAL. 
 
IN SPITE OF ALL EFFORTS MADE BY THE INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITY, THE SECURITY COUNCIL\'S RESOLUTION, THE 
HELSINKI DECISIONS, UNPROFOR MISSION, THE 
SITUATION IN BOSIA-HERCEGOVINA HAS TAKEN A 
DRAMATIC TURN FOR WORSE. 
 
THE SERBIAN AGGRESSORS HAVE INTENSIFIED THEIR 
ATTACKS AT ALL POSITIONS OF ALREADY EXISTING 
CONFRONTATION (SARAJEVO, BOSNIAN POSAVINA, MOSTAR, 
DUBROVNIK, SLAVONSKI BROD, ZUPANJA...) AND OPENED 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01169  01 OF 03  141311Z 
NEW FRONT-LINES (GORAZDE, TRAVNIK, BUGOJNO, 
JAJCE...). 
 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
NNNN 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
