TAGS: PGOV, PREL, PHUM, MOPS, PREF, ECON, HR, PREL, PHUM, MOPS, PREF, ECON, HR, PREL, PHUM, MOPS, PREF, ECON, HR, PREL, PHUM, MOPS, PREF, ECON, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- ZAGREB UPDATE:  SEPT 28, 1992 
 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1.  AS UN/EC PEACE ENVOYS VANCE AND OWEN MET WITH 
CROATIAN AUTHORITIES IN ZAGREB LAST FRIDAY, THE 
COUNTRY\'S PARLIAMENT ERUPTED INTO DEBATE OVER THE 
PASSAGE OF A LAW GRANTING AMNESTY TO SOME OF THOSE 
WHO FOUGHT FOR SERBIA AGAINST CROATIA.  A SECOND 
SESSION OF CROATIA\'S NEW NATIONAL DEFENSE COUNCIL 
APPROVED THE FORMATION OF A SPECIAL COMMITTEE TO 
PROMOTE MILITARY COOPERATION WITH B-H.  LOCAL 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01854  01 OF 04  281540Z 
GOVERNMENTS HAVE ORDERED THE FIRST GROUP OF REFUGEES 
TO LEAVE THEIR TEMPORARY RESIDENCES IN HOTELS AND 
RETURN TO THEIR HOMES IN THE PINK ZONE AROUND 
SIBENIK.  ETHNIC CLEANSING REPORTEDLY CONTINUES IN 
THE BARANJA AREA (SECTOR EAST).  DESPITE GOVERNMENT 
EFFORTS TO PRIVATIZE REMAINING PUBLIC-OWNED 
ENTERPRISES, FEWER THAN ONE-QUARTER HAVE BEEN SOLD 
THUS FAR.  A COURT-ORDERED SEARCH UNCOVERED LARGE 
AMOUNTS OF EXPLOSIVES AND ARMS AT THE DOWNTOWN 
ZAGREB PARTY HEADQUARTERS OF ULTRA-RIGHTIST LEADER 
PARAGA.  OVER THE WEEKEND, ALL LOCAL PAPERS GAVE 
WIDE COVERAGE TO THE LATEST U.S. ANNOUNCEMENTS OF 
ATROCITIES IN B-H. 
 
CROATIAN SABOR PASSES AMNESTY LAW 
------------------------------------- 
 
2.  DURING THE SECOND AND FINAL DAY OF ITS LATEST 
SESSION (ON SEPTEMBER 25), CROATIA\'S SABOR PASSED 
THE AMNESTY LAW PROPOSED BY PRESIDENT TUDJMAN AFTER 
SOME STORMY DEBATES.  THE LEGISLATION EXCUSES ALL 
THOSE WHO FOUGHT AGAINST CROATIA BUT DID NOT COMMIT 
WAR CRIMES.  THE LOCAL PRESS NOTED THAT THE ACTION 
WAS 
TIMED TO COINCIDE WITH THE VANCE-OWEN MEETINGS IN 
ZAGREB TO PROVE THAT CROATIA IS DOING ITS PART TO 
REESTABLISH PEACE IN CROATIA. 
 
3.  MOST OF THE OPPOSITION PARTIES WERE AGAINST THE 
MEASURE.  CROATIAN NATIONAL PARTY AND SOCIAL LIBERAL 
PARTY LEADERS CALLED THE LAW ONE-SIDED, AND 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01854  01 OF 04  281540Z 
EXPRESSED DOUBT THAT IT CAN BE EFFECTIVELY 
ADMINISTERED.  THE CROATIAN PEASANT PARTY SUGGESTED 
POSTPONING ENACTMENT OF THE LAW, SINCE SERBIAN 
FORCES CONTINUE DAILY BOMBARDMENTS OF CROATIAN 
TOWNS PARTICULARLY IN SLAVONIA.  ULTRA-RIGHT LEADER 
DOBROSLAV PARAGA ASSERTED THE LAW IS AN 
 
 
