ENCOURAGEMENT TO THE ENEMY.  SABOR PRESIDENT STIPE 
MESIC DEFENDED THE LAW BECAUSE IT APPLIES ONLY TO 
THOSE WHO WERE \"MISLED,\" NOT TO CRIMINALS. 
 
4.  ALL CROATIAN DAILIES FRONT-PAGED THE ISSUE, AND 
A NUMBER FEATURED EDITORIALS EXPRESSING CONCERN 
ABOUT HOW TO IMPLEMENT THE LEGISLATION SINCE IT WAS 
RUSHED THROUGH.  ONE DAILY PUBLISHED A POLL 
SEPTEMBER 28 IN WHICH ABOUT 55 PERCENT OF 
RESPONDENTS SUPPORTED THE AMNESTY LAW, NEARLY 30 
PERCENT WERE AGAINST, AND ABOUT 15 PERCENT WERE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
