12.  OVER THE WEEKEND, ALL LOCAL PAPERS GAVE WIDE 
COVERAGE TO THE LATEST U.S. ANNOUNCEMENTS OF CRIMES 
IN B-H.  THE PRESS HIGHLIGHTED THE U.S. SUBMISSION 
TO THE UN OF A LIST OF 3,000 MUSLIM MEN, WOMEN, AND 
CHILDREN KILLED IN SERB PRISON CAMPS NEAR BRCKO AS 
WELL AS WASHINGTON\'S CALL FOR THE UN SECURITY 
COUNCIL ESTABLISH A COMMISSION ON WAR CRIMES IN B-H. 
 
