WAR AGAINST ORGANIZED CRIME IN OSIJEK 
------------------------------------- 
 
8.  CROATIAN MINISTER OF THE INTERIOR IVAN JARNJAK 
ATTENDED A MEETING OF POLICE LEADERS IN OSIJEK WHERE 
HE STRESSED THE NEED TO TAKE ACTION AGAINST THE 
LAWLESSNESS THAT HAS BEEN PLAGUING THE CITY OVER THE 
LAST FEW MONTHS.  A NEW POLICE CHIEF AND DEPUTY WERE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01869  03 OF 03  291614Z 
NAMED, AND THE FORMER POLICE CHIEF WAS MADE CHIEF OF 
THE BORDER POLICE AND COORDINATOR WITH UNPROFOR. 
THE POLICE ARE TO CONCENTRATE ON THE PREVENTION OF 
TERRORIST AND CRIMINAL INCIDENTS. 
 
