E.O. 12356:  DECL: OADR 
TAGS: PGOV, PREL, PHUM, PREF, HR 
SUBJECT:  CGY001:  UNPROFOR\'S DAUNTING TASK IN CROATIA 
-         -- ANOTHER GRIM REPORT FROM SECTOR EAST 
 
26.  UNPROFOR OFFICIALS HAVE ASKED SERBIAN AUTHORITIES 
TO EXCAVATE THE SUSPECTED GRAVES, BUT THEY HAVE DONE 
NOTHING.  IN RESPONSE TO DIRECT QUESTIONS FROM THE 
CSCE DELEGATION ABOUT THE HARASSMENT, MURDER, AND 
INTIMIDATION OF NON-SERBS IN VUKOVAR, \"PRESIDENT\" 
ILICH SAID \"WE HAVE NO EVIDENCE ABOUT THESE THINGS.\" 
 
------- 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01962  08 OF 08  091326Z 
27.  THE SERBIAN LEADERSHIP IN VUKOVAR, LIKE THEIR 
COUNTERPARTS IN KNIN, HAVE MADE FOR THEMSELVES A 
HOBBESIAN WORLD OF THE DARKEST DIMENSIONS.  THE 
SAVAGERY THEY HAVE UNLEASHED AND NOW AID AND ABET HAS 
MADE LIFE A VIRTUAL HELL FOR ALL THE NON-SERBS WITHIN 
THEIR GRASP.  YET IT IS THE SERBS WHO CLAIM THAT THEY 
ARE THE ONES THREATENED AND MISUNDERSTOOD. 
PREDICTABLY, MUCH OF THE DELEGATION\'S TWO-HOUR 
MEETING IN VUKOVAR WAS TAKEN UP WITH A NOW-FAMILIAR 
RECITATION OF ALLEGED SERBIAN GRIEVANCES STRETCHING 
BACK TO BEFORE THE AUSTRO-HUNGARIAN EMPIRE. 
 
28.  IN SECTOR EAST, AT LEAST, THE ALREADY POOR ODDS 
OF UNPROFOR\'S BEING ABLE TO IMPLEMENT THE VANCE PLAN 
-- WITH ITS CURRENT FORCE LEVELS AND MANDATE -- 
APPEAR TO BE STEADILY RECEDING. 
 
NEITZKE 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
