------------ 
THE SUBJECTS 
------------ 
 
5. (U)  X., F.B., AND A.V. ARE FROM DIFFERENT 
VILLAGES IN THE VICINITY OF PRIJEDOR, BOSNIA.  THEY 
WERE TAKEN CAPTIVE BY SERBIAN FORCES IN LATE MAY 1992 
AND CONFINED, EACH FOR APPROXIMATELY THREE MONTHS, IN 
OMARSKA CAMP.  X. SAID SHE WAS ONE OF THIRTY-EIGHT 
WOMEN DETAINED AT THE CAMP DURING THIS PERIOD.  (NOTE: 
THE SERBS HAVE CONSISTENTLY DENIED THAT ANY WOMEN 
WERE HELD AT OMARSKA CAMP.)  X. SAID MANY OF THE 
WOMEN ARRIVED ON MAY 26, WHEN THE CAMP WAS OPENED. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02038  02 OF 09  161554Z 
 
6. (U)  X., F.B., AND A.V. PROVIDED THE LISTS AND 
DESCRIPTIONS BELOW OF OMARSKA CAMP\'S PERSONNEL 
STRUCTURE.  AFTER REPEATED QUESTIONING BY THE 
INTERVIEWER, TOGETHER AND INDIVIDUALLY, X., F.B., AND 
A.V. (OR AT LEAST TWO OF THE THREE OF THEM) 
PERSONALLY IDENTIFIED EVERY OMARSKA CAMP OFFICIAL 
LISTED IN THIS REPORT. 
 
------------------------- 
MAJOR PRIJEDOR AREA CAMPS 
------------------------- 
 
7. (U)  OMARSKA IS ONE OF FOUR VERY LARGE CAMPS IN 
THE PRIJEDOR AREA.  IT WAS AN ALUMINUM MINE BEFORE 
THE WAR.  THE OTHER THREE CAMPS ARE KERATERM, 
TRNOPOLJE, AND MANJACA.  CIVILIANS WERE INTERNED AT 
ALL FOUR CAMPS, WHILE MOST ALLEGED POWS WERE SENT TO 
MANJACA.  MANY PRISONERS DESCRIBED OMARSKA AS THE 
 
WORST OF THE FOUR.  MANY PRISONERS WERE MOVED AMONG 
THE CAMPS DURING THEIR INTERNMENT. 
 
--------------------- 
COMMANDERS AT OMARSKA 
--------------------- 
 
8. (U)  OMARSKA CAMP WAS COMMANDED BY DRAGO PRCAC, A 
RETIREE FROM PRIJEDOR.  HIS ADMINISTRATIVE DEPUTY WAS 
A MIDDLE-AGED WOMAN NAMED NADA BALABAN.  BALABAN KEPT 
THE CAMP RECORDS, I.E., THE PAYROLL LEDGER OF THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02038  02 OF 09  161554Z 
GUARDS AND OFFICERS, THE GUARD SHIFT SCHEDULE, ETC. 
(NOTE:  X. COMMENTED THAT IF THESE LEDGERS COULD BE 
FOUND, THEY WOULD HAVE COMPLETE DETAILS OF WHO WORKED 
 
 
