SUBJECT:  CYGOOL:  HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN BOSNIA- 
-         HERCEGOVINA - CASES OF X., F.B., AND A.V.; 
-         THE PERSONNEL STRUCTURE AT OMARSKA CAMP 
 
 
26.  F.B. AND SEVERAL OTHER PRISONERS WITNESSED THE 
SENSELESS BEATING AND DEATH OF RIZA HADJALIC.  RIZA 
HAD RECEIVED HIS DAILY SLICE OF BREAD AND WAS WALKING 
AWAY, WHEN A GUARD SAID \"DOBAR TEK\" (GOOD APPETITE). 
RIZA REPLIED SPONTANEOUSLY \"BUJUM,\" THE MULSIM DIALECT 
EQUIVALENT.  SEVERAL GUARDS IMMEDIATLEY SET UPON RIZA 
AND BEAT HIM SENSELESS.  AFTERWARDS RIZA LAY ON HIS 
BACK AND VOMITTED.  NO ONE WAS ALLOWED TO TURN HIM 
OVER.  RIZA SUFFOCATED ON HIS VOMIT IN FRONT OF THE 
OTHERS. 
 
27. (U)  X., F.B., AND A.V. CONSIDERED CIGO MAMUZO 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02038  09 OF 09  161657Z 
THE WORST GUARD IN OMARSKA.  THEY WITNESSED AND HEARD 
OF HIS KILLING MORE PRISONERS THAN ANY OTHER GUARD. 
A.V. SAW MAMUZO KILL AHIL DEDIC ON MAY 28 ON A BUS 
OUTSIDE THE CAMP GATE WHEN HE WAS FIRST BROUGHT TO 
OMARSKA.  MAMUZO BEAT AHIL ON THE HEAD WITH THE 
WOODEN BUTT OF A RIFLE UNTIL HIS SKULL BROKE. 
 
------------------------ 
ROBBERIES FROM PRISONERS 
------------------------ 
 
28. (U)  MANY GUARDS TOOK THE PRISONERS PERSONAL 
PROPERTY.  HOWEVER, BRANKO AND MILOJICA BERIC WERE 
IDENTIFIED BY A.V. AND F.B. AS THE WORST OF THE 
GUARDS IN THIS RESPECT.  BRANKO ESPECIALLY STOLE 
WATCHES AND JEWELRY AND BOTH STOLE FOREIGN CURRENCY 
FROM THE PRISONERS.  A.V. AND F.B. WITNESSED THESE 
ROBBERIES SEVERAL TIMES. 
 
NEITZKE 
 
 
 
