52-YEAR-OLD BLUE-COLLAR WORKER. ALL FIVE ARE BOSNIAN 
 
MUSLIMS FROM VILLAGES IN THE PRIJEDOR REGION.  ALL 
ARRIVED AT KERATERM CAMP IN MID-JUNE AND SPENT 
ABOUT TWO MONTHS THERE BEFORE BEING TRANSFERRED 
TO TRNOPOLJE IN EARLY AUGUST. 
 
------------------------ 
KERATERM SENIOR OFFICERS 
------------------------ 
 
5. (U)  J.A. AND H.E. IDENTIFIED THREE PERSONS WHO 
WERE SENIOR OFFICERS AT KERATERM.  ALTHOUGH THEY 
DISAGREED ON THE PRECISE POSITIONS OF THESE THREE 
OFFICERS, J.A. AND H.E. IDENTIFIED THE SAME THREE 
INDIVIDUALS.  J.A. IDENTIFIED DRASKO DOSEN (NICKNAMED 
KAJIN) AS THE COMMANDER OF KERATERM AT LEAST FROM 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02173  02 OF 05  271603Z 
JUNE 14 TO JULY 15.  (H.E., ON THE OTHER HAND, 
THOUGHT DOSEN HAD BEEN ONE OF THE THREE SHIFT 
LEADERS.)  GUARDS AT KERATERM TOLD THE PRISONERS THAT 
DOSEN WAS WANTED BY THE CROATS FOR CRIMES HE HAD 
COMMITTED DURING THE SERBO-CROATIAN WAR.  DOSEN IS IN 
HIS MID-THIRITIES, FROM LTHE VILLAGES OF JUTRUGOSKA, 
NEAR PRIJEDOR. 
 
6. (U)  J.A. IDENTIFIED KOMJENOVIC (FNU - POSSIBLY 
IVICA; NICKNAMED KOLA) AS THE SECOND COMMANDER OF 
KERATERM, TAKING OVER FROM DOSEN ON JULY 15 AND 
REMAINING UNTIL EARLY AUGUST.  (H.E. THOUGHT 
KOMJENOVIC WAS ANOTHER OF THE THREE SHIFT LEADERS.) 
J.A. AND H.E., AS WELL AS SEVERAL OTHER EX-PRISONERS, 
BELIEVE KOMJENOVIC GAVE THE ORDER TO SHOOT AT THE 
JULY 24 MASS KILLING AT KERATERM (REFTEL, AND BELOW). 
KOMJENOVIC IS ALSO ABOUT THIRTY AND IS FROM THE 
VILLAGE OF LJUBIJA. 
 
7. (U)  J.A. IDENTIFIED DUSKO SIKIRIC (NICKNAMED 
KOMMANDANT) AS THE THIRD CAMP COMMANDER IN SEQUENCE, 
INSTALLED JUST A FEW DAYS BEFORE J.A. LEFT KERATERM. 
(H.E. BELIEVED THAT SIKIRIC WAS ALL ALONG \"THE\" 
OFFICIAL CAMP COMMANDER.)  SIKIRIC WAS OVER FORTY 
YEARS OLD AND USED TO BE THE HEAD OF THE CELPAK PAPER 
FACTORY IN PRIJEDOR.  H.E. SAID SIKIRIC OFTEN WATCHED 
THE GUARDS BEAT THE PRISONERS. 
 
------ 
GUARDS 
------ 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02173  02 OF 05  271603Z 
 
8. (U)  H.E. SAID KERATERM HAD THREE GUARD SHIFTS.  A 
SHIFT RAN FROM SIX AM TO SIX PM.  H.E., WHO MAINTAINED 
(ABOVE) THAT KOMJENOVIC AND DOSEN WERE TWO SHIFT 
LEADERS, COULD NOT REMEMBER THE NAME OF THE THIRD 
SHIFT LEADER.  ACCORDING TO H.E., HOWEVER, THIS THIRD 
SHIFT LEADER WAS THE WORST.  WHEN THIS THIRD SHIFT 
LEADER HAD THE NIGHT SHIFT, A MINIMUM OF THREE MEN 
WERE BEATEN NIGHTLY, WITH AT LEAST ONE DYING. 
 
 
 
