9. (U)  J.A. IDENTIFIED THREE GUARDS HE SAW TORTURE 
OTHER PRISONERS:  A PAIR OF TWIN BROTHERS NAMED 
BANOVIC (FIRST NAMES BSELIEVED TO BE PETROBRAG AND 
ZELJKO) AND A MAN NAMED KONDIC (FNU).  J.A. SAID 
KONDIC OFTEN PARTICIPATED IN THE \"NIGHTLY GAMES\" WITH 
THE PRISONERS.  S.B. SAID THAT ONE NIGHT KONDIC HAD 
CALLED FOR EMSUD BAHONJIC TO COME OUT OF THE 
\"DORMITORY,\" WHEREUPON KONDIC BEAT HIM.  S.B. SAID HE 
SAW BAHONJIC\'S BODY IN FRONT OF THE DORMITORY DOOR 
THE NEXT MORNING.  ALL HIS TEETH HAD BEEN COMPLETELY 
KNOCKED OUT BY A PIPE, AND HIS KNEE CAP HAD BEEN 
DEEPLY GOUGED WITH A KNIFE. 
 
------------------ 
SPECIFIC INCIDENTS 
------------------ 
 
10. (U)  N.B., S.B., AND H.C. IDENTIFIED ZORAN ZIGIC 
AS ONE OF THE MOST BRUTAL GUARDS AT THE CAMP.  ZIGIC 
IS A TAXI DRIVER FROM PRIJEDOR.  S.B. SAID THAT ON 
HIS (S.B.\'S) SECOND DAY IN THE CAMP ZIGIC CALLED OUT 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02173  03 OF 05  280114Z 
THE NAMES OF FORTY PRISONERS FROM THE VILLAGE OF 
KAMICANI, INCLUDING S.B.  ZIGIC SCREAMED AT THEM, 
UNDER FOURTEEN WITH ZIGIC BEAT SEVERAL OF THE MEN 
OUTSIDE THE DORMITORY WITH A POLICE BATON.  THE 
PRISONERS WERE ASKED WHO HAD KEPT FIREARMS AT HOME. 
S.B.\'S NEIGHBOR IDENTIFIED S.B.  THEN S.B. AND 
ANOTHER PRISONER WERE BEATEN BRUTALLY BY ZIGIC AND 
ONE OF THE BANOVIC TWINS.  THEY USED THICK ELECTRIC 
CABLES AND TRUNCHEONS ALL OVER S.B.\'S BODY.  HE WAS 
BEATEN TWO MORE TIMES. 
 
11. (U)  ON THE OCCASION OF S.B.\'S THIRD BEATING, 
THREE DAYS LATER, THE TWO GUARDS DOING THE BEATING 
YELLED AT HIM ABOUT HIS SUPPOSED INVOLVEMENT IN THE 
SHOOTING ON THE SERB VILLAGE OF BALTEN.  S.B. TRIED 
TO DEFEND HIMSELF AND A SCUFFLE ENSUED.  ONE OF THE 
BANOVIC TWINS PULLED OUT A KNIFE AND APPEARED INTENT 
ON GOUGING OUT S.B\'S EYE.  S.B. MANAGED TO PUSH 
BANOVIC\'S HAND AWAY.  BANOVIC THEN SLASHED THE RIGHT 
SIDE OF S.B.\'S NECK.  NEXT BANOVIC FIRED A PISTOL 
(UNLOADED AS IT TURNED OUT) POINT-BLANK AT S.B.\'S 
TEMPLE.  S.B. THEN \"CONFESSED\" TO HAVING FIRED ON 
BALTEN, ALTHOUGH IN FACT HE HAD NOT DONE SO.  BANOVIC 
THEN TRIED TO CUT OFF S.B.\'S EAR, BUT S.B. AGAIN 
DEFLECTED THE KNIFE.  THEN BANOVIC STABBED S.B. IN 
HIS LEFT THIGH, TWISTED THE KNIFE, AND PULLED OUT A 
PIECE OF S.B.\'S FLESH.  BANOVIC DID THE SAME TO 
S.B.\'S RIGHT THIGH.  S.B. SHOWED EMBOFF THE SCARS. 
S.B. SAID THE CUTS WERE ABOUT TEN CENTIMETERS DEEP. 
 
12. (U)  AFTER THE KNIFINGS, S.B. HAD SAT IN 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02173  03 OF 05  280114Z 
EXCRUCIATING PAIN FOR ABOUT TEN MINUTES WITH BLOOD 
SOAKING HIS PANTS.  THE GUARDS ORDERED HIM TO MARCH 
TO THE BATHROOM AND CLEAN HIMSELF UP.  S.B. MANAGED 
TO BANDAGE HIS LEGS WITH STRIPS RIPPED FROM HIS 
 
 
