BLOODY TROUSERS.  S.B. ESTIMATED HE LOST MORE THAN 
ONE-AND-A-HALF LITERS OF BLOOD THAT DAY.  A FEW 
NIGHTS LATER, THE GUARD ZIGIC AGAIN CALLED INTO THE 
\"DORMITORY\" FOR S.B. TO COME OUT, BUT S.B. REFUSED TO 
ANSWER.  ZIGIC ORDERED OTHERS TO FIND HIM.  AT THE 
DOOR, ZIGIC ASKED HIM, \"WHERE ARE YOU FROM?\" 
\"KAMICANI,\" SAID S.B.  \"YOU FOUGHT AT BALTEN?\", ZIGIC 
QUESTIONED.  S.B. REPLIED THAT HE HAD NOT AND THAT 
HIS HOUSE WAS ON THE BORDER OF KAMICANI AND KOZARAC. 
S.B. SAID ZIGIC, STRANGELY, NEVER CAME FOR HIM AGAIN. 
 
13. (U)  H.C. SAID ZIGIC AND A GUARD NAMED DUSAN 
KNEZEVIC (NICKNAMED DUCA) BEAT HIM WITH A POLICE 
BATON THAT HAD A SPIKED LEAD BALL ATTACHED TO IT. 
SIGIC AND KNEZEVIC SINGLED OUT PRISONERS WHO RECEIVED 
PACKAGES FROM THEIR WIVES AND FAMILIES.  THEY GAVE 
THE PRISONERS THE PACKET AND THEN BEAT THEM FIERCELY. 
N.B. SAID ZIGIC AND THE GUARD DUCA BEAT PEOPLE 
NIGHTLY.  THEY WOULD CAME TO THE DORMITORY AND CALL 
OR PEOPLE.  ALMOST INEVITABLY ONE OR TWO OF THE 
TORTURED PRISONERS DIED, ESPECIALLY WHEN DUCA 
PARTICIPATED.  THEY USED RIFLE BUTTS, BATONS WITH 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02173  04 OF 05  271606Z 
SPIKED BALLS, HEAVY WIRE CABLES, AND BASEBALL BATS. 
------------------- 
MASS MURDER JULY 24 
------------------- 
 
14. (U)  N.B. PROVIDED SEPARATE TESTIMONY REGARDING 
THE JULY 24 MASS MURDER OF OVER ONE HUNDRED PRISONERS 
(REFTEL).  PRISONERS WERE KEPT IN FOUR SEPARATE ROOMS 
AT KERATERM.  N.B. WAS IN ROOM TWO.  ROOM THREE IS 
WHERE PRISONERS WERE MOST SEVERELY TORTURED AND WHERE 
THE MASSACRE OCCURRED.  THE DETAILS OF N.B.\'S STORY 
AGREE WITH THE ACCOUNTS GIVEN IN REFTEL.  FROM A 
WINDOW IN ROOM TWO, N.B. SAW THE GUARD SHIFT CHANGE 
ON SCHEDULE AT SIX PM.  BUT THEN IT CHANGED AGAIN TWO 
HOURS LATER.  MORE GUARDS WERE STATIONED IN FRONT OF 
THE ROOMS.  N.B. SAID THE GUARDS HAD AUTOMATIC RIFLES. 
WHEN THE DISTURBANCES STARTED BECAUSE OF THE 
INSUFFERABLE CONDITIONS IN THE ROOM, THE GUARDS FIRED 
A FEW SHOTS.  N.B. HEARD A VOICE SHOUT, \"DON\'T SHOOT 
WITHOUT AN ORDER FROM KOLA,\" (KOMJENOVIC).  WHEN THE 
RIOTING GREW WORSE.  N.B. HEARD KOMJENOVIC SAY, 
\"FIRE|\"  N.B. HEARD RAPID GUNFIRE AND SCREAMS. 
 
15. (U)  THE FOLLOWING DAY GUARDS CHOSE TWO PRISONERS 
FROM ROOMS ONE AND TWO EACH TO REMOVE THE DEAD. 
THESE PRISONERS COUNTED 99 DEAD AND 42 WOUNDED, N.B. 
REPORTED.  THEY WERE ORDERED TO PUT THE WOUNDED ON 
THE SAME TRUCK AS THE DEAD.  THE TRUCK WAS LABELED 
PRIJEDOR AUTOTRANSPORT.  NONE OF THE WOUNDED OR THE 
DRIVER OF THE TRUCK (ANOTHER PRISONER) WAS SEEN AGAIN. 
N.B. SAID A SIMILAR INCIDENT HAPPENED IN THE SAME 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02173  04 OF 05  271606Z 
ROOM THE NEXT DAY, IN WHICH 21 DIED AND FIVE WERE 
WOUNDED. 
 
 
 
