FROM THE SOUTH, HAVE BEEN FORCED TO NEGOTIATE WITH 
SERBIAN FORCES IN THE HOPE OF ESTABLISHING A 
PROTECTED CORRIDOR FOR RELIEF SUPPLIES FROM 
BELGRADE.  ICRC-ZAGREB OFFICIALS DID NOT DISCOUNT A 
POSSIBLE SERB ATTACK ON TRAVNIK ITSELF BUT NOTED THAT 
THE CITY APPEARED TO BE WELL DEFENDED. 
 
