SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- APPROACHING THE BREAKING POINT: 
-         CROATIA AND THE BOSNIAN REFUGEE PROBLEM 
 
ENTER CROATIA EACH WEEK/WEEK.  THIS FIGURE DOES NOT 
INCLUDE PROBABLY AN EQUAL NUMBER OF ILLEGAL REFUGEE 
ENTRANTS, OR SOME 9,000 WHO FLED TO CROATIA WITH THE 
FALL OF BOSANSKI BROD, OR THE SEVERAL THOUSAND WHO 
HAVE REACHED CROATIA IN THE WAKE OF JAJCE\'S FALL AND 
AMONG WHOM TYPHOID HAS NOW BROKEN OUT IN THE ALREADY 
TENSE REGION AROUND SPLIT.  CROATIAN OFFICIALS ARE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  02 OF 09  131608Z 
LOATH TO TRUMPET THE FACT THAT THIS HEAVY REFUGEE 
FLOW CONTINUES -- INDEED, WHAT GETS PUBLICIZED HERE 
IS THEIR OCCASIONAL REFUSAL OF ENTRY -- FOR FEAR OF 
THE DESTABILIZING IMPACT THIS WOULD HAVE ON ALREADY 
STRAINED PUBLIC ATTITUDES TOWARD THE REFUGEES. 
 
5.  CROATIAN MILITARY AND CIVILIAN OFFICIALS TELL US 
THERE ARE NO PLANS TO TURN BACK BY FORCE OF ARMS 
ANTICIPATED HUGE FLOWS OF REFUGEES FROM THE IMPENDING 
  CALAMITY IN B-H THIS WINTER; PRIVATELY, THEY SAY THEY 
  EXPECT TO BE CONFRONTED WITH AT LEAST 100,000 TO 
  300,000 NEW ARRIVALS.  AT THE SAME TIME, CROATIAN 
  OFFICIALS SAY THERE IS ALMOST NO UNUSED HARDENED 
  SHELTER LEFT, AND CROATIA WILL SIMPLY BE UNABLE TO 
  HOUSE ANYWHERE NEAR THE NUMBER OF REFUGEES LIKELY 
  EVEN UNDER \"BEST CASE\" SCENARIOS.  CROATIAN OFFICIALS 
  ARE ALSO -- HELPLESSLY, THEY ADMIT -- EXAMINING WHAT 
  THEY CALL \"HORROR\" SCENARIOS INVOLVING UP TO ONE 
  MILLION MORE ARRIVALS FROM B-H, WHICH WOULD RESULT IN 
  SOCIAL BREAKDOWN IN CROATIA. 
 
  6.  CROATIA HAD A \"GENTLEMAN\'S A433.3,5\" WITH THE 
  UNHCR TO MOVE EX-DETAINEES FROM B-H THROUGH THE 
  KARLOVAC TRANSIT FACILITY WITHIN 15 DAYS.  THE WAIT 
  FOR ALL BUT THE FEW WHO HAVE DEPARTED KARLOVAC HAS 
  NOW GROWN TO OVER TWO MONTHS.  DESPITE LOCAL TENSION 
  RESULTING FROM THE EXTENDED PRESENCE OF THESE 
  FREE-TO-ROAM EX-DETAINEES IN WAR-TORN, ECONOMICALLY 
  DEPRESSED KARLOVAC, THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT HAS JUST 
  MADE AVAILABLE SOME 500-700 MORE SPACES IN THIS TOWN. 
  ITS ONGOING EFFORTS TO SECURE MORE SPACE IN OTHER 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02392  02 OF 09  131608Z 
  CROATIAN COMMUNITIES, HOWEVER, ARE MEETING STRONG 
  LOCAL RESISTANCE, INCLUDING THREATS OF PUBLIC 
  DISORDER FROM AUTHORITIES ALREADY GLUTTED WITH 
  REFUGEES AND DISPLACED PERSONS. 
. 
 
 
