SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- APPROACHING THE BREAKING POINT: 
-         CROATIA AND THE BOSNIAN REFUGEE PROBLEM 
 
WESTERN DIPLOMATIC ENERGY FOCUSSED ON THE SMALL, THUS 
FAR DISTRACTING MOVEMENTS OF ESSENTIALLY BIT PLAYERS 
IN BELGRADE, WHILE IT IS ABUNDANTLY CLEAR TO CROATS 
THAT -- IN SERBIA, THE KOSOVO, SECTOR EAST, SECTOR 
SOUTH, AND THE BOSNIAN SERB \"CORRIDOR\" -- MILOSEVIC, 
DIRECTLY OR THROUGH HIS JUNIOR PARTNERS IN WAR CRIMES, 
STILL RUNS THE SHOW. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  04 OF 09  131612Z 
 
9.  COMMENT CONCLUDED:  OPPORTUNISTIC SELF-INTEREST, 
GREED, ALONG WITH A LEGITIMATE DESIRE TO PROTECT 
BOSNIAN CROATS, WAS AMONG CROATIA\'S MOTIVES FOR 
INTERVENING MILITARILY IN B-H IN THE FIRST PLACE. 
AND THERE REMAINS IN ZAGREB A NEAR-UBIQUITOUS, POTENT 
HERCEGOVINIAN ELEMENT WHICH STILL CRAVES ANNEXATION 
IN B-H AND DOES NOT WHOLLY TRUST TUDJMAN TO DO THEIR 
BIDDING.  WE MUST AND WE WILL, THEREFORE, CONTINUE TO 
KEEP THE CROATS\' FEET TO THE FIRE.  BUT OUR AND OTHER 
WESTERN GOVERNMENTS\' EXHORTATIONS TO CROATIA TO ACCEPT 
WHAT IS IN FACT AN EVER MORE SOCIALLY AND FINANCIALLY 
DESTABILIZING NUMBER OF BOSNIAN REFUGEES -- WHILE 
SERBIAN ETHNIC CLEANSING IN B-H AND CROATIA ITSELF 
CONTINUES APACE -- ARE UNLIKELY TO MEET WITH GREAT 
SYMPATHY.  DIRECT WESTERN OR INTERNATIONAL FINANCIAL 
ASSISTANCE TO CROATIA TO HELP IT CARRY ITS REFUGEE 
BURDEN -- COUPLED WITH AN OCCASIONAL PUBLIC 
ACKNOWLEDGEMENT OF THAT BURDEN -- WOULD TAKE MUCH OF 
THE STING OUT OF OUR REPEATED APPROACHES. 
 
END SUMMARY AND COMMENT. 
 
--------------------------------------------- -------- 
CROATIA STILL ACCEPTS HUNDREDS OF REFUGEES PER DAY... 
--------------------------------------------- -------- 
 
10.  IN A NOV 11 MEETING, AT WHICH THE CHARGE PRESSED 
VICE PREMIER MATE GRANIC ON CROATIAN ADMISION OF 
REFUGEES AND EX-DETAINEES, GRANIC INSISTED ON 
PROVIDING THE FOLLOWING DETAILS ON CROATIA\'S POLICY 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02392  04 OF 09  131612Z 
AND PRACTICE REGARDING B-H REFUGEES AND DISPLACED 
CROATS.  GRANIC SAID CROATIA STILL LEGALLY ADMITS 
HUNDREDS OF REFUGEES EACH DAY.  ASIDE FROM REFUGEES 
APPLYING INDIVIDUALLY FOR ADMISSION TO CROATIA 
ITSELF, ANYONE WITH A PLAUSIBLE DOCUMENT INDICATING 
 
 
