PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  05 OF 09  131614Z 
REFUGEES FROM SERB-OVERRUN JAJCE, PARTICULARLY THOSE 
WHO WERE ILL OR NEEDED MEDICAL TREATMENT (SOME OF 
WHOM ARE NOW DIAGNOSED WITH TYPHOID). 
 
--------------------------------------------- --------- 
...REQUIRING CASH OUTLAYS OF THREE MILLION USD PER DAY 
--------------------------------------------- --------- 
 
11.  GRANIC ACKNOWLEDGED THAT STATISTICS ARE IMPRECISE 
BUT SAID CROATIA NOW CARES FOR AT LEAST 450,000 
MAINLY MUSLIM REFUGEES FROM B-H, 35,000 CROATIAN 
REFUGEES FROM SERBIA, AND 265,000 DISPLACED CROATS. 
GRANIC PROVIDED PER-PERSON-PER-DAY STATISTICS, BROKEN 
DOWN BY HOUSING CATEGORY, ON THE DIRECT COST TO THE 
GOC OF MAINTAINING THESE PEOPLE.  THE COMPLICATED 
MATH IN FACT WORKS OUT TO ABOUT 3 MILLION USD PER DAY, 
WHICH GOES LARGELY TOWARD TOKEN REIMBURSEMENT FOR 
ROOM AND BOARD PROVIDED BY HOTELS.  GRANIC SAID THE 
GOVERNMENT IS NOW TWO TO THREE MONTHS IN ARREARS ON 
THESE DIRECT PAYMENTS. 
 
12.  THE AMOUNTS THE HOTELS RECEIVE DO NOT EVEN BEGIN 
TO COVER MAINTENANCE, SUPPLIES, AND UTILITIES 
EXPENSES, LET ALONE INFRASTRUCTURE DETERIORATION, OR 
LOST OPPORTUNITY COSTS (E.G., THERE ARE NOW ONLY 180 
AVAILABLE TOURIST/BUSINESS HOTEL ROOMS IN ALL OF 
SPLIT).  GRANIC SAID THAT THE AVERAGE REFUGEE-HOUSING 
TOURIST HOTEL IS RUN DOWN TO THE POINT OF REQUIRING 
TOTAL REHABILITATION AFTER ONLY THREE MONTHS. 
(NOTE:  EMBOFFS CAN ATTEST FIRST-HAND THAT THIS 
APPEARS TO BE THE CASE.)  MOREOVER, THE GOC PROVIDES 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02392  05 OF 09  131614Z 
THE REFUGEES FREE HEALTH CARE, EDUCATION, AND OTHER 
SOCIAL SERVICES -- AND ALL OF THESE SYSTEMS ARE NOW 
UNDER SERIOUS STRAIN.  GRANIC NOTED, FOR EXAMPLE, 
THAT HOSPITAL BIRTHS IN ZAGREB ARE UP OVER 30 PERCENT. 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
