SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- APPROACHING THE BREAKING POINT: 
-         CROATIA AND THE BOSNIAN REFUGEE PROBLEM 
 
--------------------------------------------- -------- 
...AND OTHER EXPENSES OF SEVERAL MILLION MORE USD/DAY 
--------------------------------------------- -------- 
 
13.  MOST FAMILIES WHO HAVE TAKEN IN REFUGEES RECEIVE 
SOME IN-KIND SUPPORT FROM HUMANITARIAN AGENCIES BUT 
(IN CONTRAST TO FAMILIES HOUSING DISPLACED CROATS) 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  06 OF 09  131616Z 
THEY RECEIVE NO FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE.  CONSEQUENTLY, 
MANY OF THESE HOST FAMILIES HAVE LONG SINCE STOPPED 
PAYING FOR ELECTRICITY AND GAS, THE FULL COST OF 
WHICH THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT HAS HAD TO PAY.  GRANIC 
CITED THE EXAMPLE OF THE TOWN OF MAKARSKA (POP. 
17,000) ON THE ADRIATIC COAST, WHOSE INHABITANTS HAVE 
TAKEN IN 20,000 REFUGEES AND 3,000 DISPLACED PERSONS 
BUT STOPPED PAYING UTILITY BILLS MONTHS AGO.  ONE 
RESULT IS THAT THE GOC IS NOW MONTHS BEHIND ON 
PAYMENTS FOR ELECTRICITY IMPORTED FROM SLOVENIA. 
 
--------------------------------------------- ------ 
...WHICH HAS CONTRIBUTED HEAVILY TO HYPER-INFLATION 
--------------------------------------------- ------ 
 
14.  PAYMENTS FOR THE REFUGEES AND DISPLACED NOW 
AMOUNT TO SOME 20 PERCENT OF CROATIA\'S NATIONAL 
BUDGET.  THIS AMOUNT, COMBINED WITH THE COST OF 
SUPPORTING 275,000 UNEMPLOYED WORKERS AND 700,000 
PENSIONERS (WHO RECEIVE ON AVERAGE LESS THAN 
ONE-THIRD OF WHAT THE GOVERNMENT PAYS FOR REFUGEES IN 
HOTELS), HAS CONTRIBUTED GREATLY TO A BUDGET DEFICIT 
WHICH HAS SPAWNED HYPER-INFLATION.  THE AVERAGE RATE 
OF INFLATION OVER THE PAST TWO MONTHS, ANNUALIZED, 
COMES TO OVER 2,500 PERCENT.  THE GOC HAS RECEIVED 
AND EXPRESSED GRATITUDE FOR A CONSIDERABLE AMOUNT OF 
HUMANITARIAN ASSISTANCE IN FOOD, MEDICINE, HYGENE 
SUPPLIES, CLOTHES, AND THE LIKE, BUT IT HAS RECEIVED 
ONLY TINY AMOUNTS OF AID (LOW MILLIONS) TO HELP OFFSET 
ITS DAY-TO-DAY REFUGEE/DISPLACED-RELATED EXPENSES. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02392  06 OF 09  131616Z 
----------------------------- 
...AND RISING SOCIAL TENSIONS 
----------------------------- 
 
15.  GRANIC SAID THERE IS VERY LITTLE UNOCCUPIED 
 
 
