TAGS: PREF, PHUM, UNHCR, UN, HR, BK 
SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- APPROACHING THE BREAKING POINT: 
-         CROATIA AND THE BOSNIAN REFUGEE PROBLEM 
 
 
17.  GRANIC SAID CROATIAN POLICY ON ADMITTING 
ADDITIONAL REFUGEES IS HEAVILY INFLUENCED BY THREE 
FACTORS IN ADDITION TO SPACE LIMITATIONS AND THE 
DIRECT COSTS INVOLVED: 
 
-    -- FIRST AND FOREMOST, CROATIA, LIKE THE UN 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  08 OF 09  131620Z 
ITSELF, WILL NOT WITTINGLY LEND DE FACTO SUPPORT TO 
SERBIAN ETHNIC CLEANSING.  CROATIA\'S PROCLAIMING A 
WIDE-OPEN BORDER WOULD RISK SETTING OFF A MASS 
MIGRATION OF POTENTIALLY OVER A MILLION PEOPLE. 
 
-    -- SECONDLY, ACTIVELY ADMITTING SUBSTANTIAL 
NUMBERS OF ADDITIONAL REFUGEES INTO CROATIA COULD 
RESULT IN A VIOLENT ERUPTION THAT WOULD TEAR APART 
THE FABRIC OF CROATIAN SOCIETY.  WITH THAT IN MIND, 
THE GOVERNMENT HAS REFRAINED FROM WIDELY PUBLICIZING 
THE COST OF MAINTAINING THE REFUGEES FOR FEAR OF 
PROVOKING ITS CITIZENS WHO HAVE SEEN THEIR STANDARD 
OF LIVING REDUCED BY OVER 50 PERCENT IN THE LAST YEAR 
AND A HALF.  (NOTE:  THE AVERAGE CROAT NOW EARNS LESS 
THAN 150 DOLLARS PER MONTH.) 
 
-    -- THIRDLY, THE GOC IS DISAPPOINTED BY THE SLOW 
RESPONSE OF THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY TO THE APPEAL 
TO TAKE EX-DETAINEES TRANSITING KARLOVAC; THEY 
ARRIVED UNDER A GENTLEMAN\'S AGREEMENT WITH UNHCR 
THAT THEY WOULD STAY NO MORE THEN 15 DAYS; MOST OF 
THE FIRST GROUP ARE STILL HERE OVER TWO MONTHS LATER. 
 
-------------------------------------- 
BUT CROATIA HAS NOT CLOSED ITS BORDERS 
-------------------------------------- 
 
18.  NEVERTHELESS, GRANIC SAID, CROATIA -- UNLIKE 
SLOVENIA AND ITS OTHER \"WESTERN\" NEIGHBORS -- HAS NOT 
CLOSED ITS BORDERS.  NOR, DESPITE FACING THE PROSPECT 
OF A MASS INFLUX IN THE COMING MONTHS, HAS CROATIA 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02392  08 OF 09  131620Z 
ANY PLANS TO BLOCK ENTRY OF HUGE GROUPS OF REFUGEES 
BY FORCE OF ARMS. 
 
19.  ON THIS SAME SUBJECT, CROATIAN ARMY CHIEF OF 
STAFF GENERAL TUS TOLD OUR DOD REP NOVEMBER 6 THAT 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
