CROATIA, WHILE LACKING THE MEANS TO CARE FOR A LARGE 
NEW FLOW OF REFUGEES, ALSO LACKED THE MEANS TO STOP 
THEM EVEN IF IT WANTED TO.  TUS WENT ON TO COMPLAIN, 
AS OUR DOD REP HAS ALREADY REPORTED, THAT CROATIA IS 
REPEATEDLY CHASTISED FOR NOT ACCEPTING MORE REFUGEES 
BY COUNTRIES WHICH TAKE FEW OR NO REFUGEES THEMSELVES 
AND WHICH REFUSE TO ADDRESS THE ROOT CAUSE OF 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02392  09 OF 09  131621Z 
CONTINUING REFUGEE FLOWS.  CROATIAN HOTELS, SCHOOLS, 
AND HOSPITALS ARE OVERFLOWING WITH REFUGEES, TUS 
ADDED, COMMENTING THAT CROATIA MAY FACE A HOPELESS 
SITUATION UNLESS THE WORLD TAKES DECISIVE ACTION. 
 
