E.O. 12356: N/A 
TAGS: PHUM, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- U.S. HELSINKI COMMISSION DEL CALLS 
-         FOR RECOGNITION OF MACEDONIA, MILITARY INTER 
-         VENTION IN B-H; AND THE ARREST OF KARADJIC 
 
 
------- 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1.  ON COMPLETION OF THEIR VISIT TO MACEDONIA AND 
CROATIA NOVEMBER 15, A HELSINKI COMMISSION DELEGATION 
COMPRISED OF SEN. DENNIS DECONCINI AND REP. FRANK 
MCCLOSKEY ISSUED A STATEMENT CALLING FOR:  IMMEDIATE 
RECOGNITION OF MACEDONIA;  INCLUSION OF MACEDONIA IN 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02405  01 OF 05  161626Z 
CSCE, THE UN, AND OTHER INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS; 
MORE INTENSIVE DIALOGUE BETWEEN SKOPJE AND ATHENS; 
AND AN INTER-ETHNIC MACEDONIAN HUMAN RIGHTS 
COMMISSION.  THEY URGED EUROPE AND THE U.S. TO ASSUME 
THEIR SHARE OF THE BOSNIAN REFUGEE BURDEN.  THEY 
CALLED FOR \"MORE DIRECT INTERVENTION, INCLUDING 
MILITARY INTERVENTION, IN BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA BY THE 
INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY, INCLUDING THE UNITED STATES,\" 
TERMING IT A \"POLITICAL NECESSITY AND MORAL 
OBLIGATION.\"  AND THEY URGED THE IMMEDIATE ARREST OF 
RADOVAN KARADJIC AND HIS ASSOCIATES AS A START TOWARD 
BRINGING TO JUSTICE THOSE RESPONSIBLE FOR WAR CRIMES 
AND GENOCIDE.  END SUMMARY. 
 
2.  BEGIN TEXT OF STATEMENT: 
 
COMMISSION ON SECURITY AND COOPERATION IN EUROPE 
WASHINGTON, D.C. 20515 
 
STATEMENT OF THE HELSINKI COMMISSION DELEGATION TO 
MACEDONIA AND CROATIA 
 
ZAGREB, NOVEMBER 15, 1992 - ON NOVEMBER 13-14, 1992, A 
DELEGATION OF THE COMMISSION ON SECURITY AND 
COOPERATION IN EUROPE -- THE HELSINKI COMMISSION-- 
VISITED THE REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA, AND ON NOVEMBER 15, 
THE REPUBLIC OF CROATIA.  THIS DELEGATION WAS LED BY 
SENATOR DENNIS DECONCINI (DEMOCRAT - ARIZONA) AND 
INCLUDED REPRESENTATIVE FRANK MCCLOSKEY 
(DEMOCRAT-INDIANA).  AT THE END OF THEIR VISIT, 
SENATOR DECONCINI AND REPRESENTATIVE MCCLOSKEY MADE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02405  01 OF 05  161626Z 
THE FOLLOWING STATEMENT: 
 
\"THIS DELEGATION OF THE HELSINKI COMMISSION CAME TO 
MACEDONIA DEEPLY CONCERNED OVER THE PROSPECTS FOR THIS 
 
 
