SUBJECT:  CGYOOL -- U.S. HELSINKI COMMISSION DEL CALLS 
-         FOR RECOGNITION OF MACEDONIA, MILITARY INTER 
-         VENTION IN B-H; AND THE ARREST OF KARADJIC 
 
ENCOURAGE MACEDONIA\'S POLITICAL LEADERS TO FORM A 
HUMAN RIGHTS COMMISSION WHICH WOULD INCLUDE 
REPRESENTATIVES OF THE VARIOUS ETHNIC GROUPS AND HAVE 
THE INDEPENDENCE AND AUTHORITY TO INVESTIGATE REPORTED 
HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN AN EFFECTIVE WAY. 
 
\"WE ALSO URGE THAT MUCH GREATER ATTENTION BE GIVEN TO 
THE WORSENING REFUGEE SITUATION IN MACEDONIA.  THE 
CAMP WHICH WE VISITED, FOR EXAMPLE, WAS CROWDED, AND 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02405  04 OF 05  161630Z 
WITHOUT HEAT OR ELECTRICITY.  HAVING ARRIVED DURING 
SUMMER MONTHS, THESE REFUGEES ALSO NEED PROPER CLOTHES 
AND FOOTWEAR TO GET THEM THROUGH THE WINTER. 
 
\"OUR VISIT TO CROATIA ON NOVEMBER 15 GAVE US A 
FIRST-HAND VIEW OF THE SITUATION FOR REFUGEES AND 
DISPLACED PERSONS THERE.  IN THE CITY OF KARLOVAC, WE 
MET WITH FORMER INTERNEES AT SERBIAN CONCENTRATION 
CAMPS IN BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA WHO REPORTED THE MOST 
HORRIBLE ATROCITIES, INCLUDING THE TORTURE AND RANDOM 
KILLING OF PRISONERS.  THESE PEOPLE, HOWEVER, 
EXPRESSED MORE CONCERN FOR THOSE LEFT BEHIND THAN THEY 
DID FOR THEIR OWN FUTURES AS REFUGEES.  WE ALSO HAD AN 
OPPORTUNITY TO MEET WITH THE PRESIDENT OF CROATIA AND 
OTHER SENIOR CROATIAN OFFICIALS, WITH WHOM WE 
DISCUSSED THE CONFLICT IN BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA, THE 
RESULTING REFUGEE CRISIS, THE STATUS OF THE UN 
PROTECTED AREAS IN CROATIA, AND DOMESTIC DEVELOPMENTS, 
INCLUDING THE OPERATION OF A FREE MEDIA.  OUR 
DELEGATION WAS ALSO PLEASED TO BE HERE AT THE OPENING 
OF THE U.S. ARMY\'S 212TH MOBILE ARMY SURGICAL HOSPITAL 
(MASH) UNIT AT PLESO AIRPORT IN ZAGREB, WHICH WILL BE 
USED BY THE UNPROFOR. 
 
\"WE APPLAUD THOSE AMERICAN SOLDIERS WHO WILL OPERATE 
THE MASH HOSPITAL, AND PRAISE AS WELL THE MANY FOREIGN 
CIVILIANS WE MET IN CROATIA WHO ARE WORKING TO ASSIST 
THE REFUGEES, A TRULY OVERWHELMING TASK.  THE REFUGEES 
TOLD US THAT INTERNATIONAL  ATTENTION, ESPECIALLY BY 
THE INTERNATIONAL COMMITTEE OF THE RED CROSS, HAD BEEN 
INSTRUMENTAL IN THEIR RELEASE, AND THAT THE UN HIGH 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02405  04 OF 05  161630Z 
COMMISSION FOR REFUGEES HAD GREATLY FACILITATED THEIR 
TRANSIT IN CROATIA. 
 
\"WE COMMEND THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT FOR THEIR 
 
 
