GENEVA FOR USDEL ICFY -- JACKOVICH; USVIENNA FOR USDEL CSCE 
 
E.O. 12356:  OADR 
TAGS:  PREL, MOPS, PREF, HR, BK 
SUBJECT:  CGYOOL:  PRES TUDJMAN TELLS SENATOR MOYNIHAN 
-         IT\'S TIME FOR AIR STRIKES AGAINST THE 
-         SERBS; CAUTIONS AGAINST LIFTING ARMS EMBARGO 
 
WITH MORTARS TAKING RANDOM SHOTS AT A CITY, BUT THE 
ORGANIZATION OF A FLOTILLA TO BOMBARD A CITY WAS AN 
ACT FOR WHICH ONLY SENIOR OFFICERS COULD BE 
RESPONSIBLE. 
 
5.  TUDJMAN SAID HE TOO HAD TOURED THE COASTAL AREA 
AND HAD SEEN FIRSTHAND THE SCALE OF DESTRUCTION.  HE 
POINTED OUT THAT THE DEVASTATION WAS FAR GREATER 
SOUTH OF DUBROVNIK, IN THE DIRECTION OF MONTENEGRO. 
HE HAD LIVED THROUGH A WORLD WAR, BUT THE BARBARITY 
OF ACTION IN THIS CONFLICT WAS UNPRECEDENTED. 
 
-------------------- 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02522  02 OF 04  301209Z 
SARAJEVO IMPRESSIONS 
-------------------- 
 
6.  SENATOR MOYNIHAN TOLD THE PRESIDENT THAT HE HAD 
OVERNIGHTED IN SARAJEVO NOV 24, TOURED THE CITY, MET 
WITH PRESIDENT IZETBEGOVIC, AND BEEN BRIEFED BY UNHCR 
ON THE PRECARIOUS FOOD SUPPLY SITUATION.  HE HAD BEEN 
TOLD BY UNHCR THAT SARAJEVO WAS DOWN TO ONLY ONE 
DAY\'S FOOD SUPPLY; INCOMING FOOD ON CONVOYS AND 
RELIEF FLIGHTS IS DISTRIBUTED AND CONSUMED.  TUDJMAN 
SAID IZETBEGOVIC HAD PROBABLY INFORMED THE SENATOR 
THAT SOME 128,000 BOSNIANS HAD BEEN KILLED AND 30,000 
GIRLS AND WOMEN RAPED BY SERBIAN FORCES IN B-H.  THESE 
FIGURES MIGHT, OF COURSE, BE EXAGGERATED, BUT EVEN IF 
THE REAL FIGURES WERE ONLY HALF, THE NUMBERS WERE 
STILL OUTRAGEOUS. 
 
---------------------------- 
ON THE WAR CRIMES COMMISSION 
---------------------------- 
 
7.  NOTING THAT THE UN SECURITY COUNCIL HAD 
ESTABLISHED A WAR CRIMES COMMISSION, THE SENATOR 
ASKED THE PRESIDENT WHAT STEPS THAT THE U.S. AND THE 
INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY SHOULD TAKE NEXT.  TUDJMAN 
SAID BLUNTLY THAT SANCTIONS ALONE WILL NOT STOP 
SERBIAN AGGRESSION.  SERBIAN POLITICS HAS BECOME 
IRRATIONAL.  SERBIAN EXTREMISTS FEEL THAT THEY HAVE A 
BETTER CHANCE TO CREATE A \"GREATER SERBIA\" BY WAR 
THAN BY OTHER MEANS.  THEY CITE THE EXAMPLE OF HOW 
SERBIAN-DOMINATED \"YUGOSLAVIA\" WAS CREATED IN THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02522  02 OF 04  301209Z 
AFTERMATH OF WORLD WAR I AND HOW ANOTHER SERBIAN- 
DOMINATED SOCIALIST FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF YUGOSLAVIA 
HAD BEEN CREATED AFTER WORLD WAR II.  THESE EXTREMISTS 
ARE COUNTING ON THE WAR\'S PERPETUATING A POLITICAL 
RIFT AMONG EUROPEAN STATES.  THIS POLICY DIVISION AND 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
