E.O. 12356:  OADR 
TAGS:  PREL, MOPS, PREF, HR, BK 
SUBJECT:  CGYOOL:  PRES TUDJMAN TELLS SENATOR MOYNIHAN 
-         IT\'S TIME FOR AIR STRIKES AGAINST THE 
-         SERBS; CAUTIONS AGAINST LIFTING ARMS EMBARGO 
 
LACK OF RESOLVE, COUPLED WITH SUPPORT FROM ORTHODOX- 
LEANING RUSSIA, WOULD HELP THEM.  THERE ARE CREDIBLE 
REPORTS THAT SEVERAL HUNDRED RUSSIAN \"VOLUNTEERS\" ARE 
NOW FIGHTING ON THE SERBIAN SIDE IN B-H. 
 
8.  TUDJMAN CALLED FOR THE WEST TO EMPLOY SELECTIVE 
AIR STRIKES.  WESTERN GROUND FORCES ARE NOT NEEDED. 
THE AIR POWER SHOULD BE DIRECTED AGAINST SERBIAN AIR 
BASES, MILITARY FACTORIES, ARTILLERY EMPLACEMENTS, 
AND OTHER MILITARY SITES.  THE SERBS ARE NOW OPENLY 
BOASTING ABOUT THEIR MILITARY MIGHT AND THEIR INTENT 
TO BEGIN BUILDING \"GUIDED MISSILES.\"  SELECTIVE AIR 
STRIKES COULD HELP GALVANIZE OPPOSITION TO MILOSEVIC 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02522  03 OF 04  300917Z 
INSIDE SERBIA, WHERE THERE IS EVIDENT RESISTANCE TO 
HIS POLICIES.  SOME 100,000 YOUNG MEN ARE REPORTED TO 
HAVE EVADED THE SERBIAN DRAFT CALL BECAUSE THEY 
OPPOSE THE WAR AND MILOSEVIC\'S POLICIES. 
 
--------------------------------------------- ------ 
TUDJMAN:  LIFTING ARMS EMBARGO WILL PROLONG B-H WAR 
--------------------------------------------- ------ 
 
9.  GENERAL MORILLON, THE UNPROFOR COMMANDER IN 
SARAJEVO, HAD TOLD SENATOR MOYNIHAN THAT HE WAS 
STRONGLY OPPOSED TO LIFTING OF THE ARMS EMBARGO. 
ASKED FOR HIS VIEW, TUDJMAN SAID THAT LIFTING THE 
ARMS EMBARGO WOULD MERELY ENSURE THAT THE DEATH AND 
DEVASTATION SPREAD AND CONTINUED FOR AT LEAST ANOTHER 
YEAR OR TWO.  THE SERBS ALREADY HAVE SUCH AN 
ADVANTAGE IN COMBAT AIRCRAFT, TANKS, AND ARTILLERY 
THAT THEIR MILITARY SUPERIORITY WOULD NOT BE 
CHALLENGED ANYTIME SOON, EVEN IF ARMS STARTED TO FLOW 
TO THEIR OPPONENTS IMMEDIATELY. 
 
10.  TUDJMAN SAID THE SOLUTION TO THE B-H CRISIS IS 
TO STOP SERBIAN AGGRESSION AND AIR STRIKES OUGHT TO 
BE USED TO THAT END.  HE SPECULATED THAT B-H MIGHT 
HAVE TO BECOME A UN \"PROTECTORATE\" TO BE SAVED.  HE 
SAID IT HAD BEEN A MISTAKE FOR THE EC COUNTRIES AND 
ESPECIALLY THE UNITED STATES TO MAKE SO REPETITIVELY 
CLEAR AT THE OUTSET OF THE CRISIS THAT THEY WOULD NOT 
INTERVENE MILITARILY.  THE SERBS HAD SEEN IN THIS 
STANCE A VIRTUAL GREEN LIGHT FOR MILITARY ACTION 
WITHOUT FEAR OF RETALIATION. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02522  03 OF 04  300917Z 
- 
 
--------------------------------------------- ---- 
SERBIAN GOAL WAS TO RE-ESTABLISH COMMUNIST SYSTEM 
--------------------------------------------- ---- 
 
 
