-         HERCEGOVINA - CASE OF S.V., MUSLIM MALE, 42 
 
TO SURRENDER.  A SERBIAN OFFICER NICKNAMED CIGO TOLD 
THE GROUP THE WHOLE VILLAGE HAD TWO HOURS TO 
SURRENDER.  CIGO WAS THE HEAD OF THE TANK REGIMENT 
WHICH ATTACKED KEVLJANI.  S.V. SAID HE SURRENDERED TO 
CIGO ALL THE WEAPONS THE GROUP HAD, IN HOPES THAT THE 
VILLAGE WOULD BE SPARED.  HOWEVER, THE SERBIAN ARMY 
BURNED MOST HOUSES TO THE GROUND, AND SENT ALL 
MUSLIMS AND CROATIANS IN BUSES TO PRIJEDOR.  AT 4:00 
P.M, THE MEN WERE TAKEN TO THE KERATERM FACTORY ON 
THE EDGE OF TOWN, AND THE WOMEN AND CHILDREN WERE 
TAKEN TO THE YOUTH CENTER IN TOWN.  S.V. SAID 24 
BUSES PULLED UP TO KERATERM.  HOWEVER, THE CAMP WAS 
FULL AND THE PRISONERS COULD NOT UNLOAD.  THE CONVOY 
CONTINUED ONWARD IN A LOW-PROFILE, ROUND-ABOUT WAY 
THROUGH TOMASICA TO OMARSKA CAMP.  THEY ARRIVED ABOUT 
11:00 P.M. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02544  02 OF 06  011241Z 
 
5.  (U)  S.V. SAID HE WAS IN BUILDING NUMBER 11, IN A 
ROOM 15 BY 15 METERS LARGE.  HE BELIEVES OVER 450 MEN 
WERE FORCED INTO THE ROOM.  THE ROOM WAS TOO SMALL 
FOR EVERYONE TO LIE DOWN, SO THEY TOOK TURNS SITTING 
AND STANDING.  S.V. SLEPT HERE FOR 22 DAYS.  ONLY 
AFTER 3 DAYS DID THE MEN RECEIVE ANY WATER, ABOUT 10 
LITERS TO DRINK FOR 450 MEN.  THE PRISONERS WERE MADE 
TO RUN A TYPE OF OBSTACLE COURSE WHEN THEY WERE FED. 
ENTERING AND EXITING THE CAFETERIA, THEY HAD TO PASS 
SINGLE FILE BETWEEN SERBIAN GUARDS, WHO TRIPPED AND 
BEAT ALMOST EACH PRISONER AS HE RAN BY.  BENCHES AND 
TABLES BLOCKED THEIR PATH, AND, IF THE PRISONERS 
STUMBLED OVER THESE, THEY WERE BEATEN EVEN MORE.  A 
MEAL CONSISTED OF 90 G. OF BREAD AND MAYBE SOME SOUP 
BROTH OR A CABBAGE LEAF.  OFTEN, S.V. SAID, 24 TO 60 
HOURS WOULD PASS BETWEEN MEALS. 
 
6.  (U)  ON HIS 22ND DAY AT THE CAMP (AROUND JUNE 
18-19), S.V. WAS CALLED OUT OF THE ROOM AT 2 A.M.  HE 
WAS INTERROGATED BY ZDRAVKO GOVEDARICA, A SERBIAN 
FROM THE VILLAGE OF MRKONJIC GRAD, NEAR JAJCE, WHOM 
HE KNEW BEFORE THE WAR.  THE MAN WAS AN OFFICER, WITH 
THREE CHEVRON MARKS ON HIS UNIFORM, S.V. SAID.  S.V. 
WAS REPEATEDLY QUESTIONED ABOUT THE LOCATION OF A 
LARGE GUN CALLED A MITRALJEZ BREDA.  S.V. DENIED ANY 
KNOWLEDGE OF THIS GUN, AND CLAIMED THAT THE TO IN 
KEVLJANI NEVER OWNED SUCH A GUN.  THE KEVLJANI TO HAD 
SURRENDERED ALL THEIR WEAPONS TO CIGO, DURING THE 
SERBIAN ATTACK ON THEIR VILLAGE. 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02544  02 OF 06  011241Z 
7.  (U)  S.V. WAS TAKEN TO BUILDING 10, TO A ROOM 
 
 
