TAGS:  PREF, PHUM, HR, BK 
SUBJECT:  CYGOOL:  HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN BOSNIA- 
-         HERCEGOVINA - CASE OF S.V., MUSLIM MALE, 42 
 
WITH FOUR SOLDIERS.  S.V. WAS MADE TO UNDRESS TO HIS 
UNDERWEAR, AND TOLD TO LIE DOWN ON HIS STOMACH ON THE 
TILE FLOOR.  ONE GUARD TOOK AN IRON CHAIR, PUT IT ON 
S.V.\'S BACK AND SAT DOWN.  ANOTHER GUARD TOOK A LARGE 
CALIBER AUTOMATIC RIFLE AND BEAT S.V. ON HIS SPINE 
WITH THE BUTT OF THE RIFLE, POUNDING EACH VERTEBRA 
TWICE.  A THIRD GUARD CONTINUALLY KICKED S.V. ALONG 
HIS LEGS AND GROIN.  ONE GUARD POUNDED HIS RIB CAGE 
CONTINUALLY.  S.V. NOW HAS 4 BROKEN RIBS ON HIS LEFT 
SIDE.  THE INSPECTOR GOVEDARICA ENTERED THE ROOM 
DURING S.V.\'S BEATING.  S.V. SCREAMED FOR THE GUARDS 
TO STOP, BUT THEY CONTINUED.  ONE GAVE HIM A SHEET OF 
MEDICAL PILLS PACKAGED IN A METAL AND PLASTIC, 
POP-THROUGH SHEET TO BITE ONTO TO PREVENT HIM FROM 
SCREAMING.  THIS METAL/PLASTIC SHEET ONLY CUT UP 
S.V.\'S MOUTH, LEAVING SCARS WHICH HE SHOWED TO 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02544  03 OF 06  011243Z 
EMBOFF, AND MADE HIM ALMOST UNABLE TO EAT FOR WEEKS. 
- 
8.  (U)  S.V. LOST CONSCIOUSNESS, BUT WHEN HE AWOKE, 
THE FOUR GUARDS WERE STANDING AROUND HIM, AND BEGAN 
TO BEAT HIM AGAIN, ON HIS LEGS, SHOULDERS, AND HEAD. 
HE SAID HE HEARD A VOICE SAY SEVERAL TIMES \"NOT ON 
HIS HEAD|\"  ONE GUARD TOOK A POLICE BATON, STRADDLED 
S.V.\'S BACK, AND BEAT HIS BACK AND RIBS CONTINUALLY. 
S.V. SAID HE FELT THE PAIN OF ONLY THE FIRST TEN 
BLOWS, THEN FELT NO MORE.  ANOTHER GUARD PULLED OUT A 
KNIFE AND SAID HE WOULD CIRCUMCIZE S.V.  THE GUARD 
THEN CUT S.V.\'S KNEE CAP, BUT S.V. SAID HE DID NOT 
EVEN FEEL THE KNIFE AS HE WATCHED BLOOD POUR OUT OF 
HIS LEG. 
 
9.  (U)  THE GUARDS MADE HIM STAND UP, BUT S.V. 
PRETENDED TO FAINT.  THE GUARDS DID NOT BELIEVE HE 
FAINTED, AND FORCED S.V. UP AGAIN.  ON HIS THIRD 
ATTEMPT TO STAND, S.V. DID LOSE CONSCIOUSNESS AS HE 
FELL ON HIS LEFT SIDE, WITH THE BROKEN RIBS.  THE 
GUARDS THREW WATER ON HIM TO WAKEN HIM.  THEY 
RETURNED HIS CLOTHES, AND S.V. WAS ABLE TO PULL ON 
HIS PANTS AND BOOTS BEFORE THEY WALKED HIM BACK TO A 
ROOM.  S.V. SAID HE WAS THE FIRST PRISONER IN OMARSKA 
TO BE RETURNED TO THE ROOMS AFTER A BEATING, AND NOT 
KILLED OR TAKEN TO THE SO-CALLED WHITE HOUSE.  S.V. 
WAS TO BE AN EXAMPLE TO THE OTHERS OF WHAT MIGHT 
HAPPEN TO THEM.  IT WAS 5:00 A.M.  S.V. WAS BEATEN 
FOR THREE HOURS.  HE SAID HE WAS SO BLACK AND BLUE 
THAT THERE WAS NOT ONE WHITE SPOT AS LARGE AS A 
FINGERTIP ON HIS ENTIRE BODY. 
