10.  (U)  S.V. TOOK ONE STEP INTO THE ROOM AND 
FAINTED.  HE LOST COMPLETE CONTROL OF HIS MUSCLES AND 
HAD A DIARRHEA ATTACK THERE.  HE WAS UNABLE TO WASH 
HIMSELF FOR OVER ONE MONTH, HE SAID.  S.V. THOUGHT HE 
LAY THERE FOR A FEW HOURS, BUT WAS TOLD HE LAY 
UNCONSCIOUS FOR TWO DAYS.  HE CAME TO WHEN HE HEARD 
HIS NAME CALLED SEVERAL TIMES.  THE CAMP GUARDS WERE 
CALLING FOR HIM TO EXIT THE ROOM.  AS S.V. WAS UNABLE 
TO WALK, SIX OTHER PRISONERS PUT HIM ON A BLANKET, 
AND CARRIED HIM INTO THE HALLWAY.  ONE GUARD ASKED, 
\"WHERE\'S YOUR GUN?\"  THEY WERE LOOKING FOR S.V.\'S 
PERSONAL HUNTING RIFLE FROM HIS HOME, WHICH S.V. HAD 
TURNED OVER TO CIGO WITH ALL THE OTHER GUNS IN THE 
TOWN.  THE GUARDS EVEN ASKED FOR ALL SEVENTY BULLETS 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02544  04 OF 06  011243Z 
THAT S.V. OWNED AT THAT TIME. 
 
11.  (U)  FROM THIS HALLWAY, S.V. WAS CARRIED ON HIS 
BLANKET TO ANOTHER ROOM OF 36 MEN WHO WERE ALL SICK. 
S.V. SAID HE OCCUPIED A SPACE BEHIND THE DOOR OF THE 
ROOM, ABOUT 80 CENTIMETERS LONG.  AS HE LAY FOR 
SEVERAL DAYS IN A FETAL POSITION, HE WAS OCCASIONALLY 
ABLE TO MOVE HIS HEAD, HANDS, AND FEET, BUT HE 
RECEIVED ABSOLUTELY NO MEDICAL ATTENTION WHATSOEVER. 
A COUSIN OF HIS WAS IN THIS ROOM AND TENDED TO HIM. 
ONE DAY, GUARDS CAME INTO THE ROOM AND BEAT PEOPLE AT 
RANDOM WITH POLICE BATONS.  HIS COUSIN WAS 
PISTOL-WHIPPED IN THE FACE.  S.V. LAY BEHIND THE 
DOOR, AND SO WAS SPARED MORE INJURY AT THIS TIME. 
 
12.  (U)  S.V. COUGHED DESPERATELY.  HE SUCCEEDED IN 
TURNING ONTO HIS BACK AFTER TWO DAYS OF TRYING.  HE 
HAD JUST A FEW GULPS OF WATER DAILY.  HIS WOUNDS 
BEGAN TO HEAL SLOWLY.  HIS COUSIN MANAGED TO BRING A 
LITTLE FOOD TO HIM DURING THE NEXT FEW DAYS.  AFTER A 
WEEK, S.V. WANTED TO GO TO THE CAFETERIA TO EAT WITH 
THE OTHERS, BUT HAD TO RUN THE OBSTACLE COURSE JUST 
LIKE THE REST OF THE PRISONERS. 
 
13.  (U)  TWO WEEKS LATER, THE GUARDS BEGAN 
SYSTEMATICALLY TO EMPTY OUT SEVERAL ROOMS, INCLUDING 
THE SICK ROOM S.V. WAS IN.  S.V. WAS PUT IN A MUCH 
LARGER ROOM, IN ROOM 15 WITH SEVERAL HUNDRED MEN. 
FOR 37 DAYS AFTER HIS BEATING, HE WAS LEFT ALONE. 
THEN HE WAS SENT A SECOND TIME FOR QUESTIONING TO 
INSPECTOR DRAGE MEAKIC, WHOSE BROTHER WAS THE CAMP 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02544  04 OF 06  011243Z 
COMMANDER.  MEAKIC WAS A POLICE CRIMINAL INSPECTOR 
BEFORE THE WAR WHO WAS KNOWN TO S.V.  MEAKIC SHOWED 
GREAT INTEREST IN A LIST OF 101 MEN FROM KEVLJANI, OF 
 
 
