ALL THREE ETHNIC GROUPS, WHO WERE IN THE TO THERE. 
S.V.\'S NAME WAS ON THIS LIST.  HE UNDERWENT A THIRD 
QUESTIONING WITHIN THE NEXT FEW DAYS. 
- 
14.  (U)  ROOM 15 HELD ABOUT 300-350 MEN.  IT HAD A 
SMALL BATHROOM AREA, WITH LONG, CEMENT, TROUGH-STYLE 
SINKS.  FOR LACK OF SPACE, MEN SLEPT IN AND UNDER 
THESE SINKS.  THREE FAUCETS WORKED, SO IT WAS THE 
ONLY ROOM WITH WATER AVAILABLE TO THE PRISONERS. 
S.V. GOT A PLACE UNDER ONE SINK.  THE STENCH WAS 
TERRIBLE, AS THE SINKS WERE USED AS TOILETS BY THE 
PRISONERS.  HE SLEPT 10 DAYS IN THIS PLACE.  THEN HE 
WAS MOVED ACROSS THE HALL TO THE SHOWER STALLS.  TWO 
PEOPLE SLEPT IN EACH STALL, ONE METER SQUARE.  S.V. 
SAID HE COULD ONLY STRETCH HIS LEGS IF HE EXTENDED 
THEM UP THE SIDE WALL.  HE STAYED HERE UNTIL EARLY 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02544  05 OF 06  011244Z 
AUGUST, WHEN THE ICRC AND JOURNALISTS CAME TO THE 
CAMP. 
 
15.  (LOU)  S.V. NAMED SEVEN OF EIGHT PEOPLE HE SAID 
WERE TAKEN AWAY FROM THIS SHOWER AREA AND NEVER SEEN 
AGAIN.  THEY WERE: 
-   IBRO PAUNOVIC (PROTECT), FROM PRIJEDOR,  WHO WAS 
    THE TECHNICAL DIRECTOR OF THE OMARSKA AND 
    TOMASICA MINES 
-   ESO MEHMEDAGIC (PROTECT), AN ALMOST BLIND MAN 
-   STJEPAN MARIC (PROTECT) 
-   MIROSLAV SOLAJA (PROTECT), DIED FROM WOUNDS 
    INFLICTED DURING A BEATING. 
-   MIROSLAV (FNU) 
-   SAKIB PERVANIC (PROTECT), TAKEN AWAY BY A MAN 
    WHOM S.V. IDENTIFIED AS THE SON OF RADE GRUBAN, A 
    SERB. 
-   SMAJO GARIBOVIC (PROTECT), 
 
16.  (U)  IN EARLY AUGUST, THE GUARDS AT OMARSKA 
BECAME VERY UNSETTLED AND MOVED MEN FROM ROOM TO 
ROOM.  184 MEN, INCLUDING S.V. WERE TRANSFERRED TO A 
GARAGE ABOUT 25 METERS SQUARE.  AFTER 3 DAYS, 88 OF 
THEM, INCLUDING S.V., WERE TAKEN TO THE SOCALLED 
WHITE HOUSE .  THE NEXT DAY, AUGUST 6, 1200 MEN WERE 
SENT ON A CONVOY TO MANJACA AS S.V. LATER FOUND OUT. 
THEN 1000 MEN WERE SENT TO TRNOPOLJE CAMP.  ONLY THE 
184 MEN SINGLED OUT BEFORE WERE LEFT IN OMARSKA. 
THEY WERE LED TO A LARGE ROOM WHERE THEY HAD TO 
ASSEMBLE AND MAKE ARMY BEDS. 
17.  (U)  S.V. WAS LED AWAY BY FOUR SOLDIERS TO A 
