COCKROACH AND MADE S.V. EAT IT FROM HIS HAND.  THIS 
GUARD THEN CLAIMED THAT S.V. BIT HIM.  THREE OF THE 
SOLDIERS BEAT S.V. VICIOUSLY ON HIS CHEST, BACK AND 
LEGS WITH POLICE BATONS.  WHEN S.V. FELL, A GUARD 
STOOD ON HIS FACE AND RUBBED IT WITH HIS BOOT INTO 
THE FLOOR.  WHEN S.V. WAS SENT TO THE BATHROOM TO 
WASH, A GUARD FOLLOWED, AND BEAT HIM WITH THICK CABLE 
WIRE ALONG THE WAY.  S.V. SAID HE BELIEVES HE WAS THE 
LAST MAN SEVERELY BEATEN IN OMARSKA CAMP. 
 
18.  (U)  ALTHOUGH THE PRISONERS HAD MADE 120 BEDS, 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02544  06 OF 06  011245Z 
THEY WERE NOT ALLOWED TO SLEEP ON THEM, BUT HAD TO 
SLEEP ON THE FLOOR OF THE HALLWAY IN THAT BUILDING. 
ON AUGUST 12, INTERNATIONAL JOURNALISTS ARRIVED AT 
OMARSKA.  THE SERBS TOLD THE JOURNALISTS THAT THE 
PRISONERS THERE HAD BEEN HELD FOR TWO TO THREE WEEKS 
FOR INTERROGATION.  THE JOURNALISTS HAD BROUGHT ICRC 
REGISTRATION CARDS AND REGISTERED ALL THE PRISONERS. 
S.V. SAID THE REPORTERS TOLD THEM THAT THEY WERE NOW 
CITIZENS OF THE U.N.  THE PRISONERS WERE ALLOWED TO 
SLEEP ON THE BEDS FOR THREE NIGHTS.  ON AUGUST 21, 
ALL THE REMAINING PRISONERS IN OMARSKA WERE TAKEN TO 
MANJACA CAMP.  S.V. SAID THAT THE MEN WERE NO LONGER 
BEATEN REGULARLY AND SEVERELY FROM THAT POINT AND 
THAT THE ICRC CAME REGULARLY TO CHECK ON THEIR 
CONDITION AND BRING THEM FOOD. 
 
