USVIENNA FOR USDEL CSCE 
 
AND OUTSIDE THE AREA WERE IN SHORTER SUPPLY.  IN 
NORTHWEST BOSNIA, STAFFER BELIEVES THE FOOD SUPPLY IN 
GENERAL IS PROBABLY STILL ADEQUATE TO MAINTAIN 
MINIMUM NUTRITION REQUIREMENTS IF RPT IF PEOPLE HAVE 
ACCESS TO THE MARKET.  PEOPLE IN BANJA LUKA WHO WERE 
NOT UNDER SOME KIND OF HOUSE ARREST OR IN PRISON AND 
WHO HAD MONEY OR VALUABLES WOULD BE ALL RIGHT. 
PEOPLE IN THE COUNTRYSIDE WHO HAVE STOCKED UP FOR 
WINTER AS THEY TRADITIONALLY DO AND WHOSE LARDERS AND 
CUPBOARDS HAVE NOT BEEN LOOTED WOULD ALSO BE OK. 
HOWEVER, THE TENS OF THOUSANDS OF POOR PEOPLE, THE 
HOMELESS, AND THE ELDERLY WERE ALREADY HAVING A ROUGH 
TIME SURVIVING AND THINGS WOULD WORSEN AS WINTER 
CONTINUED.  THE SITUATION, HOWEVER, IS SIGNIFICANTLY 
LESS BAD THAN IN SARAJEVO OR THE OTHER BESIEGED 
CITIES AND MORE ACTIVE WAR ZONES. 
 
