SUBJECT:  1992 CROATIA HUMAN RIGHTS REPORT -- EMBASSY 
-         COMMENTS ON DEPARTMENT\'S RE-DRAFT 
 
REF: (A) 92 STATE 408075; (B) 92 ZAGREB 2463 
 
1.  LIMITED OFFICIAL USE -- ENTIRE TEXT. 
 
----------------------------------------- 
GENERAL COMMENTS ON DEPARTMENT\'S RE-DRAFT 
----------------------------------------- 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  02863  01 OF 08  311857Z 
2.  REF A\'S RE-DRAFT OF THE CROATIA HUMAN RIGHTS 
REPORT CONSTITUTES, IN OUR VIEW, A MAJOR AND AS YET 
UNSUBSTANTIATED REORIENTATION OF THE DRAFT REPORT WE 
SUBMITTED IN REF B. 
 
3.  IN LIGHT OF ALL THAT HAS HAPPENED IN CROATIA IN 
1992, IT MIGHT BE POSSIBLE BY PICKING AND CHOOSING TO 
\"DOCUMENT\" VIRTUALLY ANY CASE ONE WERE INCLINED TO 
MAKE REGARDING THE HUMAN RIGHTS PERFORMANCE OF THE 
CROATIAN GOVERNMENT.  OVERALL BALANCE WILL BE CRITICAL 
TO THE CREDIBILITY OF THIS YEAR\'S REPORT.  IN OUR 
DRAFT WE SOUGHT CAREFULLY TO STRIKE A BALANCE WHICH 
ACCURATELY REFLECTS THE HUMAN RIGHTS SITUATION IN 
THIS COUNTRY OVER THE PAST YEAR. 
4.  IN PARAGRAPH 11 OF REF A WE ARE ADVISED TO MAKE A 
\"SPECIAL EFFORT\" TO DOCUMENT HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES BY 
THE CROATS -- OTHERWISE THE STRONG U.S. INDICTMENT OF 
SERBIAN ABUSES IN SERBIA AND BOSNIA-HERCEGOVINA WILL 
SEEM LESS CREDIBLE.  IT IS POSSIBLE THAT WE 
MISUNDERSTAND THE INTENT OF THIS REQUEST, BUT, FOR 
THE RECORD, WE WOULD BE EXTREMELY UNCOMFORTABLE 
TAKING SUCH A CALCULATED APPROACH TO DESCRIBING 
CROATIA\'S HUMAN RIGHTS PERFORMANCE.  MORE PLAINLY 
PUT, WE DON\'T THINK CROATIA\'S AND SERBIA\'S 1992 HUMAN 
RIGHTS REPORTS SHOULD BE DRAFTED OR CONSIDERED \"IN 
TANDEM.\" 
 
5.  THIS FORMERLY EVACUATED MISSION HAD ALMOST NO 
FILES FROM THE FIRST HALF OF 1992 AND EXPERIENCED AN 
ALMOST TOTAL CHANGEOVER OF PERSONNEL LAST SUMMER. 
YET WE FULLY ACKNOWLEDGED, AND WE INCLUDED IN OUR 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02863  01 OF 08  311857Z 
DRAFT, SERIOUS HUMAN RIGHTS SHORTCOMINGS AND EVEN 
ALLEGATIONS OF HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS, IN TERRITORY 
CONTROLLED BY THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT IN 1992.  IF 
THE DEPARTMENT IS ABLE TO AUGMENT WHAT WE INCLUDED IN 
OUR DRAFT WITH HARD EVIDENCE WHICH CASTS CROATIA\'S 
HUMAN RIGHTS PERFORMANCE IN A DIFFERENT LIGHT, THIS 
SHOULD OBVIOUSLY BE DONE.  BUT WE WOULD LIKE TO STICK 
WITH THE FACTS AND KEEP OUR FOCUS ON CROATIA. 
 
6.  MANY OBSERVERS OF THE CROATIAN SCENE, INCLUDING 
HARSH CRITICS OF THE GOVERNMENT, WOULD TEND TO 
DISMISS A GRATUITOUSLY SEVERE REPORT AS MERELY 
REFLECTING A DEEP-SEEDED STATE DEPARTMENT BIAS 
AGAINST CROATS.  WE HERE DO WHAT WE CAN TO CORRECT 
THIS UNFORTUNATE MISPERCEPTION.  BUT A HUMAN RIGHTS 
REPORT OF REF A\'S ORIENTATION RUNS THE RISK OF BEING 
REJECTED OUT OF HAND.  THIS IS NOT/NOT AN ARGUMENT 
FOR NOT TAKING A TOUGH, OBJECTIVE VIEW OF THIS 
VERY-IMPERFECT GOVERNMENT\'S HUMAN RIGHTS PERFORMANCE, 
BUT WE SHOULD LIMIT OURSELVES TO THAT. 
 
END GENERAL COMMENTS ON REF B RE-DRAFT. 
7.  N.B.  ALL PARAGRAPH REFERENCES BELOW ARE TO 
REF A.  THROUGHOUT, FOR SUGGESTED INSERTIONS OR 
CHANGES, WE USE DOUBLE SLASHES (//) TO SET OFF TEXT 
FOR INCLUSION OR SUBSTITUTION. 
 
8.  PARA 5, SENTENCE ONE.  THIS CONSTRUCTION IS NOT 
ACCURATE.  WE SUGGEST SUBSTITUTING //CROATIA, WHOSE 
TERRITORY FORMERLY CONSTITUTED ONE OF THE CONSTITUENT 
REPUBLICS OF THE SOCIALIST FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02863  01 OF 08  311857Z 
YUGOSLAVIA, DECLARED ITS INDEPENDENCE ON JUNE 25, 
1991.// 
 
9.  PARA 5, SENTENCE TWO, COMMENT: IT IS TENDENTIOUS 
IN THE EXTREME TO STATE THAT CROATIA\'S DECLARATION OF 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
