CROATIA IN 1992.  A CRITICAL DISTINCTION MUST BE MADE 
BETWEEN SUCH CRIMES COMMITTED ON CROATIAN GOVERNMENT 
CONTROLLED TERRITORY, COMPARATIVELY FEW IN NUMBER, 
AND DOCUMENTED KILLINGS IN AREAS UNDER LOCAL SERBIAN 
CONTROL, WHICH WERE FAR MORE NUMEROUS AND OFTEN 
INVOLVED DIRECT COMPLICITY OF LOCAL SERBIAN 
AUTHORITIES.  THE HIGHEST LEVELS OF THE GOVERNMENT OF 
CROATIA HAVE PLEDGED THAT ALL CRIMES AGAINST CITIZEN 
WILL BE PROSECUTED TO THE FULLEST EXTENT OF THE LAW. 
WITHIN MOST PARTS OF THE UNPAS, THE SITUATION IS 
INCOMPARABLY WORSE.  IN THE AREAS UNDER THE CONTROL 
OF THE SO-CALLED KNIN GOVERNMENT, MURDERS OCCUR 
REGULARLY AND NO PERPETRATORS HAVE BEEN BROUGHT TO 
JUSTICE.  IN SECTOR EAST, FOR EXAMPLE, A SERBIAN 
EXTREMIST WAS IDENTIFIED AS THE GUNMAN IN THREE 
SEPARATE MURDERS COMMITTED IN THE SUMMER OF 1992.  HE 
WAS DETAINED AND RELEASED TWICE BY THE ETHNIC SERBIAN 
\"AUTHORITIES\" AND THEN ALLOWED TO CROSS OVER INTO 
SERBIA AFTER HIS THIRD ARREST.// 
 
