38.  REF A, NOTE 19: EMBASSY ZAGREB REPORTING AND THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  02863  05 OF 08  311902Z 
INTERNATIONAL NEWS MEDIA HAVE DETAILED THE SPECIFIC 
ACTIVITIES OF SERBIAN EXTREMISTS IN THE UNPAS.  IN 
SECTOR EAST, SERBIAN PARAMILITARIES, INCLUDING THUGS 
FROM SERBIA WHO WORK FOR THE TERRORIST ARKAN, FORCE 
THEIR WAY INTO HOUSES FOR THE PURPOSE OF TAKING A 
\"CENSUS\" OF PEOPLE AND BELONGINGS.  NON-SERBS, 
INCLUDING HUNGARIANS AND SLOVAKS, ARE THEN PRESSURED 
BY PHYSICAL INTIMIDATION TO SIGN OVER THEIR PROPERTY 
AND LEAVE.  IN ISOLATED HOMESTEADS, GUNMEN WALK 
THROUGH THE TARGETED FARMYARDS SHOOTING AT WINDOWS 
AND PEOPLE IN THE HOUSES.  CREDIBLE REPORTS FROM 
INTERNATIONAL OBSERVERS HAVE DOCUMENTED FORCIBLE 
ENTRY INTO HOMES AND THEN THE MURDER OR ASSAULT OF 
THE OCCUPANTS, MOSTLY OLD WOMEN AND MEN.  MURDERS OF 
MOSTLY ELDERLY CROATS TAKE PLACE IN SECTOR SOUTH ON 
AN ALMOST WEEKLY BASIS. 
 
39.  REF A, NOTE 20: THE CULPRITS, WHO STRUCK AT 
NIGHT, HAVE NOT BEEN CONCLUSIVELY IDENTIFIED.  IT IS 
BELIEVED THAT CROATS, PROBABLY DISPLACED FROM BARANJA 
AND SLAVONIA, MOTIVATED BY REVENGE, WERE 
RESPONSIBLE. 
 
