FUNCTIONING FCC-LIKE AGENCY.  GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS 
WHO DISCUSSED THIS QUESTION RAISED THE MATTER OF 
ECONOMIC VIABILITY, SPECIFICALLY WHETHER OR NOT THERE 
WAS A SUFFICIENT ADVERTISING BASE TO MAKE ECONOMIC 
SENSE FOR MULTIPLE NEW STATIONS.  THE GOVERNMENT IS 
PROBABLY NOT SURE WHAT KIND OF COMMUNICATIONS POLICY 
IT WANTS AND WHAT MAKES ECONOMIC AND SOCIAL GOOD 
SENSE.  FOR THESE AND PROBABLY OTHER REASONS, THERE 
IS LITTLE INCENTIVE TO MOVE FAST, AND SO FAR, LITTLE 
PUBLIC PRESSURE OR EVIDENCE OF CONCERN. 
 
