57.  REF A, NOTE 32: IT IS UNWISE FOR NON-SERBIAN 
CROATS TO TRAVEL IN SERBIAN-CONTROLLED PORTIONS OF 
THE UNPAS.  EVERYONE TRAVELLING IN THE 
CROATIAN-CONTROLLED PORTION OF SECTOR WEST NEEDS 
PROPER IDENTIFICATION AND PAPERS.  FOREIGNERS AND 
MEMBERS OF INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS HAVE NO 
PROBLEMS TRAVELLING IN FREE CROATIA BUT SHOULD 
EXERCISE CAUTION IN NON-FREE UNPA AREAS. 
 
58.  REF A, NOTE 33: IN THE EYES OF THE BOSNIAN 
GOVERNMENT THESE INDIVIDUALS WERE DRAFT-AGE MALES 
LIABLE FOR MILITARY SERVICE WHO WERE EVADING SUCH 
SERVICE.  WE ARE NOT AWARE THAT THOSE WHO WERE 
RETURNED HAD EVER BEEN ACCORDED REFUGEE STATUS. 
 
59.  REF A, PARA 62 LINE ONE: ADD //CROATS HAVE 
HAD//.  A FIRST REFERENCE TO \"CDU\" SHOULD BE SPELLED 
OUT AS \"CROATIAN DEMOCRATIC UNION.\" 
 
60.  PARA 63: OUR ORIGINAL LANGUAGE IS MORE 
ACCURATE.  ONLY A VERY FEW WESTERN OBSERVERS CALLED 
THE ELECTIONS SERIOUSLY FLAWED.  WE ARE AWARE OF NO 
SUBSTANTIATED ALLEGATIONS OF INTIMIDATION OF VOTERS 
AND MEDIA ACCESS IN THE CAMPAIGN WAS GENERALLY 
CONSIDERED FAIR. 
 
61.  REF A, NOTE 34: IT IS HIGHLY UNLIKELY THAT ANY 
OF THE SHORTCOMINGS ALLEGED CHANGED THE RESULTS. THE 
HDZ IS WELL-ORGANIZED AND RAN AN EFFECTIVE CAMPAIGN. 
THE OPPOSITION WAS FRAGMENTED AND DID A MUCH LESS 
EFFECTIVE JOB IN GETTING ITS MESSAGE ACROSS. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
