AND IN 1991 AS WELL. 
 
65.  REF A, NOTE 37: MUSLIMS AND THE OTHER 
NATIONALITIES IN CROATIA HAVE NOT BEEN MAJOR TARGETS 
OF DISCRIMINATION.  THERE HAVE BEEN NONE OF THE 
FRENCH- OR GERMAN-STYLE ANTI-FOREIGN RIOTS, STONINGS, 
OR MOB SCENES.  MAZOWIECKI BASED HIS CRITIQUE LARGELY 
ON NUMBERS, I.E., THAT MORE SERBS THAN CROATS HAD NOT 
YET ACQUIRED CITIZENSHIP.  THEREFORE, THEY ARE 
DISCRIMINATED AGAINST. 
 
66.  REF A, NOTE 38: THE STATEMENT WAS BASED ON 
DISCUSSIONS WITH WOMEN IN CROATIA, PRESS ARTICLES OF 
CRIMINAL AND COURT ACTIVITIES, AND RESPONSES OF 
VISITING INTERNATIONAL EXPERTS. 
 
67.  REF A, NOTE 39: AN INCREASE IN REPORTING OF 
ABUSE MAY BE DUE TO A COMBINATION OF FACTORS SUCH AS 
INCREASED SENSITIVITY TO WOMEN\'S RIGHTS ISSUES. 
 
68.  REF A, NOTE 40: CERTAIN CLERICAL STAFF HAVE A 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02863  07 OF 08  311904Z 
RIGHT TO STRIKE BUT \"ESSENTIAL SERVICES\" PERSONNEL 
MUST REMAIN ON DUTY.  RETENTION OF POLICE PERSONNEL 
ON DUTY IS AN ESPECIALLY SENSITIVE TOPIC.  IN 1991, 
VIRTUALLY ALL OF SERBS IN THE SERBIAN-DOMINATED 
POLICE FORCES WENT OVER TO THE JNA IN THE WAR, 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
