11.  A REPORT PUBLISHED IN THE CHRISTMAS ISSUE OF THE 
WEEKLY NEWSMAGAZINE \"GLOBUS\" LEVELLED WAR CRIMES CHARGES 
AGAINST SABOR REPRESENTATIVE TOMISLAV MERCEP, KNOWN IN 
SOME CROATIAN CIRCLES AS THE DEFENDER OF VUKOVAR AND OF 
GOSPIC.  THE ARTICLE INCLUDES EXTRACTS FROM CROATIAN 
INTERIOR MINISTRY DOCUMENTS, CLASSIFIED AS \"STATE 
SECRETS,\" WHICH CLAIM THAT SOME 20 EXECUTIONS WERE 
 
SIPDIS 
CARRIED OUT IN 1991 BY A POLICE SQUAD LED BY MERCEP. 
THE KILLINGS ALLEGEDLY TOOK PLACE IN PAKRACKA POLJANA, 
WHERE THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT IN LATE 1993 PERMITTED UN 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00118  03 OF 03  111511Z 
WAR CRIMES INVESTIGATORS TO EXAMINE A MASS GRAVE. 
INTERIOR MINISTER IVAN JARNJAK SAID DECEMBER 28 THAT AN 
INQUIRY INTO THE ALLEGED WAR CRIMES HAD ALREADY BEGUN. 
JARNJAK ALSO SAID HE DID NOT KNOW HOW THE DOCUMENTS WERE 
OBTAINED BY THE PRESS BUT THAT THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT 
IS INVESTIGATING THE LEAK. 
 
GALBRAITH 
 
 
