------ 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
FAMILIES FROM ALL OVER CROATIA, AND HAS DETAILS ON 
8,000 CASES OF PERSONS MISSING IN THE WAR, ALTHOUGH 
THEY ESTIMATE UP TO 11,000 MAY BE MISSING.  (N.B. DR. 
SEPAROVIC NOTED THAT THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT OFFICIALLY 
LISTS 7,000 MISSING, BUT HIS INSTITUTE BELIEVES THE 
NUMBER MAY BE AS HIGH AS 15,000.)  SHE SPOKE OF VUKOVAR 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00176  02 OF 04  131753Z 
-- THE LOVELY DANUBE CITY THAT WAS LEVELLED BY SERBIAN 
AND YUGOSLAV ARMY FORCES EARLY IN THE 1991 WAR.  TWO 
HUNDRED AND SIXTY SICK AND INJURED PEOPLE WERE REMOVED 
BY SERBS FROM THE CITY HOSPITAL IN THE PRESENCE OF RED 
CROSS OBSERVERS, DRIVEN AW 
AY ON BUSES, AND NEVER SEEN 
AGAIN, BUTULA SAID. 
 
5.  BUTULA\'S OWN SON -- A FORMER EXCHANGE STUDENT IN 
OHIO -- WENT MISSING DURING THE WAR.  SHE WAS ONLY ABLE 
TO LOCATE AND REGAIN HIS REMAINS AFTER MANY MONTHS OF 
FRUSTRATING AND EXHAUSTIVE EFFORTS VIA THE RED CROSS 
AND OTHER ENTITIES.  BUTULA RECALLED THE AGONY OF 
UNCERTAINTY, AND INSISTED THAT SERB REFUSAL TO ACCOUNT 
FOR THE DEAD AMONG THE MISSING CONSTITUTED \"A KIND OF 
PSYCHOLOGICAL WAR AGAINST CROATIAN WOMEN.\"  BUTULA SAID 
HER ORGANIZATION DID NOT BELIEVE THAT THE INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITY -- NOTABLY THE RED CROSS -- WAS DOING ENOUGH 
TO INSIST ON FULL ACCOUNTING OF MISSING PERSONS. 
 
6.  AMBASSADOR GALBRAITH OBSERVED THAT A KEY STEP IN 
ADDRESSING THE PROBLEM IS TO CONTINUE TO PUBLICIZE IT 
WIDELY, AND TO THAT END, THE VISIT ON JANUARY 6 BY 
AMBASSADOR ALBRIGHT AND A/S SHATTUCK TO VUKOVAR AND AN 
IDENTIFIED MASS GRAVE SITE NEARBY HAD REFOCUSED 
INTERNATIONAL ATTENTION ON WHAT HAPPENED THERE. 
------------------------------- 
ATROCITIES AND ETHNIC CLEANSING 
------------------------------- 
 
7.  DR. SEPAROVIC LED THE GROUP INTO A GENERAL 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00176  02 OF 04  131753Z 
DISCUSSION OF WAR CRIMES AND ATROCITIES BY STATING THAT 
MOST SUCH ACTS IN THIS CONFLICT HAVE FLOWED FROM THE 
DELIBERATE STRATEGY OF ETHNIC CLEANSING, A MODERN 
ELABORATION ON THE ANCIENT TACTIC OF LAND CONQUEST 
THROUGH TERROR.  DR. LANG AGREED THAT THIS HAD BEEN THE 
SIMPLE AND RUTHLESSLY EFFECTIVE PLAN OF THE SERBS FROM 
THE OUTSET, THOUGH LATER IMITATED BY OTHER SIDES.  \"AT 
THE END OF THIS CENTURY IT HAS BEEN SHOWN THAT GENOCIDE 
IS REALLY THE MOST PROFITABLE FORM OF AGGRESSION,\" LANG 
ADDED. 
 
8.  MR. GOLDSTEIN FOCUSED ON MASS RAPE AS A 
PARTICULARLY NEW AND HORRIFIC ELEMENT OF THESE TACTICS 
AND OPINED THAT \"RAPE AS A MASS EVENT\" IS A DIRECTED 
AND SYSTEMATIC EFFORT, THOUGH THAT IS DIFFICULT TO 
PROVE.  TO MAKE THE POINT, HE OBSERVED THAT EVEN IN THE 
BARBAROUS STRUGGLE BETWEEN USTASHA, CHETNIK AND 
PARTISAN FORCES IN WORLD WAR II, MASS RAPE HAD NOT 
FIGURED PROMINENTLY AMONG THE MANY ATROCITIES 
COMMITTED.  (AMBASSADOR GALBRAITH NOTED THAT GOLDSTEIN 
 
 
