------------------- 
THE MEDIA AS WEAPON 
------------------- 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00176  03 OF 04  131753Z 
 
9.  PROFESSOR ROKSANDIC SPOKE AT LENGTH ON THE ROLE OF 
THE MEDIA AS A WEAPON OF WAR AND THE SIGNAL INSTIGATION 
TO THIS ETHNIC CONFLICT.  THE USE OF MASS MEDIA AT THE 
OUTSET AND THROUGHOUT THE WARS IN CROATIA AND BOSNIA- 
HERZEGOVINA TO FAN ETHNIC SUSPICIONS AND ANXIETIES INTO 
ACTS OF VIOLENCE IS, IN ITSELF, A WAR CRIME, ROKANDIC 
ARGUED.  A/S SHATTUCK TOOK THE POINT FURTHER, ASKING IF 
ROKANDIC WAS SUGGESTING A DELIBERATE EXPLOITATION OF 
MEDIA BY SERB LEADER MILOSEVIC IN PARTICULAR, AND THAT 
SUCH TACTICS SHOULD COME WITHIN THE AUTHORITY OF THE 
WAR CRIMES TRIBUNAL.  ROKSANDIC SAID THAT IT SHOULD BE 
INVESTIGATED. 
 
10.  LANG AGREED AND EXPANDED ON THIS THEME. 
ASSESSMENTS THAT THE CONFLICT IN FORMER YUGOSLAVIA WAS 
AN INEVITABILITY OWING TO CERTAIN TRAITS AMONG \"THE 
BALKAN PRIMITIVES\" ARE \"RACIST AND DECEPTIVE, \" LANG 
SAID.  THIS IDEA -- CIRCULATED WIDELY IN WESTERN MEDIA 
AND AMONG POLICY ANALYSTS -- CONTRIBUTED TO 
INTERNATIONAL INACTION IN THE CRISIS AND HENCE WAS 
POSSIBLY FUELED BY SERB PROPAGANDA EFFORTS. 
 
------------------- 
WHAT IS TO BE DONE? 
------------------- 
 
11.  THE GROUP AGREED THAT ONGOING EFFORTS TO INTERRUPT 
HUMANITARIAN AID CONVOYS IN THE REGION CONSTITUTED A 
WAR CRIME AGAINST CIVILIAN POPULATIONS AND THAT THIS 
WAS ONE AREA IN WHICH ACTION COULD STILL BE TAKEN TO 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00176  03 OF 04  131753Z 
SAVE LIVES, NOT JUST EXACT RETRIBUTION AFTER THE FACT. 
 
12.  THEY ALSO AGREED THAT OTHER HUMAN RIGHTS 
VIOLATIONS CONTINUE UNABATED AND MUST BE STOPPED, BUT 
LANG OBSERVED THAT HUMAN RIGHTS DISCUSSIONS IN THE 
BALKANS NOW OFTEN BECOME BOGGED DOWN IN ARGUMENTS ABOUT 
\"WHO IS MORE VICTIMIZED,\" WHICH OBSCURE PRIORITIES AND 
STUNT EFFECTIVE ACTION. 
 
13.  A/S SHATTUCK AND AMBASSADOR GALBRAITH ASKED THE 
GROUP TO COMMENT ON U.S. INSISTE 
NCE THAT MINORITY 
RIGHTS ARE KEY TO ANY PEACE PROCESS, AND MUST BE 
OBSERVED BOTH IN LAW AND IN FACT.  ROKSANDIC AGREED BUT 
SAID \"THAT DISCUSSION HAS NOT YET TAKEN PLACE\" IN 
CROATIA BETWEEN CROATS AND THE ELEMENTS OF THE SERB 
MINORITY WHICH DESIRE PEACEFUL COEXISTENCE.  \"REAL 
DEMOCRATIZATION\" IS THE PRECURSOR TO SUCH A DIALOGUE, 
AND ONLY TRULY DEMOCRATIC INSTITUTIONS -- NOTABLY A 
FAIR JUDICIARY --  CAN PROVIDE THE ASSURANCES 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
