SET ON FIRE, SEVEN WOUNDED ON STRETCHERS, FOUR 
CIVILIANS, AND THREE SOLDIERS WERE SHOT ABOVE THE 
RAVINE IN THE VILLAGE OF POLJANKE; 38 PRIS 
ONERS SHOT 
IN THE VILLAGE OF BIKOSE; 
 
    -- JUNE 11, 1993, VITEZ:  EIGHT DIED, AND OVER 20 
CHILDREN WERE SERIOUSLY WOUNDED BY MUSLIM ARTILLERY 
SHRAPNEL; 
 
    -- JUNE 11, 1993;   DRENOVIK, KAKANJ:  EIGHT 
CIVILIANS KILLED, NINE WOUNDED, SEVEN CIVILIANS FROM 
THE BRADARIC FAMILY TOOK REFUGE; UNPROFOR REFUSED TO 
HELP; 
 
    -- JUNE 16, 1993,  BUSOVACKE STAJE, BUSOVACA: 
CONVOY CARRYING FOOD ATTACKED-- FOURTEEN CTVILIANS 
AND EIGHT HVO SOLDIERS KILLED, EIGHTEEN WOUNDED; 
 
