TAGS: PHUM, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: TFSROL:  SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
         EYE-WITNESS DESCRIBES TORTURE/EXECUTIONS IN 
         LUKA AND BATKOVIC CAMPS, NAMES PERPETRATORS 
 
 
------------ 
INTRODUCTION 
------------ 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00827  01 OF 04  281646Z 
 
1.  (U)  THIS IS THE FIRST IN A SERIES OF REPORTS OF 
INTERVIEWS OF WAR CRIMES VICTIMS CONDUCTED IN LATE 
1993 IN MAOCA, BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA, BY A DART/ZAGREB 
FIELD REP AND AN AMCIT IRC REP WHILE THEY WERE IN THE 
AREA ASSESSING HUMANITARIAN ASSISTANCE NEEDS.  THIS 
REPORT NAMES VICTIMS AND, IN SOME CASES, PERPETRATORS 
AND DETAILS SPECIFIC CRIMES.  THE PERSONS INTERVIEWED 
FOR THESE REPORTS SEEMED TO THE AMCIT INTERVIEWERS TO 
BE A REPRESENTATIVE SAMPLE OF HUNDREDS OF VICTIMS AND 
EYEWITNESSES NOW LIVING IN THE TUZLA POCKET, MANY OF 
WHOM ALREADY HAVE SWORN STATEMENTS ON FILE WITH LOCAL 
WAR CRIMES COMMISSIONS. 
 
----------------- 
THE FIRST WITNESS 
----------------- 
 
2.  (LOU)  MEHMED ARNAVTOVIC (STRICTLY PROTECT), 
HEREAFTER REFERRED TO AS THE WITNESS, IS A BOSNIAN 
MUSLIM FROM THE BRCKO MUNICIPALITY.  HE WAS BORN 
JANUARY 1, 1964, AND WAS A CIVILIAN AT THE TIME OF 
HIS ARREST BY BOSNIAN SERB FORCES ON MAY 10, 1992. 
- 
--------------------------------- 
ARREST AND INCARCERATION IN BRCKO 
--------------------------------- 
 
3.  (U)  AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST, THE WITNESS WAS 
AT HOME WITH HIS WIFE, PARENTS, SISTER IN LAW AND HER 
HUSBAND, AND SIX NEIGHBORS.  THEY HAD ALL BEEN HIDING 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00827  01 OF 04  281646Z 
IN HIS HOUSE FOR TEN DAYS.  ON MAY 10, BOSNIAN SERB 
SOLDIERS CAME TO THE HOUSE AND ARRESTED THE WITNESS, 
HIS FATHER, AND ANOTHER ADULT MALE RELATIVE AND TOOK 
THEM TO A TEMPORARY PRISON CAMP KNOWN AS \"LUKA\" IN 
THE PORT AREA OF BRCKO.  THE WOMEN IN THE HOUSE WERE 
SET FREE BUT REQUIRED TO STAY IN ASSIGNED PLACES IN 
BRCKO. 
 
4.  (U)  UPON ARRIVING AT LUKA, THE WITNESS WAS 
ORDERED INTO ONE OF A SERIES OF CONNECTED WAREHOUSES 
EACH OF WHICH WAS APPROXIMATELY 20 BY 50 METERS IN 
SIZE.  THERE WERE ALREADY APPROXIMATELY 100 PRISONERS 
IN \"HIS\" WAREHOUSE WHEN THE WITNESS ENTERED.  FOR THE 
FIRST 15 MINUTES, THE WITNESS AND THE OTHERS WERE 
FORCED TO SIT WITH THEIR HEADS DOWN WHILE SERBIAN 
SOLDIERS HIT THEM WITH RIFLE BUTTS.  SEVERAL OF THE 
MEN WERE EXECUTED ON THE SPOT BY GUNSHOTS TO THE HEAD. 
 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
