TAGS:  PHUM, PREF, HR, BK 
SUBJECT: TFSROL:  SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
         EYE-WITNESS DESCRIBES TORTURE/EXECUTIONS IN 
         LUKA AND BATKOVIC CAMPS, NAMES PERPETRATORS 
 
DARKENED WAREHOUSE AND BEAT PEOPLE RANDOMLY.  AT 
ABOUT 2200, FOUR SERBS ENTERED AND TOOK ALL VALUABLES 
FROM THE PRISONERS. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00827  03 OF 04  281646Z 
 
8.  (U) THE NEXT DAY WAS MUCH THE SAME ROUTINE, BUT 
THAT NIGHT AND FOR THE REST OF THE TIME THE WITNESS 
WAS IN LUKA, SERBS CAME IN WITH FLASHLIGHTS AND TOOK 
20 TO 30 PRISONERS EACH NIGHT.  THE OTHER PRISONERS 
WOULD THEN HEAR SHOTS AND SCREAMS.  THE NEXT DAY, 
FOUR MEN WOULD BE TAKEN EITHER TO LOAD BODIES INTO 
REFRIGERATOR TRUCKS OR TO THROW THEM INTO THE SAVA 
RIVER. 
 
9.  (U) ONE PRISONER, MIRSAD MUJAGIC, WHO WAS A 
POLICEMAN BEFORE THE WAR, WAS BEATEN BY TWELVE 
BLACK-CLAD SERBS WITH BASEBALL BATS.  THEY 
SYSTEMATICALLY BROKE HIS FINGERS, ARMS, AND KNEES. 
THEN, RANKO CESIC, ONE OF THE MAIN SERBS FROM BRCKO, 
KILLED MUGAJIC WITH A PISTOL.  WITH CESIC WAS MIODRAG 
CAJEVIC, ALSO FROM BRCKO. 
 
10.  (U) TWO DAYS LATER, A SERBIAN CAPTAIN, DRAGAN 
KABLINOVIC, WHO WORKED IN THE SAME FACTORY AS THE 
WITNESS, CAME INTO THE WAREHOUSE LOOKING FOR SEVEN 
YOUNG MEN TO CLEAN UP GLASS AT THE MEDICAL CLINIC. 
THE WITNESS ASKED TO BE TAKEN AS WELL, AND HIS REQUEST 
WAS GRANTED.  AT THE CLINIC, THEY WERE GREETED BY 
ABOUT 70 SERBS STANDING IN TWO ROWS WAITING TO BEAT 
THE SEVEN MEN TO DEATH.  ONE OF THE SERBS, HOWEVER, A 
MAN NAMED MICIN, REFUSED TO ALLOW THEM TO HIT THE MEN 
MORE THAN ONCE.  AN EARLIER GROUP OF VICTIMS WAS NOT 
SO LUCKY, AS THEY WERE LYING ON THE GROUND COVERED IN 
BLOOD AND UNABLE TO STAND.  TWO DAYS LATER, THE 
WITNESS LEARNED THAT MICIN TOOK ADAM ZELEZIC AND HIS 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00827  03 OF 04  281646Z 
SON MLADEN TO THE WITNESS\' HOUSE WHERE ADAM\'S WIFE 
WAS STAYING.  THEY TOLD MICIN THAT THE WITNESS WAS 
ALSO IN LUKA AND ASKED HIM TO GET HIM.  THE NEXT DAY, 
MAY 14, MICIN RETRIEVED THE WITNESS FROM LUKA AND 
TOOK HIM TO THE WITNESS\' HOUSE.  THEY STAYED IN THEIR 
LARGE APARTMNT TWO MONTHS UNDER HOUSE ARREST, UNTIL, 
ON JULY 14, ALL THE MUSLIM MEN FROM THAT AREA WERE 
TAKEN IN THREE BUSSES TO THE PRISON CAMP \"BATKOVIC\" 
NEAR BIJELJINA. 
 
-------------------- 
BATKOVIC PRISON CAMP 
-------------------- 
 
11.  (U) THE WITNESS SAID THAT THE PRISONERS WERE 
BEATEN AT LEAST TEN TIMES A DAY AT BATKOVIC.  THE 
WITNESS BELIEVED THERE WERE APPROXIMATELY 1,600 
PRISONERS.  THE WITNESS LIVED IN A 14 METER BY 20 
 
 
