SUBJECT: TFSROL:  SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
         EYE-WITNESS DESCRIBES TORTURE/EXECUTIONS IN 
         LUKA AND BATKOVIC CAMPS, NAMES PERPETRATORS 
 
METER WAR 
EHOUSE WHERE PRISONERS WERE FORCED TO SIT 
WITH THEIR HEADS DOWN AND WERE BEATEN AT RANDOM.  THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00827  04 OF 04  281647Z 
WITNESS SAID AT 
LEAST 13 PRISONERS DIED OF BEATINGS, BUT HE WAS 
UNABLE TO PROVIDE ANY NAMES.  THE WITNESS WAS ABLE TO 
IDENTIFY ONE AS THE OWNER OF A JEWELRY STORE AND 
ANOTHER AS A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.  THE WITNESS SAID 
THAT EKREM CUDIC FROM BRCKO WAS FORCED TO WORK EVEN 
THOUGH VERY ILL AND WAS BADLY BEATEN FOR NOT BEING 
ABLE TO WORK HARDER.  ONE DAY, EKREM CUDIC TOOK AWAY 
A GUARD\'S RIFLE AND SLAPPED HIM.  THE OTHER GUARDS 
SHOT AND KILLED HIM. 
 
12.  (U)  ACCORDING TO THE WITNESS, THE MOST CRUEL 
GUARDS AT THE BATKOVIC CAMP WERE GLIGOR BEGOVIC AND 
DZEMAL (\"SPAJZER\") ZAHIROVIC , A GYPSY FROM ZENICA 
WHO WAS LIKE A TRUSTEE OR KAPO.  THE DIRECTOR OF THE 
CAMP WAS VELIBOR (\"VELJO\") STOJANOVIC;  HIS SUPERIOR 
WAS A JNA COLONEL NAMED PETAR DMITROVIC. 
 
13.  (U)  THE WITNESS SAID THAT CONDITIONS WERE VERY 
DIFFICULT FOR THE FIRST MONTH IN THE BATKOVIC CAMP, 
UNTIL A VISIT FROM ICRC WAS ANNOUNCED.  UNTIL THEN, 
PRISONERS HAD ONLY ONE BLANKET APIECE TO COVER THE 
BARE CONCRETE FLOOR.  AFTERWARDS, THEY WERE GIVEN 
STRAW FOR THE FLOOR.  BEFORE THE ICRC ARRIVED, A CORN 
CRIB WAS EMPTIED AND SOME OF THE MEN WERE MOVED 
THERE.  THE ICRC WAS TOLD THESE MEN WERE REFUGEES, 
NOT PRISONERS.  ALSO, ABOUT 15 REGULAR PRISONERS WERE 
TAKEN AWAY TO A BUNKER EVERY TIME THE ICRC VISITED. 
THESE WERE 14 CIVILIANS AND ONE SOLDIER, A MAN NAMED 
NEDIM MOSTAREVIC.  BEFORE EACH VISIT THE GUARDS WOULD 
ALSO REMOVE ABOUT 150 PEOPLE (CHILDREN AND MEN OVER 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00827  04 OF 04  281647Z 
55) AND HIDE THEM IN A DISTANT FIELD.  THE NAME OF 
THE CAMP WAS ALSO CHANGED FROM \"CONCENTRATION CAMP 
BATKOVIC\" TO \"COLLECTIVE CENTER BATKOVIC\".  THIS 
BECAME VERY IMPORTANT, SINCE MEN WHO RECEIVED MAIL 
FROM THE RED CROSS WITH THE WRONG ADDRESS WERE 
SEVERELY BEATEN  ONCE THE MEN WERE REGISTERED BY THE 
ICRC, THEY WERE CONFIDENT THEY WOULD NOT BE KILLED, 
BUT THEY WERE STILL BEATEN REGULARLY. 
 
14.  (U)  ON OCTOBER 5, 1992, THE WITNESS WAS 
RELEASED IN A PRISONER EXCHANGE. 
 
NEITZKE 
 
 
