                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00872  01 OF 05  021700Z 
 
------------ 
INTRODUCTION 
------------ 
 
1. (U) THIS IS ONE IN A SERIES OF REPORTS OF 
INTERVIEWS WITH WAR CRIMES VICTIMS CONDUCTED IN 
LATE 1993 IN MAOCA, BOSNIA-HERCEGOVINA, BY A 
DART/ZAGREB FIELD REP AND AN AMCIT IRC REP WHILE 
THEY WERE IN THE AREA ASSESSING HUMANITARIAN 
ASSISTANCE NEEDS. 
 
------------------- 
WITNESS INFORMATION 
------------------- 
 
2. (LOU) ZEJCIR OSMIC (STRICTLY PROTECT), HEREAFTER 
REFERRED TO AS THE WITNESS, IS A BOSNIAN MUSLIM 
FROM THE BRCKO MUNICIPALITY.  HE WAS BORN ON MAY 
19, 1945, AND WAS A CIVILIAN SHOP ASSISTANT AT THE 
MERKUR COMPANY IN BRCKO AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST 
BY BOSNIAN SERB FORCES ON MAY 1, 1992. 
 
--------------------------------- 
ARREST AND INCARCERATION IN BRCKO 
--------------------------------- 
 
3. (U) THE WITNESS, A SHOP ASSISTANT IN BRCKO, WAS 
VISITING HIS BROTHER\'S HOME IN BRCKO ON MAY 1, 1992. 
HE AND HIS BROTHER SAW MANY SERB SOLDIERS IN BLACK 
UNIFORMS WHO SAID THEY WERE \"ARKAN\'S MEN.\"  THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00872  01 OF 05  021700Z 
WITNESS SUGGESTED TO HIS BROTHER THAT THEY TRY TO 
LIMITED OFFICIAL USE                                     3 
 
RUN AWAY.  AS THEY ATTEMPTED TO ESCAPE FROM THE 
CENTER OF BRCKO, THEY WERE STOPPED AT THE 
RAILWAY STATION BY \"RED BERETS\" (WHO THE WITNESS 
SAID HE BELIEVED WERE FROM NIS IN SERBIA) AND 
WERE ASKED TO SHOW THEIR IDENTIFICATION CARDS. 
THEY WERE THEN ARRESTED AND TAKEN TO LUKA PRISON 
CAMP IN A JEEP.  WHEN THEY ARRIVED AT LUKA, THEY 
SAW MANY MEN, WOMEN, AND CHILDREN LINED UP ALONG 
THE WALL OF THE COMPANY MANAGEMENT OFFICE.  THE 
WITNESS WAS BEATEN WITH A RUBBER TRUNCHEON BY 
SERB POLICEMEN FROM BIJELJINA AND THEN DRAGGED 
INTO A WAREHOUSE WHERE THERE WERE ABOUT 600 MEN 
AND BOYS SITTING WITH THEIR HEADS DOWN.  MANY 
WERE BRUISED AND BLEEDING.  THE WITNESS SAW A 
PASSAGEWAY TO ANOTHER WAREHOUSE WITH MORE PEOPLE. 
 
 
