HE SAW THAT SOME WERE BADLY BEATEN.  HE DID NOT 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00872  02 OF 05  021700Z 
DARE TO LOOK AROUND TOO MUCH, HOWEVER, AS IT WAS 
NOT ALLOWED AND HE FEARED BEING BEATEN AGAIN. 
 
4. (U) SHORTLY AFTER THE WITNESS ARRIVED IN THE 
WAREHOUSE, \"ARKAN\'S SOLDIERS\" BROUGHT IN A CROAT 
NAMED STIPE AND ASKED THE PRISONERS WHO WAS 
READY TO KILL HIM.  WHEN NO ONE ANSWERED, 
\"ARKAN\'S MEN\" FORCED STIPE TO KNEEL AND SHOT HIM 
IN THE HEAD. 
 
5. (U) IN ANOTHER INCIDENT ON HIS FIRST DAY OF 
CONFINEMENT, HE SAID HE WITNESSED THE KILLING OF 
A LITTLE GIRL WHO WAS SIX OR SEVEN YEARS OLD BY 
ONE OF \"ARKAN\'S SOLDIERS.\"  HE SAID THAT ALL THE 
PRISONERS HAD BEEN ORDERED TO STAND AGAINST THE 
WALL, AND WHEN THE GIRL TRIED TO PLAY WITH SOME 
OTHER CHILDREN BY THROWING THEM A BALL, THE 
SOLDIER KICKED HER, KNOCKING HER INTO THE WALL 
HEAD FIRST.  SHE DIED WITHOUT REGAINING 
CONSCIOUSNESS.  THE WITNESS SAID HE WAS ONLY A 
FEW METERS AWAY FROM THIS INCIDENT. 
 
6. (U) THE WITNESS SPENT 17 DA 
YS AT LUKA.  HE 
SAID THERE WERE NO LIGHTS IN THE WAREHOUSE, AND 
EVERY NIGHT SOLDIERS WOULD TAKE 20 TO 30 PEOPLE 
AT RANDOM.  THE PRISONERS WOULD THEN HEAR SHOTS 
AND SCREAMS FROM BEHIND THE WAREHOUSE.  HE SAID 
LIMITED OFFICIAL USE                                     4 
 
(PRESUMABLY BASED ON THE TESTIMONY OF SURVIVORS) 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00872  02 OF 05  021700Z 
THAT SOMETIMES ALL BUT FOUR OF THOSE TAKEN FROM 
THE WAREHOUSE ON A GIVEN NIGHT WOULD BE KILLED, 
AND THESE SURVIVORS WOULD THEN HAVE TO LOAD THE 
CORPSES ONTO TRUCKS.  OTHER TIMES, ALL THOSE 
TAKEN OUT WOULD BE KILLED AND ADDITIONAL 
PRISONERS WOULD BE TAKEN OUT THE NEXT DAY TO 
DISPOSE OF THE BODIES. 
 
7. (U) THE WITNESS ALSO SAW AN EXAMPLE OF 
INTELLECTUALS/ELITES BEING KILLED.  ONE DAY 
WHILE PERFORMING FORCED LABOR COLLECTING GARBAGE 
IN THE TOWN, HE WITNESSED TWO MEN, LEJDAHJA 
MUMINOVIC, THE PRESIDENT OF A TRADE UNION IN 
BRCKO, AND A WELL-KNOWN SALESMAN DRAGGED FROM 
THEIR HOMES AND SHOT. 
 
8. (U) THE WITNESS STATED THAT, A FEW DAYS AFTER 
HIS ARREST, HE SAW WOMEN, CHILDREN, AND OLD 
 
 
