UNABLE TO MOUNT THE TRUCK, SHOT HIM TO DEATH 
WITH A PISTOL. 
 
9. (U) THE WITNESS REMEMBERED THE FOLLOWING 
GUARDS FROM LUKA:  TESIC (LNU) AND GORAN (LNU), 
BOTH OF WHOM COMMITTED MANY KILLINGS, PEDJA 
BOJANIC, AND MILOS CAJEVIC. 
 
---------------- 
RESCUE FROM LUKA 
---------------- 
 
10. (U) THE WITNESS WAS RELEASED FROM THE LUKA 
CAMP WHEN A SERB COLLEAGUE FROM HIS COMPANY SAW 
HIM AND WENT TO THE CAMP COMMANDER TO SEEK HIS 
RELEASE.  THE MAN, RAJKO KRALJEVIC (STRICTLY 
PROTECT) WAS A GOOD MAN AND NOT A NATIONALIST, 
ACCORDING TO THE WITNESS.  TWO SOLDIERS CAME TO 
THE WITNESS AND TOLD HIM TO FOLLOW THEM.  HE WAS 
LIMITED OFFICIAL USE                                     5 
 
CERTAIN HE WOULD BE KILLED.  INSTEAD HE WAS 
TAKEN TO A PIG FARM BY HIS FRIEND AND WORKED AND 
SLEPT THERE FOR THE NEXT YEAR. 
 
---------- 
BIMEX FARM 
---------- 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00872  03 OF 05  021701Z 
 
11. (U) THE FARM THE WITNESS WAS TAKEN TO 
BELONGED TO THE BIMEX COMPANY AND WAS LOCATED 
ABOUT THREE KILOMETERS FROM BRCKO.  HE SAID 32 
MUSLIMS AND SIX CROATS WERE PERFORMING FORCED 
LABOR THERE.  THE MEN WORKED DAY AND NIGHT WITH 
ONLY FOUR TO FIVE HOURS OF SLEEP AND WERE BEATEN 
OFTEN.  SOMETIMES THEY WERE TAKEN TO THE FEED 
MILL IN BRCKO TO LOAD CATTLE FEED.  ONCE, IN THE 
SPRING OF 1993, HE SAW TWO MUSLIM GIRLS, FAHIRA 
CACKOVIC AND SABINA DELICIC, WITH CHETNIKS IN 
BRCKO, BUT THEY WERE NOT ALLOWED TO SPEAK TO 
EACH OTHER. 
 
---------- 
