TAGS: PHUM, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, PREF, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: TFSROL: SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
         EYEWITNESS DESCRIBES KILLINGS AND ATROCITIES 
         IN BRCKO, LUKA, AND BATKOVIC 
 
REF:  (A) ZAGREB 827; (B) ZAGREB 872 
 
------------ 
INTRODUCTION 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00919  01 OF 07  041724Z 
------------ 
 
1.  (U)  THIS IS ONE IN A SERIES OF REPORTS OF 
INTERVIEWS OF WAR CRIMES VICTIMS CONDUCTED IN LATE 
1993 IN MAOCA, BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA, BY A DART/ZAGREB 
FIELD REP AND AN AMCIT IRC REP WHILE THEY WERE IN THE 
AREA ASSESSING HUMANITARIAN NEEDS.  THIS REPORT NAMES 
VICTIMS AND, IN SOME CASES, PERPETRATORS AND DETAILS 
OF SPECIFIC CRIMES. 
 
----------- 
THE WITNESS 
----------- 
 
2.  (LOU)  ADMIR TOSKIC (STRICTLY PROTECT), HEREAFTER 
REFERRED TO AS THE WITNESS, IS A BOSNIAN MUSLIM FROM 
THE BRCKO MUNICIPALITY.  HE WAS BORN JANUARY 11, 
1969, AND WAS AN UNEMPLOYED CIVILIAN AT THE TIME OF 
HIS ARREST BY BOSNIAN SERB FORCES ON MAY 7, 1992. 
 
--------------------- 
THE WITNESS\'S ACCOUNT 
--------------------- 
3.  (U) THE WITNESS WAS IN HIS APARTMENT IN NOVO 
BRCKO ON MAY 7, 1992, WHEN TWO MASKED MEN ORDERED 
EVERYONE (ABOUT 500 PEOPLE) OUT OF THE BUILDING ON 
THE PRETEXT THAT THEY HAD TO BE EVACUATED BECAUSE OF 
THE SHELLING.  THEY WERE ALL TAKEN TO THE ARMY 
BARRACKS WHERE SERBS WERE IMMEDIATELY SEPARATED AND 
RELEASED, WHILE CROATS AND MUSLIMS WERE HELD. 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00919  01 OF 07  041724Z 
4.  (U)  ABOUT TWO HOURS LATER, MILENKO VOJINOVIC, 
AKA \"DR. BELI,\" THE PRESIDENT OF THE SDS IN BRCKO, 
CAME TO THE BARRACKS AND ASKED FOR 20 VOLUNTEERS TO 
CLEAN UP BROKEN GLASS AROUND THE POLICE STATION AND 
THE CENTER OF TOWN.  THE WITNESS VOLUNTEERED ALONG 
WITH 26 OTHER MEN, AND THEY WERE IMMEDIATELY DIVIDED 
INTO TWO GROUPS.  THE WITNESS\'S GROUP BEGAN CLEANING 
UP GLASS AROUND THE POLICE STATION. 
 
5.  (U) BETWEEN 4:30 AND 5:00 P.M., WITNESS HEARD 
SCREAMS, SWEARING, AND TWO SHOTS FROM INSIDE THE 
POLICE STATION.  HE ALSO HEARD A (SERBIAN) \"CETNIK\" 
SONG BEING SUNG.  THEN, A GROUP OF STRANGERS 
INCLUDING A WOMAN -- WHOM HE LATER DETERMINED TO BE 
NAMED SEKA AND FROM NOVI SAD -- CAME OUT OF THE 
POLICE STATION.  THEY BEGAN BEATING THE MEMBERS OF 
THE WITNESS\'S GROUP AND MAKING THEM KNEEL WITH THEIR 
HEADS DOWN WHILE THEY WAITED TO BE TAKEN FOR 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
NNNN 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 01        ZAGREB  00919  02 OF 07  041725Z 
ACTION SS-00 
 
INFO  LOG-00   AID-01   AMAD-01  CIAE-00  C-01     OASY-00  EB-01 
