TOOK A PHOTO.  THE WITNESS SPECULATED THAT THE CAP 
WAS PUT ON KRSO TO MAKE IT LOOK IN THE PHOTO AS IF HE 
WERE A SOLDIER. 
 
6.  (U) NEXT, A MAN WITH A MOUSTACHE WHOM THE WITNESS 
DID NOT KNOW ORDERED HIM AND ANOTHER YOUNG MAN TO GO 
IN FRONT OF THE POSAVINA HOTEL TO COVER UP TWO DEAD 
BODIES.  ONE OF THE BODIES WAS ON ITS BACK.  THE 
WITNESS COULD SEE THAT THE VICTIM\'S THROAT HAD BEEN 
CUT AND HIS PENIS CUT OFF.  THE OTHER BODY (ALSO A 
MAN) WAS LYING FACE DOWN, SO THE WITNESS DID NOT SEE 
WHAT HAD BEEN DONE TO HIM.  AFTER THE WITNESS 
AND THE 
OTHER YOUNG MAN COVERED THE BODIES WITH A TENT, THEY 
WERE ORDERED TO MOVE AWAY.  THE WITNESS QUICKLY 
WALKED BACK TOWARD THE POLICE STATION.  HE HEARD TWO 
SHOTS BEHIND HIM AND NEVER SAW THE OTHER YOUNG MAN 
AGAIN, SO HE ASSUMED THE GUARD SHOT HIM.  BACK AT THE 
POLICE STATION, HE REJOINED HIS GROUP.  A GIRL NAMED 
VIOLETA, WHO WAS SEKA\'S DAUGHTER, LINED THE GROUP UP 
AND MADE THEM SING A SONG ABOUT A TURKISH WOMAN WHO 
SAID IN FRONT OF A MOSQUE THAT SHE HAD ONLY LOVED A 
SERB. 
 
7.  (U) THE GROUP WAS THEN LED INTO THE POLICE 
STATION AND WERE FORCED TO LOOK AT THE SERBIAN FLAG 
WHILE A MAN NAMED GORAN JELISIC BEAT THEM WITH A 
RUBBER TRUNCHEON.  THE WITNESS REMEMBERED GORAN\'S ARM 
WAS COVERED WITH BLOOD FROM HIS VICTIMS.  VIOLETA 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00919  02 OF 07  041725Z 
SAID, \"WHICH ONE DO WE DO NOW, NUMBER 53 OR 54?\" 
GORAN REPLIED, \"I WON\'T LEAVE BRCKO UNTIL I KILL 500.\" 
 
8.  (LOU) AT THIS POINT, FIVE OF THE WITNESS\'S FORMER 
