9.  (U)  THE WITNESS AND HIS BROTHER WENT TO ANOTHER 
APARTMENT, AND AFTER A FEW DAYS HAD TO GO OUT TO TRY 
TO BUY BREAD.  THEY AND TWO OTHERS INCLUDING ADMIR 
SARAJLIC (AKA DEBA) WERE STOPPED BY A SERB SOLDIER 
AND ASKED FOR THEIR IDENTIFICATION CARDS.  THEY HAD 
NO IDENTIFICATION, BECAUSE IT HAD BEEN TAKEN FROM 
THEM AT THE TIME OF THEIR FIRST ARREST.  THE SOLDIER 
ARRESTED THEM AND TOOK THEM ALL TO ROOM 13 AT THE 
BRCKO POLICE STATION. 
- 
10.  (U) THE MEN WERE INITIALLY TAKEN INTO ROOM 13 
WHERE THEY SAW TWO YOUNG MEN, MIRZA KARDAL AND SENAD 
BECIREVIC, WHO HAD BEEN HORRIBLY BEATEN.  WITNESS 
DESCRIBED THE ROOM AS BEING APPROXIMATELY TWO METERS 
BY TWO METERS AND COMPLETELY COVERED WITH BLOOD. 
WHILE ENTERING THE STATION, WITNESS SAW PETAR DJOKIC 
(SECRETARY OF THE SDS) AND PETAR KAURINOVIC AND KRSTO 
MIHAJLOVIC (POLICE INSPECTORS).  DJOKIC TOOK DEBA 
SARAJLIC AWAY.  THE WITNESS AND HIS BROTHER WERE THEN 
QUESTIONED BY POLICE INSPECTORS DRAJISA AND 
KAURINOVIC.  AFTERWARDS, THEY RETURNED TO ROOM 13, 
AND AFTER TWO OR THREE HOURS A POLICEMAN PUT 
HANDCUFFS ON THEM AND TOOK THEM TO LUKA PRISON CAMP 
ALONG WITH DEBA. 
 
11.  (U) THE WITNESS AND FIVE OTHERS WERE PUT INTO 
ONE CORNER OF THE FIRST WAREHOUSE AT LUKA.  AFTER 
ABOUT 10 MINUTES, GORAN JELISIC CALLED FOR SENAD 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00919  03 OF 07  041725Z 
BECIREVIC, AND WHEN SENAD RETURNED HE HAD ONCE AGAIN 
BEEN BEATEN BLOODY.  THEN IVAN (LNU) FROM BIJELJINA 
ENTERED WITH BRASS KNUCKLES AND BEAT THE WITNESS AND 
DEBA. 
 
12.  (U) LATER, A YOUNG GIRL THE WITNESS KNEW AS 
MONIKA ENTERED WITH A BAG AND A PISTOL AND COLLECTED 
ALL REMAINING VALUABLES AND IDENTIFICATION CARDS. 
GORAN ASKED MONIKA IF SHE WOULD LIKE TO KILL A BALJA 
(DEROGATORY TERM FOR A MUSLIM).  THEY THEN LEFT THE 
WAREHOUSE AND WITNESS HEARD SHOTS AND SCREAMS.  AT 
THIS TIME, HE WAS ABLE TO LOOK UP AND OBSERVE ANOTHER 
LARGE GROUP OF PRISONERS IN AN ADJOINING WAREHOUSE. 
 
13.  (U) A SHORT TIME LATER, GORAN JELISIC RETURNED 
