MAN THEN RETURNED TO THE WAREHOUSE TO THE SAME CORNER 
FROM WHICH THEY HAD BEEN CALLED.  SUDDENLY, GORAN 
RUSHED IN, FORCED HIS PISTOL INTO THE FOURTH MAN\'S 
MOUTH AND SHOT HIM.  THE WITNESS STOOD 
THERE HELPLESSLY, WANTING ONLY TO HAVE THE NIGHTMARE 
OVER.  HE SAID HE HAD NO IDEA WHY GORAN DID NOT KILL 
HIM LIKE THE OTHERS. 
 
14.  (LOU) THE NEXT DAY, THE WITNESS WENT TO THE 
TOILET WITHOUT PERMISSION.  GORAN JELISIC ORDERED HIM 
INTO HIS OFFICE AND SCREAMED, \"SIT DOWN|\"  ADMIR 
SARAJLIC WAS ALREADY THERE BEING INTERROGATED AND WAS 
BEING BEATEN WITH STICKS AND HAMMERS.  AT THAT 
MOMENT, THE PHONE RANG, AND AFTER A BRIEF 
CONVERSATION, GORAN ASKED ADMIR HIS NAME.  ADMIR 
REPLIED AND GORAN SAID, \"YOU\'RE LUCKY.  YOU WERE 
FOURTH ON THE LIST TO BE SHOT, AND THIS BLOODY MONKEY 
WAS FIFTH, BUT YOU\'RE BOTH RELEASED.\"  THEY WERE 
TAKEN BACK TO THE SAME WAREHOUSE AND, AT TWILIGHT, 
WERE RELEASED ALONG WITH THE WITNESS\'S BROTHER.  THEY 
WENT FIRST TO THEIR AUNT\'S APARTMENT, THEN TO 
ANOTHER, AND FINALLY TO HIS OWN IN NOVO BRCKO. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
