AND IVCEV WERE WELL KNOWN FOR BURNING HOUSES.  ALSO 
DURING THIS STAY, WITNESS SAW THE REPEATED BEATINGS 
OF ONE OSMAN VATIC WHO WAS ACCUSED OF HAVING GIVEN 
50,000 DM TO THE SDA. 
17.  (LOU) IT WAS DURING THIS PERIOD OF INCARCERATION 
THAT WITNESS BEGAN WORKING IN THE DUTY-FREE ZONE 
(DFZ) OF THE PORT OF BRCKO.  THE DFZ WAS RUN BY A MAN 
WHO WORKED FOR ONE CAPTAIN DRAGAN.  TWO OF CAPTAIN 
DRAGAN\'S MEN HE KNEW WERE NESO (NFI) FROM BOR IN 
SERBIA AND CVELE (NFI) FROM LESKOVAC (BOTH STRICTLY 
PROTECT).  THEY WERE VERY GOOD TO THE PRISONERS WHO 
WORKED IN THE DFZ.  THE WITNESS AND OTHERS WORKED 
MOVING AND LOADING STOLEN GOODS FOR SHIPMENT TO 
SERBIA.  HIS FIRST JOB WAS TO MOVE AND LOAD INTO 
SERBIA-BOUND TRUCKS ALL THE STOCK FROM A PLUMBING 
SUPPLY COMPANY CALLED \"BEDRO.\"  THIS TOOK SEVERAL 
DAYS. EACH DAY THEY LOADED THREE TO FOUR LARGE 
TRUCKS. 
 
