SUBJECT: TFSROL: SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
         EYEWITNESS DESCRIBES KILLINGS AND ATROCITIES 
         IN BRCKO, LUKA, AND BATKOVIC 
 
THEM TO LEAVE ANYTHING SHARP BEHIND.  THEY THEN HAD 
TO PASS IN PAIRS BETWEEN TWO ROWS OF SERBS WHO BEAT 
THEM WITH RIFLES, CLUBS, AND STICKS.  THE THREE OR 
FOUR SERBS FROM BRCKO WHO HAD BEEN ON EACH BUS JOINED 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00919  06 OF 07  041727Z 
THE OTHER \"CETNIKS\" IN THIS \"RITUAL.\"  AS HE AND HIS 
BROTHER REACHED THE WAREHOUSE, THE WITNESS WAS 
STOPPED BY ZORAN (LNU) FROM BRCKO WHO ASKED ABOUT A 
GIRL HE HAD LIKED IN SCHOOL, AMELA OMEROVIC.  WHEN 
THE WITNESS SAID HE DID NOT KNOW HER WHEREABOUTS, 
ZORAN BEAT THE WITNESS AND HIS BROTHER ON THE HEAD 
AND IN THE KIDNEYS.  IN THE MORNING, THE NEW 
PRISONERS WERE TAKEN TO HAVE THEIR HEADS SHAVED, AND 
THEIR LIVES IN BATKOVIC BEGAN. 
 
20.  (U) FOR THE FIRST MONTH OR TWO, THERE WERE 
REGULAR BEATINGS, ESPECIALLY OF WHAT THE \"CETNIKS\" 
CALLED \"EXTREME CASES.\"  THESE INCLUDED A 14-YEAR-OLD 
BOY WHO WAS ACCUSED OF CUTTING THE EYES OUT OF SERBS; 
A TOOLMAKER ACCUSED OF MAKING KNIVES; AND A 
BODYBUILDER WHO, APPARENTLY, WAS BEATEN JUST BECAUSE 
HE WAS SO WELL BUILT.  DURING THIS TIME, ONE WOULD BE 
BEATEN JUST FOR LIFTING ONE\'S HEAD.  THE WORST 
ABUSERS WERE:  ZORAN (LNU, FROM BIJELJINA); GLIGOR 
BEGOVIC; TOJIC (LNU); NIKOLIC (LNU); MAJOR GORAN 
(LNU, FROM GORAZDE); DZEMAL ZAHIROVIC (AKA SPAJZER, A 
GYPSY FROM ZENICA); FIKRET SMAJLOVIC (AKA PIKLE OR 
PIKLIC); OMER BRODLIC (FROM BRCKO); MERSED (LNU, FROM 
BRCKO); AND ESAD BEDRIC (AKA ESO, FROM TESANJ). 
 
21.  (U) AT THE END OF AUGUST 1992, THE ICRC VISITED 
THE CAMP.  THE PRISONERS WERE TOLD TO SAY BATKOVIC 
WAS A \"COLLECTIVE CENTER\" AND THAT THEY WERE 
RECEIVING THREE MEALS PER DAY AND WERE BEING TREATED 
WELL.  THE SERBS WOULD INFILTRATE THEIR OWN PEOPLE 
AMONG THE PRISONERS, SO NO ONE DARED COMPLAIN.  THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00919  06 OF 07  041727Z 
WITNESS FAINTED DURING THE ICRC VISIT, AND AFTER THEY 
LEFT, GLIGOR AND PIKLIC BEAT HIM, KNOCKING OUT HIS 
TEETH.  THEY ALSO BEAT TWO OTHERS.  THE NEXT DAY, THE 
WITNESS WAS INCLUDED IN THE GROUP OF \"EXTREME CASES\" 
AND WAS TAKEN AWAY DURING FUTURE ICRC VISITS.  THE 
ICRC, ACCORDING TO THE WITNESS, DID NOT CHECK THE 
LISTS REGULARLY DURING THEIR TWO VISITS PER MONTH. 
IF THEY DID CHECK, THEY WERE TOLD THE MISSING WERE 
AWAY ON LABOR DETAILS AND WOULD RETURN IN THE 
EVENING.  THIS SEEMED TO SATISFY THE ICRC OFFICIALS. 
AFTER THE ICRC LEFT, THE GUARDS WOULD BEAT PEOPLE WHO 
WROTE \"CAMP\" INSTEAD OF \"CENTER\" ON THE RETURN 
ADDRESSES OF THEIR LETTERS. 
 
22.  (U) BEGINNING IN SEPTEMBER 1992, MOST OF THE 
WORST GUARDS WERE REPLACED BY GOOD PEOPLE FROM THE 
BIJELJINA AREA.  THEY OFTEN WORKED FOR LOCAL FARMERS 
OR IN BUSINESSES.  LOCAL CITIZENS GAVE THEM FOOD AND 
 
 
