TAGS: PHUM, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  TFSROL: SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
          EYEWITNESS ACCOUNT OF MURDERS, MISTREATMENT 
          OF CIVILIANS, AND OTHER ABUSES 
 
REF: (A) ZAGREB 827; (B) ZAGREB 872; (C) ZAGREB 919 
 
1.  (U) SUMMARY:  THIS IS ONE IN A SERIES OF REPORTS 
(REFTELS) OF INTERVIEWS WITH WAR CRIMES VICTIMS 
CONDUCTED IN LATE 1993 IN MAOCA, BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA, 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00930  01 OF 05  071400Z 
BY A DART/ZAGREB FIELD REP AND AN AMCIT IRC REP WHILE 
THEY WERE IN THE AREA ASSESSING HUMANITARIAN NEEDS. 
THIS REPORT NAMES VICTIMS AND, IN SOME CASES, 
PERPETRATORS AND DETAILS SPECIFIC CRIMES.  END 
SUMMARY. 
 
----------- 
THE WITNESS 
----------- 
 
2.  (LOU) HASIB BEGIC IS A BOSNIAN MUSLIM FROM THE 
BRCKO MUNICIPALITY.  HE WAS BORN MAY 9, 1946, AND WAS 
A CIVILIAN FACTORY FOREMAN AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST 
BY BOSNIAN SERB FORCES ON MAY 6, 1992.  (NOTE: THE 
WITNESS FREELY AGREED TO OPEN USE OF HIS NAME; FOR 
CONSISTENCY, HOWEVER, WE HAVE IN THE FOLLOWING REPORT 
REFERRED TO HIM AS \"THE WITNESS.\" END NOTE.) 
 
--------------------- 
THE WITNESS\'S ACCOUNT 
--------------------- 
 
3.  (U) AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST, THE WITNESS WAS 
HIDING WITH NEIGHBORS IN HIS HOME.  HE SAID SERB 
NEIGHBORS WOULD WARN THEM WHEN \"CETNIK\" SOLDIERS WERE 
NEARBY, BUT COULD NOT HELP THEM, BECAUSE THEY WERE 
AFRAID OF THE SOLDIERS COMMANDED BY ARKAN AND CESA. 
ON MAY 6, 1992, SERBIAN SOLDIERS CAME TO THE 
WITNESS\'S NEIGHBORHOOD WITH A TRUCK, SAYING THEY WERE 
TO TAKE EVERYONE TO A FACTORY CALLED \"LASER.\"  AT 
FIRST, THEY LOADED MEN, WOMEN, AND CHILDREN, BUT WHEN 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00930  01 OF 05  071400Z 
IT BECAME APPARENT THERE WAS NOT ENOUGH ROOM FOR 
EVERYONE, THEY HAD THE WOMEN AND CHILDREN GET OFF AND 
TOOK ONLY THE MEN.  THE MEN WERE TAKEN TO THE 
RESTAURANT AT THE \"LASER\" FACTORY, WHERE THERE WERE 
ALREADY ABOUT 200 MEN, WOMEN, AND CHILDREN.  SERB 
NEIGHBORS IN UNIFORM TOLD THEM THEY WOULD BE TAKEN TO 
CELIC AND BREZOVO POLJE THE NEXT DAY.  ON MAY 7, TWO 
BUSES CAME BUT TOOK ONLY THE WOMEN, CHILDREN AND 
ELDERLY.  ONE BUS DEPARTED TOWARD CELIC AND THE OTHER 
WENT IN THE DIRECTION OF BREZOVO POLJE.  THE MEN WERE 
TOLD THEY WOULD BE TRANSPORTED ON MAY 8. 
 
4.  (U) DURING THE NIGHT OF MAY 7, BETWEEN 8:00 AND 
10:00 PM, TWO RUFFIANS FROM THE BAND OF THE NOTORIOUS 
SERBIAN WAR CRIMINAL \"ARKAN\" -- GORAN (NICKNAMED 
\"ADOLF\") AND \"CUPO\" (SO-CALLED BECAUSE OF HIS LONG 
HAIR) -- TOGETHER WITH AN UNNAMED SERB FROM BRCKO, 
CAME INTO THE RESTAURANT.  GORAN ORDERED THE SERB 
FROM BRCKO TO POINT HIS RIFLE AT THE PRISONERS AND 
 
 
