THEN BEGAN SWEARING AND HITTING THE TABLE WITH A 
STICK.  THE THREE THEN TOOK FOUR PRISONERS OUTSIDE, 
BEAT THEM SEVERELY, AND STOLE THEIR VALUABLES.  ONE 
OF THOSE BEATEN WAS THE WITNESS\'S NEIGHBOR FROM 
BRCKO, OSMAN ZAHIROVIC.  AFTER ABOUT 30 MINUTES, THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00930  02 OF 05  071401Z 
SERBS LEFT. 
 
5.  (U) ON MAY 8, THE MEN WERE GIVEN THE CHOICE OF 
GOING TO CELIC OR BREZOVO POLJE.  MOST CHOSE CELIC, 
SINCE IT WAS IN FREE TERRITORY.  THE BUS CAME TWICE. 
THE WITNESS MANAGED TO BOARD THE BUS FOR THE SECOND 
TRIP, BUT BECAME WORRIED WHEN THEY HEADED INTO BRCKO, 
INSTEAD OF TOWARD CELIC.  THE BUSES TOOK THEM TO THE 
UKA WAREHOUSE AREA NEAR THE BRIDGE OVER THE SAVA 
RIVER.  THE WITNESS NOTICED ALL THE WINDOWS IN THE 
WAREHOUSES HAD BEEN BLOWN OUT, HE ASSUMED AS A RESULT 
OF DEMOLITION OF THE BRIDGE.  AS THE DETAINEES GOT 
OFF THE BUS, THE MEN WERE ORDERED TO THROW ALL 
PERSONAL DOCUMENTS INTO A LARGE CRATE AT THE 
ENTRANCE.  THE WITNESS SAW THREE OR FOUR SERB 
SOLDIERS AND A SERB GIRL. THE GIRL SAID SHE HAD BEEN 
SHOT IN THE CHEST BY MUSLIMS, ALTHOUGH SHE LOOKED 
PERFECTLY HEALTHY.  THERE WERE ALREADY 600 TO 700 
PRISONERS IN THE WAREHOUSES. 
 
6.  (U) ABOUT TWO HOURS LATER, GORAN ENTERED WITH 
DOCUMENTS IN HIS HAND AND ANNOUNCED, \"EVERYONE WHOSE 
NAME I READ NOW WILL BE TAKEN TO BE SHOT.\"  HE THEN 
READ ABOUT 150 NAMES, ABOUT HALF OF THOSE IN THE 
WAREHOUSE.  THEN, LAUGHING, HE ANNOUNCED THEY WERE 
NOT TO BE SHOT BUT WERE TO BE SENT HOME.  THOSE WHOSE 
NAMES HE READ WERE THEN RELEASED. 
 
7.  (U) A SHORT TIME LATER, GORAN DISCOVERED THE 
IDENTIFICATION CARDS OF TWO YOUNG MEN WHO WERE NOT 
FROM THE BRCKO AREA.  HE ASKED THEM WHY THEY WERE IN 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00930  02 OF 05  071401Z 
BRCKO, AND THEY REPLIED THAT THEY WERE VISITING 
FRIENDS.  GORAN SHOUTED, \"YOU CAME TO FIGHT AGAINST 
US.\"  HE TOOK THE TWO MEN OUTSIDE AND SHOT THEM. 
 
8.  (U) ON THE FOURTH DAY, THE WITNESS WAS INCLUDED 
IN A GROUP THAT WAS TO BE RELEASED, BUT THE SOLDIERS 
SAID THEY HAD RUN OUT OF THE PROPER FORMS, SO HE WAS 
MOVED TO ANOTHER WAREHOUSE AT LUKA. 
 
9.  (U) THE WITNESS SAID THAT BETWEEN MAY 8-18 
DETAINEES, MOSTLY YOUNGER MEN, WERE SELECTED AT 
RANDOM, LINED UP AGAINST A WALL AND SHOT.  ON MAY 9, 
GORAN (\"ADOLF\") BROUGHT IN A VERY FAT MAN, ALLEGEDLY 
A CROAT CAPTURED IN BRCKO.  THE MAN\'S RIGHT EAR HAD 
BEEN CUT OFF, HE WAS CARRYING IT IN HIS RIGHT HAND. 
HE HAD A HANDKERCHIEF IN HIS LEFT HAND WITH WHICH HE 
WAS WIPING BLOOD OFF HIS HEAD.  GORAN ORDERED THE MAN 
TO SQUAT AND ASKED THE PRISONERS WHICH OF THEM WAS 
WILLING TO KILL HIM, PROFFERING A LARGE PISTOL.  NO 
 
 
