ONE ACCEPTED.  THE MAN BEGAN BEGGING THE PRISONERS TO 
KILL HIM SAYING, \"DON\'T LET THE \'CETNIKS\' KILL ME.\" 
ALL REFUSED.  CALLING THEM ALL COWARDS, GORAN STARTED 
PUSHING THE FAT MAN OUT THE DOOR.  A SERB SOLDIER AT 
THE DOOR HIT THE MAN IN THE BACK WITH A DULL SWORD 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00930  03 OF 05  071402Z 
AND HE FELL.  NEXT, THE WITNESS HEARD TWO SHOTS, 
WHEREAFTER THE \"CETNIKS ASKED FOR FOUR VOLUNTEERS TO 
REMOVE THE BODY. 
- 
10.  (U) THE CORPSES OF MURDERED DETAINEES WERE TAKEN 
TO TWO LOCATIONS IN LUKA, THE WITNESS SAID.  ONE WAS 
A SHED NEAR THE ENTRANCE TO THE TOWN.  TRUCKS WOULD 
COME TO REMOVE THESE BODIES DURING THE NIGHT.  THE 
WITNESS HIMSELF CARRIED TWO BODIES TO THIS SHED ON 
MAY 10 OR 11, HELPED BY HIS NEIGHBOR, EDHEM RIBIC. 
DETAINEE WORKING PARTIES WERE ALWAYS ACCOMPANIED BY 
SERB GUARDS.  THERE WERE ALREADY FIVE OR SIX BODIES 
IN THE SHED, HE SAID.  THE OTHER PLACE WAS ALONG THE 
RAILWAY TRACK NEAR THE WAREHOUSES.  BODIES COLLECTED 
THERE WERE LATER THROWN INTO THE SAVA RIVER.  THE 
WITNESS HELPED THREE OTHER PRISONERS CARRY ONE BODY 
TO THE SECOND COLLECTION POINT, ALSO ON MAY 10 OR 
11.  THERE WERE ALREADY TWO BODIES THERE.  ONE WAS 
STILL ALIVE AND GROANING.  THE OTHER THREE DETAINEES 
WERE SENT BACK TO THE WAREHOUSE, BUT THE WITNESS WAS 
KEPT BEHIND WITH A BUCKET TO CLEAN UP THE BLOOD. 
WHILE HE WAS DOING THIS,  ANOTHER BODY WAS CARRIED IN 
AND HE WAS ORDERED TO CLEAN UP THE BLOOD FROM THAT 
ONE AS WELL. 
 
11.  (U) ONE NIGHT THE SOLDIERS PAIRED OFF THE 
YOUNGER AND OLDER MEN AND FORCED THEM TO PUNCH EACH 
OTHER.  A SERB SOLDIER STOOD BEHIND EACH PRISONER TO 
MAKE SURE THEY PUNCHED HARD.  WHEN IT BECAME APPARENT 
THEY WOULD BE BEATEN NO MATTER WHAT THEY DID, THE 
WITNESS REFUSED TO PUNCH HARD.  EVENTUALLY, HE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00930  03 OF 05  071402Z 
FAINTED.  HE WAS LATER TOLD THIS WENT ON FOR 
ONE-AND-A-HALF HOURS. 
 
12.  (U) AT NIGHT \"SOLDIERS\" FROM ARKAN\'S AND CESA\'S 
GROUPS WOULD REGULARLY ENTER THE WAREHOUSE, AND BY 
THE GLARE OF AUTOMOBILE HEADLIGHTS WOULD SELECT AND 
BEAT MEN.  THE VICTIMS WERE TAKEN OUT IN GROUPS; 
LATER THEY WOULD CALL FOR FOUR MEN TO CARRY THE 
BODIES AWAY.  OFTEN ONLY THRE 
E OF THE FOUR 
\"VOLUNTEERS\" WOULD RETURN, HE SAID, THE OTHER HAVING 
BEEN KILLED. 
 
13.  (U) ON MAY 12, \"ADOLF\" ASKED FOR A VOLUNTEER TO 
CLEAN HIS OFFICE.  THE WITNESS VOLUNTEERED.  HE 
CLEANED UP THE REMAINS OF A MEAL AND WAS ABOUT TO 
LEAVE WHEN THE SERB BROUGHT TWO YOUNG MEN TO THE 
FRONT (OUTSIDE) OF THE OFFICE.  HE HAD ONE LIE DOWN 
WITH HIS HEAD OVER THE DRAIN PIPE;  PLACING HIS FOOT 
 
 
