ON THE MAN\'S NECK, GORAN SHOT HIM TWICE IN THE HEAD. 
THEN HE DID THE SAME WITH THE SECOND.  GORAN THEN 
SAID TO THE WITNESS, \"WE WON\'T KILL YOU.  GO BACK TO 
THE WAREHOUSE.\"  THE WITNESS SAID \"ADOLF\" ALSO TOLD 
HIM THAT HE HAD KILLED 88 PEOPLE, AND \"PLANNED TO 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00930  04 OF 05  071402Z 
KILL MORE.\"  UNTIL MAY 18, GORIC SAID, THE \"CETNIKS\" 
WOULD ALWAYS CLAIM THAT THOSE WHO WERE SUMMARILY 
EXECUTED OR KILLED BY THESE BEATINGS HAD BEEN \"SHOT 
BY SNIPERS.\" 
 
14. (LOU) THE WITNESS CREDITS ONE SERB, A \"MAJOR 
VOJKAN\" (STRICTLY PROTECT), WITH SAVING MANY 
PRISONERS\' LIVES AT THE LUKA WAREHOUSE.  THIS SERB 
OFFICER TOLD THE PRISONERS HE FELT SORRY FOR THE 
MUSLIMS AND CROATS AND WOULD FIGHT TO TRY TO PROTECT 
THEM AND \"EVEN DIE WITH THEM IF NECESSARY.\"  WHENEVER 
HE WAS IN CHARGE, NO ONE FROM ARKAN OR CESA\'S GROUPS 
WAS ALLOWED TO ENTER THE WAREHOUSE.  THIS OFFICER WAS 
LATER REMOVED FROM BEING IN CHARGE, BUT TOLD THE 
PRISONERS HE WOULD CONTINUE TO CHECK ON THEM.  HE 
DID, INDEED, COME TO VISIT EVERY THREE TO FOUR DAYS. 
 
15.  (U) ON MAY 18, MAJOR VOJKAN, GORAN (\"ADOLF\") AND 
A \"CAPTAIN WITH BLACK HAIR\" ASSEMBLED THE WAREHOUSE 
DETAINEES AND READ THEM A DECREE.  IT SAID THAT 
CROATIA AND THE WORLD HAD HEARD WHAT WAS GOING ON AT 
LUKA AND THAT THERE WOULD BE NO MORE KILLINGS.  THE 
DETAINEES WOULD, HOWEVER, CONTINUE TO BE BEATEN.  FOR 
THE REST OF THE TIME THE WITNESS WAS AT LUKA, THERE 
WERE NO MORE KILLINGS.  HE WORKED MOST DAYS, 
PRIMARILY CLEANING BARRACKS, APARTMENTS, AND HOSPITAL 
ROOMS.  CERTAIN INDIVIDUALS WERE STILL REGULARLY 
BEATEN AT NIGHT. 
 
16.  (LOU) ON JUNE 23, THE WITNESS WAS TAKEN FROM 
LUKA BY AN ETHNIC CROAT NAMED IVICA STANJEC (STRICTLY 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00930  04 OF 05  071402Z 
PROTECT), THE CANTEEN MANAGER AT HIS FACTORY 
\"BIMAL.\"  THIS MAN\'S WIFE WAS A SERB, SO HE WAS 
ALLOWED TO GO HOME AND TO TAKE ONE OLDER PRISONER 
WITH HIM.  HE TOOK THE WITNESS TO HIS APARTMENT IN 
THE \"S\" SETTLEMENT.  AFTER 10 OR 12 DAYS, THE WITNESS 
AND A FRIEND WERE ABLE TO ARRANGE SHELTER WITH 
ANOTHER FRIEND IN GRCICA WHERE THEY REMAINED UNTIL 
JULY 14. 
 
17.  (U) ON JULY 14, TWO LOCAL SERB SOLDIERS CAME TO 
THE WITNESS\'S FRIEND\'S HOUSE AND TOLD THE MEN TO GET 
ON A BUS.  THEY WERE TOLD NOT TO TAKE ANYTHING, 
BECAUSE THEY WOULD \"BE COMING BACK IN 15 MINUTES.\" 
THERE WERE ONLY CROAT AND MUSLIM MEN ON THE BUS AND, 
ONCE ON BOARD, THEY WERE TOLD THEY WERE BEING TAKEN 
TO WORK AT THE \"INTERPLET\" CLOTHING FACTORY IN 
BIJELJINA.  WHEN THE BUSES GOT TO BIJELJINA, HOWEVER, 
THEY KEPT ON GOING TO BATKOVIC. 
 
 
 
