CROAT, WAS BROUGHT INTO THE WAREHOUSE WITH HIS SEVERED 
EARS IN HIS HANDS.  HIS CAPTORS HUMILIATED HIM FOR FOUR 
HOURS, FORCING HIM TO CRAWL AROUND THE WAREHOUSE UNTIL HE 
BEGGED THE OTHER PRISONERS TO KILL HIM.  EVENTUALLY, HE 
WAS SHOT TO DEATH BY GORAN JELISIC (AKA ADOLF).  GORAN 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00941  02 OF 03  081033Z 
CALLED CUMUROVIC BY NAME AND WHEN CUMUROVIC STEPPED 
FORWARD, GORAN STABBED HIM IN THE HEART WITH A KNIFE. 
 
6.  (U) THE WITNESS SAW OTHERS MURDERED DURING HIS TIME 
AT LUKA.  WHEN A 17-YEAR-OLD MALE WHOSE NAME HE THINKS 
WAS FADIL DENJAGI 
C REFUSED TO ADMIT HE POSSESSED WEAPONS, 
RANKO CESIC TOOK HIM OVER TO A WATER DRAIN AND SHOT HIM 
IN THE HEAD.  TWO YOUNG MEN FROM JANGA, NEAR BIJELJINA, 
WERE CALLED FORWARD BY GORAN AND ENVER (LNU).  THEIR 
FAMILY NAME WAS \"SOMETHING LIKE PETROVIC.\"  THEIR FATHER 
WAS ALBANIAN AND THEIR MOTHER CROAT.  THEY WERE BADLY 
BEATEN WITH BILLY CLUBS DURING THE NIGHT AND DRAGGED OUT 
AND SHOT IN THE MORNING.  GORAN AND ENVER EACH KILLED 
ONE.  THE BODIES WERE THROWN INTO THE SAVA RIVER. 
7.  (U) THE WITNESS FREQUENTLY PASSED THE BIMEX SWINE 
BREEDING FARM ON HIS WAY TO FARMS WHERE HE PERFORMED 
FORCED LABOR.  THERE WERE THREE LARGE PITS TO WHICH 
BODIES WERE TAKEN IN A TAM TRUCK WITH LICENSE NUMBER 
BC-519-15, DRIVEN BY ONE ACO STEVANOVIC.  THE PITS WERE 
ON THE WAY FROM BRCKO TO THE BIMEX FARM THREE KILOMETERS 
EAST OF BRCKO.  THE WITNESS GAVE THE FOLLOWING 
INSTRUCTIONS FOR LOCATING THE SITE:  DESCEND A HILL 
TOWARD A BROOK AND STOP JUST BEFORE CROSSING THE BRIDGE. 
ON THE RIGHT SIDE, OUTSIDE THE FENCED AREA OF THE FARM 
AND ALONGSIDE THE BROOK, IS THE SITE.  JUST BEYOND THE 
SITE IS A GAS STATION THAT USED TO BE OWNED BY A MAN 
NAMED MUSTRAFOVIC.  THE WITNESS SAID THE PITS WERE AT 
LEAST 15 METERS LONG. 
 
8.  (LOU) THE WITNESS WAS TAKEN OUT OF LUKA ON JUNE 12 BY 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00941  02 OF 03  081033Z 
A SERB FRIEND AND NEIGHBOR NAMED MIODRAG MITROVIC 
(STRICTLY PROTECT).  HIS FRIEND TOOK HIM INTO HIS OWN 
HOME FOR THE NIGHT AND TOLD HIM HE WAS ASTONISHED BY WHAT 
WAS HAPPENING. 
 
9.  (U) FOR THE NEXT YEAR, THE WITNESS WORKED AT BIMEX 
AND SURROUNDING FARMS DOING THE WORST JOBS AND BEING 
BEATEN AND MISTREATED BY TWO \"CETNIKS,\" ZORAN MITRIC AND 
TOSO VUJIC. 
 
10.  (LOU) THE WITNESS WAS RELEASED ON JULY 18, 1993.  HE 
CREDITS TWO SERB FRIENDS WHO WERE BIMEX WORKERS, SRETEN 
VAJIC AND LAZO DODIC (BOTH STRICTLY PROTECT), FOR 
ARRANGING HIS RELEASE.  HE ALSO SAID MAKSO SIMEUNOVIC 
(STRICTLY PROTECT), THE PRESIDENT OF THE SERBIAN 
COMMISSION FOR EXCHANGE, HELPED GAIN HIS FREEDOM. 
 
11.  (LOU) THE WITNESS IS CONCERNED FOR HIS TWO UNCLES 
AND THEIR THREE SONS WHO HE SAYS WERE STILL IN BRCKO AS 
 
 
