TAGS: PHUM, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, PREL, MOPS, HR, BK, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  TFSROL: SEVERE HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES IN B-H: 
          EYEWITNESS DETAILS MURDER, BEATINGS IN LUKA AND 
          BATKOVIC 
 
REF: (A) ZAGREB 827; (B) ZAGREB 872; (C) ZAGREB 919; 
(D) ZAGREB 930; (E) ZAGREB 941 
 
1.  (U) SUMMARY:  THIS IS ONE OF A SERIES OF REPORTS OF 
INTERVIEWS (REFTELS) WITH WAR CRIMES VICTIMS CONDUCTED IN 
LATE 1993 IN MAOCA, BOSNIA-HERCEGOVINA, BY A DART/ZAGREB 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00945  01 OF 03  081147Z 
FIELD REP AND AN AMCIT IRC REP WHILE THEY WERE IN THE 
AREA ASSESSING HUMANITARIAN NEEDS.  THIS REPORT NAMES 
VICTIMS AND, IN SOME CASES, PERPETRATORS AND DETAILS OF 
SPECIFIC CRIMES.  END SUMMARY. 
 
----------- 
THE WITNESS 
----------- 
 
2.  (LOU) AMIR DIDIC (STRICTLY PROTECT), HEREAFTER 
REFERRED TO AS THE WITNESS, IS A BOSNIAN MUSLIM FROM 
POLANKA, A VILLAGE SOUTHWEST OF BRCKO.  HE WAS BORN MAY 
1, 1967.  HE WAS A CIVILIAN AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST BY 
BOSNIAN SERB FORCES ON MAY 19, 1992. 
 
--------------------- 
THE WITNESS\'S ACCOUNT 
--------------------- 
 
3. (U) AT THE TIME OF HIS ARREST, THE WITNESS WAS DRIVING 
WITH HIS AUNT AND A FRIEND.  HE AND HIS FRIEND WERE TAKEN 
TO THE POLICE STATION IN BRCKO, WHERE THEY WAITED ONE 
HOUR BEFORE BEING TAKEN WITH 15 OTHER MEN TO A WAREHOUSE 
COMPLEX KNOWN AS LUKA WHICH WAS BEING USED AS A PRISON 
CAMP.  WHEN THEY ARRIVED, THEY WERE PUT IN A WAREHOUSE 
WITH 100-150 OTHER PRISONERS WHO WERE SINGING \"CETNIK\" 
SONGS.  THEY WERE SEARCHED, AND THEIR VALUABLES WERE 
TAKEN.  THEY WERE TAKEN ONE BY ONE FOR INTERROGATION BY 
POLICE INSPECTORS.  THIS INITIAL INTERROGATION WAS 
RELATIVELY NORMAL.  BECAUSE WITNESS WAS FROM THE FREE 
TERRITORY, HE WAS ASKED ABOUT THE ARMY OF 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00945  01 OF 03  081147Z 
BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA.  AFTERWARDS, HE WAS RETURNED TO THE 
WAREHOUSE. 
 
4.  (U) AFTER ALL 15 MEN HAD BEEN QUESTIONED, BOSNIAN 
SERBS CAME INTO THE WAREHOUSE AND BEGAN BEATING THEM. 
THESE (SERBS) INCLUDED GORAN JELISIC FROM BIJELJINA, 
MONIKA (LNU) FROM BRCKO, RANKO (LNU) FROM BRCKO, IVAN 
(LNU) FROM BIJELJINA, AND SEVERAL OTHERS FROM BIJELJINA. 
ACCORDING TO THE WITNESS, THE FOUR NAMED ABOVE DID MOST 
OF THE KILLING IN LUKA.  HE DESCRIBED RANKO AS TALL AND 
MUSCULAR, WITH BLACK HAIR; AND MONIKA AS 18 OR 19 YEARS 
OLD, SHORT, NICE-LOOKING, WITH BLACK SHOULDER-LENGTH 
HAIR.  (NOTE: THE BRCKO MUNICIPALITY WAR CRIMES 
COMMISSION IN MAOCA HAS PHOTOS OF MONIKA AND INFORMATION 
THAT SHE OPENED A BOUTIQUE CALLED \"MONIKA\" IN BIJELJINA 
AFTER MARRYING GORAN JELISIC.  END NOTE.) 
 
5.  (U) AFTER BEATING THE PRISONERS FOR ABOUT AN HOUR, 
THE SERBS LEFT THE WAREHOUSE.  BY THEN IT WAS GETTING 
 
 
