PAGE 02        ZAGREB  01327  03 OF 03  011808Z 
         CROATIA 
 
OFFICIALS OF TWO SMALL OPPOSITION PARTIES) THAT 
LED TO CHARGES OF STIFLING THE FREE EXPRESSION 
OF OPPOSITION VIEWS. 
 
14.  CROATIA SHOWS A STRONG RESPECT, IN LETTER 
AND IN PRACTICE, FOR INDIVIDUAL RIGHTS, AND 
INCREASING INTERCHANGE WITH WESTERN EUROPEAN 
SOCIE 
TIES HAS BROUGHT A GREATER AWARENESS OF 
GOVERNMENT OBLIGATIONS IN THIS REGARD.  THE 
GOVERNMENT USUALLY TAKES ACTION TO INVESTIGATE 
AND/OR PROSECUTE SERIOUS ABUSES, BUT RESPONSE 
CAN BE SLOW AND INEFFECTIVE.  MINORITIES IN 
CROATIA -- IN PARTICULAR THE ROUGHLY 11 PERCENT . 
SERB MINORITY -- HAVE BEEN SUBJECT, AGAIN IN 
1993, TO CRIMES OF VIOLENCE COMMITTED BY 
NATIONALIST EXTREMISTS.  SERBIAN REPRESENTATIVES 
ALSO COMPLAIN THAT THEY SUFFER DISCRIMINATION 
AND HARASSMENT IN A WIDE VARIETY OF AREAS, FROM 
ABNORMAL SLOWNESS IN THE ISSUANCE OF GOVERNMENT 
DOCUMENTS TO DISCRIMINATION IN HIRING AND FIRING. 
 
15.  FREEDOM OF SPEECH AND PRESS REMAINS AN 
ISSUE.  THE GOVERNMENT EXERCISES A STRONG 
INFLUENCE OVER MOST MEDIA, BUT THE PRESS 
NEVERTHELESS WILL AND DOES PRINT MATERIAL 
CRITICAL OF THE GOVERNMENT AND ITS LEADERS. 
CRITICS HAVE POINTED OUT THAT THE PRACTICE OF 
ALLOWING MEMBERS OF THE SABOR TO REMAIN IN 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01327  03 OF 03  011808Z 
CHARGE OF KEY PRINT AND ELECTRONIC MEDIA IS AN 
INVITATION TO ABUSE; THE GOVERNMENT HAS DONE 
NOTHING TO CORRECT THE PROBLEM. 
 
16.  CROATIA HAS AN ORGANIZED AND EFFECTIVE 
JUDICIAL SYSTEM, THAT OPERATES TO AN ADEQUATELY 
FAIR AND REASONABLE STANDARD, ALTHOUGH IT IS NOT 
YET FREE OF ETHNIC BIAS OR POLITICAL INFLUENCE. 
IN MANY AREAS, WORK REMAINS TO BE DONE IN 
CREATING LAWS AND PROCEDURAL SAFEGUARDS TO 
ACCORD WITH MORE GENERAL PRONOUNCEMENTS 
CONTAINED IN THE CONSTITUTION.  WESTERN 
COUNTRIES, INCLUDING THE UNITED STATES, ARE 
DEVELOPING TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS IN THE 
AREA OF JUDICIAL REFORM. 
GALBRAITH 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
