DELIVERIES THROUGHOUT B-H DURING MARCH.  WFP FOOD 
DELIVERIES, COMBINED WITH HUMANITARIAN AID 
CONVOYS FROM UNHCR, ICRC, AND NGOS TOTALLED OVER 
42,800 MT OF FOOD AID TO THE FOLLOWING AREAS OF 
B-H: 3,243 MT TO BIHAC; 4,236 MT TO BANJA LUKA; 
16,201 MT TO CENTRAL B-H; 6,303 MT TO EASTER B-H; 
4,362 MT TO SOUTHERN B-H; AND 8,471 MT TO 
SARAJEVO.  THE AMOUNT OF SUPPLIES DELIVERED TO 
CENTRAL B-H WAS PARTICULARLY HIGH DUE TO AN 
INCREASE IN ROUTES AND GREATER FACILITY IN 
PASSING THROUGH CHECKPOINTS IN THAT AREA.  (NOTE: 
IN FEB 1994, UNHCR DELIVERED 22,475 MT, AND IN 
JAN 1994, 30,332 MT.  THE MONTHLY AVERAGE FOR 
1993 WAS 22,000 MT.  UNHCR HAS SET A MONTHLY 
 
 
