TARGET OF 33,000 MT FOR THE NEXT SIX MONTHS.) 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01372  02 OF 08  061706Z 
4.  ALTHOUGH WFP B-H PROGRAM OFFICER REPORTED AN 
INCREASE IN FOOD DELIVERIES, HE EMPHASIZED THAT 
THE HUMANITARIAN SITUATION IS STILL VERY MUCH 
DEPENDENT ON THE PRECARIOUS MILITARY AND 
POLITICAL SITUATION.  CONVOYS CAN BE OBSTRUCTED 
AND THEIR CONTENTS CONFISCATED AT ANY TIME.  WFP 
STRONGLY WARNED AGAINST UNDUE OPTIMISM AMONG THE 
INTERNATIONAL HUMANITARIAN COMMUNITY AT THIS 
TIME. 
 
--------------------------------------------- ---- 
UNHCR RESUMES CONVOYS THROUGH SERB-HELD TERRITORY 
---------------------------- 
--------------------- 
 
5.  AFTER A TWO-DAY SUSPENSION OF HUMANITARIAN 
CONVOYS THROUGH BOSNIAN SERB-HELD TERRITORY DUE 
TO SECURITY PROBLEMS, UNHCR RESUMED SENDING 
CONVOYS THROUGH BSA TERRITORY ON APRIL 2.  (SEE 
DART SITREP 69 FOR DETAILS.)  ON APRIL 2, 2 UNHCR 
CONVOYS FROM BELGRADE DELIVERED 124 MT OF FOOD 
AND FUEL TO SARAJEVO VIA ZVORNIK, CAPARDE, 
VLASENICA, AND PALE.  ALSO ON APRIL 2, 1 UNHCR 
CONVOY DELIVERED 80 MT WHEAT FLOUR FROM BELGRADE 
TO TUZLA VIA ZVORNIK.  ON APRIL 3, 4 CONVOYS FROM 
BELGRADE TRAVELLED THROUGH BSA-HELD TERRITORY: 2 
TO TUZLA, VIA ZVORNIK; AND 2 TO SREBRENICA, VIA 
ZVORNIK AND BRATUNAC.  ON APRIL 4, 2 CONVOYS FROM 
BELGRADE DELIVERED 127 MT OF WHEAT FLOUR AND FUEL 
TO TUZLA VIA ZVORNIK.  ON APRIL 5, 1 CONVOY FROM 
BELGRADE DELIVERED 115 MT OF WHEAT FLOUR TO TUZLA 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01372  02 OF 08  061706Z 
VIA ZVORNIK. 
 
---------------------------------------- 
CONVOYS TO SELECTED AREAS, MARCH 25 - 31 
---------------------------------------- 
 
6.  UNHCR/ZAGREB REPORTED THE FOLLOWING CONVOY 
INFORMATION FOR THE WEEK OF MARCH 25 - 31.  WHEN 
TWO FIGURES ARE GIVEN FOR THE NUMBER OF CONVOYS, 
THE FIRST NUMBER DENOTES NUMBER ACCOMPLISHED AND 
THE SECOND INDICATES CONVOYS ATTEMPTED. 
UNSUCCESSFUL CONVOYS WERE DENIED PASSAGE OR 
OTHERWISE OBSTRUCTED.  THE FOURTH COLUMN DENOTES 
THE ETHNIC GROUP IN CONTROL OF THE AREA: M - 
MUSLIM, S - SERB, C - CROAT.  THE NUMBERS FOR 
METRIC TONNAGES INDICATE PRIMARY DISTRIBUTION 
FIGURES AND DO NOT PORTRAY SECONDARY (LOCAL) 
DISTRIBUTION. 
 
