CONVOY INCIDENTS, APRIL 1 - 5 
----------------------------- 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01372  04 OF 08  061707Z 
 
7.  ON APRIL 1, UNHCR/ZAGREB REPORTED 1 CANCELLED 
CONVOY TO BANJA LUKA, CARRYING 4 MT OF FUEL VIA 
BOSANSKA GRADISKA, BECAUSE THERE WAS NO NEED OF 
FUEL.  UNHCR/ZENICA REPORTED 2 CANCELLED CONVOYS, 
1 EACH TO KACUNI AND KAKANJ, DUE TO MECHANICAL 
PROBLEMS WITH THE VEHICLES. 
 
8.  ON APRIL 2, UNHCR/ZAGREB REPORTED 2 CANCELLED 
CONVOYS, 1 TO BANJA LUKA AND 1 TO VELIKA KLADUSA, 
CARRYING A TOTAL OF 347 MT OF WHEAT FLOUR, BEANS, 
AND OIL, BECAUSE THE CONVOY TEAMS RETURNED LATE 
FROM THEIR PREVIOUS MISSIONS. 
- 
9.  ON APRIL 3, UNHCR DID NOT REPORT ANY CONVOY 
INCIDENTS OR CANCELLATIONS. 
 
10.  ON APRIL 4, UNHCR/BELGRADE REPORTED THAT 2 
CONVOYS TO GORAZDE, SCHEDULED TO CARRY A TOTAL OF 
112 MT OF FUEL AND MIXED FOOD ITEMS, VIA UZICE, 
VISEGRAD, KOTROMAN, DOBRON, AND MEDJEDJA, WERE 
OBSTRUCTED BECAUSE CLEARANCE FOR THE ESCORT 
VEHICLE WAS NOT GRANTED BY BSA AUTHORITIES IN 
BELGRADE.  UNHCR/METKOVIC REPORTED THAT TWO 
CONVOYS TO SARAJEVO, CARRYING A TOTAL OF 170 MT 
OF MIXED FOOD ITEMS VIA STOLAC, GACKO, FOCA, AND 
PALE, WERE OBSTRUCTED WHEN THE BSA DID NOT 
PROVIDE CLEARANCE.  UNHCR/ZENICA ALSO REPORTED 
THAT 1 CONVOY TO SARAJEVO, CARRYING 70 MT OF FOOD 
VIA KISELJAK, WAS OBSTRUCTED WHEN THE BSA DID NOT 
PROVIDE IT WITH THE NECESSARY CLEARANCE.  IN 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01372  04 OF 08  061707Z 
ADDITION, UNHCR/ZENICA REPORTED THAT 1 CONVOY TO 
VARES WAS CANCELLED BECAUSE THE CONVOY TEAM HAD 
NOT RETURNED FROM ITS PREVIOUS MISSION. 
 
11. ON APRIL 5, UNHCR/BELGRADE REPORTED THAT 1 
CONVOY TO GORAZDE WAS OBSTRUCTED BECAUSE SERBIAN 
AUTHORITIES IN BELGRADE DENIED CLEARANCE TO THE 
ESCORT VEHICLES.  THE CONVOY WAS CARRYING 130 MT 
OF MIXED FOOD ITEMS, VIA UZICE, VISEGRAD, 
KOTROMAN, DOBRUN, AND MEDJEDJA TO GORAZDE. 
 
