SUBJECT: TFSROL:  DART FIELD OFFICER\'S VISIT WITH 
        BOSNIAN GOVERNMENT\'S REPRESENTATIVE IN 
        ZENICA 
 
AN INTEREST IN THE COAL MINES IN CENTRAL BOSNIA. 
ACCORDING TO THE MINISTER, THE BRITISH SEEM TO BE 
INTERESTED IN FINDING PLACES TO DEPOSIT 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01634  04 OF 04  251058Z 
RADIOACTIVE MATERIAL AND OTHER HAZARDOUS WASTE. 
THEY WERE ESPECIALLY INTERESTED IN THE ABANDONED 
TUNNELS OF SOME OF THE OLDER MINES WHERE THE COAL 
HAD PLAYED OUT.  THE FRENCH, HE SAID, WERE 
INTERESTED IN THE GAS IN THE MINES.  IT WASN\'T 
CLEAR WHETHER THEY WERE INTERESTED IN NATURAL GAS 
DEPOSITS, OR IN THE COAL GASIFICATION PROCESS. 
NO ONE HAS YET SHOWN AN INTEREST IN OIL 
EXPLORATION, THE MINISTER SAID. 
- 
-------------------------- 
CROATS AND SERBS IN ZENICA 
-------------------------- 
 
11.  THE MINISTER SAID THAT ALTHOUGH MOST OF THE 
CROATIAN POLITICAL LEADERS HAVE LEFT, THE 
CROATIANS WHO REMAIN IN ZENICA ARE WELL- 
REPRESEN 
TED BY THEIR CHURCH LEADERS AND 
INTELLECTUALS IN THE COMMUNITY.  THERE WERE 
22,000 CROATS IN THE ZENICA REGION BEFORE THE 
WAR.  NOW THERE ARE 15,000.  TWENTY PER CENT OF 
THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT POSITIONS ARE DIVIDED 
EQUALLY BETWEEN THE SERB AND CROATIAN CITIZENS OF 
THE REGION.  THERE WERE 20,000 SERBS IN THE 
ZENICA REGION BEFORE THE WAR.  BETWEEN 10,000 AND 
15,000 REMAIN.   THE LEADER OF THE LOCAL ORTHODOX 
CHURCH IS THEIR SPOKESMAN. 
 
---------- 
CONCLUSION 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01634  04 OF 04  251058Z 
---------- 
 
12.  THIS VERY INFORMATIVE MEETING SHOWED THE 
MINISTER OF ZENICA TO BE A SOPHISTICATED, 
INTELLIGENT MAN WITH A FULL PLATE OF PROBLEMS AND 
PLANS TO HELP REBUILD HIS COUNTRY.  THE RETURN TO 
NORMALIZATION WILL BE A DIFFICULT ROAD, BUT THE 
BOSNIAN GOVERNMENT APPEARS TO BE LOOKING BEYOND 
IMMEDIATE DIFFICULTIES AND FORMULATING PLANS FOR 
LONG-TERM REDEVELOPMENT. 
 
GALBRATIH 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
 
