8.  RESOURCE CONSTRAINTS 
------------------------ 
 
WITH THE ARRIVAL IN MAY OF A NEW POL/ECON SECTION CHIEF 
AND THE FILLING IN AUGUST OF A NEW POLITICAL REPORTING 
OFFICER JOB, OUR RESOURCE PICTURE HAS IMPROVED 
SOMEWHAT.  NEVERTHELESS, THE CONTINUED THREAT OF WAR, 
AND THE MISSION\'S HIGH-PRIORITY ROLE IN DEVELOPING AND 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02605  02 OF 02  081702Z 
EXECUTING POLICY FOR THE \"RSK\"-GOC NEGOTIATIONS OVER 
REINTEGRATION OF THE UNPA ZONES, PLACE CONSIDERABLE NEW 
DEMANDS ON THE RESOURCES WE HAVE.  THE POSSIBILITY OF A 
SHORT-TERM NEW POSITION FOCUSED SPECIFICALLY ON HUMAN 
RIGHTS, WHICH IS STILL PENDING, IS URGENTLY NEEDED TO 
ADD REPORTING FLEXIBILITY.  OVERALL, THE VOLUME AND 
QUALITY OF OUR REPORTING OF \"NORMAL\" EVENTS SUCH AS 
DOMESTIC POLITICS AND FOREIGN POLICY WILL CONTINUE TO 
BE AFFECTED IN UNPREDICTABLE WAYS BY EXOGENOUS 
DEVELOPMENTS SUCH AS PROGRESS IN THE WAR IN BOSNIA OR 
FURTHER \"RSK\"-GOC HOSTILITIES, AND BY THE NUMBER OF 
VISITORS. 
 
