-- \"SERBIAN KRAJINA\": THE PLAN\'S USE OF THIS TERM IS 
\"COMPLETELY UNACCEPTABLE\" BECAUSE IT HAS NO BASIS IN 
FACT, HISTORY, OR CONSTITUTIONAL LAW. 
 
-- OVERLAPPING LEGISLATION:  THE PLAN\'S PROVISION THAT 
CROATIAN LAW WOULD PREVAIL IN THE AUTONOMOUS AREA, BUT 
THAT KNIN COULD ALSO APPROVE LAWS THAT WOULD HAVE TO BE 
HONORED BY CROATIAN AUTHORITIES \"NEGATES THE BASIC 
CONDITIONS OF THE SOVEREIGNTY OF ONE NATION\" SO IT IS 
\"HARDLY PROBABLE\" THAT CROATIA COULD ACCEPT IT. 
 
-- FLAG AND COAT-OF-ARMS:  CURIOUSLY, GIVEN PRESIDENT 
TUDJMAN\'S EARLIER RHETORIC AGAINST THESE PROVISIONS, 
VJESNIK SIMPLY REPORTS WHAT THE PLAN PROPOSES, WITHOUT 
SPECIFICALLY REJECTING IT. 
 
-- TWO EQUALLY VALID CURRENCIES:  \"DIFFICULT TO SEE 
(THIS IDEA) AS AN AFFIRMATION OF SOVEREIGNTY....\"  (THE 
ARTICLE INCORRECTLY SUGGESTS THAT CROATIA WOULD BECOME 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
