\"DUBIOUS,\" THOUGH THE PLAN LEAVES IT TO THE PARTIES TO 
WORK OUT SPECIFICS. 
 
-- SEPARATE GOVERNMENT IN THE SERB AUTONOMOUS AREA: 
\"MUCH\" OF WHAT THE PLAN PROPOSES IS \"UNACCEPTABLE.\" 
THE ARTICLE SINGLES OUT THE SUGGESTION THAT SERBS 
ELECTED TO THE SABOR FROM THE KRAJINA AND THOSE ELECTED 
ELSEWHERE IN CROATIA WOULD FORM A SINGLE PARLIAMENTARY 
GROUP FOR ATTACK, NOTING THIS WOULD MAKE THEM 
\"PROFESSIONAL SERBS\" RATHER THAN REPRESENTATIVES OF 
DIFFERENT POLITICAL PARTIES/OPTIONS. 
 
-- DEFENSE:  THE PROVISION THAT THE CROATIAN ARMY COULD 
ENTER THE \"KRAJINA\" (BEYOND THE BORDER AREAS) ONLY BY 
INVITATION OF THE SERB AUTHORITIES \"ENCROACHES SHARPLY\" 
ON CROATIAN SOVEREIGNTY AND \"SIMPLY CANNOT BE 
ACCEPTED.\"  HERE, THE PLAN\'S AUTHORS ARE \"GROSSLY 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
