INTERFERING IN THE INTERNAL AFFAIRS OF THE REPUBLIC OF 
CROATIA.\" 
 
-- COURTS:  THE PROPOSAL THAT KRAJINA OFFICIALS WOULD 
BE NEITHER ANSWERABLE TO, NOR REPLACEABLE BY, THE 
CROATIAN CENTRAL GOVERNMENT IS \"ESPECIALLY 
UNACCEPTABLE.\" 
 
-- SLAVONIA (SECTOR EAST): MANY OF THE PLAN\'S SPECIAL 
ARRANGEMENTS FOR SECTOR EAST ARE QUESTIONABLE; THERE IS 
NO REASON FOR DEMILITARIZATION OF THE AREA, WHICH 
\"CANNOT BE ACCEPTABLE;\" LIKEWISE UNACCEPTABLE IS THE 
PROPOSED TWO-YEAR UN MANDATE OVER THE AREA. (COMMENT: 
CROATIAN CONTACT GROUP REP AMB. ZUZUL, HOWEVER, HAS 
DOWNPLAYED PROBLEMS ON THIS ISSUE.) 
 
-- CITIZENSHIP:  THESE PROVISIONS ARE \"VERY UNUSUAL.\" 
DUAL CITIZENSHIP (IN CROATIA AND THE \"FEDERAL REPUBLIC 
OF YUGOSLAVIA\") IS DUBIOUS.  THE PROVISION THAT NO ONE 
IN CROATIA (EXCEPT PERSONS SPECIFICALLY ACCUSED OF 
DEFINED WAR CRIMES) WOULD BE SUBJECT TO PROSECUTION BY 
KNIN OR ZAGREB AUTHORITIES FOR ACTS COMMITTED DURING 
THE WAR \"WILL BE ESPECIALLY INTERESTING\" TO CROATIAN 
REFUGEES AND DISPLACED PERSONS WHO SUFFERED BRUTAL SERB 
AGGRESSION (BUT THE ARTICLE DOES NOT SPECIFICALLY 
REJECT THIS CLAUSE). 
 
-- THE VJESNIK ARTICLE CLOSES WITH A NOD TO THE 
SUPPOSED NEGOTIABILITY OF THE PLAN\'S PROVISIONS, BUT 
POINTS OUT THAT THERE IS A LOT THAT IS UNACCEPTABLE 
BECAUSE IT GOES WELL BEYOND THE RELEVANT UNSC 
