COMMENT 
------- 
 
5.  (LOU) THE VJESNIK PIECE AFFORDS THE CROATIAN PUBLIC 
ITS FIRST DETAILED, GOVERNMENT-AUTHORIZED LOOK AT SOME 
OF THE MORE ODIOUS (TO THE CROATS) ELEMENTS OF THE 
PLAN.  THIS CRITIQUE WILL STRIKE A BROAD AND RESPONSIVE 
CHORD AMONG THE GENERAL PUBLIC.  SOME OF THE SPECIFIC 
OBJECTIONS SEEM TO DENY EVEN THE ESSENCE OF TRUE LOCAL 
AUTONOMY.  IT IS CONCEIVABLE -- BARELY -- THAT THESE 
COULD BE MODIFIED IN THE COURSE OF NEGOTIATIONS (SHOULD 
ANY EVER TAKE PLACE).  THE MOST FIRMLY STATED CONCERNS 
IN THE \"VJESNIK\" CRITIQUE, HOWEVER, ARE THOSE OF 
CROATIAN GOVERNMENT AUTHORITY IN AREAS SUCH AS DEFENSE, 
AND THE ROLE OF THE CENTRAL GOVERNMENT AS THE FINAL 
ARBITER OF ISSUES, EVEN IN THE \"AUTONOMOUS AREAS\" 
(I.E., \"SOVEREIGNTY\"), AND THESE ARE POINTS ON WHICH 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
