1.   FAO RECEIVES 3.5 MILLION ECUS FROM ECHO FOR 
SPRING SEED PROGRAM.  CROATIAN AUTHORITIES 
CONTINUE TO BLOCK FUEL DELIVERIES FOR SERB-HELD 
TERRITORY.  KRAJINA SERBS GRANT CLEARANCE ONLY 
ONCE A WEEK FOR CONVOYS TO BIHAC POCKET.  UNHCR 
RESTARTS FUEL DELIVERIES UNDER INA CONTRACT. 
POLICY IN MOSTAR ON ILLEGAL CROSSINGS OF THE 
CONFRONTATION LINE.  VODOVOD ASSUMES 
RESPONSIBILITY OF LOWER WATER PROJECT IN 
SARAJEVO.  UPDATE ON WFP PIPELINE.  FOR JAN 30 - 
31:  CONVOY INCIDENTS; UNHCR SUCCESSFUL CONVOY 
DELIVERIES; UNHCR SARAJEVO AIRLIFT; AND JTF 
PROVIDE PROMISE AIRDROP OPERATIONS.  END SUMMARY. 
 
