FAO RECEIVES ECHO FUNDS FOR SEED PROGRAM 
---------------------------------------- 
 
2.   DURING THE JAN 31 WFP/ZAGREB MEETING, UNHCR 
ANNOUNCED THAT ECHO IS FUNNELING SOME FUNDS TO 
FAO THAT WERE ORIGINALLY EARMARKED FOR UNHCR. 
ONE OF FAO\'S CONSULTANTS IN ZAGREB TOLD DART THAT 
THEY EXPECT TO RECEIVE 3.5 MILLION ECUS 
(APPROXIMATELY USD 4.27 MILLION) FOR THE SEED 
PROGRAM.  UNHCR\'S DEPUTY CHIEF OF MISSION FOR B-H 
REMARKED THAT THE REALLOCATION PUTS UNHCR IN A 
DIFFICULT POSITION, AS FAO IS SOMEWHAT OF AN 
IMPLEMENTING PARTNER IN A SENSE.  HOWEVER, UNHCR 
RECOGNIZES THAT THE SEED PROJECTS ARE CRUCIAL, SO 
IT HAS AGREED TO THE DIVERSION OF ECHO FUNDS TO 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 

 
 
 
 
 
                           UNCLASSIFIED 
 
