INA-CONTRACTED FUEL DELIVERIES TO RESUME 
---------------------------------------- 
 
5.   UNHCR\'S DEPUTY CHIEF OF MISSION FOR B-H 
REPORTED THAT THE OFFICE OF DISPLACED PERSONS AND 
REFUGEES (ODPR) IN MOSTAR HAS \"RELUCTANTLY 
AGREED\" TO ALLOW FUEL CONVOYS TO MOVE FROM 
METKOVIC THROUGH CENTRAL B-H AGAIN.  UNHCR 
SLIGHTLY REVISED THEIR DISTRIBUTION TARGETS IN 
ORDER TO PLACATE THE BOSNIAN CROATS IN THE ZENICA 
REGION WHO FELT THAT DISTRIBUTION WAS SKEWED IN 
FAVOR OF THE BOSNIAN MUSLIMS (SEE REFTELS A, B, 
AND C FOR BACKGROUND).  THE FIRST CONVOY IN 
SEVERAL MONTHS TO TRANSPORT THE INA-CONTRACTED 
FUEL FROM METKOVIC IS SCHEDULED FOR TUZLA ON FEB 
1.  (NOTE:  REFTEL C REPORTED THAT UNPROFOR HAD 
AGREED TO SUPPLY FUEL TO UNHCR FROM VITEZ UNDER A 
DEAL REACHED IN EARLY JANUARY BETWEEN THE TWO UN 
BODIES.  UNHCR\'S DEPUTY CHIEF OF MISSION FOR B-H 
CLARIFIED THAT THE JAN 18 FUEL CONVOY FROM VITEZ 
TO SARAJEVO WAS A \"ONE-OFF DEAL\", AND THAT THIS 
NEW BREAKTHROUGH WITH MOSTAR\'S ODPR WOULD RESTART 
THE DELIVERY OF FUEL THROUGH FEDERATION-HELD 
TERRITORY. 
 
