7.   IN THE CASE THAT A MILITARY AGE MAN OR 
SOLDIER IS CAUGHT CROSSING THE LINE ILLEGALLY, 
THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES WILL APPLY:  A) AFTER 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 

 
 
 
 
 
                           UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00470  03 OF 05  021357Z 
ARREST THE WEU POLICE WILL BE INFORMED.  IF NO 
OTHER CRIMINAL ACT HAS BEEN COMMITTED, THE PERSON 
MAY ONLY BE HELD UP TO 3 DAYS, AND THEN MUST BE 
TRANSFERRED TO HIS OWN SIDE.  PERSONAL BELONGINGS 
WILL BE RETURNED IMMEDIATELY; B) IF ANOTHER 
CRIMINAL ACT HAS BEEN COMMITTED, THE PERSON WILL 
BE TAKEN TO COURT AND LEGAL PROCEDURES WILL 
FOLLOW.  THE WEU POLICE WILL BE ALLOWED TO 
MONITOR THE PROCEEDINGS; C) IF THE PERSON IS 
SUSPECTED OF HAVING COMMITTED A WAR CRIME, THE 
WEU POLICE WILL TAKE PART IN THE LEGAL 
PROCEEDINGS.  AFTER INVESTIGATION, THE CASE WILL 
BE HANDED TO THE INTERNATIONAL CRIMINAL TRIBUNAL 
FOR THE FORMER YUGOSLAVIA. 
 
--------------------------------------------- ---- 
VODOVOD TAKES OVER OPERATION OF LOWER WATER PLANT 
--------------------------------------------- ---- 
 
8.   ON JAN 27, THE PROTOCOL WAS SIGNED THAT 
TRANSFERRED THE LOWER SITE OF THE IRC (SOROS- 
FUNDED) WATER TREATMENT PLANT TO SARAJEVO\'S WATER 
COMPANY, VODOVOD (REFTEL D REPORTED THAT THE 
TRANSFER WAS EXPECTED TO OCCUR BEFORE THE END OF 
JANUARY).  THE DONOR IS STILL OBLIGED TO DELIVER 
THE BIO-MONITORING EQUIPMENT, WHICH HAS NOT YET 
BEEN DELIVERED.  THE SARAJEVO CITY GOVERNMENT IS 
RESPONSIBLE FOR INSTALLING THE EQUIPMENT AND 
TRAINING THE PERSONNEL THAT WILL UTILIZE THE 
EQUIPMENT.  VODOVOD WILL ALSO SUBMIT MONTHLY 
REPORTS TO THE DONOR ON PLANT OPERATIONS AND THE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 

 
 
 
 
 
                           UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00470  03 OF 05  021357Z 
RESULTS OF THE RAW AND TREATED WATER QUALITY 
ANALYSIS.  THE SECOND WATER TREATMENT SITE, KNOWN 
AS THE MOSCANICA OR UPPER SITE, IS STILL UNDER 
THE SUPERVISION OF IRC WHILE TESTS AND TRIALS ARE 
BEING CONDUCTED. 
 
--------------------------- 
UPDATE ON WFP FOOD PIPELINE 
--------------------------- 
 
9.   WFP ANNOUNCED THAT MANY OF THE MAIN 
WAREHOUSES IN B-H ARE EXPERIENCING A \"HAND TO 
MOUTH\" DISTRIBUTION PROBLEM.  FORTUNATELY, THE 
PREDICTED SHORTAGES OF BULK COMMODITIES INCLUDING 
FLOUR AND BEANS/PULSES WERE AVERTED BY AN EU 
DONATION.  THE EU DONATION HAS ALSO HELPED TO 
COVER SHORTAGES IN THE HI-QUALITY FOODS INCLUDING 
SUGAR, MEAT, FISH, AND CHEESE.  WFP REPORTED THAT 
FOOD STOCKS SHOULD BE SUFFICIENT FOR B-H THROUGH 
MARCH AND APRIL.  HOWEVER, WFP IS CONCERNED ABOUT 
THE LACK OF PLEDGES FROM MAY ON.  IMMEDIATE 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
