E.O. 12356: DECL: OADR 
TAGS:  PGOV PREL HR SR BK 
SUBJECT:  POLITICAL PARTY KALEIDOSCOPE:  SOME OPPOSITION 
          PARTIES\' SUPPORT Z-4, AUTONOMY 
 
MAYOR ALDO SKIRA, AND PARTY SECRETARY EMIL SOLDATIC.  THE 
MAIN ISSUE ON THE AGENDA WAS THE RECENT RULING AGAINST 
REGIONAL AUTONOMY BY THE CONSTITUTIONAL COURT WHICH STRUCK 
DOWN 19 PROVISIONS OF THE ISTRIAN COUNTY STATUTE 
PERTAINING TO OFFICIAL USE OF THE ITALIAN LANGUAGE AND 
DECENTRALIZATION OF LOCAL ADMINISTRATION. 
 
7.  SOLDATIC SAID THAT THE IDS\'S OPTIONS TO CHANGE THE 
COURT\'S DECISION ARE LIMITED.  THE CONSTITUTIONAL COURT\'S 
RULING WAS FINAL AND THERE WAS NO AVENUE FOR PURSUING AN 
APPEAL.  IDS, HOWEVER, WILL CONTINUE TO LOBBY THE SABOR 
FOR CHANGES IN THE CONSTITUTION.  BEYOND THAT THE IDS WILL 
TRY TO REFORMULATE SOME STATUTES INTO SOMETHING ACCEPTABLE 
TO THE GOC AND CONTINUE TO TEST THE LAW TO SEE HOW MUCH 
AUTONOMY ZAGREB WILL ALLOW.  THEY ADDED, HOWEVER, THAT NOT 
ONLY COULD THE DECISION PROVIDE MOTIVATION TO ANTI-CROAT 
EXTREMISTS IN BOTH ITALY AND ISTRIA TO PURSUE MORE VOCAL 
CAMPAIGNS FOR SEPARATISM AND BORDER CHANGES, BUT IT ALSO 
DID NOT BODE WELL FOR THE POSSIBILITY OF GOC CONCESSIONS 
TO KNIN. 
 
8.  ALONG WITH THE SNS, IDS UNANIMOUSLY OPPOSED 
TERMINATION OF THE UNPROFOR MANDATE.  IN PRIVATE JAKOVCIC 
SAID THAT THE GOC DECISION ON UNPROFOR AND THE \"RSK\'S\" 
REFUSAL TO EVEN LOOK AT THE Z-4 PLAN MADE HIM, FOR THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00817  02 OF 02  231648Z 
FIRST TIME, \"REALLY SCARED FOR THE FUTURE.\"  BOTH SIDES 
HAD TAKEN EXTREME POSITIONS WHICH WERE NOT EASY TO BACK 
DOWN FROM, AND THE GOC WAS NOT FACING UP TO THE 
POSSIBILITY THAT IT COULD LOSE A WAR WITH THE \"RSK,\" 
ESPECIALLY WITH BSA AND FRY SUPPORT.  HE SAID HE HAD 
CONSIDERED THE IDEA OF OFFERING TO LEAD A GROUP OF 
OPPOSITION LEADERS TO KNIN IN AN EFFORT TO RESTART 
NEGOTIATIONS, BUT ADMITTED THAT THE IDEA HAD PROBLEMS (FOR 
INSTANCE, WHAT WOULD THEY DO IF GREETED WITH THE \"RSK\" 
FLAG AND ANTHEM).  ALSO, OTHER OPPOSITION PARTIES PROBABLY 
WOULD NOT SUPPORT SUCH A MOVE BECAUSE MANY ARE SUPPORTING 
THE GOC POSITION. 
 
----------------------------- 
CROATIAN PEASANTS PARTY (HSS) 
----------------------------- 
 
9.  THE HSS TYPIFIES THE STANCE ASSUMED BY MOST OF THE 
REST OF THE OPPOSITION.  NEW HSS PRESIDENT ZLATKO TOMCIC, 
IN A CALL ON THE AMBASSADOR NOVEMBER 8, SAID THAT THE HSS 
SUPPORTED THE GOC DECISION TO TERMINATE THE UNPROFOR 
MANDATE, BUT THEY WOULD SUPPORT A REVISION OF THE MANDATE 
(UNDER A DIFFERENT NAME) IF IT PROVIDED GUARANTEES TO 
CONTROL CROATIA\'S BORDERS.  TOMCIC SAID THAT IN GENERAL 
THE HSS SUPPORTS THE Z-4 PLAN AS A BASIS FOR DISCUSSION 
BUT HAD SERIOUS RESERVATIONS, PARTICULARLY ON THE ISSUE OF 
TIES TO SERBIA.  TOMCIC CLAIMED THE HSS WAS IN FAVOR OF 
ADMINISTRATIVE AUTONOMY FOR THE SERBS, BUT WHEN ASKED BY 
THE AMBASSADOR IF THIS MEANT THAT SERBS COULD PURCHASE, 
FOR EXAMPLE, SCHOOL TEXTBOOKS FROM SERBIA, TOMCIC 
ANSWERED, \"ABSOLUTELY NOT.\"  A FLUSTERED SILENCE ENSUED 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00817  02 OF 02  231648Z 
WHEN THE AMBASSADOR POINTED OUT THAT THAT WOULD DENY 
AUTONOMY TO THE SERBS. 
 
------- 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
10.  THE ATTITUDE OF THE HND AND IDS (AND SNS) -- THIRD, 
AND, ROUGHLY, SIXTH LARGEST PARTIES IN THE SABOR -- IS A 
SMALL HOPEFUL SIGN THAT ATTITUDES AMONG THE OPPOSITION\'S 
CONSTITUENCIES HAVE NOT SOLIDIFIED AGAINST SERB AUTONOMY 
AND THE Z-4.  THERE ARE AT LEAST A FEW VOICES CHALLENGING 
TUDJMAN\'S RATHER UNREALISTIC ASSESSMENT OF WHAT UNPROFOR\'S 
DEPARTURE WILL MEAN FOR CROATIA. 
 
GALBRAITH 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
