TAGS: PHUM, PREF, BK, PREF, BK, HR, War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  BANJA LUKA MUSLIM LEADERS ARRESTED FOR 
          \"ESPIONAGE\" FACE POSSIBLE DEATH SENTENCE 
 
1.  THIS IS AN ACTION REQUEST.  SEE PARA 7. 
 
2.  (U) IN THE PAST TWO WEEKS, OVER TEN OF THE MOST 
PROMINENT MUSLIM COMMUNITY LEADERS IN THE BANJA LUKA 
REGION HAVE BEEN ARRESTED AT THEIR MERHAMET OFFICES AND IN 
THEIR HOMES BY SERB MILITARY AUTHORITIES.  THE DETAINED 
INCLUDED NIJAZ KARASELIMOVIC, THE 73-YEAR-OLD PRESIDENT OF 
MERHAMET BANJA LUKA.  POLICE ALSO CARRIED AWAY COMPUTERS 
AND DISKS CONTAINING THE ORGANIZATION\'S RECORDS.  THERE 
ARE UNCONFIRMED REPORTS OF SIMILAR ARRESTS IN NOVI GRAD 
(FORMERLY BOSANSKI NOVI) AND PRNJAVOR.  AFTER THESE 
ARRESTS AND THOSE OF THE SDA LEADERSHIP FIVE MONTHS AGO, 
THE ONLY REMAINING MUSLIM COMMUNITY LEADER IN BANJA LUKA 
IS THE RELIGIOUS MUFTI, IBRAHIM HALILOVIC. 
 
3.  (LOU) ACCORDING TO AP/HINA, MERHAMET ZAGREB SOURCES, 
AND KARASELIMOVIC\'S SON EMIR (PROTECT), THESE PRISONERS 
ARE CURRENTLY UNDER DETENTION IN A MILITARY PRISON, HAVE 
BEEN INDICTED BY THE MILITARY PROSECUTOR IN BANJA LUKA FOR 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01090  01 OF 02  101652Z 
ESPIONAGE, AND MAY BE SUMMARILY EXECUTED IF CONVICTED. 
EFFORTS BY INTERNATIONAL AGENCIES TO VISIT THE PRISONERS 
HAVE BEEN REBUFFED SO FAR.  LOCAL SOURCES IN CONTACT WITH 
THEIR FAMILIES TOLD US THAT, IN PRISON, THE MUSLIMS WERE 
BEATEN AND TORTURED BY THE MILITARY AUTHORITIES.  THE 
INDICTMENT ALLEGES THAT THESE INDIVIDUALS CARRIED OUT 
ESPIONAGE ACTIVITIES IN THE FORM OF CONTACTS WITH FOREIGN 
EMBASSIES IN ZAGREB, AND REPORTEDLY NAMED THE BOSNIAN 
EMBASSY.  PREVIOUS TO HIS ARREST, EMBOFF HAD MET WITH 
KARASELIMOVIC IN ZAGREB ON FEBRUARY 21 TO DISCUSS THE 
WORSENING HUMAN RIGHTS SITUATION FOR MINORITIES IN THE 
BANJA LUKA REGION.  AN ACCOUNT FROM BANJA LUKA\'S \"GLAS 
SRPSKI\" LINKED THESE ALLEGED ESPIONAGE ACTIVITIES WITH 
THOSE OF THE SDA LEADERSHIP \"VALTER GROUP,\" SIMILARLY 
CHARGED, AND CURRENTLY ON TRIAL BY THE MILITARY 
PROSECUTOR. 
 
4.  (U) THE FOLLOWING INDIVIDUALS ARE REPORTED TO BE 
IMPRISONED AT THE MALI LOGOR BARRACKS IN BANJA LUKA AT 
THIS TIME: 
 
MERHAMET BANJA LUKA: 
  NIJAZ KARASELIMOVIC, PRESIDENT 
  BECO FILIPOVIC, VICE-PRESIDENT 
  ISMET PELAK, ATTORNEY 
  ADIL MEDIC, EXCHANGE COMMISSION MEMBER AND 
     CONVOY MANAGER 
  MEHMED BAJRIC, EXECUTIVE BOARD MEMBER AND 
     CONVOY LEADER 
  ENVER IBRAHIM-BEGOVIC, (NO FURTHER INFORMATION) 
  (BAKIR IBRAHIM-BEGOVIC, FATHER OF ENVER, WAS RELEASED) 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01090  01 OF 02  101652Z 
 
MERHAMET PRIJEDOR 
  NIJAZ KAPETANOVIC, PRESIDENT 
  ADIL SOLO, VICE PRESIDENT 
  SEDIKA CERIC, SECRETARY 
 
MERHAMET SANSKI MOST 
  AMIR TALIC, FORMER PRESIDENT 
  (TWO OTHERS FROM SANSKI MOST HAVE BEEN RELEASED) 
5.  (LOU) OUR CONTACTS STATED THAT AS A RESULT OF THESE 
DETENTIONS, PANIC HAS SPREAD AMONG THE MUSLIM AND OTHER 
MINORITY COMMUNITIES IN BANJA LUKA.  FIVE THOUSAND PEOPLE 
ARE REPORTEDLY PREPARED TO LEAVE IMMEDIATELY IN FEAR FOR 
THEIR LIVES. 
 
6.  (LOU) UNHCR CONTACTS TOLD US THIS INCIDENT HAS 
SIGNIFICANTLY IMPAIRED THEIR EFFORTS AND THOSE OF OTHER 
INTERNATIONAL GROUPS TO MAINTAIN CONTACT WITH THE MINORITY 
COMMUNITIES AND DELIVER AID TO THE REGION.  THEY BELIEVE 
THAT THE SERB AUTHORITIES HAVE \"DECAPITATED\" THE MUSLIM 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
