UNHCR BUDGET CUTS AFFECT OFDA GRANTEE 
------------------------------------- 
 
5.   DURING A RECENT TRIP TO CENTRAL B-H, DART 
REPRESENTATIVES WERE TOLD BY IRC THAT THE PROPOSED 
UNHCR FUNDING REQUEST FOR SCHOOL AND HEALTH CENTER 
REHABILITATION WOULD NOT BE APPROVED.  A FAX FROM 
UNHCR/ZAGREB TO IRC INDICATED THAT \"MRS. 
 OGATA (UN 
HIGH COMMISSIONER FOR REFUGEES) HAS REDUCED THE 
UNHCR BUDGET FOR BOSNIA, AND THUS THE IRC PROPOSAL 
WOULD NOT BE FUNDED.\"  WHEREAS UNHCR USED TO BE THE 
BIGGEST CONTRIBUTOR TO IRC PROGRAMS, IRC/BOSNIA HEAD 
OF OFFICE REPORTED THAT IRC NO LONGER HAS ANY AID 
PROJECTS FUNDED BY UNHCR.  FURTHERMORE, IRC\'S HEAD 
OF OFFICE IS CONCERNED THAT THEIR OPERATIONS WILL BE 
SERIOUSLY HAMPERED IF UNHCR CONTINUES TO RECALL THE 
VEHICLES AND EQUIPMENT PROVIDED FOR IRC\'S USE. 
 
---------------------- 
UNHCR CONVOY INCIDENTS 
---------------------- 
 
6.   IN ADDITION TO THE CONVOY CANCELLATIONS DUE TO 
SECURITY CONCERNS DETAILED IN PARA 2, UNHCR/ZAGREB 
REPORTED SEVERAL OTHER CANCELLATIONS ON APR 24 AND 
25.  FIVE CONVOYS WERE CANCELLED ON APR 24, AND 2 ON 
APR 25, PENDING NEGOTIATIONS ON ACCESS TO THE BIHAC 
POCKET.  TWO CONVOYS TO CAZIN WERE DENIED CLEARANCE 
BY THE KRAJINA SERBS - ONE ON APR 24 AND ONE ON APR 
25. 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 

 
 
 
 
 
                           UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01681  02 OF 03  151652Z 
- 
------------------------ 
UNHCR SUCCESSFUL CONVOYS 
------------------------ 
 
7.   ON APRIL 24, UNHCR/METKOVIC REPORTED ONE 
SUCCESSFUL CONVOY TO TUZLA (160 MT OF MIXED FOOD). 
 
8.   ON APRIL 25, UNHCR/METKOVIC REPORTED TWO 
SUCCESSFUL CONVOYS TO ZENICA (A TOTAL OF 109 MT OF 
MIXED FOOD AND SLEEPING BAGS). 
 
9.   ALL OTHER CONVOYS WERE CANCELLED BY UNHCR FOR 
SECURITY REASONS.  SEE PARA 2 FOR DETAILS. 
 
---------------------- 
UNHCR SARAJEVO AIRLIFT 
---------------------- 
 
10.  THE HUMANITARIAN AIRLIFT TO SARAJEVO HAS BEEN 
INTERRUPTED SINCE APR 8 WHEN AN AMERICAN AIRCRAFT 
WAS HIT BY 10 ROUNDS OF SMALL ARMS FIRE.  AS 
REPORTED IN REFTEL, THE UNHCR AIRLIFT IS NOT 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
