METHOD TO TILL THEIR LAND IN THESE SUMMER MONTHS.  DZAKULA 
SAID THAT SUCH FAMILIES SHOULD BE GIVEN THE CONFISCATED 
ANIMALS OF SERBS WHO HAD LEFT THE REGION (UNTIL THE LATTER 
GROUP RETURNED) AND SHOULD BE SOLD BACK THEIR EQUIPMENT TO 
CONTINUE THEIR LIVELIHOODS. 
 
6.  THE CROATS MUST NOT WAIT FOR THE OTHER THREE SECTORS 
TO BE REINTEGRATED TO SOLVE THE \"SERBIAN PROBLEM.\"  THAT 
PROCESS MUST BE STARTED NOW, INSISTED DZAKULA.  LOCAL 
SERBS BELIEVE THERE IS AN EXTREME RESISTANCE ON THE PART 
OF THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT TO COOPERATION WITH THE SERB 
POPULATION.  THE REMAINING SERBS WERE QUICKLY LOSING FAITH 
AND THEIR WILL TO STAY.  GROUPS SUCH AS \"THE ASSOCIATION 
FOR CROATIAN REFUGEES\" MUST BE RENAMED AND BEGIN WORK TO 
RETURN ALL REFUGEES IN CROATIA, INCLUDING SERBS, CROATS 
AND OTHERS.  THERE WERE 14,000 DISPLACED CROATS FROM THE 
AREA, BUT 75,000 DISPLACED SERBS, HE SAID.  (NOTE: THE 
75,000 FIGURE IS FOR SERBS DISPLACED IN 1991 AND SINCE.) 
THE GOC MUST BEGIN TO SHOW IT WAS INTERESTED IN SOLVING 
THE PROBLEMS OF ALL THESE PEOPLE.  ONLY THEN WOULD THE 
FLEEING SERB POPULATION BEGIN TO RETURN. 
 
