REDUCING SUPPORT FOR THE REBEL REGIME, AND WOULD ALMOST 
CERTAINLY HAVE A POSITIVE IMPACT ON CROATIA\'S RELATIONS 
WITH THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY. 
 
10. SARINIC\'S REACTION WAS COOL, BUT NOT NEGATIVE.  NO ONE 
FROM THE SERB COMMUNITY HAD APPROACHED HIM WITH A FORMAL 
REQUEST FOR A MEETI 
NG.  IF HE RECEIVED ONE, HE WOULD 
\"CATALYZE\" IT, AND PERHAPS EVEN PARTICIPATE HIMSELF. 
SARINIC ARGUED THAT THE GOC HAD \"TRIED ITS BEST\" TO SHOW 
SERBS IN WESTERN SLAVONIA THAT LIFE IN CROATIA WAS 
POSSIBLE, AND REPEATED THAT THE GOC WAS READY TO RECEIVE 
ALL SERBS WHO WANTED TO RETURN.  THE GOC HAD PROBLEMS, 
HOWEVER, WITH \"LOCAL PEOPLE\" WHO RESIST THE GOC\'S 
DECISIONS.  ACCORDING TO SARINIC, \"DECISIONS TAKEN AT THE 
HIGHEST LEVEL ARE NOT IMPLEMENTED LOCALLY.  IT IS NOT 
EASY.\" 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02493  03 OF 03  031644Z 
 
11. COMMENT:  THE REALITY OF RESISTANCE AMONG MANY (BUT 
NOT ALL) OF THE DISPLACED PERSONS, WAR VETERANS, AND EVEN 
AVERAGE CROATIANS FOR FULL PROTECTION OF THE HUMAN AND 
CIVIL RIGHTS OF THE SERB COMMUNITY IS PRECISELY WHY THE 
GOC MUST TAKE AN ACTIVIST APPROACH ON THE ISSUE.  WE PLAN 
TO CONTINUE TO PUSH THE GOC TO BEGIN A PROCESS OF DIALOGUE 
(UNDER MODIFIED Z-4 AUSPICES) WITH THE \"LOYAL\" SERB 
COMMUNITY AS A \"SECOND TRACK\" WHICH CAN BE FOLLOWED IN 
PARALLEL TO, BUT INDEPENDENT OF, THE NORMAL Z-4 
NEGOTIATIONS WITH KNIN. 
 
