SUBJECT:  HUMAN RIGHTS ABUSES - SREBRENICA 
 
REF:  A) GENEVA 5948  B) ZAGREB 2788 (NOTAL) 
 
------------------------ 
INTRODUCTION AND SUMMARY 
------------------------ 
 
1.  DECONTROL ON RECEIPT.  SENSITIVE BUT UNCLASSIFIED - 
TREAT ACCORDINGLY. 
 
2. (U)  DRL A/S SHATTUCK TRAVELED TO TUZLA AND ZENICA JULY 
31-AUGUST 1 TO ASCERTAIN THE DIMENSION OF THE HUMAN RIGHTS 
CRIMES COMMITTED DURING THE BOSNIAN SERB ARMY\'S ATTACK AND 
OCCUPATION OF TWO UN SAFE AREAS, SREBRENICA AND ZEPA.  THE 
FOLLOWING IS A FIRST-HAND ACCOUNT OF A DISPLACED TEENAGER 
FROM THE SREBRENICA ENCLAVE WHO SURVIVED A MASS EXECUTION 
OF MUSLIM MEN BY THE BSA.  THE SUBJECT AGREED TO SPEAK 
ONLY ON THE CONDITION THAT HIS NAME OR DESCRIPTION NOT BE 
REVEALED PUBLICLY OR DISSEMINATED FOR FEAR THAT THAT WOULD 
ENDANGER RELATIVES STILL UNDER SERBIAN DETENTION IN B-H. 
END SUMMARY. 
 
3. (LOU)  NEDJAD AVDIC IS A TALL, UNDERNOURISHED 
SEVENTEEN-YEAR-OLD BOY FROM THE VILLAGE OF SEBIOCINA, NEAR 
VLASENICA IN SERB-OCCUPIED EASTERN BOSNIA.  HE FLED THIS 
VILLAGE IN MID-1992 WITH HIS PARENTS AND THREE YOUNGER 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02953  01 OF 04  031520Z 
SISTERS AFTER THE BSA ATTACKED IT.  AFTER A YEAR IN 
KONJEVIC POLJE, THE FAMILY MOVED AGAIN TO SLAPOVICA, NEAR 
SREBRENICA.  AVDIC HAD ONLY FINISHED SEVENTH GRADE WHEN HE 
WAS FIRST DISPLACED IN 1992, AND HAD HAD NO FORMAL 
SCHOOLING SINCE THAT TIME, ONLY SOME INFORMAL CLASSES. 
AVDIC IS REFERRED TO AS N.A. THROUGHOUT THIS MESSAGE.  HE 
SAID HE WAS SAVED BY OSMAN HALILOVIC, (O.H.) A THIRTY-FIVE 
YEAR OLD MUSLIM, WHOSE STORY WAS REPORTED IN REF B. 
 
------------------------------------ 
FLIGHT FROM SREBRENICA AND SURRENDER 
------------------------------------ 
 
4. (U)  ON JULY 6, N.A. HEARD THE FIRST DETONATIONS OF THE 
BSA SHELLING OF THE SREBRENICA ENCLAVE.  HE AND HIS FAMILY 
FLED TO UNDERGROUND SHELTERS WHERE THEY HID FOR THREE 
DAYS.  WHEN DUTCH UNPROFOR TROOPS PULLED BACK INTO THE 
TOWN OF SREBRENICA, MANY CIVILIANS FLED, HE SAID, SOME TO 
THE WOODS, SOME TOWARDS THE TOWN.  N.A. AND HIS FATHER 
FLED INTO THE WOODS, AND HIS MOTHER AND SISTERS SOUGHT 
SHELTER IN THE UNPROFOR CAMP IN POTOCARI.  THE WOODS WERE 
FILLED WITH MILITARY AND CIVILIAN MEN AND SOME WOMEN AND 
CHILDREN, N.A. SAID.  DURING THE COURSE OF BSA SHELLING, 
HE AND HIS FATHER, A SOLDIER, WERE SEPARATED.  AFTER ONE 
DAY OF HIDING, THE SERB SOLDIERS SURROUNDED THE AREA AND 
CALLED OUT OVER A MEGAPHONE FOR THE PEOPLE TO SURRENDER. 
N.A. SAID THE CALL PROMISED THE MUSLIMS THEY WOULD BE 
ACCORDED ALL THE RIGHTS OF THE GENEVA CONVENTION IF THEY 
SURRENDERED. 
 
5.  (U)  N.A. CLAIMED THAT 1000-2000 MEN AND BOYS 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02953  01 OF 04  031520Z 
SURRENDERED BY MID-AFTERNOON.  THEY WERE FORCED BY THE 
SERBS TO STAND SINGLE FILE ON THE ROAD WITH THEIR HANDS 
BEHIND THEIR BACKS.  THE WOUNDED WERE GIVEN NO MEDICAL 
AID.  N.A. SAID THAT SEVERAL TANKS WERE STOPPED ALONG THE 
ROAD AND THE COLUMN WAS FORCED TO FILE PAST A CHECKPOINT 
TOWARDS SOME TRUCKS AND BUSES.  THE SERB GUARD VIOLENTLY 
THREATENED THE GROUP WITH HIS RIFLE, AND INSISTED THEY 
SURRENDER ALL THEIR MONEY, GOLD AND OTHER VALUABLES, OR 
THEY WOULD BE SHOT.  N.A. HAD A BAG WITH SOME CLOTHING AND 
HE SURRENDERED IT. 
 
6.  (U)  THE BUSES, OVERLOADED WITH WOMEN AND CHILDREN, 
DROVE PAST THE GROUP ON THE ROAD TOWARDS VLASENICA.  THE 
BSA FORCED THE MEN, INCLUDING THE WOUNDED, TO RUN SINGLE 
FILE IN THE OTHER DIRECTION WITH HANDS LIFTED, SHOWING THE 
SERB THREE-FINGER SYMBOL.  N.A. SAID THEY RAN UNTIL THEY 
REACHED THE VILLAGE OF SANDIC, ORIGINALLY A MUSLIM 
VILLAGE.  THE MEN, HELD IN A SMALL FIELD, WERE APPROACHED 
BY BSA SOLDIERS WHO VERBALLY ASSAULTED THEM.  N.A. SAID 
THEY SHOUTED AT THE GROUP, \"WE ARE FROM SERBIA.  WE\'RE 
GOING TO TAKE YOU TO A HANGAR IN BRATUNAC AND HOLD YOU FOR 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
