A PRISONER EXCHANGE.  IF YOU START ANY TROUBLE, YOU WILL 
BE KILLED.\"  THE SERBS FORCED THEM TO LIE ON THEIR 
STOMACHS, CLAP THEIR HANDS BEHIND THEIR BACKS AND SHOUT 
\"LONG LIVE SERBIA, LONG LIVE THE KING.\"  SOME SOLDIERS 
WALKED AMONG THE PRONE MEN, KICKING THEM AND HITTING THEM 
WITH RIFLE BUTTS.  N.A. SAW SOME SOLDIERS FIRING INTO A 
BURNING HOUSE ABOUT 100 METERS AWAY.  HE DID NOT KNOW IF 
ANYONE WAS INSIDE.  A SERBIAN COMMANDER LECTURED THEM OVER 
A MEGAPHONE.  N.A. SAID THAT BOTH UNIFORMED ARMY AND 
POLICE WERE PRESENT.  SOME POLICE WORE FIELD BLUE 
UNIFORMS, HE SAID. 
 
7.  (U)  N.A. SAID HE LAY THERE FOR OVER TWO HOURS.  AT 
DUSK, THE MEN WERE FORCED ONTO LARGE TRUCKS THAT HAD 
ARRIVED.  HE SAW DEAD BODIES ALONG THE ROAD AS HE RAN TO 
THE TRUCKS.  HE BELIEVED HE SAW 5-7 TRUCKS IN ALL.  HE 
RODE ON THE LAST ONE, CLOSED WITH A CANVAS COVER SO THE 
MEN COULD NOT SEE OUT.  THROUGH A SMALL HOLE, N.A. SAW A 
BSA VOLKSWAGEN GOLF FOLLOW THE CONVOY.  HE ESTIMATED THERE 
WERE ABOUT 150 MEN PACKED ONTO HIS TRUCK.  N.A. SAID THE 
CONVOY DROVE TO BRATUNAC, WHERE THEY SPENT THE NIGHT IN 
THE TRUCKS.  THEY WERE GIVEN NO FOOD OR WATER, AND WERE 
CONTINUOUSLY INSULTED AND JEERED AT BY SOLDIERS.  IN THE 
MORNING, THE CONVOY CONTINUED TOWARD KRAVICA.  THROUGH THE 
HOLE, N.A. SAW BUSES OF WOMEN AND CHILDREN FOLLOWING THE 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02953  02 OF 04  031520Z 
CONVOY.  N.A. SAID THAT SOME MEN CLAIMED THEY SAW UNPROFOR 
VEHICLES ALONG THE WAY.  AT THE BRATUNAC TOWN BORDER, THE 
CONVOY AGAIN STOPPED FOR TWO TO THREE HOURS.  STILL THEY 
RECEIVED NO WATER.  WHEN THE TRUCKS STARTED UP AGAIN, 
SOMEONE CALLED OUT THAT THEY WOULD BE REUNITED WITH THEIR 
FAMILIES AND EXCHANGED.  N.A. SAID THEY DROVE IN THE 
DIRECTION OF KARAKAJ.  HE ESTIMATED THAT THERE WERE 100- 
150 PEOPLE ON EACH TRUCK. 
 
------------- 
AT THE SCHOOL 
------------- 
 
8.  (U)  AFTER A SHORT TIME, THE TRUCKS TURNED OFF AND 
STOPPED IN FRONT OF A SCHOOL.  THE BUSES BEHIND FILLED 
WITH WOMEN LEFT THE CONVOY.  THE MEN WERE FORCED TO FILE 
INTO THE SCHOOL WHERE A SERB GUARD AT THE ENTRANCE HIT 
EACH WITH THE BUTT OF HIS RIFLE.  N.A. ENTERED THE LAST OF 
4-5 ROOMS WITH MANY OTHERS.  WHEN SOMEONE CALLED OUT FOR 
WATER, A SHOT WAS FIRED THROUGH THE GLASS ABOVE THE DOOR, 
RICOCHETED OFF THE CEILING AND WOUNDED FIVE MEN IN HIS 
ROOM.  THEY SPENT THE DAY WITHOUT ANY FOOD OR WATER.  AT 
DARK, GROUPS OF TWO-THREE MEN WERE CALLED OUT FOR 
INTERROGATION.  N.A. HEARD SHOTS FIRED IN THE CORRIDORS, 
AND OUTSIDE THE BUILDING.  HE ALSO HEARD LOTS OF MOANING 
AND YELLING BUT HE DID NOT KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.  N.A WAS 
BROUGHT TO A SMALL ROOM WHERE HE WAS FORCED TO TAKE OFF 
HIS SHIRT AND SHOES, AND A SOLDIER TIED HIS HANDS BEHIND 
HIS BACK.  HE THEN FILED OUT OF THE SCHOOL WHERE, IN THE 
DIM MOONLIGHT, HE SAW MANY DEAD BODIES IN THE YARD.  HE 
COULD NOT SAY HOW THE DEAD HAD BEEN KILLED. 
                   LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 

 
 
 
 
 
                       LIMITED OFFICIAL USE 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02953  02 OF 04  031520Z 
 
-------------------- 
AT THE KILLING FIELD 
-------------------- 
 
9.  (U)  THE MEN WERE FORCED ONTO TRUCKS AGAIN AND ORDERED 
TO SIT.  THEY WERE PACKED TOO TIGHTLY AND COULD NOT MOVE. 
A VOICE ORDERED THEM TO SIT AGAIN AND SOMEONE FIRED A 
BURST OF MACHINE GUN FIRE INTO THE SIDE OF THE TRUCK, 
WOUNDING SEVERAL PEOPLE.  THE TRUCKS DROVE OFF AND AFTER 
FIVE MINUTES TURNED ONTO A DIRT ROAD.  AFTER ANOTHER FIVE 
MINUTES, THEY STOPPED.  N.A. SAID HE HEARD ROUNDS FIRED 
INTO THE GROUND.  ABOUT THREE MINUTES LATER, THE BACK OF 
THE TRUCKS WERE OPENED AND MEN ORDERED OFF IN GROUPS OF 
FIVE.  N.A. SAID HE WAS IN THE MIDDLE OF THE LAST TRUCK. 
AFTER EACH GROUP LEFT, THE MEN HEARD GUNFIRE.  N.A. HEARD 
ONE MUSLIM SAY TO A SERB SOLDIER, \"WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS 
TO INNOCENT PEOPLE?  I SAVED YOUR WIFE AND CHILD IN OUR 
APARTMENT.\"  THE SERB REPLIED, \"SHUT UP.  I\'LL CHOSE WHO I 
WANT TO DO WHAT TO.\" 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
