TO LAY DOWN THEIR ARMS.  HOWEVER, HE MAINTAINED THAT THE 
GOC WOULD ONLY AGREE TO NEGOTIATE WITH BABIC AS LONG AS 
FIGHTING STILL CONTINUED.  SHOULD THE \"ARSK\" NOT SURRENDER 
AND THE HV TAKE COMPLETE CONTROL OVER THE TERRITORY 
MILITARILY, NEGOTIATIONS WITH BABIC WOULD NO LONGER BE AN 
OPTION.  THE GOC WOULD THEN SEEK OUT OTHER SERB LEADERS 
AND INTERLOCUTORS WHO STILL WISHED TO REMAIN IN THE 
SECTOR, SUCH AS VJEKOSLAV DJAKULA IN WESTERN SLAVONIA. 
 
11.  BABIC HAD TO BE CONTACTED THAT SAME EVENING ABOUT 
CEASEFIRE NEGOTIATIONS, SARINIC INSISTED, FOR THIS IDEA TO 
BE AT ALL SUCCESSFUL.  THE AMBASSADOR AGREED TO BE THE 
POINT OF INITIAL CONTACT WITH BABIC, AND WOULD PLAY AN 
ADDITIONAL ROLE AS REQUESTED BY THE PARTIES, SUBJECT TO 
WASHINGTON\'S APPROVAL.  HE INSISTE 
D THAT SUCH NEGOTIATIONS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02986  03 OF 05  052148Z 
INCLUDE A POSITIVE POLITICAL SETTLEMENT FOR A WESTERN 
KRAJINA WITHIN CROATIA.  SARINIC WAS SKEPTICAL ABOUT 
BABIC\'S ABILITY TO DELIVER ON THE MILITARY FRONT, BUT 
AGREED.  THE AMBASSADOR EMPHASIZED THAT SUCH A SETTLEMENT 
MUST MAKE LOCAL SERBS FEEL MORE COMFORTABLE IN THEIR 
CHOICE TO REMAIN IN KRAJINA.  BABIC WAS AN IDEAL 
INTERLOCUTOR BECAUSE HE HAD POPULAR SUPPORT AMONG THE 
PEOPLE OF KRAJINA.  THE CONTINUED PRESENCE OF THE 
INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY WAS ESSENTIAL IN GAINING THE 
CONFIDENCE OF THE LOCAL SERBIAN POPULATION.  A POSITIVE 
RESOLUTION IN THE KRAJINA ALSO HELD SIGNIFICANT 
IMPLICATIONS FOR FURTHER DEVELOPMENTS IN SECTOR EAST. 
 
12.  SARINIC REPLIED THAT CROATIA WOULD BE PREPARED TO 
DISCUSS ISSUES OF CIVILIAN AUTHORITY AND CULTURAL 
AUTONOMY, AS WELL AS COUNTY TERRITORIAL BOUNDARIES.  THE 
AMBASSADOR SUGGESTED THAT DISCUSSIONS WITH BABIC BE HELD 
IN ZAGREB AT A LOCATION OF THE GOC\'S CHOOSING, PREFERABLY 
NOT IN SECRET.  HE SUGGESTED OTHER INTERLOCUTORS THE GOC 
MIGHT WISH TO CONSIDER MIGHT BE VOJNOVIC, AND RADOVAN 
JOVIC, A RECENT USIS IV RECIPIENT.  SARINIC URGED THAT 
SUCH DISCUSSION START IMMEDIATELY.  AS SOON AS MILITARY 
ACTION FINISHED, CIRCUMSTANCES IN THE KRAJINA WOULD 
CHANGE, AND HE WOULD NO LONGER BE AMENABLE TO HOLDING 
DISCUSSIONS WITH BABIC. 
 
---------------------------------------- 
KRAJINA MUST RETAIN A SERBIAN POPULATION 
---------------------------------------- 
 
13.   THE AMBASSADOR INSISTED TO SARINIC THAT THE GOC MAKE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02986  03 OF 05  052148Z 
EVERY EFFORT TO PROTECT THE LOCAL CIVILIAN POPULATION AND 
ENSURE THAT CONDITIONS ARE CREATED TO ENCOURAGE THE LOCAL 
POPULATION TO STAY.  SARINIC REPLIED THAT THE GOC WAS 
CONSTRAINED BY PUBLIC OPINION, WHICH WAS CONVINCED \"ONE 
HUNDRED PERCENT\" THAT A MILITARY SOLUTION WAS THE ONLY WAY 
TO RESOLVE THE KRAJINA PROBLEM.  THE AMBASSADOR POINTED 
OUT THAT THE GOC AND THE GOBH NOW HAD THE PERFECT 
OPPORTUNITY TO CREATE FACTORS ON THE GROUND TO PAVE THE 
WAY FOR A VIABLE PEACE SETTLEMENT IN THE REGION LATER THIS 
YEAR. 
- 
------------------- 
BILDT OUT ON A LIMB 
------------------- 
 
14.  SARINIC EXPRESSED SHOCK AND DISMAY AT ICFY SPECIAL 
ENVOY CARL BILDT\'S STATEMENT EQUATING PRESIDENT TUDJMAN 
AND RSK LEADER MARTIC, CHARACTERIZING IT AS \"STUPID.\" 
ICFY MUST DEAL WITH CROATIA AND SUCH UNDIPLOMATIC AND 
UNPROFESSIONAL STATEMENTS WERE COMPLETELY UNPRODUCTIVE. 
HE SUGGESTED THAT THE GOC WOULD REFUSE FURTHER DISCUSSIONS 
WITH BILDT. 
 
