SECTOR EAST PROVOCATIONS 
------------------------ 
 
15.  SARINIC REMAINED CONCERNED ABOUT \"ARSK\" SHELLING ON 
OSIJEK AND VINKOVCI.  HE INSISTED THAT THE HV CONSIDERED 
THESE ATTACKS TO BE ONLY PROVOCATIONS, AND WOULD NOT 
RETALIATE.  HE CLAIMED THAT OVER 600 SHELLS HAD FALLEN ON 
VINKOVCI AND 6 ON OSIJEK SINCE THE START OF THE HV\'S 
ACTION.  HE SHOWED US AN UNCONFIRMED AND UNRELIABLE MEDIA 
REPORT FROM BANJA LUKA AS OF 1300 LOCAL ON AUGUST 5 THAT 
THE \"ARSK\" HAD GAINED CONTROL OF NUSTAR, SIX KILOMETERS 
NORTH OF VINKOVCI. 
 
---------------------- 
DUBROVNIK AND TREBINJE 
---------------------- 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  02986  04 OF 05  052148Z 
 
16.  CILIPI AND KONAVLJE CONTINUED TO BE SHELLED BY THE 
BSA, SARINIC CONTINUED.  THE WATER PIPELINE TO HERCEG-NOVI 
IN MONTENEGRO HAD BEEN PARTIALLY DESTROYED IN THIS 
SHELLING AND THE GOC COULD NOT REPAIR IT UNTIL THE 
SHELLING STOPPED.  SARINIC SAID THE GOC WOULD NOT 
\"BLACKMAIL\" THE SERBS WITH WATER.  AS IN SECTOR EAST, THE 
HV WOULD NOT REACT TO SUCH PROVOCATIONS UNLESS THE SERBS 
MADE GOOD ON THEIR CLAIMS TO DESTROY THE ENTIRE HISTORICAL 
CENTER OF DUBROVNIK.  IT WAS NOT IN CROATIAN INTERESTS TO 
OPEN ANOTHER FRONT, HE REITERATED. 
 
---------------------------------------- 
SET UP OF MILITARY AND CIVIL AUTHORITIES 
---------------------------------------- 
 
17.  MINISTER-AT-LARGE MAJDAK WOULD CONTINUE TO BE THE GOC 
INTRA-GOVERNMENTAL COORDINATOR OF ACTIVITIES FOR WESTERN 
KRAJINA, JUST AS HE WAS FOR WESTERN SLAVONIA, SARINIC 
INFORMED US.  AT 1430, HE SAID, PRESIDENT TUDJMAN HAD 
NAMED GENERAL CERMAK 
 AS THE \"KNIN COMMANDER\" AND HAD ASKED 
HIM TO CONSOLIDATE POLITICAL-MILITARY CONTROL OF THE 
SECTORS.  SARINIC SAID AN ANNOUNCEMENT OF THIS POSITION 
WOULD BE FORTHCOMING LATER TODAY.  (NOTE: IT WAS NOT 
ANNOUNCED AT THE MOD PRESS CONFERENCE AT 1800.) 
 
----------------- 
LATE DEVELOPMENTS 
----------------- 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  02986  04 OF 05  052148Z 
18.  AT A TELEVISED MOD PRESS CONFERENCE AT 1800 LOCAL, 
THE SPOKESMAN, GENERAL IVAN TOLJ, CONFIRMED THAT BENKOVAC 
HAD FALLEN AT 17:55.  HE SAID THE HV OPERATION WAS 
PROCEEDING TWICE AS FAST AS THEY HAD EXPECTED AND THAT 
EIGHTY PERCENT OF THE TASK HAD BEEN ACCOMPLISHED.   THE HV 
HAD CUT SEVERAL SERB COMMUNICATION LINES (DRNIS-KNIN, 
OBROVAC-GRACAC, GOSPIC-LJUBOVO, GOSPIC-GRACAC, AND DUBICA- 
KOSTAJNICA).  THE HV HAD ENGAGED THE FORCES OF THE 7TH 
KNIN CORPS (10,000 TROOPS) AND 15TH ILJICKI CORPS (15,000 
TROOPS) IN THE SOUTH, AND THE 21ST AND 39TH CORPS IN THE 
NORTH.  TOLJ OPINED THAT \"TODAY WAS AN HISTORICAL DAY FOR 
CROATIA, EUROPE AND THE WORLD.\" 
 
19.  REFUSING TO GIVE NUMBERS, TOLJ INSISTED THAT THE HV 
HAD SUFFERED MINIMAL CASUALTIES, AND DID NOT HAVE 
INFORMATION ABOUT HOW MANY SERB TROOPS HAD FLED TO BOSNIA. 
THE HV COMMANDER IN OGULIN TOLD POLOFF AND DATT THAT 40 
PERCENT OF HIS CASUALTIES WERE CAUSED BY MINEFIELDS.  HE 
CONFIRMED THAT SERB GUERRILLA ACTIONS CONTINUED IN THE 
SLUNJ AREA OF SECTOR NORTH, BUT INSISTED THAT THE HV WAS 
UNCONCERNED THAT THE \"ARSK\" AND THE BSA MIGHT LAUNCH A 
COUNTER-OFFENSIVE FROM BOSNIA IN THE COMING DAYS.  HE 
REPEATED SARINIC\'S ACCOUNT OF THE DEATH OF THE DANISH 
PEACEKEEPER.  HV FORCES, HE MAINTAINED, WERE UNDER STRICT 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
