"764","8/12/1995 15:38","95ZAGREB3082","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","CONFIDENTIAL SECTION 01 OF 04 ZAGREB 03082 
 
SIPDIS 
 
SECDEF WASHDC//ISA/ISP// 
NSC WASHDC 
 
C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 01 OF 04 ZAGREB 003082 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
BRUSSELS ALSO FOR USEU 
USVIENNA ALSO FOR USDEL CSCE 
 
E.O. 12356: DECL: 8/12/00 
TAGS: War Crimes 
SUBJECT:  BIHAC SIEGE LIFTED, ATTENTION TURNING TO 
          ASSISTANCE NEEDS, POLITICAL DEVELOPMENTS, NEXT 
          MILITARY MOVES 
 
 
------- 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1.  (C)  POLOFFS, REFCOORD, AND DART VISITED BIHAC AUGUST 
11 TO ASSESS HUMANITARIAN SITUATION AND DISCUSS 
POLITICAL/MILITARY DEVELOPMENTS IN THE WAKE OF THE GOC 
OFFENSIVE TO RETAKE \"RSK\" TERRITORY.  UN OFFICIALS 
COMPLAINED ABOUT THE INADEQUACY OF UN SAFE AREA POLICY 
WHICH ONLY PROTECTS BIHAC TOWN, WHILE THE ENTIRE POCKET IS 
IN RANGE OF SERB GUNS.  THEY DISCUSSED THE REFUGEE AND 
DISPLACED PERSON PROBLEM; CURRENTLY THERE ARE ABOUT 40,000 
DP\'S IN THE BIHAC POCKET, AND PROBABLY BETWEEN 15-20,000 
REFUGEES LOYAL TO FIKRET ABDIC (AND POSSIBLY ALSO 
INCLUDING \"RSK\" SERBS) ON THE ROAD NEAR THE VILLAGE OF 
KRSTINJA IN CROATIA.  THE UN ASSESSES THAT A FULLY ARMED V 
CORPS WILL BE ON THE OFFENSIVE AGAIN IN ONE TO TWO WEEKS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  03082  01 OF 04  121603Z 
TO SECURE THE ENTIRE UNA-SANSKI CANTON.  MEANWHILE, LOCAL 
OFFICIALS PROVIDED US WITH A SHOPPING LIST OF REQUIREMENTS 
FOR REBUILDING LIFE IN THE CANTON AND DISCUSSED THE GOOD 
RELATIONS BETWEEN MUSLIM AND CROAT RESIDENTS.  END 
SUMMARY. 
 
2.  (U) POLOFFS, REFCOORD, AND DART VISITED BIHAC AUGUST 
11 TO ASSESS HUMANITARIAN SITUATION AND DISCUSS 
POLITICAL/MILITARY DEVELOPMENTS IN THE WAKE OF THE GOC 
OFFENSIVE TO RETAKE \"RSK\" TERRITORY. 
 
--------------------------------------------- -- 
UNPROFOR VIEWS ON THE HUMANITARIAN SITUATION... 
--------------------------------------------- -- 
 
3.  (C) POLOFFS MET WITH THE DANISH UN COMMANDER, COL. 
JASPER HELSOE (PROTECT), AND CIVIL AFFAIRS OFFICER RUS 
BALLANTYNE (PROTECT) AT BANBAT HQ IN CORALICI.  THEY 
COMPLAINED THAT THE UN SAFE AREA POLICY WAS GROSSLY 
INADEQUATE IN THE CASE OF BIHAC, WHERE ONLY THE TOWN WAS 
PROTECTED, BUT THE ENTIRE POCKET WAS IN RANGE OF SERB 
GUNS.  THEY NOTED THAT THE POWER STATION AND WATER 
TREATMENT PLANT ARE BOTH OUTSIDE OF THE SAFE AREA AND WERE 
FREQUENTLY TARGETED 
 
4.  (U) BOTH STRESSED THAT IT WAS ALL THEY COULD DO TO 
MANAGE THE VARIOUS FLOWS OF DISPLACED PERSONS IN THE 
CANTON THAT HAVE OCCURRED ALMOST CONTINUOUSLY OVER THE 
LAST FOUR YEAR.  THE SMALL SIZE OF THE BIHAC POCKET MEANT 
THAT ANY TIME SHELLING STARTED, LARGE NUMBERS OF PEOPLE 
WOULD FLEE, USUALLY TO BIHAC TOWN, SEVERELY TAXING LIMITED 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  03082  01 OF 04  121603Z 
SERVICES AND SUPPLIES.  THEY ESTIMATED THAT 20 PERCENT OF 
THE AREA\'S POPULATION FLED FROM ABDIC CONTROLLED TERRITORY 
TOWARD THE SOUTH.  ABDIC\'S \"REPUBLIC OF WESTERN BOSNIA\" 
ALSO CONTAINED ABOUT 20 PERCENT OF THE AVAILABLE FARM 
LAND.  AS A RESULT, LOCAL AUTHORITIES WERE FORCED TO FEED 
MORE PEOPLE FROM LESS LAND.  THIS PROBLEM, COUPLED WITH 
THE INABILITY OF AID CONVOYS TO REACH THE POCKET, HAS 
CREATED A CONTINUING PROBLEM FOR LOCAL OFFICIALS TRYING TO 
SUSTAIN AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTION.  PRODUCE WAS OFTEN 
CONSUMED BEFORE THE HARVEST AND LITTLE WAS RESERVED TO 
PROVIDE SEEDS FOR THE NEXT PLANTING. 
 
5.  (U) THERE ARE CURRENTLY ABOUT 40,000 DP\'S IN THE BIHAC 
POCKET, AND PROBABLY BETWEEN 15-20,000 REFUGEES LOYAL TO 
FIKRET ABDIC (AND POSSIBLY ALSO INCLUDING \"RSK\" SERBS) ON 
THE ROAD NEAR THE VILLAGE OF KRSTINJA IN CROATIA.  HELSOE 
HAD BEEN UNSUCCESSFUL AT OBTAINING CLEARANCE FROM THE GOC 
TO VISIT THESE PEOPLE THE DAY BEFORE (SIMILAR PROBLEMS 
WITH ACCESS HAVE BEEN REPORTED BY UNHCR AND ICRC, SEPTEL). 
HELSOE SAID HE NEEDED BOTH ACCESS TO THE REFUGEES FROM THE 
GOC AND ASSURANCES FROM THE GOBH THAT THESE MEN WOULD BE 
COVERED BY THE AMNESTY SHOULD THEY WISH TO RETURN HOME TO 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
