VELIKA KLADUSA.  THE UN NEEDS TO HELP ESTABLISH THE 
CREDIBILITY OF THE GOBH WITH REFUGEES WHO ARE SCARED OF 
RETRIBUTION.  THERE ARE RUMORS AMONG THE REFUGEES THAT 100 
ABDIC FOLLOWERS ARE STILL IN JAIL IN BIHAC FROM LAST YEAR, 
WHEN THE GOBH OFFERED AN AMNESTY (NOTE: CANTON OFFICIALS 
CONFIRMED TO US THAT THERE ARE SOME ABDIC FOLLOWERS STILL 
IN JAIL UNDER WAR CRIMES CHARGES.)  THE UN WOULD LIKE GOBH 
OFFICIALS, POSSIBLY AT THE MINISTERIAL LEVEL, TO TALK TO 
THE REFUGEES AND ENCOURAGE THEM TO COME BACK. 
 
6.  (U) WE HEARD FROM BOTH THE UN AND CANTON OFFICIALS 
THAT A DEAL FOR RETURNING THE ABDIC REFUGEES TO VELIKA 
KLADUSA HAD BEEN SIGNED BY THE GOC, GOBH, ABDIC, AND 
REFUGEE REPRESENTATIVES, EFFECTIVE AUGUST 11.  IN AN 
ASIDE, GOBH OFFICIALS OPINED THAT ABDIC MUST BE IN CROATIA 
IF HE HAD SIGNED THE AGREEMENT.  (NOTE: WHEN ATTEMPTING TO 
PASS THROUGH THE REFUGEES ON OUR RETURN FROM BIHAC WE WERE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  03082  02 OF 04  121603Z 
TOLD BY PEOPLE ON THE ROAD THAT ABDIC WAS PERSONALLY 
LEADING THE COLUMN.  WE WERE NOT ABLE TO GET TO THE HEAD 
OF THE COLUMN TO TRY TO FIND ABDIC BECAUSE REFUGEES WERE 
BLOCKING THE ROAD AND WE HAD TO FIND AN ALTERNATE ROUTE.) 
 
--------------------------- 
AND THE NEXT MILITARY MOVES 
--------------------------- 
 
7.  (C) UN OFFICIALS IN CORALICI NOTED THAT AS A RESULT OF 
THE HV DEFEAT OF THE \"ARSK,\" THE PRESSURE ON BIHAC\'S 
NORTHERN BORDER WAS RELIEVED AND V CORPS COULD REDIRECT 
ABOUT 10-12,000 TROOPS TO THE FRONT LINE WITH THE BSA. 
ACCORDING TO THE UN, V CORPS NOW HAS A \"LIFETIME\" SUPPLY 
OF AMMUNITION (BALLANTYNE NOTED THAT ON ONE OCCASION HE 
SAW TEN 10 TON TRUCKS MOVING SOUTH CARRYING AMMO AND 
WEAPONS FOR V CORPS), AT LEAST FOUR TANKS, APC\'S, AND 
ARTILLERY TAKEN FROM ABDIC\'S \"REPUBLIC OF WESTERN BOSNIA.\" 
V CORPS IS EXPECTED TO MOVE SOUTH AND EAST AND EXPECTS TO 
TAKE PRIJEDOR.  THE UN CITED RUMORS THAT THE HVO AND V 
CORPS HAVE ALREADY LINKED UP AT KULEN VAKUF, ABOUT 30 
KILOMETERS SOUTHEAST OF BIHAC ON THE CROATIAN BORDER. 
 
--------------------------------------------- 
CANTON GOVERNMENT REPRESENTATIVES - AID NEEDS 
--------------------------------------------- 
 
8.  (U)  IN BIHAC TOWN, THE DELEGATION MET WITH CANTON 
GOVERNOR VELADZIC, PRESIDENT OF THE CANTON GOVERNMENT 
FERIZOVIC, AND CANTON PARLIAMENT PRESIDENT ADEM BORIC. 
ALL THREE WERE EUPHORIC THAT THE CANTON HAD FINALLY BEEN 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 

 
 
 
 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  03082  02 OF 04  121603Z 
LIBERATED FROM SERBIAN ENCIRCLEMENT.  ONLY ONE FRONT 
REMAINED INSTEAD OF FOUR, FERIZOVIC OFTEN REPEATED.  EVEN 
SO, ALL AREAS OF THE CANTON STILL REMAINED WITHIN REACH OF 
BSA HEAVY WEAPONS.  BIHAC SAFE AREA WAS SHELLED REGULARLY, 
RECEIVING 6 SHELLS LATE ON AUGUST 9.   THE GOVERNOR 
OUTLINED A LONG WISH LIST OF ITEMS THAT THE AREA 
DESPERATELY NEEDED. HE WAS CRITICAL OF THE INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITY\'S LACK OF IMMEDIATE RESPONSE TO THE CHANGING 
HUMANITARIAN SITUATION.  FIVE DAYS AFTER ITS LIBERATION, 
ONLY A \"SYMBOLIC QUANTITY\" OF ASSISTANCE HAD ARRIVED 
DESPITE OPEN ROADS FROM CROATIA, VELADZIC INSISTED. 
(NOTE:  THE QUICKEST ROUTE FROM ZAGREB TO VELIKA KLADUSA, 
THROUGH VOJNIC, WAS BLOCKED IN CROATIA ON AUGUST 11 BY 
FLEEING COLUMNS OF REFUGEES LOYAL TO OPPORTUNISTIC MUSLIM 
LEADER FIKRET ABDIC.  SEE SEPTEL.  END NOTE.) 
 
9.  (U)  ONLY ONE CONVOY HAD ARRIVED IN THE AREA FOR 13 
MONTHS, FERIZOVIC STATED  THE POCKET\'S POPULATION HAD 
BEEN CUT OFF FOR FOUR YEARS AND EVERYONE INSIDE, EITHER IN 
THEIR OWN HOME OR DISPLACED, SUFFERED EQUALLY.  VELADZIC\'S 
WISH LIST FOLLOWS IN HIS ORDER OF NECESSITY: 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
