TAGS: KAWC, ICTY, PGOV, PREL, HR RV 
SUBJECT: DOES THE OTP HAVE A STRATEGY FOR CROATIA? 
 
WANT TO USE ICTY\'S LEVERAGE TO PUSH THE GOC TO FIND GOTOVINA, 
AND \"LEGALISTS,\" WHO BELIEVE THAT ICTY\'S SOLE FUNCTION IS TO 
RULE ON COMPLIANCE/NON-COMPLIANCE AND INFORM THE UNSC OF ITS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00305  02 OF 03  120644Z 
FINDINGS.  (OSORIO LISTED HIMSELF AND CHIEF PROSECUTOR DEL 
PONTE AS \"ACTIVISTS.\")  OSORIO SAID THAT THE ICTY ALREADY HAS 
RECEIVED A PROTEST NOTE FROM THE RUSSIAN AMBASSADOR IN THE 
HAGUE ACCUSING THE TRIBUNAL OF A DOUBLE STANDARD FOLLOWING 
DEL PONTE\'S SPEECH TO THE UN LAST OCTOBER -- A SPEECH IN 
WHICH SHE DECLARED SERBIA TO BE IN NON-COMPLIANCE FOR ITS 
FAILURE TO DELIVER RATKO MLADIC, BUT ONLY WARNED CROATIA OVER 
ITS FAILURE TO DELIVER GOTOVINA.  OSORIO EXPECTS MORE 
COMPLAINTS FROM THE RUSSIANS OVER THE OTP\'S GOTOVINA GAMBIT; 
HE ANTICIPATED THAT THE RUSSIANS WILL INSIST AGAIN THAT ICTY 
SHOULD DECLARE CROATIA NON-COMPLIANT.  HOWEVER, OSORIO ARGUES 
THAT, UNLIKE THE MLADIC CASE, THE OTP NEEDS TO PRESS FOR 
VISIBLE ACTION TO DEBUNK THE GOC ARGUMENT THAT GOTOVINA FLED 
THE REGION. 
 
WHERE\'S THE PROOF? 
------------------ 
 
7. (C) OTP FRUSTRATION WITH GOC PASSIVITY ON GOTOVINA IS 
UNDERSTANDABLE; THE GOC DREADS THE PROSPECT OF HAVING TO 
TRANSFER GOTOVINA TO THE HAGUE AND DESPERATELY DOES NOT WANT 
THE GENERAL TO BE IN CROATIA.  HOWEVER, OUR EXPERIENCE WITH 
MUCH OF WHAT WE KNOW OF THE OTP\'S \"EVIDENCE\" ON GOTOVINA IS 
THAT IT IS BASED ON CIRCULAR REPORTING AND HEARSAY.  WHILE 
GOTOVINA VERY WELL MAY BE IN THE REGION, WE HAVE SEEN 
NOTHING, ASIDE FROM THE SFOR SIGHTING, TO UNDERPIN THE HARSH 
OTP STATEMENT THAT GOTOVINA IS \"WALKING FREELY\" IN CROATIA 
(AND WE HAVE BEEN ASKING OSORIO AND THE CROATIANS FOR 
MONTHS).  PER REF B, OTP POLITICAL ADVISOR JEAN-JAQUES JORIS 
TOLD OUR COLLEAGUES IN THE HAGUE THAT \"CROATIAN AND FOREIGN 
SOURCES\" SUPPORTED THE OTP CLAIM THAT GOTOVINA WAS MOVING 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00305  02 OF 03  120644Z 
FREELY IN CROATIA.  HE SAID THAT THE CROATIAN SOURCE WAS (OR 
INCLUDED) PRESIDENT MESIC.  HOWEVER, MESIC\'S FOREIGN POLICY 
ADVISOR TOLD US THAT MESIC BASED HIS STATEMENT ON A CROATIAN 
INTELLIGENCE REPORT, WHICH, WE KNOW FOR A FACT, WAS BASED ON 
A FALSE SIGHTING OF GOTOVINA IN ZAGREB AND OTHER CIRCULAR 
REPORTING.  OTHER REPORTED \"SIGHTINGS\" OF GOTOVINA HAVE 
PROVEN TO BE EQUALLY UNSUBSTANTIATED. 
 
DOCUMENT SHARING 
---------------- 
 
8. (C) OSORIO SAID HE WAS NOT CONSULTED BEFORE HARTMANN 
ISSUED HER STATEMENT.  IN HIS VIEW CRITICISM OF THE GOC\'S 
PERFORMANCE ON INFORMATION SHARING WAS OVERSTATED AND THE 
GOC, AS A RULE, WAS RESPONSIVE ON DOCUMENT REQUESTS. 
ACCORDING TO OSORIO, THERE ARE THREE OUTSTANDING DOCUMENT 
DELIVERY PROBLEMS:  1) THE GOC HAS FAILED TO DELIVER BODY 
COUNT AND AUTOPSY RESULTS CONDUCTED BY THE CROATIAN MILITARY 
AFTER OPERATION STORM; 2) THE GOC HAS NOT MET A DEADLINE TO 
PROVIDE DEMOGRAPHIC DATA WHICH ICTY NEEDS TO HELP DEMONSTRATE 
YUGOSLAV ETHNIC CLEANSING FOR THE MILOSEVIC TRIAL; AND 3) THE 
GOC HAS MISSED A NUMBER OF DEADLINES ON INFORMATION LINKED TO 
INVESTIGATIONS OF CROATIAN WAR CRIMES IN BOSNIA.  IN THE CASE 
OF THE FIRST TWO DOCUMENT SHARING ISSUES, OSORIO TOLD US THAT 
THE GOC FAILURE TO DELIVER THE DOCUMENTS WAS A TECHNICAL, 
SHORT-TERM HICCUP.  IN FACT, IN THE CASE OF THE BODY COUNT 
INFORMATION, OSORIO SAID THAT HE HAD OBTAINED A BOOTLEG COPY 
FROM THE HEAD OF THE GOC COMMISSION FOR MISSING PERSONS.  IN 
THE CASE OF THE OUTSTANDING BIH INFORMATION, THE ISSUE COULD 
HAVE BEEN HANDLED \"THROUGH REGULAR CHANNELS,\" OSORIO 
ASSERTED. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00305  02 OF 03  120644Z 
 
9.  (C) ALTHOUGH PROBLEMS EXIST, THERE IS ALSO PROGRESS. 
OSORIO CONFIRMED THAT THE GOC GAVE PERMISSION FOR THE OTP AND 
THE CROATIAN PROSECUTORS\' OFFICE TO BEGIN TO SHARE 
INFORMATION DIRECTLY.  AN ICTY PROSECUTOR WAS SENT TO ZAGREB 
FEBRUARY 5 TO WORK WITH HIS COUNTERPARTS TO SOLIDIFY THE 
CROATIAN CASE AGAINST LOWER LEVEL PERPETRATORS IN THE MEDAK 
POCKET AND TO SEEK ADDITIONAL INFORMATION TO BOLSTER THE 
OTP\'S CASE AGAINST GENERAL ADEMI FOR CRIMES COMMITTED IN THE 
SAME OPERATION. 
 
BOBETKO: CASE FROZEN 
-------------------- 
 
10.  (C) OSORIO CONFIRMED THAT, AFTER REVIEWING THE ICTY 
MEDICAL SPECIALISTS\' REPORT, CHIEF PROSECUTOR DEL PONTE 
RECOMMENDED TO THE PRESIDING JUDGE THAT THE TRIAL OF FORMER 
CROATIAN CHIEF OF THE GENERAL STAFF JANKO BOBETKO BE 
SUSPENDED BECAUSE OF HIS POOR HEALTH.  ICTY WILL SEND ANOTHER 
MEDICAL TEAM TO ZAGREB IN THREE TO FOUR MONTHS TO REVIEW 
BOBETKO\'S HEALTH, BUT BARRING A MIRACULOUS RECOVERY FROM 
PROGRESSIVE HEART AND RENAL FAILURE, OTP\'S PURSUIT OF THE 
HIGHEST RANKING CROATIAN TO BE INDICTED BY ICTY IS AT AND 
 
