END.  OSORIO DID NOT INDICATE THAT THE OTP WOULD CONDUCT A 
\"LESSONS LEARNED\" EXERCISE OVER BOBETKO.  HE DID EXPRESS 
HOPE, HOWEVER, THAT IN THE AFTERMATH OF THE BOBETKO CRISIS, 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00305  03 OF 03  120645Z 
ICTY FINALLY WOULD ESTABLISH THE BASIC STANDARDS WHICH WOULD 
HELP PROSECUTORS DETERMINE THE FITNESS OF AN INDICTEE TO 
STAND TRIAL. 
 
11. (C) WITH BOBETKO OUT OF THE PICTURE, THE OTP IS 
STRUGGLING TO MAKE SENSE OF ITS PROSECUTION STRATEGY FOR THE 
ENTIRE MEDAK POCKET WAR CRIMES CASE.  BOBETKO WAS AT THE TOP 
OF THE PYRAMID OF THE MILITARY CHAIN OF COMMAND -- INDICTEE 
RAHIM ADEMI WAS THE CHIEF MILITARY OFFICER IN THE FIELD. 
GENERAL MIRKO NORAC, WHOSE INDICTMENT WAS DEFERRED AT THE 
REQUEST OF THE GOC SO THAT IT COULD TRY A SEPARATE WAR CRIMES 
CASE (\"GOSPIC\") LOCALLY, HEADED THE CROATIAN MILITARY UNIT 
PRINCIPALLY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ATROCITIES AT MEDAK.  WITH 
BOBETKO GONE, OSORIO SAID THAT THE OTP WILL HAVE TO REEXAMINE 
THE INDICTMENT AGAINST ADEMI AND THE PENDING INDICTMENT 
AGAINST NORAC.  (OSORIO TOLD US THAT ICTY RECENTLY HAD 
DISCUSSED WITH CHIEF PROSECUTOR MLADEN BAJIC THE POSSIBILITY 
THAT HE INCLUDE NORAC IN THE LOCAL CROATIAN INDICTMENT OF 
LOWER-LEVEL SOLDIERS THAT BAJIC IS PREPARING.) 
 
12. (C) ACCORDING TO OSORIO, MEDAK IS IMPORTANT FOR ICTY, NOT 
JUST BECAUSE THE OTP BELIEVES THIS TO BE ONE OF THEIR 
STRONGEST CROATIA CASES, BUT BECAUSE IT WILL BE A TEST-BED 
FOR ITS EFFORTS TO PROVE THAT THE GOC CONCEPTUALIZED AND 
PRE-PLANNED THE 1995 OPERATION STORM AS AN ETHNIC CLEANSING 
OPERATION.  OSORIO HAS TOLD US THAT THE PROSECUTION BELIEVES 
IT HAS EVIDENCE THAT THE SAME ORGANIZED TECHNIQUES TO RAZE 
SERB VILLAGES IN MEDAK WERE USED ON A WIDER SCALE AFTER 
OPERATION STORM. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00305  03 OF 03  120645Z 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
13. (C) THE OTP IS UNDERSTANDABLY FRUSTRATED.  THE BOBETKO 
CASE, AND YEARS AND YEARS OF WORK, IS SLIPPING AWAY WITHOUT A 
DAY IN COURT.  JUSTICE IS DENIED AND THE GOC, WHICH EVADED 
FOR MONTHS ITS RESPONSIBILITY TO ACT AS ICTY\'S AGENT ON THE 
CASE, HAS COME OUT THE WINNER.  THE BRITISH, WHO WENT OUT ON 
A LIMB TO SUPPORT THE OTP ON BOBETKO BY SUSPENDING CROATIA\'S 
STABILIZATION AND ASSOCIATION AGREEMENT, ARE FURIOUS WITH THE 
OTP ABOUT THIS.  SO ARE WE.  IN THE PROCESS OF BACKING DEL 
PONTE, WE DAMAGED OUR RELATIONSHIP WITH DEPUTY PRIME MINISTER 
GORAN GRANIC, ONE OF THE GOC\'S KEY DECISIONMAKERS.  AS A 
RESULT OF THE BOBETKO CRISIS, THOSE IN CROATIA -- INCLUDING 
THOSE WITHIN THE GOC -- WHO ARGUED THAT CROATIA SHOULD HOLD 
FIRM FOR A SOLUTION MORE TO ITS LIKING WERE VINDICATED.  THEY 
MAY BE EMBOLDENED TO TAKE THE SAME HARD, \"WE KNOW BETTER,\" 
STANCE ON NEW ICTY INDICTMENTS OR ON OTHER THORNY ISSUES SUCH 
AS REFUGEE RETURN. 
 
14. (C) THE OTP\'S ACTIONS HAVE ENORMOUS CONSEQUENCES FOR 
CROATIA, THE REGION AND US.  BOBETKO\'S REAL AND SERIOUS 
MEDICAL AILMENTS WERE WELL KNOWN -- A RESPECTED CROATIAN 
HUMAN RIGHTS LEADER TOLD THE AMBASSADOR SHORTLY AFTER BOBETKO 
WAS INDICTED THAT \"NO ONE WHO KNEW BOBETKO\'S MEDICAL 
CONDITION WOULD HAVE INDICTED HIM,\" AND WONDERED WHY DEL 
PONTE DECIDED NOT TO DO SO.  AS REPORTED REF D, DEL PONTE -- 
DESPITE GOC REQUESTS AND OTP STAFF INTENT -- PASSED UP AN 
OPPORTUNITY TO INTERVIEW THE 83-YEAR OLD GENERAL BEFORE 
ISSUING THE INDICTMENT, APPARENTLY FOR NO SOLID REASON. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00305  03 OF 03  120645Z 
15. (C) HARTMANN\'S UNSUBSTANTIATED STATEMENT, THE OTP\'S LACK 
OF CONSULTATION WITH ITS OWN REPRESENTATIVE ON THE GROUND, 
AND THE DEVELOPMENT OF A \"STRATEGY\" WITHOUT PRIOR DISCUSSION 
WITH THE ICTY\'S INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY SUPPORTERS SUGGESTS 
THAT THE OTP WILL STUMBLE AGAIN, THIS TIME ON THE GOTOVINA 
CASE.  THE OTP MUST DO BETTER.  AS A FIRST STEP, WE SHOULD 
DEMAND THAT THE OTP PRESENT TO US ITS EVIDENCE THAT GOTOVINA 
IS \"FREELY MOVING\" IN CROATIA.  AS THINGS STAND, WE ARE 
SKEPTICAL OTP HAS EVIDENCE -- WE SHOULD DEMAND TO KNOW.  IF 
IT DOES HAVE EVIDENCE AND IT IS CREDIBLE,  WE SHOULD INSIST 
THAT THE OTP CONSULT WITH US AND THE BRITISH ABOUT ITS 
\"STRATEGY\" FOR PRESSING THE GOC TO ACT.  THE QUESTION IS NOT 
WHETHER WE SHOULD PRESS THE GOC ON WAR CRIMES AND ICTY 
COOPERATION, BUT HOW TO ORCHESTRATE THAT PRESSURE TO THE BEST 
EFFECT.  OTHERWISE, WE RISK GOING OUT ON A LIMB AGAIN FOR DEL 
PONTE ONLY TO HAVE IT BREAK UNDER US. 
ROSSIN 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
