SIPDIS 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 02/12/2013 
TAGS: PREF, PREL, OSCE, EUN, UNHCR, ECON, HR 
SUBJECT: GOC PUSHING BACK ON IC CRITICISM ON RETURNS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00337  03 OF 04  121721Z 
 
12.  (C) OTHER LEADING IC REPS RAISED QUESTIONS ABOUT RENTAL 
COMPENSATION FOR CURRENT OWNERS WHO ARE NOT OCCUPYING THEIR 
PROPERTIES AND FOR DAMAGE RESULTING FROM THE LOOTING OF 
PROPERTIES BY TEMPORARY OCCUPANTS AS THEY VACATE THEM.  CACIC 
REPLIED THAT THE GOC WILL PROVIDE RENTAL COMPENSATION TO 
THOSE WHO QUALIFY UNDER THE LAW BUT HE DID NOT SAY WHEN IT 
WOULD BEGIN.  AS FOR LOOTING, CACIC SAID THE GOC DID NOT HAVE 
THE MONEY TO COMPENSATE EVERYONE WHOSE PROPERTY HAD BEEN 
LOOTED.  HE EXPRESSED SURPRISE THAT CROATIA WAS BEING ASKED 
TO PROVIDE SUCH COMPENSATION WHEN NO OTHER COUNTRY IN THE 
REGION WAS ASKED TO DO SO. 
 
INCREASING THE STAKES 
--------------------- 
 
13. (C) IC PRESSURE ON THE GOC TO STEP UP TO THE RETURNS 
ISSUE HAS INCREASED RECENTLY IN WAYS IT APPARENTLY CANNOT 
IGNORE.  WE NEED TO JUDGE THE GOC BY ITS ACTIONS AND BY 
RESULTS ON THE GROUND, NOT BY RHETORIC OR DECLARATIONS.  SO 
FAR, WHAT IS CLEAR -- CACIC\'S PERSONAL LEAD MADE THIS CLEAR 
-- IS THAT MORE CAREFULLY \"MANAGING\" THE RETURNS ISSUE WITH 
THE IC IS PART OF THE GOC\'S EFFORT TO MAINTAIN MOMENTUM 
TOWARD THE EU AND NATO.  IT WAS LESS OBVIOUS THAT ACTUALLY 
SOLVING THIS BIG PROBLEM IS ON THE GOC\'S AGENDA -- MOST OF 
WHAT CACIC TALKED ABOUT WAS EITHER OLD HAT TO THOSE WHO WORK 
THESE ISSUES OR INSUFFICIENTLY DETAILED TO BE GROUNDS FOR 
CONFIDENCE THAT THE GOC IS TURNING OVER A NEW LEAF. 
 
14. (C) THIS EVENT WAS ONLY THE LATEST SIGN THAT THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00337  03 OF 04  121721Z 
INCREASED IC PRESSURE IS REACHING AND RESONATING AT THE 
HIGHEST GOC LEVELS, AND THAT THE GOC KNOWS THE STAKES HAVE 
INCREASED.  THE ANNOUNCEMENT OF THE PLAN TO ADDRESS THE 
OCCUPANCY AND TENANCY RIGHTS PROBLEM IS PROOF OF THAT; THE 
ISSUE HAS LANGUISHED SINCE THE IC RAISED IT, TO LITTLE 
EFFECT, WITH PM RACAN IN DECEMBER 2001.  ON ITS FACE, CACIC\'S 
PLAN WOULD REPRESENT A REAL STEP FORWARD, BUT THE SHORTFALL 
HERE ALWAYS IS IMPLEMENTATION AND WE WILL BE WATCHING 
CAREFULLY.  CACIC\'S PRESENTATION LEFT US NO MORE CONVINCED 
THAN BEFORE THAT THE GOC HAS ANY REAL DESIRE, WILL OR INTENT 
TO ACT ON RETURNS ISSUES ESPECIALLY IN THIS ELECTION YEAR. 
 
...BUT OSCE/EU WAVERING 
------------------------ 
 
15. (C) THAT SAID, GOC PUSH BACK FOLLOWING THE IC PRINCIPALS 
JANUARY 23 LETTER TO PM RACAN SUSPENDING PARTICIPATING IN THE 
JOINT LEGAL WORKING GROUP IS HAVING AN IMPACT.  OSCE HOM 
SEMNEBY WAS QUICK, AND AT PAINS, TO PUT OUT A BEST-CASE 
LAUDATORY PRESS RELEASE ON CACIC\'S ANNOUNCED OCCUPANCY AND 
TENANCY RIGHTS PLAN.  SEMNEBY ALSO PULLED EVERY CONCEIVABLE 
PUNCH IN AN EXCESSIVELY POSITIVE BRIEFING ON THESE ISSUES TO 
THE EU WESTERN BALKANS WORKING GROUP (COWEB) IN BRUSSELS 
FEBRUARY 6.  YET AGAIN IN AN IC PANEL BRIEFING FOR A VISITING 
OSCE PARLIAMENTARY DELEGATION FEBRUARY 10, SEMNEBY TOOK A 
NOTABLY SOFTER LINE ON THE GOC THAN DID UNHCR, THE UN LIAISON 
OFFICE OR OUR OWN EMBASSY PARTICIPANT.  IT IS CLEAR TO US AND 
TO SEMNEBY\'S AMERICAN DEPUTY HOM (PROTECT) THAT SEMNEBY IS 
GETTING COLD FEET OUT OF FEAR THAT THE OSCE-GOC RELATIONSHIP 
WILL SOUR AND HE WILL END UP COLD-SHOULDERED AND VILIFIED 
LIKE HIS PREDECESSOR BERNARD PONCET.  THAT COULD HAPPEN, BUT 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00337  03 OF 04  121721Z 
IF SO IT WOULD BE OF LIMITED IMPORT FOR REAL IC INTERESTS 
HERE.  THE OSCE MISSION IS LIKE UNMOVIC -- IF THE HOST 
COUNTRY REJECTS AND OBSTRUCTS PEOPLE WHO CAN ONLY HELP IT 
RESOLVE ISSUES OF INTERNATIONAL CONCERN, BUT NOT ENFORCE, ITS 
VALUE DISAPPEARS AND IT COULD AS EASILY GO AWAY.  WE ARE 
CONVEYING TO THE OSCE MISSION AND TO SEMNEBY THAT WHILE WE 
WANT THEM TO TRY TO MAINTAIN GOOD RELATIONS WITH THE GOC, 
THEY WILL NOT HAVE OUR SUPPORT IF THEY LOSE FOCUS AND 
SACRIFICE BASIC PRINCIPLES IN THE PROCESS. 
 
16. (C) OF PERHAPS MORE CONCERN ARE INDICATIONS THAT EUROPEAN 
COMMISSION PRESSURE ALSO PEAKED LAST MONTH WITH THEIR ACTIVE 
SUPPORT FOR SUSPENDING THE JOINT LEGAL WORKING GROUP. THE 
COMMISSION DEPUTY HEAD JOINED SEMNEBY IN SOFT-PEDALING 
CRITICISM OF THE GOC AT THE OSCE PARLIAMENTARY DELEGATION 
BRIEFING.  THE COMMISSION AND OSCE MISSIONS INCREASINGLY LINK 
THEIR WORK AND OPERATE IN TANDEM; FOR EXAMPLE, SEMNEBY AND 
THE COMMISSION DEPUTY MET TOGETHER WITH CACIC THE WEEK BEFORE 
HIS PUBLIC BRIEFING, AND THE TWO INVARIABLY LINK THEIR 
MANDATES AND POLICY AGENDAS IN PRIVATE AND PUBLIC STATEMENTS 
HERE IN ZAGREB.  TALKING TO MOST EU AMBASSADORS HERE, WE FIND 
A BROAD MAJORITY CRITICAL OF GOC PERFORMANCE BUT NOT EAGER TO 
DO ANYTHING THAT WOULD OBSTRUCT HANDLING OF CROATIA\'S 
IMMINENT EU APPLICATION IN ANY WAY OTHER THAN THE NORMAL 
