TAGS: PREL, PGOV, KPAO, KMDR, HR, IZ 
SUBJECT: TFIZ01: CROATIA: POLITICIANS BACK GOC OPPOSITION 
TO MILITARY ACTION WITHOUT NEW UNSCR 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00631  02 OF 02  191658Z 
\"VJESNIK\'S\" LEADING FOREIGN AFFAIRS COLUMNIST, LAMENTS THE 
GOC\'S \"PERILOUS SYNDROME OF REACTING OFFICIALLY TO UNOFFICIAL 
RUMORS.\"  \"FOR THE MOST PART, EUROPE IS SILENT, EXCEPT FOR 
CROATIA.\"  CROATIA WILL NOT PLAY ANY ROLE IN THE DECISION TO 
ATTACK IRAQ AND ITS \"EUROPEAN CLAMORING\" IN THE PRESS AND 
PUBLIC WILL NOT DO ANY GOOD EITHER, HE WROTE IN HIS MARCH 18 
COLUMN.  HE ADDED THAT IF CROATIA\'S \"NEW\" POSITION TO OPPOSE 
MILITARY ACTION OUTSIDE THE UN FRAMEWORK WOULD HAVE RULED OUT 
NATO ATTACKS ON THE FRY.  WHILE HE AGREED WITH RACAN\'S 
DECISION TO POSTPONE HIS TRIP TO LONDON, HE LAMBASTED RACAN\'S 
\"ILLOGICAL\" DECISION TO TALK TO THE PRESS ABOUT WHY.  IN 
SPEAKING ABOUT CANCELLING THE VISIT, RACAN SAID THAT 
\'OBVIOUSLY WE ARE NOT ON THE SAME SIDE\' ... THIS STATEMENT IS 
ONE OF A SERIES OF DIPLOMATIC GAFFES WHICH ARE UNFORTUNATELY 
TYPICAL FOR A CROATIAN FOREIGN POLICY BURDENED WITH 
SHORT-SIGHTEDNESS AND IGNORANCE.\"  BOTH LOPANDIC AND AN 
INTERVIEWER FROM ANOTHER NEWSPAPER EXPRESSED THE BELIEF AS 
OUTLINED IN REFTEL THAT THE GOC WAS SIDING WITH FRANCE IN 
ORDER TO CURRY FAVOR FOR ITS EU APPLICATION. 
ROSSIN 
 
