NOW THE ROMA -- VIA NATIONAL STRATEGIES.  INVARIABLY THEY 
DESCRIBE A LARGE NUMBER OF ACTIVITIES, BUT ARE SHORT ON 
DETAIL, AND CONTAIN UNREALISTIC DEADLINES AND VAGUE LINES OF 
RESPONSIBILITY.  IN ADDITION, FUNDING FOR ACTIVITIES IS 
USUALLY NOT ADDRESSED.  THE ROMA STRATEGY INCLUDES SOME 
SPECIFIC BUDGET ESTIMATES; WE COUNTED OVER $4 MILLION FOR 
ACTIVITIES IN 2003 ALONE, BUT THERE IS NO INDICATION WHERE 
THAT MONEY WILL COME FROM, OR IF THE GOC WILL BE ABLE TO 
ALLOCATE FUNDING FOR ACTIVITIES THIS YEAR.  NATIONAL 
STRATEGIES SOUND GOOD IN THEORY, BUT AT THEIR BEST THEY 
REMAIN AN EXPRESSION OF INTENT -- WHETHER OR NOT THE GOC WILL 
FOLLOW THROUGH WITH CONCRETE ACTION ON ISSUES OF CONCERN TO 
THE ROMA REMAINS TO BE SEEN.  END COMMENT. 
