TAGS: PREL, PREF, PGOV, ECON, MARR, MASS, HR, BK 
SUBJECT: CROATIA PROVIDING LIMITED SUPPORT TO CROATS IN BIH 
 
DETERMINES WHICH PROJECTS IT WILL SUPPORT IN BIH.  THE MONEY 
CAN BE USED TO REBUILD CHURCHES, HOSPITALS, LIBRARIES, 
SCHOOLS OR TO PROVIDE MATERIALS AND EQUIPMENT TO THOSE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00866  02 OF 02  181416Z 
INSTITUTIONS.  WHILE THE AIM IS TO DEEPEN TIES TO THE CROAT 
COMMUNITY, THE MFA MAINTAINS THAT GOC DOES NOT DISCRIMINATE 
BY SUPPORTING PROJECTS THAT ARE EXCLUSIVELY FOR CROATS.  OUR 
CONTACTS MAINTAIN THAT SERBS AND MUSLIMS HAVE ACCESS TO THE 
PUBLIC FACILITIES THAT ARE LOCATED IN VARIOUS COMMUNITIES. 
 
7. (C) THERE HAVE BEEN NO COMPLAINTS FROM OHR OR THE IC IN 
BOSNIA CONCERNING THE USE OF THESE CULTURAL FUNDS.  THE ONLY 
COMPLAINTS HAVE COME FROM BOSNIAN CROAT LEADERS (HDZ) WHO 
CLAIM THAT THE GOC IS PROVIDING ONLY \"PEANUTS.\"  (COMMENT: 
THIS IS TRUE COMPARED TO THE $85 MILLION PER YEAR THE TUDJMAN 
GOVERNMENT USED TO PROVIDE TO THE BOSNIAN CROATS DURING AND 
AFTER THE WAR.  THIS MONEY, WHICH WAS CHANNELED THROUGH THE 
NOW DEFUNCT HERCEGOVACKA BANKA, WAS SUPPOSED TO BE USED TO 
PURCHASE MILITARY EQUIPMENT, PAY SALARIES OF HVO SOLDIERS, 
AND PROVIDE SOCIAL ASSISTANCE TO CROATS IN BOSNIA.  MUCH OF 
IT WAS STOLEN BY THE CRIMINAL BOSNIAN CROAT LEADERSHIP. END 
COMMENT.) 
 
HEALTH INSURANCE 
---------------- 
 
8. (C) BIH AMBASSADOR TO CROATIA DIZDAREVIC TOLD US THAT THE 
GOC DOES NOT PROVIDE DIRECT PAYMENTS TO THE GOBIH FOR HEALTH 
INSURANCE FOR ETHNIC CROATS IN BOSNIA.  RATHER, THE GOC 
ALLOWS THEM TO RECEIVE HEALTH CARE IN CROATIA AT COSTS 
SIMILAR TO WHAT CROATIAN CITIZENS PAY.  THEY ARE NOT TREATED 
AS FOREIGNERS, WHO PAY HIGHER COSTS.  CROATS IN BOSNIA THAT 
USE HEALTHCARE FACILITIES IN BOSNIA RECEIVE COVERAGE UNDER 
BOSNIA,S HEALTHCARE SYSTEM.  THE GOC IS SEEKING TO 
DISCOURAGE CROATS IN BOSNIA FROM TRAVELING TO CROATIA BY 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00866  02 OF 02  181416Z 
REBUILDING AND EXPANDING SERVICES PROVIDED BY THE MAIN 
HOSPITAL IN MOSTAR. 
 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
9. (C) WE ARE CONFIDENT THAT GOC-PROVIDED ASSISTANCE TO 
CROATS IN BOSNIA IS TRANSPARENT AND DONE IN COOPERATION WITH 
GOBIH OFFICIALS.  THE TYPES OF ASSISTANCE BEING PROVIDED 
OUGHT TO HAVE A STABILIZING EFFECT IN BIH.  IT ALSO ALLOWS 
THE GOC TO CLAIM CREDIT FOR SEEKING TO MAINTAIN GOOD 
RELATIONS WITH ITS NEIGHBOR.  AMBASSADOR DIZDAREVIC TOLD US 
THAT THE GOBIH DOES NOT HAVE ANY MISGIVINGS ABOUT GOC 
INTENTIONS WITHIN BOSNIA AND IS PLEASED WITH THE ROLE THE GOC 
IS PLAYING.  THE GOC WOULD LIKE TO REDUCE THE AMOUNT OF 
SUPPORT IT IS PROVIDING TO CROATS IN BOSNIA, PARTICULARLY 
PENSION PAYMENTS AND ACCESS TO SUBSIDIZED HEALTH CARE. 
RESOLVING THE ISSUE OF DUAL CITIZENSHIP WILL BE THE ONLY WAY 
FOR THE GOC TO REMEDY THIS ISSUE. 
 
ROSSIN 
