SUBJECT: IMPLEMENTING THE CROATIA EXBS PROGRAM 
 
GROUP COMPRISED OF DAO AND POL SECTIONS REPRESENTATIVES, THE 
DOJ/ICITAP POLICE ADVISOR, U.S. CUSTOMS/SECI ADVISOR, AND 
EXBS PROGRAM MANAGER STEVE HAYWARD.  THE WORKING GROUP 
CONCURRED WITH THE GENERAL THRUST OF THE REF A ROAD MAP, 
PARTICULARLY ITS EMPHASIS ON PORT AND MARITIME SECURITY AND 
EXPORT CONTROL TRAINING.  THE DOJ/ICITAP ADVISOR COMMENTED 
THAT THE USD 55,000 IN \"TRAIN-THE-TRAINER\" EQUIPMENT 
DUPLICATED ONGOING INL- AND SEED-FUNDED ACTIVITIES.  WE 
RECOMMEND THAT THIS FUNDING BE REALLOCATED TO OTHER EXBS 
NEEDS.  THE EXBS ADVISOR WAS ASKED TO FOLLOW UP ON A INFORMAL 
PLEDGE OF WMD-PROGRAM IMPLEMENTERS TO DELIVER USD 75,000 IN 
RADIATION PAGERS THROUGH THE WMD PROGRAM, FREEING UP THOSE 
RESOURCES FOR OTHER EXBS ACTIVITIES.  THE WORKING GROUP ALSO 
RECOMMENDED THAT THE EXBS ADVISOR INCORPORATE IN THE DRAFT 
EXBS CROATIA 2003 COUNTRY PLAN PROGRAMS TO SUPPORT AND 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
