NURTURE THE GOC\'S NASCENT INTER-AGENCY BORDER SECURITY AND 
CRISIS COORDINATION BODY. 
 
NEXT STEPS 
---------- 
 
7. (SBU)  POST PROPOSES THE FOLLOWING NOTIONAL TIME-LINE FOR 
ENGAGING WITH THE GOC AND OTHER BILATERAL DONORS ON THE EXBS 
PROGRAM: 
 
-- BY APRIL 30:  NOTIFY THE GOC THAT THE EXBS PROGRAM HAS 
BEEN APPROVED, OUTLINE OUR VISION FOR IMPLEMENTING THE 
PROGRAM AND DELIVER THE EXBS \"TRIP REPORT\" (REF B). 
 
-- APRIL 30:  INFORMALLY BRIEF THE LOCAL INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITY DONORS ASSISTANCE GROUP (EU, OSCE, FRANCE, UK, 
GERMANY, AUSTRIA, CANADA) ON THE EXBS INITIATIVE.  BEGIN 
INTENSIVE CONSULTATIONS WITH THE GERMANS AND AUSTRIANS, WHO 
DIRECT THE EU/CARDS BORDER POLICE AND CUSTOMS REFORM 
INITIATIVES. 
 
-- MID-MAY:  EMBASSY EXBS WORKING GROUP TO REVIEW DRAFT EXBS 
2003 CROATIA COUNTRY PLAN THAT EXBS LJUBLJAN IS IN THE 
PROCESS OF DRAFTING. 
 
-- EARLY JUNE:  PRESENT EXBS 2003 PROPOSED WORK PLAN TO THE 
MFA AND TO REPRESENTATIVES OF THE GOC\'S MARITIME AND BORDER 
SECURITY COMMITTEE FOR COMMENT AND APPROVAL. 
 
