"7716","4/29/2003 15:18","03ZAGREB950","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","03STATE99664","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.


 ","C O N F I D E N T I A L ZAGREB 000950 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
FOR EUR/SCE NYSTROM 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 04/29/2013 
TAGS: PREL, ECON, EFIN, SI, BK, MK, SR, HK 
SUBJECT: CROATIA WILL NOT ACCEPT TRANSFER OF NBY FUNDS 

REF: STATE 99664 (NOTAL) 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: POLECON COUNSELOR NICHOLAS HILL, FOR REASONS 1.5 (B AND 
D) 
 
1.  (C) ON APRIL 29, WE MET WITH MIROSLAV KOVACIC, HEAD OF 
THE AMERICAS DEPARTMENT AT THE MFA, AT HIS REQUEST.  KOVACIC 
SAID THE MINISTRY HAD HEARD FROM THE CROATIAN NATIONAL BANK 
(CNB) THAT IT HAD BEEN REQUESTED TO ACCEPT A TRANSFER OF 
$54.6 MILLION AS CROATIA\'S PART OF UNFROZEN NBY ASSETS IN THE 
U.S.  KOVACIC REFERRED BACK TO OUR DEMARCHES OVER THE LAST 
SEVERAL MONTHS, WHICH HAD DESCRIBED A PROCESS IN WHICH, IF 
THE USG DID NOT RECEIVE HOLD HARMLESS ASSURANCES FROM ALL 
PARTIES, THE USG WOULD PROCEED WITH A GENERAL UNBLOCKING. 
KOVACIC ASKED FOR CONFIRMATION THAT THE TELEX FROM THE 
FEDERAL RESERVE BANK IN NEW YORK DID INDEED INDICATE THAT THE 
USG HAD DECIDED TO DISBURSE THE MONEY TO EACH SUCCESSOR STATE. 
 
2.  (C) USING REFTEL POINTS, WE CONFIRMED THAT THE USG HAD 
DECIDED THAT TRANSFERRING THE FUNDS DIRECTLY TO EACH 
GOVERNMENT WOULD BE THE MOST EFFECTIVE AND EFFICIENT WAY TO 
GET THE ASSETS TO THE SUCCESSOR COUNTRIES.  WE STRESSED THAT 
WE WOULD BE CONCERNED IF CROATIA TOOK ANY LEGAL STEPS THAT 
WOULD INTERFERE WITH THIS EFFORT TO RESOLVE ISSUES LEFT OVER 
FROM THE MILOSEVIC ERA.  FINALLY, WE BELIEVED THAT THE ISSUE 
OF NBY ASSETS FROZEN IN THE US UNDER MILOSEVIC-ERA SANCTIONS 
AND THE AGREEMENT ON SUCCESSION ISSUES (ASI) SHOULD BE 
HANDLED SEPARATELY. 
 
3.  (C) KOVACIC COUNTERED THAT GOC LAWYERS SAID THE TWO 
    ISSUES WERE LINKED.  THE GOC COULD NOT ACCEPT THE MONEY, 
BECAUSE THAT WOULD MEAN ACCEPTING THE KEY OF THE ASI, WHICH 
HAD NOT BEEN RATIFIED BY PARLIAMENT.  HE EXPRESSED HIS 
STRONG, PERSONAL DISAPPOINTMENT THAT THIS OUTCOME WAS NOT IN 
LINE WITH WHAT THE USG HAD TOLD THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT. 
KOVACIC SAID CROATIA HAD BEEN VERY HOPEFUL WHEN THE USG 
OFFERED ASSISTANCE TO HELP OBTAIN AN EXPLANATION OF WHAT HAD 
HAPPENED TO THE NBY DEPOSITS -- AN OFFER THAT SEEMED TO 
DISAPPEAR SUDDENLY AFTER AN OFAC VISIT TO ZAGREB AND BELGRADE 
IN DECEMBER. 
 
4.  (C) WE EXPLAINED THAT THE OFFER WAS RESCINDED AFTER 
OFFICIAL VISITORS TO CROATIA, DISMAYED BY THE HARD LINE TAKEN 
BY CROATIAN INTERLOCUTORS, CAME TO THE CONCLUSION THAT 
CROATIA WAS NOT LOOKING FOR AN EXPLANATION THAT WOULD SMOOTH 
THE WAY TO RATIFICATION OF THE ASI, BUT RATHER FURTHER 
REASONS TO BE INTRANSIGENT AND TO DEMAND COMPENSATION.  WE 
REITERATED THAT IT WOULD BE UNWISE FOR CROATIA TO TRY TO 
BRING A COURT CASE AGAINST THE USG OVER THIS ISSUE.  KOVACIC 
SAID IT WAS TOO EARLY TO SAY, BUT IT MIGHT IN THE END BE 
NECESSARY. 
MOON 
 
NNNN 
"
"7730","4/30/2003 10:11","03ZAGREB954","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 01 OF 02 ZAGREB 000954 
 
SIPDIS 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 04/27/2013 
TAGS: PREL, PGOV, PGOV, HR, HRPREL, NATO, Defense Reform (Mil & NATO) 
SUBJECT: CROATIA AT THE SIGNING OF THE ADRIATIC CHARTER 
 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: CDA PATRICK S. MOON FOR REASONS 1.5 (B,D) 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        ZAGREB  00954  01 OF 02  301022Z 
1.  (C) CROATIA TOOK SOME TIME TO WARM TO THE IDEA OF THE 
ADRIATIC CHARTER.  BECAUSE OF ITS FEAR OF BEING TRAPPED IN A 
NEW BALKAN ALLIANCE AND ALSO BECAUSE OF AN ARROGANT 
ASSUMPTION THAT ITS MORE ADVANCED LEVEL OF ECONOMIC 
DEVELOPMENT MADE IT A BETTER NATO CANDIDATE, CROATIA RESISTED 
TYING ITS FORTUNES TO ALBANIA AND MACEDONIA.  BUT CROATIA HAS 
SINCE BECOME AN ENTHUSIASTIC SUPPORTER OF THE CHARTER.  THE 
GOVERNMENT AND ESPECIALLY FM PICULA HAVE TAKEN US AT OUR WORD 
THAT EACH CANDIDATE WILL BE EVALUATED ON AN INDIVIDUAL BASIS. 
 THEY ALSO REALIZE THAT BY SIGNING, CROATIA CAN DEMONSTRATE 
ITS COMMITMENT TO WORKING COOPERATIVELY WITH OTHER 
PROSPECTIVE ALLIES.  FINALLY, PICULA HOPES THAT THE CHARTER 
WILL ENSURE THAT THE U.S. REMAINS COMMITTED TO FUTURE 
EXPANSION. 
 
2.  (C) WE EXPECT THAT THE SECRETARY\'S SCHEDULE WILL ALLOW 
VERY LITTLE TIME FOR SUBSTANTIVE CONVERSATION WITH FM PICULA. 
 THERE ARE, HOWEVER, A NUMBER OF ISSUES WHICH MAY COME UP IN 
WHICH THE SECRETARY\'S ENGAGEMENT WOULD BE VERY HELPFUL. 
 
-------------------------------- 
UN-FROZEN ASSETS FROM YUGOSLAVIA 
-------------------------------- 
 
3.  (C) CROATIA CONTINUES TO OBJECT TO OUR FORMULA TO 
UN-BLOCK FUNDS FROZEN IN THE U.S. BY MILOSEVIC-ERA SANCTIONS. 
 
POINT TO MAKE: 
 
- CROATIA NEEDS TO PUT THIS ISSUE IN THE PAST, AS OTHER 
SUCCESSOR STATES HAVE, AND ACCEPT THE TRANSFER OF FUNDS. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  00954  01 OF 02  301022Z 
 
-------------------- 
ARTICLE 98 AGREEMENT 
-------------------- 
 
4.  (C) CROATIA HAS NOT BEGUN TO NEGOTIATE AN ARTICLE 98 
AGREEMENT, AND MILITARY ASSISTANCE ESSENTIAL TO CROATIA\'S 
MODERNIZATION AND INTEROPERABILITY GOALS IS IN JEOPARDY. 
 
POINT TO MAKE: 
 
- URGE YOU TO BEGIN NEGOTIATIONS FOR AN ARTICLE 98 AGREEMENT 
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.  THE JULY 1 DEADLINE IS LOOMING AND 
CROATIA MUST NOT COUNT ON A WAIVER. 
 
---------------- 
ICTY COOPERATION 
---------------- 
 
5.  (C) CROATIA MET THE TRIBUNAL\'S RECENT DEADLINES FOR 
COOPERATION, BUT ONLY AT THE LAST MINUTE AND ONLY UNDER HEAVY 
PRESSURE.  THE INDICTMENT WAS SERVED ON GENERAL BOBETKO, 
REQUESTS FOR DOCUMENTS ARE ON THE WAY TO BEING FULFILLED, AND 
FUGITIVE ICTY INDICTEE IVICA RAJIC HAS BEEN APPREHENDED. 
 
POINTS TO MAKE: 
 
- PROMPT AND FULL COOPERATION WITH ICTY IS ESSENTIAL AND 
NON-NEGOTIABLE AND IS A LITMUS TEST FOR CROATIA\'S READINESS 
TO ADVANCE IN THE PROCESS OF INTEGRATION INTO NATO AND THE 
EU. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  00954  01 OF 02  301022Z 
 
- URGE YOU TO REDOUBLE YOUR EFFORTS TO APPREHEND ICTY 
FUGITIVE ANTE GOTOVINA. 
 
--------------- 
REFUGEE RETURNS 
--------------- 
 
6.  (C) CROATIA HAS NOT DONE ENOUGH ON THIS ISSUE.  DESPITE 
PROGRESS ON RECONSTRUCTION OF WAR-DAMAGED HOUSES, THE 
GOVERNMENT HAS FAILED TO MEET DEADLINES ON EVICTIONS OF 
THOUSANDS OF CROAT \"SQUATTERS\" IN HOMES BELONGING TO ETHNIC 
SERBS WHO FLED DURING THE WAR, NOR HAS IT MET COMMITMENTS TO 
COMPENSATE OWNERS.  NOW THE RACAN GOVERNMENT IS RESISTING 
ENGAGEMENT WITH THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY ON THIS ISSUE. 
 
POINT TO MAKE: 
 
- IT IS THE CONSENSUS OF THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY THAT 
YOUR GOVERNMENT IS NOT DOING ENOUGH TO SUPPORT REFUGEE 
RETURNS.  THIS IS A SERIOUS ISSUE, AND UNTIL IT IS ADDRESSED 
IN A SERIOUS, SYSTEMATIC WAY, IT BLOCKS CROATIA\'S INTEGRATION 
INTO EURO-ATLANTIC INSTITUTIONS. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
