SIPDIS 
 
STATE FOR S/WCI, EUR/SCE, INL/AAE, AND EUR/ACE 
THE HAGUE FOR JOHNSON/KAYE/WHEATON 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/06/2013 
TAGS: KAWC, KJUS, PREL, KJUS, PREL, UNSC, ICTY, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: ICTY/CROATIA: IMPROVING GOC COOPERATION, RAJIC 
CASE MOVING AHEAD 
 
REF: A. ZAGREB 925 
 
     B. ZAGREB 761 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: POLOFF ROBERT SILBERSTEIN, REASON 1.5 (B) AND (D) 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1. (C) ICTY ZAGREB RESREP THOMAS OSORIO TOLD US MAY 5 THAT 
THE GOC HAS IMPROVED COOPERATION IN THE MONTH FOLLOWING THE 
VISIT OF OTP CHIEF PROSECUTOR DEL PONTE TO ZAGREB.  THE GOC 
LARGELY HAS FULFILLED OUTSTANDING DOCUMENT REQUESTS AND 
APPEARED SOMEWHAT MORE PROACTIVE IN THE GOTOVINA CASE -- IT 
IS SET TO ISSUE A REWARD FOR HIS ARREST ON MAY 10.  THE IVICA 
RAJIC TRANSFER TO ICTY CUSTODY APPEARED TO BE MOVING AHEAD AS 
WELL AS THE GOC INVESTIGATION AGAINST THOSE THAT SHELTERED 
AND SUPPORTED HIM AND OTHER CROATIAN PIFWCS.  THE ONLY BLACK 
CLOUD FOR OSORIO WAS DEL PONTE\'S POOR HANDLING OF A ZAGREB 
DIPLOMATIC CORPS REQUEST FOR AN \"ICTY ISSUES CHECKLIST.\" 
DESPITE OSORIO\'S WARNINGS, DEL PONTE CIRCULATED A 
POORLY-CRAFTED DOCUMENT THAT -- IF LEAKED -- COULD CLOUD 
GOC-ICTY RELATIONS.  END SUMMARY 
 
IMPROVED COOPERATION 
-------------------- 
 
2. (C) ON MAY 5, ICTY ZAGREB RESREP THOMAS OSORIO TOLD US 
THAT THE GOC -- FOR NOW -- HAS BEEN LIVING UP TO THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        ZAGREB  01037  01 OF 02  091539Z 
COMMITMENTS PM RACAN MADE WHEN OTP CHIEF PROSECUTOR DEL PONTE 
VISITED ZAGREB A MONTH EARLIER (REF B): 
 
-- THE OTP RECEIVED THE BULK OF THE RAW CENSUS DATA IT 
REQUESTED.  WHILE SOME DATA ARE MISSING, OSORIO -- AT THIS 
POINT -- CONSIDERS THIS TO BE A TECHNICAL OVERSIGHT ON THE 
PART OF THE GOC CENSUS BUREAU AND NOT A GOC ATTEMPT TO 
OBFUSCATE. 
 
-- THE OTP IS WORKING WITH STATE PROSECUTOR BAJIC TO DEVELOP 
THE EXACT LANGUAGE THAT HE WOULD USE TO OBTAIN CROATIAN COURT 
PERMISSION TO ACCESS PRIVREDNA BANKA RECORDS RELATED TO GOC 
FINANCING OF THE WAR IN BOSNIA. 
 
-- THE OTP RECEIVED OVER 1100 PAGES OF PERSONAL DOCUMENTS OF 
THE FORMER GOC MINISTER OF DEFENSE GOJKO SUSAK, A KEY OTP 
DOCUMENT REQUEST.  OTP INVESTIGATORS ARE CLOSELY ANALYZING 
THE FILES, WHICH COULD HAVE BEARING ON A WIDE RANGE OF ICTY 
CASES, INCLUDING THE BLASKIC APPEAL. 
 
-- THE OTP ALSO WAS GIVEN ACCESS TO THE MILITARY ARCHIVES OF 
THE SEVEN CROATIAN ARMY BRIGADES THAT OPERATED IN BOSNIA FROM 
1992 TO 1994. 
 
GOTOVINA 
-------- 
 
3. (C) OSORIO SAID THAT, IN EARLY MAY, THE HEAD OF THE GOC 
OFFICE FOR COOPERATION WITH ICTY REASSURED HIM THAT THE GOC 
DECISION TO ISSUE A REWARD FOR ICTY FUGITIVE ANTE GOTOVINA 
WAS IRONCLAD.  IN A MEETING WITH US ON MAY 8, DIRECTOR 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        ZAGREB  01037  01 OF 02  091539Z 
GENERAL OF POLICE RANKO OSTOJIC CONFIRMED THAT THE GOC WOULD 
ISSUE THE GOTOVINA REWARD ON MAY 10 IN THE AMOUNT OF 350,000 
KUNA (USD 55,000).  THAT AMOUNT, SAID OSTOJIC, IS AT LEAST 
SEVEN TIMES HIGHER THAN ANY OTHER REWARD ISSUED IN CROATIAN 
HISTORY.  OSTOJIC ALSO TOLD US THAT POLICE IN THE ZADAR AREA 
-- CENTRAL DALMATIA -- HAVE BEEN GIVEN SPECIFIC ORDERS TO 
TAIL AND SURVEIL GOTOVINA FAMILY MEMBERS AND KNOWN 
SYMPATHIZERS. 
 
IVICA RAJIC 
----------- 
 
4. (C) ON APRIL 30, THE ZAGREB COUNTY COURT RULED THAT THE 
ICTY HAS JURISDICTION OVER IVICA RAJIC AND APPROVED HIS 
TRANSFER TO THE HAGUE.  RAJIC\'S LAWYERS APPEALED THE DECISION 
TO THE CROATIAN SUPREME COURT, BUT LEGAL EXPERTS TOLD US THE 
APPEAL HAS NO CHANCE OF PROSPERING.  RAJIC SHOULD BE IN ICTY 
CUSTODY NO LATER THAN THE END OF MAY. 
 
5. (C) OSORIO TOLD US THAT DEL PONTE, DURING HER MEETING WITH 
PM RACAN, MADE IT CLEAR THAT SHE WANTS ALL INFORMATION THAT 
THE GOC DEVELOPS ON HOW RAJIC LIVED FREELY (UNDER ALIAS) IN 
CROATIA FOR SEVEN YEARS AFTER HIS OTP INDICTMENT.  RACAN 
REPORTEDLY PROMISED HER THAT A \"FULL REPORT WOULD BE 
 
