"14616","3/5/2004 12:23","04ZAGREB380","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L ZAGREB 000380 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
DEPARTMENT FOR S/WCI AND EUR/SCE 
THE HAGUE FOR KAYE 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 03/06/2008 
TAGS: PGOV, PREL, KAWC, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: CROATIAN PRESS REPORTS NEW ICTY INDICTMENTS 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: DCM PATRICK S. MOON FOR REASON 1.5 (B, D) 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1.  (SBU) THE CROATIAN PRESS IS WIDELY REPORTING THAT THE 
    GOVERNMENT OF CROATIA HAS RECEIVED NEW SEALED ICTY 
INDICTMENTS FROM THE HAGUE TRIBUNAL.  THE GOVERNMENT IS 
REFUSING TO COMMENT, BUT THE PRESS CITES THAT SANADER AND 
OTHER HDZ LEADERS ARE WORKING HARD TO MANAGE POLITICAL 
FALLOUT BEFORE THE INDICTMENTS ARE MADE PUBLIC.  THE GOC 
RECOGNIZES THAT ITS COOPERATION WITH THE TRIBUNAL WILL BE 
UNDER THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY\'S MICROSCOPE; SANADER\'S 
GOVERNMENT KNOWS THAT DECISIONS ABOUT CROATIA\'S SUITABILITY 
AS AN EU CANDIDATE WILL DEPEND ON HIS ACTIONS.  END SUMMARY. 
 
2.  (SBU) ON MARCH 5, ALL OF THE CROATIAN PRESS REPORTED THAT 
NEW INDICTMENTS AGAINST MLADEN MARKAC AND IVAN CERMAK HAD 
BEEN HANDED DOWN BY THE ICTY PROSECUTOR AND THAT THEY HAD 
BEEN DELIVERED UNDER SEAL TO THE GOC OFFICE FOR COOPERATION 
WITH ICTY ON FEBRUARY 26.  THE FACT OF THE INDICTMENTS HAS 
BECOME AN OPEN SECRET IN ZAGREB, BUT GOC LEADERS REFUSE TO 
COMMENT OR SPECULATE ON THE RECORD.  INDICTMENTS AGAINST 
MARKAC AND CERMAK FOR THEIR ACTIVITIES DURING AND AFTER 
\"OPERATION STORM\" IN NOVEMBER 1995 HAVE BEEN EXPECTED IN 
ZAGREB SINCE JANUARY. 
 
3.  (SBU) PM SANADER REPORTEDLY BRIEFED PRESIDENT MESIC ABOUT 
THE INDICTMENTS ON MARCH 1.  MESIC IN TURN BRIEFED FORMER PM 
RACAN (NOW LEADER OF THE OPPOSITION) ON MARCH 2.  ACCORDING 
TO PRESS REPORTS, SANADER HAS ALSO DISCUSSED THE INDICTMENTS 
WITH ANTO DJAPIC, LEADER OF THE EXTREME NATIONALIST CROATIAN 
PARTY OF RIGHT (HSP) IN ORDER TO TEMPER THE HSP REACTION AND 
THEREBY COVER THE GOVERNMENT\'S NATIONALIST POLITICAL FLANK. 
THE PRESS REPORTS THAT SANADER WANTS THE TWO INDICTEES TO 
ANNOUNCE THE INDICTMENTS THEMSELVES, AT THE SAME TIME AS THEY 
PUBLICLY AGREE TO TRAVEL TO THE HAGUE TO ANSWER THE CHARGES. 
    THE GOVERNMENT WILL REPORTEDLY OFFER THE COURT THE SAME 
\"GUARANTEES\" FOR MARKAC AND CERMAK WHICH IT GAVE ON BEHALF OF 
ICTY INDICTEE RAHIM ADEMI, WHO WAS RELEASED BY ICTY TO AWAIT 
TRIAL AT HOME IN CROATIA. 
 
4.  (SBU) CERMAK IS ALREADY ON THE PUBLIC RECORD AS DECLARING 
HIS READINESS TO GO THE HAGUE IF INDICTED.  IN A RECENT PRESS 
INTERVIEW CERMAK NOTED THAT HE HAD ALREADY BEEN \"INTERVIEWED\" 
BY ICTY INVESTIGATORS.  HE TOLD THE PRESS THAT HE \"WOULD 
CONTINUE TO COOPERATE WITH THE HAGUE\" SO AS \"NOT TO CAUSE 
PROBLEMS FOR HIS HOMELAND,\" A CLEAR REFERENCE TO THE DAMAGE 
TO CROATIA\'S EU BID CAUSED BY ICTY PIFWC ANTE GOTOVINA\'S 
FUGITIVE STATUS. 
 
INDICTMENTS AGAINST BOSNIAN CROATS 
---------------------------------- 
 
6.  (SBU) CROATIA\'S PRESS REPORTS THAT ICTY INDICTMENTS HAVE 
BEEN HANDED DOWN ON THREE BOSNIAN CROATS, MILIVOJ PETKOVIC, 
JADRANKO PRLIC AND SLOBODAN PRALJAK, ALL FOR ACTIVITIES 
DURING THE WAR IN BIH.  PETKOVIC AND PRALJAK WERE HVO 
COMMANDERS AND PRLIC WAS PRESIDENT OF THE SHORT-LIVED 
PSEUDO-STATE OF HERCEG-BOSNA.  PRALJAK AND PETKOVIC BOTH 
RESIDE IN ZAGREB.  PETKOVIC IS CURRENTLY THE INSPECTOR 
GENERAL OF THE CROATIAN ARMY AND PRALJAK (WHO WAS RESPONSIBLE 
FOR THE DESTRUCTION OF THE ANCIENT MOSTAR BRIDGE) IS A 
BUSINESSMAN PROMINENT IN ZAGREB HIGH SOCIETY.  WHILE THESE 
THREE INDICTMENTS WILL LIKELY BE LESS POLITICALLY SENSITIVE 
-- THEY ARE ASSOCIATED WITH THE WAR IN BOSNIA AND NOT WITH 
THE RECAPTURE OF CROATIAN TERRITORY IN \"OPERATION STORM\" -- 
THEY WILL ALSO PRESENT POLITICAL CHALLENGES TO THE SANADER 
    GOVERNMENT. 
 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
7.  (C) WHILE THESE INDICTMENTS PRESENT A POLITICAL CHALLENGE 
TO THE SANADER GOVERNMENT, THEY ALSO PRESENT AN IMPORTANT 
OPPORTUNITY.  SANADER HAS BEEN SEEKING TO CONVINCE THE 
INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY -- AND PARTICULARLY EU DECISIONMAKERS 
-- THAT HIS GOVERNMENT IS DOING ALL IT CAN TO COOPERATE FULLY 
WITH THE ICTY, DESPITE CROATIA\'S FAILURE TO APPREHEND AND 
TRANSFER GOTOVINA.  IF SANADER CAN \"DELIVER\" ON THE NEW SET 
OF INDICTMENTS, HIS ARGUMENT ON GOTOVINA WILL BE 
STRENGTHENED.  QUICK AND DECISIVE ACTION COULD ALSO OVERCOME 
SPECIFIC BRITISH AND DUTCH RESERVATIONS THAT ARE BLOCKING 
CROATIA\'S EU CANDIDACY. 
FRANK 
 
NNNN 
"
"14620","3/5/2004 13:23","04ZAGREB382","Embassy Zagreb","UNCLASSIFIED//FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY","","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.


 ","UNCLAS ZAGREB 000382 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
SENSITIVE 
 
E.O. 12958: N/A 
TAGS: PREL, PGOV, ECON, EFIN, HR, Regional Issues 
SUBJECT: AGREEMENT ON SUCCESSION ISSUES RATIFIED 
 
SENSITIVE BUT UNCLASSIFIED - PLS PROTECT ACCORDINGLY 
 
1.  (U) SUMMARY:  LATE ON MARCH 3, THE CROATIAN 
PARLIAMENT RATIFIED THE AGREEMENT ON SUCCESSION ISSUES 
AND ADOPTED A CONCLUSION COMMITTING THE GOVERNMENT TO 
CONTINUE THE INVESTIGATION INTO $589 MILLION WHICH ARE 
\"MISSING\" FROM JOINT VENTURE BANK ACCOUNTS.  CROATIA IS 
    THE LAST COUNTRY OF THE FORMER YUGOSLAVIA SUCCESSOR 
STATES TO RATIFY THE AGREEMENT FIRST REACHED IN VIENNA 
IN 2001.  END SUMMARY. 
 
2.  (U) LAST MONTH THE NEW HDZ-LED CROATIAN GOVERNMENT 
PROPOSED TO PARLIAMENT THAT RATIFICATION MOVE FORWARD ON 
THE SUCCESSION AGREEMENT OF THE FORMER YUGOSLAVIA, WHICH 
ONLY CROATIA HAD NOT RATIFIED.  PRIME MINISTER IVO 
SANADER POINTED OUT THAT IT WAS THE COUNTRY\'S OBLIGATION 
TO RATIFY THIS AGREEMENT.  FOREIGN MINISTER MIOMIR ZUZUL 
SAID THAT PROLONGING THE RATIFICATION OF THE AGREEMENT 
WAS DAMAGING FOR POLITICAL REASONS AND ALSO BECAUSE 
PROPERTY VALUES SUBJECT TO THE SUCCESSION AGREEMENT WERE 
DETERIORATING.  THE PREVIOUS GOVERNMENT, NERVOUS ABOUT 
WHAT SORT OF CRITICISM THE DEAL WOULD FACE, HAD REFUSED 
TO SEND IT TO PARLIAMENT FOR A VOTE. 
 
3.  (SBU) AT THE EXPERT LEVEL, ZDRAVKO ROGIC, A TOP 
ADVISOR ON SUCCESSION ISSUES, WHO UNDER THE PREVIOUS 
GOVERNMENT HAD VIGOROUSLY OPPOSED THE DEAL WITHOUT A 
FULL ACCOUNTING OF THE MISSING MONEY, TOLD US LAST MONTH 
THAT IT WAS TIME TO MOVE AHEAD.  HE INDICATED THAT THE 
GOVERNMENT WOULD STILL WORK WITHIN THE FINANCIAL 
COMMITTEE OF THE SFRY STATES TO GET AN ACCOUNTING OF THE 
MISSING MONEY.  HE PRAISED THE NEW LEADERSHIP AT THE 
SERBIAN CENTRAL BANK AS BEING WILLING TO COOPERATE, BUT 
NOTED THAT POLITICAL UNCERTAINTIES IN BELGRADE RENDERED 
PROGRESS SLOW. 
 
4.  (SBU) RECENT PRESS REPORTS CLAIMED THE EU AND U.S. 
WERE PUTTING PRESSURE ON THE NEW GOVERNMENT TO RATIFY 
    THE SUCCESSION AGREEMENT EVEN THOUGH CROATIA STILL 
CLAIMED $589 MILLION HAD GONE MISSING FROM JOINT VENTURE 
BANKS (SOME 90 PERCENT OF THE AMOUNT \"VALUED ON 21 MARCH 
2001\" IN THE AGREEMENT).  WHILE WE HAD NOT MADE THIS A 
TOP PRIORITY IN OUR DISCUSSIONS WITH THE GOC, WE HAVE 
CONSISTENTLY MADE CLEAR THAT THE GOVERNMENT NEEDED TO 
MOVE AHEAD ON THIS ISSUE.  IN REGARD TO THE MISSING 
MONEY, WE HAVE URGED ROGIC TO FIND A WAY TO RESOLVE 
DIFFERENCES WITH BELGRADE.  THE U.S. DE-BLOCKED USD 225 
MILLION IN U.S. BANKS A YEAR AGO USING THE VIENNA 
AGREEMENT ON DIVISION OF ASSETS OF THE FORMER SFRY. 
CROATIA BECAME ENTITLED TO USD 56 MILLION AS OF MAY 
2003. 
 
5.  (SBU) ACCORDING TO ZAGREB\'S EC MISSION, THE 
EUROPEANS HAVE TAKEN A SIMILAR TACK.  THEY HAVE WANTED 
TO SEE THE AGREEMENT RATIFIED, BUT HAD NOT BEEN APPLYING 
PARTICULAR PRESSURE ON CROATIAN AUTHORITIES IN RECENT 
MONTHS. 
 
6.  (SBU) ACCORDING TO A PRESS COMMENTARY ON MARCH 3 IN 
ZAGREB DAILY DNEVNIK, RATIFICATION OF THE SUCCESSION 
AGREEMENT COULD TRIGGER RESISTANCE TO THE RETURN OF 
PROPERTY AND TENANCY RIGHTS GUARANTEED BY THE AGREEMENT. 
ASKED IF TENANCY RIGHTS WERE COVERED IN THE AGREEMENT, 
BOZO MARANDIC, THE GOVERNMENT\'S POINT PERSON ON THE 
SUCCESSION TALKS, SAID ONLY, \"YES AND NO.\"  IN FACT, 
PRIVATE PROPERTY AND \"ACQUIRED\" RIGHTS ARE COVERED IN 
ANNEX G OF THE VIENNA AGREEMENT.  ACCORDING TO 
BELGRADE\'S AMBASSADOR IN ZAGREB, ANNEX G, NOT MISSING 
MONEY FROM THE JOINT VENTURE BANKS, WAS THE REAL SOURCE 
    OF CONSTERNATION PREVENTING THE PREVIOUS GOVERNMENT FROM 
TAKING THE SUCCESSION AGREEMENT TO THE PARLIAMENT FOR 
RATIFICATION. 
 
FRANK 
 
NNNN 
