"15675","4/5/2004 5:48","04ZAGREB578","Embassy Zagreb","UNCLASSIFIED//FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY","04ZAGREB578","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","UNCLAS SECTION 01 OF 03 ZAGREB 000578 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
SENSITIVE 
 
STATE FOR EB/MTA/ATT 
 
VIENNA FOR FAS 
 
BUDAPEST FOR ENVIRO HUB 
 
E.O. 12958: N/A 
TAGS: EAGR, ECON, ETRD, SENV, TBIO, TSPL, HR, Trade 
SUBJECT: BAD TEST RESULTS FORCE GMO ISSUE 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1.  (U) THE RECENT SCANDAL AROUND THE ALLEGED PRESENCE OF 
NON-APPROVED GMOS IN 14 FOOD SAMPLES HAS SPED THE ADOPTION 
OF REGULATIONS ON LABELING AND APPROVAL OF GMOS AND STIRRED 
PUBLIC DEBATE, EVEN THOUGH SUBSEQUENT TESTS FOUND THAT ONLY 
ONE OF THE SAMPLES HAD MORE THAN ONE PERCENT GMO CONTENT. 
THE GOVERNMENT HAS TRIED TO STRIKE A COMPROMISE POSITION 
PUBLICLY, BY SAYING THAT IMPORTS OF GMOS WOULD BE PERMITTED, 
IF LABELED, BUT THAT CROATIA WOULD REMAIN \"GMO FREE\" BECAUSE 
SOWING OF GM CROPS WOULD NOT BE ALLOWED.  THE GOVERNMENT HAS 
ADOPTED THE EU-APPROVED LIST OF GM PRODUCTS AND THE EU 
THRESHOLD OF 0.9 PERCENT FOR LABELING.  MEANWHILE, VARIOUS 
REGIONS ARE CONSIDERING FOLLOWING ISTRIA\'S LEAD IN DECLARING 
\"GMO-FREE\" ZONES.  END SUMMARY. 
 
THE STORM BREAKS 
---------------- 
 
2.  (U) IN FEBRUARY, CROATIAN NATIONAL TELEVISION ANNOUNCED 
THAT THE FIRST TESTING OF GMO PRESENCE IN FOOD SAMPLES WAS 
DONE IN AN OSIJEK (IN THE RURAL EAST OF CROATIA) FOOD 
QUALITY-BIOTECHNOLOGY TESTING LABORATORY.  ONE OF ONLY TWO 
BIOTECH TESTING LABS IN CROATIA, THE FACILITY LACKS ISO 
CERTIFICATION.  IT TESTED 33 FOOD SAMPLES FOR QUALITY AND 
GMO PRESENCE.  IN 14 SAMPLES FROM BOTH CROATIAN AND FOREIGN 
COMPANIES, IT REPORTED MORE THAN ONE PERCENT OF GMO 
PRESENCE.  IN ADDITION, IT DETECTED MEAT IN \"VEGETARIAN\" 
    PATE AND PORK AND BEEF IN \"CHICKEN\" PATE.  THE GMO 
\"CONTAMINATED\" PRODUCTS WERE SOY AND SOY PRODUCTS, 
VEGETARIAN PATE, CORN FLAKES, OIL, AND CANNED CORN. 
 
3.  (U) THE STORY DOMINATED THE HEADLINES FOR SEVERAL DAYS, 
AND POPPED UP INTERMITTENTLY FOR WEEKS.  MOST NEWS STORIES 
WERE FAIRLY MATTER-OF-FACT -- NON-LABELED GMOS HAVE BEEN 
FOUND IN FOOD.  SOME NEWS PROGRAMS EVEN NOTED THAT NO 
HARMFUL EFFECTS OF GMOS HAD BEEN PROVEN.  HOWEVER, THE MERE 
FACT THAT GMOS WERE FOUND PROMPTED A PUBLIC OUTCRY.  GREENS 
PORTRAYED THE RESULTS AS VINDICATION OF YEARS OF DIRE 
WARNINGS, AND RENEWED CALLS FOR A TOTAL BAN ON BIOTECH. 
(IRONICALLY, GMOS WERE ALREADY DE FACTO BANNED.  WHILE A LAW 
HAD BEEN PASSED ALLOWING THE IMPORT OF GMOS ONCE REGISTERED 
AND LABELED, IN THE ABSENCE OF REGULATIONS, NO PERMITS COULD 
BE ISSUED.)  AS A RESULT OF THE FUROR, CONSUMERS THREATENED 
TO SUE COMPANIES THAT DID NOT LABEL GMOS, CONSUMER GROUPS 
DEMANDED THAT THE COMPANIES IN QUESTION BE PUNISHED, 
PRODUCERS THREATENED THE LAB FOR PUBLISHING PARTIAL 
INFORMATION, SUPERMARKETS PLEDGED TO WITHDRAW THE FOOD 
CONTAINING GMOS, AND THE SANITARY INSPECTION SERVICE 
TIGHTENED UP INSPECTIONS ON THE BORDER, REQUESTING GMO-FREE 
CERTIFICATES FOR FRESH PRODUCE AND COMMODITIES, TAKING 
SAMPLES, ETC. 
 
4.  (SBU) A CONTACT IN PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICES HEADQUARTERS 
FUMED TO US THAT THE LAB IN OSIJEK HAD ACTED IRREGULARLY AND 
IRRESPONSIBLY.  IN THE ABSENCE OF REGULATION OF LAST YEAR\'S 
FOOD LAW, THERE WERE NO GUIDELINES FOR TESTING.  HE 
SPECULATED THAT THE SAMPLING WAS DONE TO CREATE AN UPROAR 
AND TO POLITICIZE THE ISSUE OF GMOS.  HE ALSO QUESTIONED THE 
    VALIDITY OF THE TESTING -- CORRECTLY AS IT TURNED OUT. 
 
5.  (U) THE ZAGREB PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICE INITIALLY CROSS 
CHECKED 12 SAMPLES OF THE SAME PRODUCTS, BUT DIFFERENT LOTS 
BECAUSE THE OSIJEK LABORATORY DID NOT WANT TO SHARE ITS 
SAMPLES.  ONLY ONE SAMPLE HAD MORE THAN ONE PERCENT OF GMOS, 
FIVE HAD TRACES OF GMOS, AND SEVEN HAD NO GMOS.  AFTER THE 
ZAGREB LAB WAS FINALLY ABLE TO OBTAIN SAMPLES FROM THE 
OSIJEK LAB, AN ISO-CERTIFIED LABORATORY IN BERN PROVED THAT 
THE ZAGREB LABORATORY HAD THE CORRECT RESULTS AND THE OSIJEK 
LABORATORY WAS WRONG. 
 
6.  (U) THE ONE PRODUCT SAMPLE WITH OVER ONE PERCENT OF GMO 
PRESENCE WAS A SAUSAGE PRODUCED IN CROATIA BY A CROATIAN 
SUBSIDIARY OF THE SLOVENIAN COMPANY, PERUTNINA PTUJ.  THE 
SAUSAGE CONTAINED SOY EXTRACT THAT WAS PROBABLY BOUGHT FROM 
A DUTCH COMPANY WITH OFFICES IN ZAGREB.  THE MEDIA REPORTED 
THAT THE SOYBEANS WERE SOURCED FROM THE U.S. 
 
7.  (U) TWO OTHER SAMPLES COULD NOT BE CATEGORIZED AS GMO OR 
GMO-FREE.  ONE TESTED AT 0.76 PERCENT GMO PRESENCE IN ZAGREB 
AND 1.15 PERCENT IN BERN (IT WILL BE RETESTED) AND ANOTHER 
SAMPLE WAS CONTAMINATED WITH BROCCOLI VIRUS SIMILAR TO ONE 
GENETIC MODIFICATION (THAT PRODUCT CONTAINS BROCCOLI AND SOY 
BEANS). 
 
ZAGREB 00000578  001.2 OF 003 
 
