A DUTCH COMPANY WITH OFFICES IN ZAGREB.  THE MEDIA REPORTED 
THAT THE SOYBEANS WERE SOURCED FROM THE U.S. 
 
7.  (U) TWO OTHER SAMPLES COULD NOT BE CATEGORIZED AS GMO OR 
GMO-FREE.  ONE TESTED AT 0.76 PERCENT GMO PRESENCE IN ZAGREB 
AND 1.15 PERCENT IN BERN (IT WILL BE RETESTED) AND ANOTHER 
SAMPLE WAS CONTAMINATED WITH BROCCOLI VIRUS SIMILAR TO ONE 
GENETIC MODIFICATION (THAT PRODUCT CONTAINS BROCCOLI AND SOY 
BEANS). 
 
ZAGREB 00000578  002.1 OF 003 
 
HAVE FULL LABELING 
AND REGISTRATION REGULATIONS IN PLACE, IMPORTERS SAY THEIR 
CUSTOMERS (ESPECIALLY SUPERMARKETS) ARE ASKING FOR PROOF 
THAT PRODUCTS ARE GMO-FREE AND BORDER INSPECTORS ARE 
REQUESTING LAB CERTIFICATES THAT IMPORTS ARE GMO FREE.  THIS 
IS A PROBLEM FOR INTERNATIONAL COMPANIES WHICH SOURCE THEIR 
INPUTS ON WORLD MARKETS WHERE IT IS CUSTOMARY TO ACCEPT A 
STATEMENT FROM A SUPPLIER THAT THE PRODUCT IS GMO-FREE. 
THEY ONLY REQUEST A LAB CERTIFICATE IF THEY DISCOVER THAT 
THE SUPPLIER IS NOT RELIABLE. 
 
9.  (U) EVEN SOME CROATIAN EXPORTERS HAVE TO GIVE GMO-FREE 
CERTIFICATES TO THEIR FOREIGN CUSTOMERS.  ONE EXAMPLE IS A 
SLOVENIAN COOKING OIL FACTORY THAT IS ASKING ITS CROATIAN 
SUPPLIER TO CERTIFY ITS SUNFLOWER OIL AS GMO-FREE, DESPITE 
THE FACT THAT THERE ARE NO GMO SUNFLOWERS BEING 
COMMERCIALIZED. 
 
THE GOVERNMENT\'S NEXT STEPS 
--------------------------- 
 
10.  (U) THE COMPANY THAT PRODUCED THE SAUSAGE WITH GMO 
PRESENCE HAD TO WITHDRAW IT FROM THE MARKET (THEY DID SO 
VOLUNTARILY), AND MAY BE PUNISHED FOR NOT LABELING GMO 
PRESENCE, FOR WHICH FINES ARE SEVERE.  IN THEIR FAVOR IS THE 
FACT THAT THERE WERE NO REGULATIONS THAT ESTABLISHED 
    THRESHOLDS, DETAILS OF LABELING, OR TESTING REQUIREMENTS. 
 
11.  (U) IN REACTION TO THE UPROAR, THE CROATIAN GOVERNMENT 
SPED UP THE PROCEDURE OF FORMING THE FOOD AGENCY AND QUICKLY 
DRAFTED REGULATIONS FOR GMO LABELING AND THRESHOLDS. 
REGULATIONS ON REQUIREMENTS FOR BIOTECH TESTING LABS WILL BE 
PREPARED WITHIN A MONTH, AND PROCEDURES ON \"NOVELTY FOOD 
APPROVALS\" IN SIX MONTHS. 
 
12.  (U) AT ITS MARCH 12 SESSION, THE GOVERNMENT ADOPTED 
THE REGULATION ON THE LEVEL OF GMO IN PRODUCTS PLACED ON 
THE MARKET.  THIS REGULATION STIPULATES THAT PRODUCTS 
CONTAINING ACCIDENTAL OR TECHNOLOGICALLY UNAVOIDABLE TRACES 
OF ALLOWED GMO AT THE LEVEL OF 0.9 PERCENT OR LESS IN A 
PRODUCT OF ONE INGREDIENT, OR 0.9 PERCENT OR LESS OF 
ALLOWED GMO OF EACH INGREDIENT OF THE PRODUCT, NEED NOT BE 
MARKED AS PRODUCTS CONTAINING GMO.  AN EXCEPTION TO THIS 
THRESHOLD IS REPRODUCTIVE PLANT MATERIAL (SEED) CONTAINING 
GMO IN ANY AMOUNT, WHICH MUST BE MARKED. 
 
13.  (U) UNTIL ALL IMPLEMENTING REGULATIONS ON PERMISSION 
TO PLACE GMOS AND PRODUCTS CONTAINING GMOS ON THE MARKET IN 
THE CROATIA ARE ADOPTED, ONLY THE EU-APPROVED LIST OF 15 
VARIETIES OF SOY, CORN, RAPESEED AND COTTON ARE PERMITTED. 
 
STRANGE DEFINITION OF \"GMO-FREE\" 
-------------------------------- 
 
14.  (SBU) CROATIAN HEALTH MINISTER ANDRIJA HEBRANG, WHO IS 
ALSO THE DEPUTY PRIME MINISTER FOR THE ECONOMY, COMMENTED, 
\"THE POSITION OF THE GOVERNMENT IS THAT CROATIA MUST BE A 
    GMO-FREE COUNTRY AND GMO PRODUCTS WILL NOT BE PRODUCED IN 
CROATIA.  THOSE IMPORTED FROM ABROAD MUST BE SUBJECT TO 
STRINGENT CHECKS.\"  HOWEVER, THERE IS NO LEGAL WAY TO 
DECLARE THE COUNTRY OR A REGION \"GMO-FREE,\" ALTHOUGH THE LAW 
ON PROTECTION OF NATURE DOES HAVE PROVISIONS TO DECLARE 
CERTAIN AREAS GMO-FREE TO PROTECT NATURE PRESERVES, TOURISM 
OR ORGANIC PRODUCTION.  THAT DID NOT STOPPED ISTRIA COUNTY 
FROM DECLARING ITSELF \"GMO-FREE\" LAST YEAR.  AT THE TIME, 
THE COUNTY PREFECT SHEEPISHLY ADMITTED TO US THAT HE HAD NO 
LEGAL BASIS TO DO SO, AND NO WAY TO ENFORCE IT.  BUT \"IT\'S A 
TYPE OF MARKETING,\" HE DECLARED.  POZESKO-SLAVONSKA AND 
KRAPINSKO-AAGORSKA COUNTIES FOLLOWED SUIT.  RECENTLY EIGHT 
HSS (CROATIAN PEASANT\'S PARTY) COUNTRY PREFECTS SUGGESTED 
TO THEIR COUNTY ASSEMBLIES TO DECLARE GMO-FREE ZONES AS 
WELL. 
 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
15.  (SBU) WHILE THE OSIJEK LAB WAS SHOWN TO BE INCOMPETENT, 
IT IS LIKELY THAT THE FOES OF BIOTECHNOLOGY SCORED PUBLIC 
RELATIONS POINTS, AT LEAST IN THE SHORT-TERM.  AT THE MARCH 
12 GOVERNMENT MEETING, THE CABINET DECIDED TO BASE THE NEW 
FOOD AGENCY -- WHICH WILL APPROVE NEW BIOTECH PRODUCTS FOR 
MARKETING -- IN OSIJEK.  THE GENESIS OF THIS DECISION WAS 
NOT ENTIRELY RELATED TO THE GMO-TESTING ISSUE -- THERE HAS 
 
