ZAGREB 00000578  003.1 OF 003 
 
IN THE RURAL EAST. 
HOWEVER, THE GOVERNMENT ALSO FELT A NEED TO PLACATE THE 
PUBLIC AND LOCAL OFFICIALS IN EASTERN CROATIA. 
 
16.  (SBU) EVEN WHILE MORE AND MORE CROATIANS MAY HAVE SOME 
UNDERSTANDING THAT GMOS ARE NOT HARMFUL, THEY WANT TO KNOW 
IF GMOS ARE IN THEIR FOOD, AND IF POSSIBLE, TO AVOID THEM. 
WHILE THE GOVERNMENT DECISION TECHNICALLY OPENS THE MARKET 
TO EU-APPROVED VARIETIES, WE DOUBT THAT LABELED GMOS WILL BE 
APPEARING ON SUPERMARKET SHELVES ANY TIME SOON, ALTHOUGH 
THEY MAY BE MAKING A (REPEAT) APPEARANCE IN FEED LOTS. 
 
FRANK 
 
