"16714","5/7/2004 14:25","04ZAGREB817","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","04SECRETARY6OF29APRIL4","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L ZAGREB 000817 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
DEPARTMENT FOR EUR/SCE:KABUMOTO AND S/WCI:PROSPER 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/07/2014 
TAGS: PREL, KAWC, HR, War Crimes 
SUBJECT: FM ZUZUL SEEKS UNDERSTANDING ON GOTOVINA 
 
REF: A. SECRETARY 6 OF 29 APRIL 04 
 
     B. USNATO 429 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: AMBASSADOR RALPH FRANK, REASON: 1.5 (B) & (D) 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
1. (C) FOREIGN MINISTER MIOMIR ZUZUL SOUGHT A MEETING WITH 
    AMBASSADOR FRANK TO EXPRESS HIS DISAPPOINTMENT AT THE U.S. 
POSITION CONDITIONING SUPPORT FOR CROATIA\'S NATO ENTRY ON THE 
ARREST OF ICTY FUGITIVE ANTE GOTOVINA (REFTELS).  AMBASSADOR 
FRANK RESPONDED THAT THIS SHOULD NOT HAVE BEEN A SURPRISE AS 
THE U.S. HAS LONG STATED THAT FULL COOPERATION WITH THE ICTY 
MEANS THAT GOTOVINA IS ARRESTED AND IN THE HAGUE.  THE 
AMBASSADOR CAUTIONED THAT CROATIA CANNOT ABSOLVE ITSELF OF 
ITS RESPONSIBILITY TO LOCATE AND APPREHEND GOTOVINA BY 
ATTEMPTING TO SHOW THAT GOTOVINA IS NOT IN CROATIA.  FM ZUZUL 
PLANS A PRIVATE VISIT TO THE U.S. MAY 16-18 AND ASKED IF HE 
SHOULD TRY TO SEE THE SECRETARY ONCE AGAIN.  AMBASSADOR 
SUGGESTED THAT WHILE FM ZUZUL COULD USEFULLY MEET WITH 
AMBASSADOR PROSPER, ZUZUL SHOULD NOT WEAR OUT THE WELCOME MAT 
IN WASHINGTON BY SEEKING ADDITIONAL HIGH LEVEL MEETINGS.  END 
SUMMARY. 
 
SHOCKED, JUST SHOCKED 
--------------------- 
 
2. (C) ON MAY 4, AMBASSADOR FRANK MET WITH FOREIGN MINISTER 
MIOMIR ZUZUL TO REINFORCE THE U.S. POSITION ON ICTY FUGITIVE 
ANTE GOTOVINA.  MINISTER ZUZUL EXPRESSED HIS SURPRISE AT THE 
U.S. POSITION THAT CROATIA\'S ENTRY INTO NATO WAS CONDITIONED 
ON THE ARREST AND DELIVERY TO THE HAGUE OF ICTY FUGITIVE ANTE 
GOTOVINA.  ZUZUL SAID HE WAS DISAPPOINTED WITH WHAT HE 
DESCRIBED AS AN UNHELPFUL APRIL 30 NATO MAP REVIEW IN 
BRUSSELS (REF B), PARTICULARLY AFTER THE POSITIVE EU AVIS, 
WHICH HE THOUGHT HAD ALSO REFLECTED U.S. VIEWS. 
 
3. (C) AMBASSADOR FRANK RESPONDED THAT THE U.S. POSITION 
SHOULD NOT HAVE BEEN A SURPRISE AS IT WAS NOT NEW.  THE U.S. 
    HAS ALWAYS BEEN CLEAR THAT FULL COOPERATION WITH THE ICTY 
MEANT THAT GOTOVINA WAS ARRESTED AND DELIVERED TO THE HAGUE. 
ON APRIL 15, ZUZUL HAD BEEN TOLD DIRECTLY BY AMBASSADOR 
PROSPER THAT THE U.S. DID NOT AGREE WITH ICTY CHIEF 
PROSECUTOR DEL PONTE\'S ASSESSMENT THAT CROATIA WAS FULLY 
COOPERATIVE WITH ICTY.  ZUZUL HAD HEARD THE SAME MESSAGE FROM 
THE SECRETARY TWICE ) DURING THEIR PHONE CALL APRIL 16 AND 
IN PERSON IN BERLIN ON APRIL 28 (REF A). 
 
HELP US FIND GOTOVINA 
--------------------- 
 
4. (C) ZUZUL SAID HE WAS NOT HAPPY WITH THE CURRENT 
SITUATION, AS THE GOC WAS CONVINCED THAT GOTOVINA WAS NOT IN 
CROATIA.  THE GOC WAS NOT AFRAID OF THE POLITICAL 
CONSEQUENCES OF ARRESTING GOTOVINA.  HIS ARREST WOULD PROVIDE 
RELIEF FROM THE CURRENT DEPRESSING POSITION THE GOC WAS IN. 
ZUZUL THEN ASKED FOR U.S. ASSISTANCE IN FINDING GOTOVINA. 
 
5. (C) AMBASSADOR FRANK REMINDED ZUZUL THAT IT WAS INCUMBENT 
ON THE GOC TO FIND GOTOVINA.  IT WAS NOT ENOUGH TO ASSERT 
THAT GOTOVINA WAS NOT IN CROATIA.  THE INTERNATIONAL 
COMMUNITY WAS CONCERNED THAT SOME IN CROATIA BELIEVED THEY 
COULD \"GAME\" THE ISSUE BY WAITING OUT THE ICTY\'S COMPLETION 
STRATEGY.  CROATIA\'S PAST BEHAVIOR -- ON BOBETKO AND GOTOVINA 
) HAD PUT THE BURDEN ON CROATIA TO MATCH ITS WORDS WITH 
ACTIONS.  THE U.S. HAD GONE VERY FAR IN SUPPORTING CROATIA\'S 
NATO ASPIRATIONS.  HOWEVER, GOTOVINA IS AND WOULD REMAIN A 
MAJOR OBSTACLE TO FURTHER U.S. SUPPORT FOR CROATIA\'S NATO 
CANDIDACY.  THE GOC SHOULD TAKE THE LEAD IN THE SEARCH, AS NO 
OTHER COUNTRY COULD HAVE ACCESS TO THE CONTACTS AND LEADS 
    THAT COULD LEAD TO GOTOVINA\'S CAPTURE. 
 
ZUZUL\'S PRIVATE TRIP TO U.S. 
---------------------------- 
 
6. (C) FM ZUZUL SAID HE WAS PLANNING A PRIVATE VISIT TO 
BOSTON AND NEW YORK FROM MAY 13 AND WOULD BE IN WASHINGTON 
MAY 16-18 TO DEAL WITH PERSONAL ISSUES.  ZUZUL ASKED WHETHER 
HE SHOULD TRY TO SEE THE SECRETARY AGAIN.  THE AMBASSADOR 
SAID THAT, HAVING JUST SEEN THE SECRETARY, ZUZUL SHOULD NOT 
SEEK ANOTHER MEETING TO GO OVER THE SAME GROUND.  AMBASSADOR 
FRANK SUGGESTED THAT ZUZUL COULD USEFULLY MEET WITH 
AMBASSADOR PROSPER, IN ADVANCE OF PROSPER\'S POSSIBLE NEXT 
VISIT TO CROATIA, IF ZUZUL HAD SOMETHING NEW TO SAY ON 
GOTOVINA. 
 
FRANK 
 
NNNN 
"
"16775","5/10/2004 16:00","04ZAGREB834","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","04USNATO429","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L  ZAGREB 000834 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
DEPARTMENT FOR EUR/SCE (ENGLISH) AND EUR/RPM (SHINAGEL) 
USNATO FOR BRUCE ROGERS 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/12/2014 
TAGS: PARM, PREL, HR, NATO 
SUBJECT: CROATIAN OFFICIALS REACT TO NATO REVIEW 
 
REF: A. USNATO 429 
 
     B. ZAGREB 817 
 
Classified By: Poloff A.F.Godfrey for reasons 1.5 (b,d) 
 
Summary 
------- 
 
1.  (C) GoC officials were both encouraged and disappointed 
with their second annual review by NATO\'s North Atlantic 
Council of Croatia\'s progress towards membership.  They were 
encouraged by new optimism about Croatia expressed by many 
allies, citing that the International Staff\'s report noted 
progress on tough issues.  But GoC officials disheartened by 
what they perceived as a new position by the U.S., Croatia\'s 
former champion at NATO.  Croatian officials believe the USG 
has changed the standard by which it is measuring cooperation 
with ICTY.  We encouraged Croatia to continue its progress 
toward NATO membership, stressed that the U.S. has always 
insisted on full cooperation with international obligations 
and underscored the U.S. Mission\'s message at the NAC (ref a) 
that the continued fugitive status of ICTY indictee Gotovina 
is an obstacle to accession.  End Summary. 
 
Croatia reacts to NATO\'s \"Report Card\" 
-------------------------------------- 
 
2.  (C) Croatia took away mixed messages from its April 30 
\"26 1\" Membership Action Plan (MAP) progress review at NATO\'s 
North Atlantic Council (NAC).  In the week following the NAC 
meeting, we met with Croatia\'s MAP coordinator Pjer Simunovic 
and with Davor Stier, the lead political officer at Croatia\'s 
mission to NATO.  GoC officials were pleased by most allies\' 
recognition that Croatia was making good progress on 
sensitive issues in the political chapter of MAP.  They 
appreciated the constructive, but tough assessment of the 
work the GoC needs to do on defense reform, military 
downsizing and restructuring and also on judicial reform. 
 
Croatia: USG Moved the Goalposts on ICTY Cooperation 
--------------------------------------------- ------- 
 
3.  (C) According to Steir, the most disheartening message 
came from the U.S. representative to the NAC.  Most Allies 
took note of the ICTY Chief Prosecutor\'s positive assessment 
of Croatia\'s cooperation, noting the immediate transfer of 
eight indictees and the ICTY\'s assessment of full cooperation 
on document requests to the GoC.  According to Steir, it was 
the GoC\'s firm understanding that the USG had previously used 
the ICTY\'s assessment as its own measure of Croatia\'s 
cooperation.  Now that Del Ponte judges Croatia as \"fully 
cooperating,\" Stier continued, the U.S. has changed its 
standard, insisting that Gotovina must be in The Hague before 
the U.S. will allow Croatia to move forward toward 
membership.  Steir reiterated FM Zuzul\'s plea at the NAC that 
Croatia \"must not be held hostage to one man.\" 
 
\"A Blow to Croatia\'s Atlantic Movement\" 
--------------------------------------- 
 
4.  (C) Simunovic said that the new U.S. position at the NAC 
was a blow to Croatia\'s Atlanticists and could dampen energy 
in Zagreb for Croatia\'s NATO bid.  The EC\'s \"avis\" was not 
seen as a finish line, but as a starting point.  With this 
concrete signal, Croatia\'s reformers have a new tool with 
which to push ahead on reforms relating to the EU.  According 
to Simunovic, the message to those in Croatia who are 
responsible for managing the NATO bid was the opposite: 
despite GoC efforts and measurable achievements, Croatia is 
no closer to NATO membership. 
 
\"Give Us a \'Carrot\' in the Istanbul Communique, Please\" 
--------------------------------------------- --------- 
 
5.  (C) Simunovic and Stier asked for a strong message at the 
Istanbul summit which could re-energize Croatia\'s bid for 
NATO and boost public support for membership the way the EC\'s 
\"avis\" had for Croatia\'s EU bid.  More than anything, 
Simunovic said he fears that the Croatian public could 
develop a \"who needs NATO anyway\" attitude; support for the 
tough reforms which are not part of EU requirements -- 
especially in defense -- could fall away. 
 
6.  (C) Stier said Croatia was considering proposing draft 
language for the Summit communique to various delegations at 
NATO.  He said that proposed language would not include a 
call for an invitation -- Allies have been clear that the MAP 
aspirants should not expect that -- but would suggest that 
heads of state hail the progress of the three and direct the 
NAC to assess their suitability for an invitation after the 
next MAP review cycle in Spring 2005. 
 
7.  (C) For our part, we encouraged Croatia to continue its 
efforts in NATO\'s MAP and to address all of the issues raised 
by allies at the April 30 review.  As always, we reiterated 
to our interlocutors that Croatia should take all measures 
possible to deliver Gotovina to ICTY custody. 
FRANK 
 
 
NNNN 
"
"16856","5/12/2004 16:23","04ZAGREB842","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","04STATE101524","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.


 ","C O N F I D E N T I A L ZAGREB 000842 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/11/2009 
TAGS: MARR, PREL, HR, Defense Reform (Mil & NATO) 
SUBJECT: CROATIA HESITANT, BUT WILLING TO EXPAND ATTENDANCE 
AT ADRIATIC CHARTER PARTNERSHIP COMMISSION MEETING 
 
REF: STATE 101524 
 
    CLASSIFIED BY: POLOFF A.F.GODFREY FOR REASOSN 1.5 (B,D) 
 
1.  (SBU) CROATIA REMAINS HESITANT TO INCLUDE SERBIA AND 
MONTENEGRO AND BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA AS FULL PARTICIPANTS IN 
THE MAY 19 - 20 ADRIATIC CHARTER PARTNERSHIP COMMISSION 
MEETING.  WE DELIVERED REFTEL TALKING POINTS TO PJER 
SIMUNOVIC, CROATIA\'S POLITICAL DIRECTOR FOR NATO ISSUES. 
SIMUNOVIC SAID THAT CROATIA\'S HESITANCE STEMS FROM THE GOC 
DRIVE TO MAKE THE ADRIATIC CHARTER PARTNERSHIP A FUNCTIONAL 
BODY WHICH WILL FOCUS ON ISSUES RELATING TO WORK THE PARTNERS 
ARE DOING IN NATO\'S MAP TO QUALIFY FOR FOR FULL NATO 
MEMBERSHIP.  SIMUNOVIC POINTED OUT THAT OUR SUGGESTION TO 
INCLUDE SAM AND BIH SEEMS AT ODDS WITH THE REST OF OUR 
MESSAGE (REF), WHICH STATES THAT THE FOCUS OF PC MEETINGS 
SHOULD BE MAP-SPECIFIC, NOT ON ACTIVITIES WITH NON-CHARTER 
PARTNERS OR ON POLITICAL DECLARATIONS.  WE SUGGESTED THAT 
INCLUDING THE SAM AND BIH MINISTERS WOULD BE AN OPPORTUNITY 
FOR THE A3 STATES TO SHOW LEADERSHIP IN THE REGION FOR NATO\'S 
SHARED GOALS. 
 
2.  (SBU) ON MAY 10, SIMUNOVIC PHONED FROM BUCHAREST TO SAY 
THAT HE HAD DISCUSSED OUR PROPOSAL WITH HIS MACEDONIAN 
COLLEAGUE (POLDIR MIRA KRAJACIC) AND WOULD PROPOSE THAT A 
SEPARATE MEETING ON THE MARGINS OF THE ADRIATIC CHARTER EVENT 
INCLUDING THE THREE \"A3\" FOREIGN MINISTERS WITH THE SAM AND 
BIH FOREIGN MINISTERS.  HE REMAINED CONVINCED THAT FULL 
ENGAGEMENT OF THE MINISTERS IN THE COMMISSION\'S ACTIVITIES 
WOULD BE DISTRACTING AND WOULD DETRACT FROM THE POTENTIAL 
ACCOMPLISHMENTS OF THE COMMISSION MEETING.  HE SAID HE 
CONTINUES TO BELIEVE THAT THE ADRIATIC CHARTER SHOULD BE 
ABOUT PROGRESS TOWARDS MAP; \"THERE ARE PLENTY OF OTHER 
    ORGANIZATIONS DEDICATED TO REGIONAL COOPERATION.\"  WE THANKED 
HIM FOR THE PROPOSAL, AND SAID WE WOULD RELAY ANY WASHINGTON 
REACTION AS SOON AS POSSIBLE. 
 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
3.  (C) SIMUNOVIC HAS A POINT: THE INCLUSION OF THE BIH AND 
SAM FOREIGN MINISTERS IN ALL ASPECTS OF THE MEETING WOULD 
LIKELY MOVE THE AGENDA AWAY FROM MAP.  BUT THERE MAY BE OTHER 
REASONS FOR CROATIAN FM ZUZUL TO BE LESS THAN EAGER TO MEET 
SAM FM VUK DRASKOVIC.  DRASKOVIC HAD BEEN EXPECTED TO 
ACCOMPANY SAM PRESIDENT MAROVIC TO CROATIA ON AN OFFICIAL 
VISIT TO ZAGREB.  AFTER CROATIA\'S TOP NEWSWEEKLY PUBLISHED A 
LENGTHY INTERVIEW WITH DRASKOVIC CONTAINING SEVERAL 
STATEMENTS CONSIDERED BY MANY IN ZAGREB TO BE INFLAMMATORY, 
DRASKOVIC WAS \"DISINVITED\" BY PRESIDENT MESIC.  ZUZUL IS 
SCHEDULED TO TRAVEL TO BELGRADE TO MEET DRASKOVIC SHORTLY 
AFTER THE ADRIATIC PARTNERSHIP MEETING.  SIMUNOVIC, WHO IS IN 
CHARGE OF CROATIA\'S PR CAMPAIGN TO BUILD POPULAR SUPPORT FOR 
NATO, WOULD PROBABLY RATHER NOT HAVE THE ZUZUL-DRASKOVIC 
MEETING DISPLACE THE ADRIATIC CHARTER MINISTERIAL FROM THE 
ZAGREB HEADLINES. 
FRANK 
 
NNNN 
"
"16868","5/13/2004 9:32","04ZAGREB847","Embassy Zagreb","UNCLASSIFIED","04STATE90991|04ZAGREB847","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","UNCLAS SECTION 01 OF 02 ZAGREB 000847 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
STATE PASS USAID/ANNE CONVERY 
BELGRADE FOR MSALVETTI 
BUDAPEST FOR KPOSNER-MULLEN 
LJUBLJANA FOR SGONZALEZ 
SARAJEVO FOR MBOYNTON 
 
    E.O. 12958: N/A 
TAGS: SENV, EAID, ECIN, EWWT, PREL, HR 
SUBJECT: PERMANENT SAVA COMMISSION HAS CROATIAN SUPPORT BUT 
NEEDS CHAMPION 
 
REF: STATE 90991 
 
1.  (U) THE FOLLOWING RESPONDS TO REFTEL QUESTIONS ON THE 
STATUS OF THE SAVA RIVER BASIN INITIATIVE AND THE 
ESTABLISHMENT OF A PERMANENT COMMISSION IN ZAGREB. 
 
SUMMARY 
------- 
 
2.  ESTABLISHMENT OF A PERMANENT SAVA RIVER BASIN 
COMMISSION WITH A SECRETARIAT IN ZAGREB HAS BROAD SUPPORT 
AT THE WORKING LEVEL.  SHIFTING PERSONNEL IN THE SENIOR 
LEVELS OF THE GOC, COMBINED WITH A COMPLICATED DISTRIBUTION 
OF RESPONSIBILITIES AMONG THREE MINISTRIES, HAVE PRECLUDED 
A STRONG STATEMENT OF POLITICAL SUPPORT FOR THE INITIATIVE 
SINCE THE HDZ-LED GOVERNMENT CAME TO POWER EARLIER THIS 
YEAR.  WHILE THE GOVERNMENT MAINTAINS ITS SUPPORT FOR THE 
SECRETARIAT\'S LOCATION IN ZAGREB, THE PERMANENT COMMISSION 
 
SIPDIS 
HAS EFFECTIVELY BEEN PUT ON HOLD PENDING RATIFICATION OF 
THE INTERNATIONAL FRAMEWORK AGREEMENT BY SERBIA AND 
MONTENEGRO.  END SUMMARY. 
 
PERMANENT SECRETARIAT IN ZAGREB IS \"ALREADY SETTLED\"... 
--------------------------------------------- ---------- 
 
3.  IN RESPONSE TO REFTEL, WE SPOKE WITH KARMEN CERAR, 
    SENIOR ADVISOR IN THE DIRECTORATE OF WATER MANAGEMENT, 
MINISTRY OF AGRICULTURE, FORESTRY, AND WATER MANAGEMENT; 
NEVEN GRUBISIC, ADVISOR IN THE MINISTRY OF MARITIME 
AFFAIRS, TOURISM, TRANSPORT, AND DEVELOPMENT; SPOMENKA CEK, 
NATIONAL COORDINATOR FOR THE STABILITY PACT IN THE MINISTRY 
OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS; AND MELITA ZIZANOVIC-DAKIC, LEGAL 
ADVISOR IN THE MFA, TO ASSESS PROGRESS TOWARDS ESTABLISHING 
A PERMANENT SAVA RIVER BASIN COMMISSION.  ALL FOUR 
CONFIRMED CROATIA\'S RESOLVE TO WORK WITH NEIGHBORING 
RIPARIAN STATES TO ESTABLISH A PERMANENT SAVA RIVER BASIN 
COMMISSION. 
 
4.  CERAR CONFIRMED GOC SUPPORT FOR ZAGREB AS THE 
SECRETARIAT\'S LOCATION, ADDING THAT A PHYSICAL LOCATION ON 
 
SIPDIS 
PANTOVCAK STREET HAS ALREADY BEEN SELECTED; HOWEVER, SHE 
CAUTIONED THAT CROATIAN ENTHUSIASM FOR THE PERMANENT 
COMMISSION COULD NOT PROCEED WITHOUT SAM RATIFICATION OF 
THE IFA.  MOREOVER, CERAR NOTED THAT A DIPLOMATIC NOTE 
CONFIRMING CROATIA\'S SUPPORT WAS UNNECESSARY, AS THE GOC\'S 
RATIFICATION OF THE IFA FULLY DEMONSTRATED THE NECESSARY 
POLITICAL WILL TO PROCEED.  GRUBISIC SAID THAT THE QUESTION 
OF THE SECRETARIAT\'S LOCATION WAS ABOVE ALL LEGAL AND THAT 
THE MFA WAS FULLY RESPONSIBLE FOR QUESTIONS PERTAINING TO 
THE PERMANENT COMMISSION\'S STATUS.  CEK AFFIRMED MFA\'S 
READINESS TO PROCEED WITH THE PERMANENT COMMISSION AND EVEN 
ANNOUNCED THAT OFFICE SPACE FOR TEN HAD BEEN PREPARED. 
ZIZANOVIC-DAKIC AT THE MFA CONFIRMED THAT THE ISSUE OF THE 
SECRETARIAT\'S LOCATION IN ZAGREB WAS \"ALREADY SETTLED.\" 
 
SIPDIS 
 
...LESS SO THE DIVISION OF LABOR 
-------------------------------- 

4.  AUTHORITY FOR OVERSEEING THE SAVA RIVER BASIN 
INITIATIVE IS CURRENTLY DIVIDED AMONG THE MINISTRIES OF 
FOREIGN AFFAIRS, AGRICULTURE AND MARITIME AFFAIRS.  MFA HAS 
THUS FAR PRIMARILY FOCUSED ON THE LEGAL ASPECT, INCLUDING 
THE DRAFTING OF THE FRAMEWORK AGREEMENT.  MFA WILL RETAIN 
LEAD AUTHORITY ON THE INITIATIVE UNTIL SAM RATIFICATION IS 
COMPLETED.  WORKING LEVEL RESPONSIBILITY IS DIVIDED BY AREA 
OF TECHNICAL COMPETENCE: WASTEWATER MANAGEMENT, FLOOD 
CONTROL, AND WATER QUALITY ARE HANDLED THROUGH THE 
DIRECTORATE FOR WATER MANAGEMENT WITHIN THE MINISTRY OF 
AGRICULTURE WHILE NAVIGATION AND TRANSPORTATION ISSUES ARE 
HANDLED THROUGH THE MARITIME MINISTRY.  A/M FOR 
TRANSPORTATION ANDRIJA BEDNJICKI (MARITIME MINISTRY) AND 
DEPUTY COMMISSION MEMBER ZELJKO OSTOJIC (AGRICULTURE 
MINISTRY) HAVE BEEN THE HIGHEST-LEVEL GOC REPRESENTATIVES 
ON THE INTERIM COMMISSION AND ARE LIKELY TO REPRESENT THE 
GOC TO THE PERMANENT COMMISSION UPON ITS ESTABLISHMENT. 
WHILE BOTH CERAR AND GRUBISIC EXPRESSED THEIR MINISTRIES\' 
ENTHUSIASM, GRUBISIC SAID THE MARITIME MINISTRY FELT \"A 
LITTLE MARGINALIZED\" BY THE \"POLITICIANS\" IN THE MFA WHO 
SEEMED MORE EAGER TO FOCUS ON THE POLITICALLY PROMINENT 
FLOODING PROBLEM RATHER THAN MORE TECHNICAL TRANSPORTATION 
PROJECTS. 
 
ZAGREB 00000847  001.2 OF 002 
 
