FLOODING PROBLEM RATHER THAN MORE TECHNICAL TRANSPORTATION 
PROJECTS. 
 
ZAGREB 00000847  002.1 OF 002 
 
ECRETARIAT LOCATED IN ZAGREB IS STRONG 
AT THE WORKING LEVEL, CHANGES IN TOP-LEVEL PERSONNEL AND 
MINISTRY RESTRUCTURING HAS LEFT THE INITIATIVE IN THE HANDS 
OF TECHNOCRATS WITHOUT A CLEAR POLITICAL CHAMPION.  THOUGH 
THE MFA STRESSED THAT THE PROJECT BELONGED IN THE HANDS OF 
EXPERTS KNOWLEDGEABLE IN THE TECHNICAL ASPECTS, IT\'S 
UNCLEAR TO WHAT EXTENT BEDNJICKI AND OSTOJIC WILL BE ABLE 
TO COMMIT GOC RESOURCES WITHOUT STRONG POLITICAL SUPPORT. 
WHILE SAM\'S DELAY IN RATIFYING THE IFA HAS CERTAINLY 
CONTRIBUTED TO SLOW PROGRESS, A LACK OF CONTINUITY (BOTH IN 
PERSONNEL AT THE MINISTERIAL LEVEL AND IN COMPETENCES AMONG 
THE INVOLVED MINISTRIES) HAS PRECIPITATED SOME CONFUSION 
AND DELEGATION OF RESPONSIBILITY DOWN THE RANKS. 
 
6. SINCE THE SIGNING OF THE LETTER OF INTENT BY THE THEN 
MARITIME MINISTER IN NOVEMBER 2001, THE GOVERNMENT HAS 
CHANGED AND THE MINISTRY HAS BEEN BROADENED TO INCLUDE 
TOURISM AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT.  THE CURRENT MINISTER, 
BOZIDAR KALMETA, HAS FOCUSED LATELY MORE ON THESE 
PORTFOLIOS THAN STRICTLY ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES.  WHILE THE 
HARD-CHARGING KALMETA IS THE OBVIOUS CHOICE TO INVIGORATE 
THE INITIATIVE WITH HIGH-LEVEL POLITICAL SUPPORT, WORKING 
    LEVEL CONTACTS QUESTIONED EVEN HIS AWARENESS OF IT.  AS 
LONG AS RATIFICATION REMAINS PENDING, HIGHER LEVELS IN THE 
MFA AND MARITIME MINISTRY CAN SAFELY ALLOW THE INITIATIVE 
TO PROCEED AT THE WORKING LEVEL.  ONCE RATIFICATION HAS 
BEEN COMPLETED, WE WILL MONITOR PROGRESS TO DETERMINE IF 
 
ZAGREB 00000847  002.2 OF 002 
 
ECRETARIAT LOCATED IN ZAGREB IS STRONG 
AT THE WORKING LEVEL, CHANGES IN TOP-LEVEL PERSONNEL AND 
MINISTRY RESTRUCTURING HAS LEFT THE INITIATIVE IN THE HANDS 
OF TECHNOCRATS WITHOUT A CLEAR POLITICAL CHAMPION.  THOUGH 
THE MFA STRESSED THAT THE PROJECT BELONGED IN THE HANDS OF 
EXPERTS KNOWLEDGEABLE IN THE TECHNICAL ASPECTS, IT\'S 
UNCLEAR TO WHAT EXTENT BEDNJICKI AND OSTOJIC WILL BE ABLE 
TO COMMIT GOC RESOURCES WITHOUT STRONG POLITICAL SUPPORT. 
WHILE SAM\'S DELAY IN RATIFYING THE IFA HAS CERTAINLY 
CONTRIBUTED TO SLOW PROGRESS, A LACK OF CONTINUITY (BOTH IN 
PERSONNEL AT THE MINISTERIAL LEVEL AND IN COMPETENCES AMONG 
THE INVOLVED MINISTRIES) HAS PRECIPITATED SOME CONFUSION 
AND DELEGATION OF RESPONSIBILITY DOWN THE RANKS. 
 
6. SINCE THE SIGNING OF THE LETTER OF INTENT BY THE THEN 
MARITIME MINISTER IN NOVEMBER 2001, THE GOVERNMENT HAS 
CHANGED AND THE MINISTRY HAS BEEN BROADENED TO INCLUDE 
TOURISM AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT.  THE CURRENT MINISTER, 
BOZIDAR KALMETA, HAS FOCUSED LATELY MORE ON THESE 
PORTFOLIOS THAN STRICTLY ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES.  WHILE THE 
HARD-CHARGING KALMETA IS THE OBVIOUS CHOICE TO INVIGORATE 
    THE INITIATIVE WITH HIGH-LEVEL POLITICAL SUPPORT, WORKING 
LEVEL CONTACTS QUESTIONED EVEN HIS AWARENESS OF IT.  AS 
LONG AS RATIFICATION REMAINS PENDING, HIGHER LEVELS IN THE 
MFA AND MARITIME MINISTRY CAN SAFELY ALLOW THE INITIATIVE 
TO PROCEED AT THE WORKING LEVEL.  ONCE RATIFICATION HAS 
BEEN COMPLETED, WE WILL MONITOR PROGRESS TO DETERMINE IF 
SUFFICIENT ENERGY EXISTS TO PROCEED WITH THE INITIATIVE OR 
IF INTERVENTION AT THE MINISTERIAL LEVEL IS WARRANTED. 
FRANK 
 
