"18337","7/1/2004 17:10","04ZAGREB1228","Embassy Zagreb","CONFIDENTIAL","04STATE142628","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.


 ","C O N F I D E N T I A L ZAGREB 001228 
 
SIPDIS 
 
 
STATE FOR EUR/SCE AND S/WCI 
TREASURY FOR OFAC 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 07/01/2014 
TAGS: PREL, MOPS, EFIN, ETTC, KAWC, BK, HR, Organized Crime/Corruption 
SUBJECT: OPERATION BALKAN VICE IV: CROATIAN RESPONSE 
 
REF: STATE 142628 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: ECONOMIC OFFICER ISABELLA DETWILER, REASONS 1.5 (B AND D 
) 
 
1.  (C) ON JUNE 30, WE PRESENTED REFTEL DEMARCHE TO ANDREA 
BEKIC, HEAD OF THE AMERICA\'S DEPARTMENT AT THE FOREIGN 
MINISTRY. BEKIC WELCOMED THE NEWS OF THE ANNOUNCEMENT OF THE 
HIGH REPRESENTATIVE, AND USG ACTION TO TARGET THE SUPPORT 
NETWORK OF PIFWCS.  BEKIC SAID SHE WOULD IMMEDIATELY FORWARD 
THE INFORMATION TO THE MEMBERS OF THE ANTI-TERRORISM 
COMMITTEE, WHO ALSO WORK ON \"BALKAN VICE\" ISSUES.  FOR 
FINANCIAL ASSET LOCATION AND SEIZURE ISSUE, THIS INCLUDES THE 
MINISTRY OF FINANCE\'S FINANCIAL INTELLIGENCE UNIT, THE 
CENTRAL BANK, THE INTELLIGENCE AGENCIES, THE POLICE, THE 
STATE ATTORNEY, THE POLICE AND THE MINISTRY OF JUSTICE.  IN 
THE CASE OF ATTEMPTING TO STOP THESE INDIVIDUALS AT THE 
BORDER, BEKIC SAID SHE WOULD CONTACT THE MINISTRY OF JUSTICE 
AND THE INTELLIGENCE SERVICES. 
 
2.  (C) ON JULY 1, WE FOLLOWED UP WITH DEPUTY DIRECTOR OF THE 
ANTI-MONEY LAUNDERING DEPARTMENT AT THE MINISTRY OF FINANCE, 
IGOR BARAC.  HE HAD ALREADY INSTRUCTED HIS STAFF TO WORK ON 
THE BASIS OF THE OFAC LIST, WITHOUT WAITING FOR INSTRUCTIONS 
FROM THE MFA.  WE ALSO DELIVERED REF POINTS TO STIPICA KUNA, 
DEPUTY DIRECTOR OF THE CROATIAN BORDER POLICE, URGING HIM TO 
TAKE MEASURES WITHIN THE LAW TO BLOCK THE SANCTIONED 
INDIVIDUALS\' ACCESS TO CROATIA.  KUNA SAID THAT HE WAS 
ALREADY FAMILIAR WITH THE ISSUE, BUT WELCOMED OUR PROVIDING 
HIM THE INFORMATION DIRECTLY. 
    FRANK 
 
